1.description:
U.S. Air Force, F-15C Eagle - 493rd Fighter Squadron pilots conduct a training scramble to see how fast they can get into the air over Iceland. Icelandic Air Policing is a peacetime collective defensive mission by NATO that safeguards the integrity of Iceland's airspace. Since Iceland is a member of NATO and has no air force, air force capable NATO members take turns on a rotating schedule during the year to protect the skies over Iceland.

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman John Ennis, 48th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

2.description:
A U.S. Air Force A-10 Thunderbolt II fires an AIM-9 missile during a weapons systems evaluation program exercise over the Utah Test and Training Range on June 16, 2021. Unit - 124th Fighter Wing, 190th Fighter Squadron.

Film Credits: U.S. Air National Guard Video by Senior Master Sgt. Joshua C. Allmarasideo, 124th Fighter Wing

3.description:
Footage from the U.S. Navy's Blue Angels flight demonstration team, practicing for the 2021 airshow circuit.

Film Credits: Video by Petty Officer 2nd Class Cody Hendrix, Navy Flight Demonstration Squadron

4.description:
Sky view of U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 18th Aggressor Squadron providing adversarial force to air combat exercises during Red Flag-Alaska 21-2, out of Eielson Air Force Base, Alaska on June 18, 2021.  INFO Red Flag - Alaska: https://www.eielson.af.mil/Info/RED-FLAG-Alaska/ 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Tech. Sgt. Chris Drzazgowski, 1st Combat Camera Squadron

5.description:
The 100th ARW (Air Refueling Wing) spent five days operating out of Marrakesh Menara Airport while participating in exercise African Lion 2021. The 100th ARW refueled U.S. Air Force F-16s and Royal Moroccan Air Force F-16s during the exercise. Filmed June 2021.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman Joseph Barron, 100th Air Refueling Wing Public Affairs

6.description:
Exercise Amalgam Dart 21-01 with Canadian and U.S. forces operated across the Arctic from the Beaufort Sea to Thule, Greenland from June 10-18, 2021 at Thule Air Base in Greenland. Amalgam Dart 21-01 was conceived by NORAD (North American Aerospace Defense Command) to hone continental defense skills together in the Arctic. A bi-national Canadian and American command, NORAD employs a network of space-based, aerial and ground-based sensors, inflight refueling tankers, and jet fighter aircraft, controlled by a sophisticated network of state-of-the-art technology to deter, deny and defeat aerospace threats that originate outside or within Canada and the USA.

Film Credits: U.S. Air National Guard Video by Airman Mira Roman, CONR-1AF (AFNORTH)

7.description:
U.S. Air Force A-10 Thunderbolt II ground attack jets and HH-60 Pave Hawk helicopters work together and conduct combat search and rescue (CSAR) training during exercise Red Flag-Alaska 21 out of Eielson Air Force Base in Alaska on June 15, 2021. Red Flag-Alaska is the premier Pacific Air Forces exercise designed to integrate U.S. Military branches and Allied forces to exchange tactics, techniques and procedures, while improving interoperability. Units - 25th Fighter Squadron - 210th Rescue Squadron 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Airman 1st Class Jose Miguel T. Tamondong, 354th Fighter Wing Public Affairs -- U.S. Air Force Video by Tech. Sgt. Chris Drzazgowski, 1st Combat Camera Squadron

8.description:
U.S. Navy aircraft carrier USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78) completes the first scheduled explosive event of Full Ship Shock Trials while underway in the Atlantic Ocean, June 18, 2021. Shock trials of new ship designs using live explosives are conducted to confirm that United States warships can continue to meet demanding mission requirements under harsh conditions they might encounter in battle.

Film Credits: Video by Seaman Jackson Adkins and Seaman Apprentice Zachary Guth, Courtesy Video, USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78)

9.description:
Artillery rounds from U.S. Army M109A6 Paladin howitzers assigned to the Georgia Army National Guard's 1st Battalion, 214th Field Artillery, 648th Maneuver Enhancement Brigade, impact the training area during exercise African Lion 2021 June 16, 2021, Tan Tan, Morocco. African Lion 2021 is U.S. Africa Command’s largest, premier, joint, annual exercise hosted by Morocco, Tunisia, and Senegal, 7-18 June, 2021.

Film Credits: Video by Spc. William Hunter, Southern European Task Force Africa -- U.S. Army National Guard Video Sgt. Nathan Baker, Southern European Task Force Africa

10.description:
A HH-60 Pave Hawk helicopter is mounted with a GoPro camera on its refueling probe to expose a rare view of the helicopter as it flies during exercise Gun Smoke 2021 out of Nellis Air Force Base on May 18, 2021. Unit - 34th Weapons Squadron.

Film Credits: U.S. Air. Force Video by Airman 1st Class Zachary Rufus, Nellis AFB Public Affairs

A compilation of U.S. Military in-action scenes, backed up with music.  

Film Credits: Film clips courtesy of the U. S. Department of Defense -- Public Domain Material

12.description:
Arleigh Burke-class guided-missile destroyer USS Paul Ignatius (DDG-117) fires rounds from a Close In Weapon System (CIWS). And fires an MK-45 MOD 4 5-inch 62 caliber lightweight gun as part of a live-fire exercise during exercise At-Sea Demo/Formidable Shield, June 01, 2021. Exercise At-Sea Demo/Formidable Shield, conducted by Naval Striking and Support Forces NATO on behalf of U.S. Sixth Fleet, is a live-fire integrated air and missile defense (IAMD) exercise that improves Allied interoperability using NATO command and control reporting structures.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Nathan T. Beard - Released, Naval Striking and Support Forces NATO

13.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15E Strike Eagles from the 48th Fighter Wing takeoff and fly with the Hellenic Air Force's 115th Combat Wing at Souda Bay, Greece during exercise Poseidon's Rage on June 1-2, 2021. Poseidon's Rage, the inaugural multinational exercise serves to develop and improve U.S.- Hellenic air readiness and interoperability.

Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Rachel Maxwell, 48th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

14.description:
F-35B Lightning II fighter jets of RAF (Royal Air Force) and USMC (United States Marine Corps) takeoff and land aboard the British aircraft carrier HMS Queen Elizabeth (R08). Filmed off the coast of Portugal on May 27, 2021.

Film Credits: Courtesy Video, Natochannel -- https://www.dvidshub.net/video/796774/nato-secretary-general-visit-steadfast-defender-2021-f-35b-fighter-jets-take-off-and-land-onboard-hms-queen-elizabeth

15.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers assigned to 4th Battalion, 319th Field Artillery Regiment, 173rd Airborne Brigade (Sky Soldiers), fire M119 Howitzers during exercise Dynamic Front 21, at Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany on May 20, 2021. Exercise Dynamic Front 21 (DF21) includes approximately 1,800 participants from 15 nations, May 3 - 21, 2021 at the U.S. Army's Grafenwöhr Training Area in Germany and in Torun, Poland. DF21 is a 7th Army Training Command-led, U.S. Army Europe and Africa-directed exercise designed to increase readiness, lethality and interoperability by exercising allied and partner nations’ ability to integrate joint fires in a multinational environment at both the operation and tactical levels.

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Spc. Zack Stahlberg, 7th Army Training Command

16.description:
Amazing 360 degree cockpit footage from A-10 Thunderbolt II Demonstration Team during a practice run for the Dalhart Airshow in Texas. Filmed on May 21, 2021.

Film Credits: Video by Tech. Sgt. Sergio Gamboa, 355th Wing

17.description:
U.S. Air Force B-52 Stratofortress bombers takeoff at Morón Air Base, Spain during exercise Bomber Task Force Europe in May, 2021. Clips show takeoffs, cockpit views of inflight refueling, and aerial views of intercepts, and escorts with Polish Air Force and Danish Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcon fighter jets.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman Daniel Hernandez, 1st Combat Camera Squadron

18.description:
U.S. Air Force, 354th Fighter Squadron A-10 Thunderbolt II's arrive at Volk Field Air National Guard Base, Wisconsin, in support of Bushwhacker 21-02. Filmed in May 2021.

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Blake Gonzales, 355th Wing

19.description:
U.S. Air Force/Hellenic Armed Forces exercise Astral Knight 21 kicks off in May 2021. USAF F-16 Fighting Falcons from Aviano Air Base, Italy travel to join USAF F-15C Eagles from RAF Lakenheath, England at Larissa Air Base in Greece. Astral Knight 21 tunes the allies' integrated air and missile defense systems to defeat threats from adversarial air and missile capabilities. Units - 555th Fighter Squadron and 493d Fighter Squadron 

Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class Brooke Moeder, 31st Fighter Wing Public Affairs -- Video by Tech. Sgt. Jacob Albers, 48th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

20.description:
U.S. Air Force F-35A Lightning II strike fighters from the 33rd Fighter Wing go through preflight checks and launch at Eglin Air Force Base during final training requirements for F-35 pilots in a controlled environment, in May 2021.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman Heather LeVeille, 33rd Fighter Wing Public Affairs

21.description:
USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) flight deck operations during Exercise Northern Edge 2021 (NE21) at the Joint Pacific Alaska Range Complex in the Gulf of Alaska on May 10-11, 2021.

Film Credits: Courtesy Video - U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist Seaman Eduardo Torres, Pacific Air Forces Public Affairs

22.description:
A U.S. Air Force B-1B Lancer bomber aircraft takes-off from Yelahanka Air Force Station, Bengaluru, India on February 3, 2021.

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Christina Bennett, 28th Bomb Wing Public Affairs

23.description:
GoPro footage courtesy of U.S. Army Paratrooper 1st Lt. Blake Wilson "Pitbull 5" HHBN HSC, 82nd ABN DIV, on a jump from a C-130 Hercules during exercise Swift Response 21 over Romania on May 5, 2021.

Film Credits: Video by Sgt. Catessa Palone, 49th Public Affairs Detachment

24.description:
Exercise Rocki 21-02 combines with exercise Agile Flag 21-2, as the 19th Airlift Wing integrates with Air Combat Command, the leading wing for Mobility Air Forces, to provide airlift operations and conduct Integrated Combat Turns in a simulated deployed environment. U.S. Air Force Video filmed on April 5, 2021.

Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class Isaiah Miller, 19th Airlift Wing Public Affairs

25.description:
U.S. Marines conduct training with the M3E1 Multi-purpose Anti-armor Anti-personnel Weapon System (MAAWS) at Camp Lejeune, NC on May 6, 2021. Unit - 1st Battalion, 2d Marine Regiment (1/2), 2d Marine Division (2d MARDIV). MAAWS is the U.S. Military designation for the Carl-Gustaf M3 recoilless rifle.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Skylar M. Harris, 2nd Marine Division

26.description:
U.S. Navy aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) conducts flight deck operations during exercise Northern Edge 2021 (NE21) off the Alaskan coast. Also, helicopters launch from the carrier and capture scenic views of Alaskan wilderness. Filmed during exercise Northern Edge 2021, May 3-14, 2021.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Carlos W. Hopper, Pacific Air Forces Public Affairs -- Courtesy Video, U.S. Navy Video by USS Theodore Roosevelt Public Affairs

27.description:
U.S. Navy FA-18F Super Hornets and EA-18A Growlers conduct ground operations at Joint Base Elmendorf–Richardson, AK, and flight deck operations aboard the aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) during exercise Northern Edge 2021 (NE21), above the Joint Pacific Alaska Range Complex and Gulf of Alaska on May 5, 2021. U.S. Navy, Air Force and Marine Corps aircraft executed flight missions during NE21, demonstrating seamless, joint combat capabilities, with approximately 15,000 U.S. Service Members involved in the overall exercise.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman Amy Younger, Pacific Air Forces Public Affairs -- U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist Seaman Eduardo Torres, Pacific Air Forces Public Affairs

28.description:
A U.S. Air Force KC-135 Stratotanker assigned to the 97th Expeditionary Aerial Refueling Squadron (EARS) refuels F-16 Vipers (aka Fighting Falcons) in the sky near Iraq on Apr. 19, 2021. The 97th EARS is responsible for providing aerial refueling capabilities to support U.S. and coalition forces throughout the U.S. Central Command's area of responsibility

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Tech. Sgt. Robert Harnden, United States Air Forces Central

29.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a close-air-support exercise in a UH-1Y Venom helicopter. The GAU-21 machine gun is a lightened version of the powerful M2 Browning .50 caliber machine gun. The M134 (aka GAU-17 "Vulcan") mini-gun is a Gatling-style machine gun that can fire 6000 rounds per minute. Unit - Marine Light Attack Squadron (HMLA) 269. Filmed at Marine Corps Air-Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms, California on April 22, 2021.

Film Credits: Video by Lance Cpl. Elias Pimentel and 2nd Lt. Hudson Sadler, 2nd Marine Aircraft Wing

30.description:
U.S. Marines conduct an artillery raid exercise at Camp Lejeune, NC on April 28, 2021. Exercise Rolling Thunder distributed fires via simulated Expeditionary Advanced Bases to increase combat readiness against a peer competitor. Units - 2d Battalion, 10th Marine Regiment, 2d Marine Division, 2nd Landing Support Battalion (LSB), 2nd Marine Logistic Group and Marine Heavy Helicopter Squadron 461, 2nd Marine Aircraft Wing.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Sydney Smith, 2nd Marine Division

31.description:
U.S. Airmen with 73rd Special Operations Squadron fire the 105mm cannon aboard an AC-130J Ghostrider gunship during exercise Balikatan 21 over the Philippines on April 24, 2021. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Dalton J. Payne, 1st Marine Aircraft Wing

32.description:
Cockpit video (360 degrees view) from the A-10 Thunderbolt II Demonstration Team as it does aerobatic maneuvers during the Cocoa Beach Airshow on April 17, 2021.

Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Sergio Gamboa, 355th Wing

33.description:
U.S. Air Force maintenance personnel are in charge of servicing, inspections, launch, recovery and munitions loading of aircraft. Without this vital extension of the people who provide it, no USAF aircraft would be able to fly. The ground crews largely work in the background, secondary to the pilots. But make no mistake, without the ground crews, the pilots who fly these machines would not be able to takeoff. -- 113th Aircraft Maintenance Squadron Airmen from the District of Columbia Air National Guard work on planes to get them airworthy in exercise Green Flag 21-06 at Nellis Air Force Base, NV, on April 15, 2021. Green Flag provides combat training to joint and coalition warfighters in air-land integration and the joint employment of air power in support of the U.S. Army’s National Training Center.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Airman First Class Zachary Rufus, Nellis AFB Public Affairs

34.description:
MV-22B Osprey tiltrotor aircraft perform landing and takeoff testing, at night, aboard the USNS Mercy (T-AH-19) hospital ship off the coast of Southern California on April 19, 2021. Mercy is completing Dynamic Interface Testing, where the ship’s aviation facilities will be evaluated for compatibility with the MV-22B Osprey and MH-60 Seahawk, and establish launch and recovery windows in adverse weather conditions.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Jake Greenberg, Military Sealift Command Pacific

35.description:
Demonstration of the U.S. Navy's MANTAS T38 Devil Ray unmanned surface vehicle on April 17, 2021 at San Diego Bay, CA. 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Casey Trietsch -- U.S. Navy Video by Senior Chief Mass Communication Specialist Mike Jones -- Commander, U.S. Third Fleet, USN

36.description:
Restored WWII era P-51 Mustang named "Swamp Fox" and pilot RT Dickson practice their aerobatic routine at Breckenridge County airport in Hardinsburg, KY on April 15, 2021. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air National Guard Video by Senior Airman Chloe Ochs, 123rd Airlift Wing Public Affairs

37.description:
F-15E Strike Eagle fighter jets from the 493rd and 492nd fighter squadrons takeoff and do touch and go's and close flybys as part of exercise Point Blank 21-02 on April 6, 2021. The 48th Fighter Wing regularly takes part in this multilateral exercise as a way to strengthen interoperability with allied nations and develop skills critical to gaining and maintaining air superiority. 

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman John Ennis, 48th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

38.description:
U.S. Marine Corps UH-1Y Venom helicopters conduct a moving target training range with side-door mounted M134 Miniguns. This exercise was part of Weapons and Tactics Instructor (WTI) course 2-21, near Blue Mountain Airfields, CA on April 10, 2021. The WTI course is a seven-week training event hosted by MAWTS-1, providing standardized advanced tactical training and certification of unit instructor qualifications to support Marine aviation training and readiness, and assists in developing and employing aviation weapons and tactics. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Celestino HernandezSilvar, Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron-1

39.description:
U.S. Marines, aboard an MV-22B Osprey tilt-rotor, conduct gun range drills as part of Weapons and Tactics Instructor (WTI) course 2-21 near Yuma, AZ on April 6, 2021. The WTI course is a seven-week training event hosted by Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1), providing standardized advanced tactical training certification of unit instructors qualified to support Marine aviation training and readiness, and assists in developing and employing aviation weapons and tactics in the fleet.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Servante R. Coba, Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron-1

40.description:
USAF, 199th Fighter Squadron, F-22 Raptors take off from Marine Corps Air Station (MCAS) Iwakuni, Japan on April 5, 2021. The 199th Fighter Squadron is deployed to MCAS Iwakuni to conduct integrated training with Marine and Naval forces as part of the U.S. Indo-Pacific Command’s dynamic force employment concept.

Film Credits: Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Jackson Ricker, 1st Marine Aircraft Wing

41.description:
U.S. Soldiers assigned to 1st Squadron, 91st Cavalry Regiment, 173 Airborne Brigade, conduct a live fire exercise at 7th Army Training Command, Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany, on March 25, 2021.

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Kevin Sterling Payne, Training Support Activity Europe

42.description:
Cockpit footage from the USAF A-10 Thunderbolt II Demonstration Team flying over Davis-Monthan Air Force Base, Arizona, and Naval Air Facility El Centro, California. Video also Includes 360 degrees footage from an Air Force Heritage Flight practice during Heritage Flight Training Course at Davis-Monthan. Filmed in March 2021.

Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Sergio Gamboa, 355th Wing

43.description:
Cockpit video from Colorado Air National Guard F-16 Fighting Falcon fighter jets (aka Viper) during NORAD exercise Amalgam Dart 21-02 out of Canadian Forces Base Goose Bay, in March, 2021. The exercise took place from March 20-26 and ranged from the Beaufort Sea to Thule, Greenland and extended south down the Eastern Atlantic to the U.S. coast of Maine. Amalgam Dart 21-02 provides NORAD the opportunity to hone homeland defense skills as Canadian, U.S., and NATO forces operate together in the Arctic. A bi-national Canadian and American command, NORAD employs network space-based, aerial and ground based sensors, air-to-air refueling tankers, and fighter aircraft controlled by a sophisticated command and control network to deter, detect and defend against aerial threats that originate outside or within North American airspace.

Film Credits: Video by 2nd Lt. Benjamin Kimball -- U.S. Air National Guard Courtesy Video -- NORAD

44.description:
U.S. Marines CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters airlift Humvees and perform aerial refueling with C-130 air tankers during Weapons and Tactics Instructor (WTI) course 2-21, at Auxiliary Airfield IV, near Gila Bend, AZ, and Yuma, AZ, in March, 2021. The WTI course is a seven-week training event hosted by Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1) providing standardized advanced tactical training and certification of unit instructor qualifications to support Marine aviation training and readiness, and assists in developing and employing aviation weapons and tactics for fleet Marines. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Gerardo W. Cano and Lance Cpl. Larisa Chavez, Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron-1

45.description:
T-6 Texan II training aircraft, 434th Flying Training Squadron, flight over Laughlin Air Force Base, Del Rio, TX, with scenic views of surrounding West Texas. Laughlin AFB is the largest pilot training base in the US Air Force and turns out more pilots per year than any other training base in the USAF. Filmed on March 9, 2021.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Airman First Class David Phaff, 47th Flying Training Wing Public Affairs

46.description:
The 309th Aerospace Maintenance and Regeneration Group (AMARG), often called "The Boneyard", is a United States Air Force aircraft maintenance facility in Tucson, Arizona, located on Davis–Monthan Air Force Base. It is the largest aircraft storage unit in the world, with over 4000 aircraft.

Film Credits: Footage by Andrew Breese, A1C Kaitlyn Ergish, and SrA Sari Seibert, 355th Wing 
Music By: https://www.storyblocks.com/audio/stock/meditation-sqvrppsisk0e5ij49.html

47.description:
CMV-22B Osprey lands and takes-off aboard aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70) in 2021 as a COD (carrier on-board delivery). The CMV-22B has replaced the C-2 Greyhound (COD), in this video which landed on the former carrier, now decommissioned, USS Enterprise (CVN-65) in 2016.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Josiah J. Kunkle, USS Carl Vinson -- PO3 Jared King, LCpl Cody Woods, PO3 Devin Kates

48.description:
64th Aggressors F-16 Vipers, taxiing aircraft and take-offs during Red Flag 21-2 at Nellis Air Force Base in March, 2021.

Film Credits: Video by William Lewis, Nellis AFB Public Affairs

49.description:
U.S. Marines with 3d Battalion, 8th Marine Regiment, execute an air assault aboard CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters and MV-22B Ospreys during exercise Castaway 21.1 from the Central Training Area to Ie Shima, Okinawa, Japan, on March 11, 2021. The CH-53E helicopter can transport 37 Marines but the addition of a center row allows the accommodation of a total of 55 troops. With the Osprey, which has the speed and range of a turboprop, the maneuverability of a helicopter and the ability to carry 24 Marine combat troops twice as fast and five times farther than previous helicopters, the MV-22B Osprey gives extra capabilities for Marine Corps air assault operations. Castaway 21.1 demonstrated Marine Corps ability to integrate with joint forces to seize and defend key maritime terrain, provide low-signature sustainment, and execute long-range precision fires in support of naval operations from an expeditionary advanced base.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Jonathan Willcox, 3rd Marine Division

50.description:
Exercise Amalgam Dart 21-2 runs from March 20-26, 2021 at Thule Air Base/Pituffik Airport in Greenland. This exercise provides NORAD the opportunity to perfect homeland defense skills as Canadian, U.S., and NATO forces operate together in the Arctic. As a bi-national Canadian and American command, NORAD employs network space-based, aerial and ground based sensors, air-to-air refueling tankers, and fighter aircraft controlled by a sophisticated command and control network to deter, detect and defend against aerial threats that originate outside or within North American airspace. NATO E-3 Early Warning Aircraft, Royal Canadian Air Force CF-18 fighter aircraft, CP-140 long-range patrol aircraft, CC-130 search and rescue and tactical aircraft, and a CC-150T air refueler - as well as U.S. Air Force F-16 fighter aircraft, KC-10 Extender refueler, KC-146 Pegasus, KC-135 Stratotanker, and C-130 and C-17 transport aircraft will participate in this exercise. Canada and America may not see eye-to-eye on all things political, but they are strong Military allies nonetheless.

Film Credits: U.S. Air National Guard Video by 2nd Lt. Benjamin Kimball, North American Aerospace Defense Command

51.description:
The U.S. Navy aircraft carrier is the biggest and most lethal warship ever built by mankind. 

Film Credits: Clips courtesy of the U. S. Department of Defense, United States Navy
Music by: https://www.storyblocks.com/audio/stock/you-cant-stop-me-h-7-xmxj_kk2opp0p.html

52.description:
USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78) and the Italian aircraft carrier ITS Cavour (CVH-550) transit the Atlantic Ocean March 20, 2021, marking the first time a Ford-class and Italian carrier have operated together underway. As part of the Italian Navy’s Ready for Operations (RFO) campaign for its flagship, Cavour is conducting sea trials in coordination with the F-35 Lightning II Joint Program Office’s Patuxent River Integrated Test Force to obtain official certification to safely operate the F-35B. Gerald R. Ford is conducting integrated carrier strike group operations during independent steaming event 17 as part of her post-delivery test and trials phase of operations. 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Riley McDowell, USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78)

53.description:
Aerial snipers shoot from a helicopter - U.S. Marines with 3d Battalion, 3d Marine Regiment, and 3d Battalion, 8th Marines, at Camp Hansen, Okinawa, Japan on March 17, 2021. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Staff Sgt. Laiqa Hitt, 3rd Marine Division

54.description:
A U.S. Air Force KC-135 Stratotanker assigned to the 100th Air Refueling Wing, refueled German air force (Luftwaffe) Eurofighter Typhoon and Tornado aircraft during exercise Baltic Trident, over Germany, on March 18, 2021. 

Film Credits: Video by Tech. Sgt. Emerson Nuñez, 100th Air Refueling Wing Public Affairs

55.description:
Exercise Red Flag sometimes requires aircraft to be in the air for prolonged periods of time and conduct aerial refueling, perhaps multiple times, before a pilot's training evolution is finished. At Red Flag 21-2 a KC-135 Stratotanker from MacDill Air Force Base, crewed by members of the 84th Air Refueling Wing, Fairchild Air Force Base, refueled F-16 Vipers assigned to the 64th Aggressor Squadron, Nellis Air Force Base, on March 17, 2021. 

Film Credits: Video by Tech. Sgt. Alexandre Montes, Nellis AFB Public Affairs

56.description:
Various aircraft participate in Exercise Red Flag 21-2 at Nellis Air Force Base, NV, in March 2021. 

Film Credits: Video by William Lewis, Nellis AFB Public Affairs

57.description:
U.S. Marines F-35B Lightning II jets takeoff and land on a simulated Forward Refueling expeditionary runway near at Ie Shima, Okinawa, Japan, during exercise Castaway 21.1 on March 8-9, 2021. F-35B pilots demonstrated their ability to takeoff and land on short runways, allowing for operations in remote, austere environments throughout the Indo-Pacific region.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Josue Marquez, 3rd Marine Division

58.description:
F-15SG Strike Eagles from the Republic of Singapore Air Force, 428th Fighter Squadron’s Peace Carvin V participates in exercise Red Flag 21-2, at Nellis Air Force Base, Nevada on March 8-19, 2021. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman JaNae Capuno, 366th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

59.description:
The U.S. Army, 1-77th Field Artillery Regiment, tested their M-270 MLRS (Multiple Launch Rocket System) on a live-fire range at Grafenwoehr, Germany, February 24, 2021. 

Film Credits: Video by Spc. James Alegria, American Forces Network Bavaria

60.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcon Aircrafts (Vipers) assigned to the 480th Fighter Squadron taxi and take off, to begin exercise Agile Fury in Germany, on March 11, 2021.

Film Credits: Video by Tech. Sgt. Levi Rowse, 52nd Fighter Wing Public Affairs

61.description:
The U.S. Air Force F-35A Lightning ll Demonstration Team flies over Tucson, AZ during the 2021 Heritage Flight Training Course. 

Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Codie Trimble, F-35A Demo Team Public Affairs

62.description:
The Air Force's newest fighter jet, the F-15EX, touched down at Eglin Air Force Base on March 11, 2021. The aircraft will be the first Air Force aircraft to be tested and fielded from beginning to end, through combined developmental and operational tests. 

Film Credits: Video by Jennifer Vollmer, 96th Test Wing Public Affairs

63.description:
(CLIP-1) U.S. Marines with 2nd Reconnaissance Battalion, 2d Marine Division and Royal Marines with 32nd Raiding Squadron utilize Range G-21 for sniper training during a Dutch bilateral training between 2nd Reconnaissance Battalion and the Netherlands Marine Corps at Camp Lejeune, NC on March 8, 2021.
(CLIP-2) U.S. Marines with Marine Rotational Force Europe 21.1 (MRF-E), Marine Forces Europe and Africa, conduct an integrated live-fire sniper training event with scout snipers from Force Reconnaissance Detachment 21.1 (FORECON) and Norwegian partners in Setermoen, Norway on March 2, 2021. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Sydney Smith, 2nd Marine Division -- U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Andrew Smith, U.S. Marine Corps Forces, Europe and Africa

64.description:
A U.S. Air Force B-2 Spirit stealth bomber conducts aerial refueling over Georgia prior to a flyover of Super Bowl LV. The B-2 was joined by a B-1B Lancer bomber and a B-52 Stratofortress bomber in the flyover on February 7, 2021.

68.description:
(CLIP 1) Blue Angels had the unique opportunity to photograph the first Blue Angels Super Hornet Delta over NAS Pensacola! The Blue Angels' signature "Delta" formation is composed of the pilots who fly in the #1 through #6 positions.

(CLIP 2) Lt. Cmdr. Cary Rickoff, Blue Angel #6, conducts a training flight over NAF El Centro, CA and the Imperial Valley with Cmdr. Ben Walborn, Blue Angel #5. Here is a detailed breakdown of the maneuvers you see in clip 2: Lt. Cmdr Rickoff performs his first maneuver, the Low Transition to Immelman on take off. The maneuver begins from takeoff as he retracts his landing gear, maintaining minimum distance from the ground, then executes a high performance climb, followed by a half-loop. Next you see #6 executing a high G-force pull from behind the crowd, in order to expeditiously rendezvous with #5 for the next maneuver. The next maneuver is the Opposing Horizontal Roll. This maneuver requires #5 and #6 to perform two consecutive rolls, followed by the selection of max afterburner and execute a 7G pull to a vertical climb. The final maneuver of every show is the Pitch-Up Break (PUB). The PUB requires #1 through #6 to pitch up and away from the Delta Formation to deconflict their flight path. As they individually breakaway from the Delta Formation, they turn downwind, slowing down their aircraft in preparation for landing. 

(CLIP 3) Lt. Cmdr. Cary Rickoff, Blue Angel #6, conducts the Opposing Minimum-Radius Turn. In the Opposing Minimum-Radius Turn #5 and #6 approach from behind the crowd, passing over center point, while simultaneously rolling their aircraft 270 degrees away from each other, crossing each other’s flight path. Aircraft #5 and #6 conduct the Minimum Radius Turn, to cross back once more over show center in front of the crowd. After crossing, #5 and #6 execute 3 1/2 rolls in the climb as they complete the maneuver.

Film Credits: Video by Petty Officer 2nd Class Cody Hendrix, Navy Flight Demonstration Squadron

159.description:
The U.S. Army M119A3 Howitzer is an artillery piece (105mm) that packs a deadly punch and be transported by smaller U.S. helicopters like the UH-60 Black Hawk. It provides very accurate fire support for ground troops with a maximum range of about 10-12 miles. 

U.S. Army paratroopers assigned to 4th Battalion, 319 Airborne Field Artillery Regiment, 173rd Airborne Brigade fire the M119A3 Howitzer for a danger close mission in support of 2nd Battalion, 503rd Parachute Infantry Regiment, 173rd Airborne Brigade, in Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany on July 29, 2020. The 173rd Airborne Brigade is the U.S. Army's Contingency Response Force in Europe, providing rapidly deployable forces to the United States Europe, Africa and Central Command areas of responsibility. Forward deployed across Italy and Germany, the brigade routinely trains alongside NATO allies and partners to build partnerships and strengthen the alliance.

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Spc. Mathew Pous, 173rd Airborne Brigade

Saber Junction 20 is an exercise designed to assess the readiness of the 173rd Airborne Brigade, to execute unified land operations in a joint environment, and to promote interoperability with participating ally and partner nations. The exercise involves more than 4,000 participants from the U.S., Albania, Georgia, Latvia, Lithuania, Moldova, North Macedonia, Romania, and Ukraine.

Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Christopher Stewart, 7th Army Training Command

161.description:

The mission lasts for four months and sees the French deployed to Ämari Air Base in Estonia, supported by Spanish and UK pilots situated in Siauliai Air Base, Lithuania. NATO’s Baltic Air Policing mission is a defensive deployment that sees Allies sending planes to patrol the airspace of the three Baltic States (Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania), who do not have fighter jets. The Air Policing program keeps fighter pilots on alert 24/7 and ready to scramble in case of suspicious air activity near their borders.

Film Credits: Courtesy Video, Natochannel

168.description:
Nighttime alternate insertion and extraction training out of a live helicopter hosted by the 68th Rescue Squadron, located at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base, as part of the Combat Team Member Course. This training took place at Marana Regional Airport in Marana, Arizona on August 10, 2020.

As one of the only human based weapon systems in the Air Force, Guardian Angel must have highly trained personnel dedicated to the Air Force core function of Personnel Recovery. Guardian Angel is comprised of Combat Rescue Officers, Pararescuemen, and Survival, Evasion, Resistance, and Escape Specialists.The 68th Rescue Flight, also known as the Guardian Angel Formal Training Unit, was stood up in 2014 at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base.

“The mission of the 68th RQF and soon to be 68th Rescue Squadron is to provide standardized and efficient upgrade training for the entire Guardian Angel weapon system in order to support the Combatant Commanders Personnel Recovery requirements,” said Capt. Michael “Jeff” Ellingsen, 68th RQF commander.

Ellingsen relinquished command at a change of command ceremony and the 68th RQF transitioned to the 68th RQS on June 1, 2017.

“We only had 25 positions assigns when we were initially stood up by CC,” Ellingsen said. “We’re sitting at about 44 personnel right now. That was enough to convert us to a full-fledged rescue squadron from a numbered flight.”

With the growth of the squadron there is an increase in positions, the commander’s billet is now an O-5 and the superintendent is an established E-9.

“Now that the 68th is converting to a full-fledged rescue squadron it’s standardizing what Guardian Angel squadrons look like not only across the 23rd Wing, but the entire Air Force as well,” Ellingsen said. “It’s going to be pretty awesome to see where this place is going to be in the next three, five, ten years from now.”

The 68th RQS focuses on training in three major courses: a pararescue team leader course, a mission qualification training course, and a U.S. Special Operations Command approved military freefall jumpmaster course.

This transition also allows for future growth in the form of new courses, new training and new upgrade opportunities for multitudes of Battlefield Airmen.

“Going back to General Goldfien’s priorities, squadrons are the fundamental building blocks of the Air Force,” Ellingsen said. “That’s where people live, that’s where people reside, and that’s where families and Airmen flourish.”

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Blake Gonzales, 355th Wing

A fire erupted aboard the USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6) on the morning of July 12, 2020, while moored at the San Diego Naval Base. Base and shipboard firefighters responded to the fire, as well as helicopters from Helicopter Sea Combat Squadron (HSC-3). Video filmed on July 13, 2020.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy video by Mass Communication Specialist 1st Class Benjamin Kittleson - Released, U.S. Navy video by Lt. Joseph Pfaff - Released

179.description:
Aerial video of U.S. Air Force MQ-9 Reaper drone (remotely piloted aircraft) over the Nevada Test and Training Range (NTTR). Filmed January 2020.

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Haley Stevens, 432nd Wing Public Affairs

180.description:
U.S. Army paratroopers perform static-line and free-fall jumps from Rhode Island Army National Guard UH-60 Black Hawk helicopters over Big River Management Area, West Greenwich, RI on June 27, 2020. Units - C Co. 1/143rd Airborne, 56th Troop Command, A Co. 2/19th SFG, SOD-G, SOD-O.

Film Credits: Army National Guard Video by Pfc. David Connors, Joint Force Headquarters, RING Joint Public Affairs, Rhode Island National Guard

181.description:
U.S. Marines with Force Reconnaissance Platoon (FRP), 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU) conduct combat marksmanship training at Camp Hansen, Okinawa, Japan on June 30, 2020. The 31st MEU is the only continuously forward-deployed MEU, providing a flexible and lethal force ready to perform a wide range of military operations as the premier crisis response force in the Indo-Pacific region.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Brandon Salas, 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit

182.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a combat marksmanship range with Mossberg 500 shotguns and M27 IAR (Infantry Automatic Rifles) in Kuwait on June 26, 2020. Unit - 2nd Battalion, 5th Marine Regiment, assigned to Special Purpose Marine-Air Ground Task Force - Crisis Response - Central Command 20.2. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps video by Sgt. Brendan Custer, 13th Marine Expeditionary Unit

183.description:
U.S. Air Force Airmen from the 96th Aircraft Maintenance Squadron prepare a B-52H Stratofortress prior to taking off at Eielson Air Force Base, Alaska, during a Bomber Task Force deployment on June 16, 2020.

Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Philip Bryant, Pacific Air Forces Public Affairs

184.description:
(Clip One) - At Katterbach Army Airfield, Germany, 1-3 Attack Reconnaissance Battalion, 12th Combat Aviation Brigade, takeoff on a training mission with the full battalion on May 19, 2020. (Clip Two) - U.S. Marines with 3rd Battalion, 1st Marine Regiment, 1st Marine Division conduct live fire Military Operations in Urban Terrain training at Range 230 during Integrated Training Exercise (ITX) 5-20 on Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center (MCAGCC), Twentynine Palms, CA on June 10, 2020. (Clip Three) - U.S. Marines from VMA-214 prep and launch an AV-8B Harrier at Prince Sultan Air Base, Saudi Arabia on June 22, 2020.

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Eugen Warkentin, Training Support Activity Europe -- U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Colton Brownlee, Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center, Twentynine Palms -- Video by Staff Sgt. Amanda Stanford, 378th Air Expeditionary Wing

185.description:
Clip One// A-10 Thunderbolt II assigned to the A-10 Demonstration team, F-16 Viper assigned to the Viper Demo team and a WWII era P-51 Mustang perform a heritage flight over Sumter, South Carolina, June 17, 2020 with cockpit view from the A-10. -- Clip Two// F-35 Demo Pilot, U.S. Air Force Capt Kristin "BEO" Wolfe, performing the quick climb, a maximum G pull to the vertical after a high speed pass at .95 Mach (720 mph). This video was shot during a demonstration team practice over Hill Air Force Base, Utah.

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Kristine Legate, 355th Wing -- Video by Capt. Kippun Sumner, F-35A Demo Team Public Affairs

186.description:
U.S. Army Yuma Proving Ground's test and evaluation mission takes place in the desert of Arizona, the Arctic cold of the Alaskan interior, and the tropical jungles of Central and South America. It has jurisdiction over all of the extreme weather testing in the Army, in the desert of Arizona and the Arctic cold of the Alaskan interior. 

Film Credits: Video by Riley Williams, U.S. Army Yuma Proving Ground

187.description:
Members of the U.S. Army, 5th Special Forces Group, along with Latvian Special Forces practiced high-altitude, low-opening (HALO) jumps over Latvia on 18 June 2020. The Special Forces soldiers jumped from a Latvian Air Force Antonov AN-2 transport plane with their counterparts from the Latvian Special Operations Unit. During a HALO jump, operators free fall from high altitudes (upward from 10,000 feet) before opening their parachutes close to the ground. This technique, pioneered by Green Berets during the Vietnam War, allows for rapid, discreet insertion of special operations forces.

Film Credits: Video by Robert L Kunzig, Navy Public Affairs Support Element East - (Reserve)

188.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcon pilots from the 149th Fighter Wing fly over Lubbock, Texas on May 11, 2020, as a way to honor the selfless sacrifice of all the health care workers, first responders, military and other personnel at the forefront of the COVID crises.

Film Credits: Video by Master Sgt. Mindy Bloem, 149th Fighter Wing Public Affairs, Texas Air National Guard

189.description:
U.S. Air Force B-1B Lancer bomber aircrews prepare their aircraft for a grueling 29 hour nonstop flight to the Black Sea region and then back home to Ellsworth AFB during Bomber Task Force exercise 2020.

Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class Michael Ward, 28th Bomb Wing Public Affairs -- Video by Tech. Sgt. Emerson Nuñez, 100th Air Refueling Wing Public Affairs -- Courtesy Video by Polish Air Force, U.S. Air Forces in Europe and Air Forces Africa Public Affairs

190.description:
A 17 aircraft surge, or "Elephant Walk" was executed at Yokota Air Base, Japan on May 21, 2020 as part of exercise Samurai Surge. Members of the 36th Airlift Squadron, 459th Airlift Squadron, 374th Maintenance Group and the 353rd Special Operations Group came together to complete the evolution.

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Jessica Avallone, 374th Airlift Wing Public Affairs

191.description:
(Clip 1) F-35A Lightning II Demonstration Team pilot and commander, U.S. Air Force Capt Kristin "BEO" Wolfe, performing the "quick climb", a maximum-G pull to the vertical after the High Speed Pass at .95 Mach (720 mph).⁣⁣ 

(Clip 2) U.S. Soldiers of the 1st Battalion, 5th Infantry Regiment, 1st Brigade Combat Team, 25th Infantry Division and Norwegian soldiers of the Telemark Battalion, meet up to conduct a joint live fire range exercise at Al Asad Air Base, Iraq, May 27, 2020
 
(Clip 3) U.S. Air Force Thunderbolt II (Warthogs) deployed to Al Udeid Air Base, Qatar conduct aerial refueling missions on May 29, 2020.

Film Credits: Video by Capt. Kippun Sumner, F-35A Demo Team Public Affairs -- U.S. Army Video by Spc. Derek Mustard, Combined Joint Task Force - Operation Inherent Resolve -- U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman Brandon Cribelar, U.S. Air Forces Central Command Public Affairs

192.description:
(Clip 1) U.S. Marines with Delta Company, Infantry Training Battalion, School of Infantry - West, conduct two live-fire heavy machine gun ranges at Range 203 on Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton, California, June 8, 2020. 

(Clip 2) A U.S. Air Force B-52 Stratofortress from the 5th Bomb Wing, Minot Air Force Base, North Dakota, receives fuel from a KC-135 Stratotanker from the 100th Air Refueling Wing, RAF Mildenhall, England, during a strategic bomber mission off the northern Norwegian coast, June 3, 2020. 

(Clip 3) A U.S. Navy F/A-18E Super Hornet, operating from the Harry S. Truman Carrier Strike Group underway in the North Atlantic Ocean, intercepts two U.S. Strategic Command (USSTRATCOM) B-1B Lancers as they enter the Canadian Air Defense Identification Zone, and again as they enter the Continental U.S. North American Aerospace Defense Command (NORAD) Region, May 29, 2020. The intercepts were part of a U.S. Northern Command-led, large-scale homeland defense exercise.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Melissa I. Ugalde, Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton -- Video by Staff Sgt. Kelly OConnor, 100th Air Refueling Wing Public Affairs -- U.S. Navy Video by Lt. Neil Armstrong, Courtesy Video, USS Harry S. Truman

193.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15 Eagle fighter jets from the 44th Expeditionary Fighter Squadron (nickname - Vampires) fly combat sorties out of Prince Sultan Air Base, Saudi Arabia on June 4, 2020.  

Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Amanda Stanford, 378th Air Expeditionary Wing

194.description:
Whenever I post aircraft carrier flight deck videos lots of my subscribers comment, "It never get's old." Or, "I could watch this all day long." I agree, they are fun to watch. The dance on the deck of human beings mixed with millions of dollars of deadly hardware is always facinating. -- USS Harry S. Truman (CVN-75) conducts fixed wing flight deck operations at sea in the Atlantic Ocean during the COVID-19 pandemic on May 28, 2020.  

Film Credits: Video by Petty Officer 3rd Class Rebekah Watkins, USS Harry S Truman

195.description:
The U.S. Navy, USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71), has returned to sea from an extended stay at Naval Base Guam. The aircraft carrier was sidelined after an outbreak of COVID-19 aboard in March 2020. The Roosevelt has completed carrier qualifications and is expected to return to full duty subsequently. Video was filmed in the last week of May 2020.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist Seaman Alexander Williams, USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) -- US Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist Seaman Erik Melgar, USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71)

196.description:
Soldiers from the North Carolina Army National Guard, 105th Military Police Battalion stand guard in downtown Raleigh on May 31, 2020. Approximately 450 Guardsmen have been mobilized here due to civil unrest. The Guard will support local authorities and help safeguard the lives and property of North Carolinians and the ability for individuals to exercise their civil rights to protest peacefully. 

Film Credits: Video by Sgt. Marcel Pugh, North Carolina National Guard

197.description:
The aircraft carrier USS Harry S. Truman (CVN-75) conducts flight deck operations on May 16, 2020. The Harry S. Truman Carrier Strike Group (HSTCSG) remains at sea in the Atlantic Ocean as a certified carrier strike group ready for tasking in order to protect the crew from the risks posed by the COVID-19 pandemic. 

Film Credits: Video by Petty Officer 3rd Class Rebekah Watkins, Released by LCDR Jason Fischer, USS Harry S. Truman, PAO

198.description:
USAF flyer candidates continue to train during the coronavirus pandemic at the Air Force Research Laboratory ( AFRL) 711 Human Performance Wing centrifuge, Wright-Patterson Air Force Base, Ohio on May 05, 2020. The AFRL centrifuge is the only one rated for humans in the Department of Defense.  

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Christopher Decker, Air Force Materiel Command

199.description:
Clip 1) U.S. Navy Electronic Attack Squadron 131 in Red Flag 20-1 ground support on February 18, 2020.
Clip 2) Hush House test of F-22 engine at Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson, AK on February 9, 2020.
Clip 3) U.S. Marines with Marine Wing Support Squadron 171, Marine Aerial Refueler Transport Squadron 152 (VMGR-152), and Marine Fighter Attack Squadron 115 (VMFA-115) set up a Forward Arming and Refueling Point (FARP) at Marine Corps Air Station Iwakuni, Japan on May 14, 2020. 

Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class Bryan Guthrie, Nellis AFB Public Affairs -- Video by Airman Mario Calabro, Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson Public Affairs -- U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Tyler Harmon, 1st Marine Aircraft Wing

200.description:
Clip 1) U.S Marines with 1st Battalion, 8th Marine Regiment (V18), 2d Marine Division conduct squad-supported fire and maneuver training on Camp Lejeune, North Carolina on May 11, 2020. 
Clip 2) U.S Marines with 1st Battalion, 8th Marine Regiment, 2d Marine Division fire 81 mm mortar systems during a battalion field exercise at Camp Lejeune, North Carolina on May 13, 2020.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Sydney Smith, 2nd Marine Division

201.description:
"Fly The Barn" means get all aircraft in the air at once and do it now. It requires an incredible amount of coordination between maintenance crews, pilot briefing and preparedness, and overall situational awareness by a group of professionals in a short time. Marine Aircraft Group 24 (MAG-24) successfully launched seven CH-53E Super Stallions, eight MV-22B Ospreys, and two UH-1Y Venoms, conducting the mass air mission to increase proficiency through integrated training to produce readiness and project power at Marine Corps Air Station Kaneohe Bay, Marine Corps Base Hawaii on May 19, 2020.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Luke Kuennen, Marine Corps Base Hawaii

202.description:
Alaska Air National Guard aircraft from the 176th Wing JBER honored frontline COVID-19 responders -- pararescuemen jump from an HC-130J Combat King II -- HH-60G Pave Hawk helicopter and HC-130J complete aerial refueling. This is part of the U.S. Air Force Salute to show appreciation to the countless heroes around the world battling the COVID pandemic. 

Film Credits: Video by Petty Officer 3rd Class Victoria Granado, Alaska National Guard Public Affairs

203.description:
USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78) hosts Training Air Wing's 1 and 2 for carrier qualifications. Ford is underway in the Atlantic Ocean conducting carrier qualifications in May 2020. -- KC-135R Stratotanker from Sumpter Smith Joint National Guard Base refuels three F-35 aircraft from Luke Air Force Base en route to an air show in Canada on June 20, 2019.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Ruben Reed, USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78) -- U.S. Air National Guard Video by Tech. Sgt. Jim Bentley, 117th Air Refueling Wing

204.description:
I cleared off my Desktop (computer) of clips I have had since the 2020 COVID-19 shutdown. These are some clips I didn't upload as videos, jumbled and with no music... In order of appearance... || A B-1 Bomber approaches and connects with a KC-135 from the 186th Air Refueling Wing, Mississippi National Guard, for a quick refueling mission during Southern Strike 2020. || U.S. Marines with Bravo Battery, 1st Battalion, 12th Marine Regiment, execute fire missions on Schofield Barracks, Hawaii, Jan. 29, 2020. || U.S. Marines assigned to Headquarters Battalion, 3rd Marine Division, participate in weapons training at Camp Schwab, Okinawa, Japan, January 7, 2020. || U.S. Marines assigned to Fox Battery, 2nd Battalion, 14th Marines 4th Marine Division, complete a High Mobility Artillery Rocket System (HIMARS) mission with help from the 9th Special Operations Squadron in UTTR, Utah, January 23, 2020, as part of exercise Emerald Warrior 20.1. || U.S. Marines with Force Reconnaissance Company (FORECON), 2nd Reconnaissance Battalion, 2d Marine Division conduct a hike on skis during the Norwegian Military’s Long Range Reconnaissance Patrol (LRRP) course in Norway, Feb. 17, 2020. || U.S. Air Force medics from the 1st Special Operations Support Squadron and French combat medics onload and offload simulated casualties on a French Air Force C-130 while administering life-saving medical care during Emerald Warrior 20-1 at Alpena Combat Readiness Training Center, Michigan on January 27, 2020. || U.S. Army Rangers, assigned to the 5th Ranger Training Battalion, conduct an Airborne jump out of a CH-47 Chinook in Stringer Drop Zone, Dahlonega, GA on February 20, 2020. || U.S. Soldiers with the Alaska Air National Guard assigned to the 2nd Battalion, 211th Aviation Regiment, takes flight en route from Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson to Deadhorse, Alaska in a CH-47 Chinook for exercise Arctic Eagle on February, 24, 2020. || Participants with Recruiting Stations Nashville and Louisville visited MCRD Parris Island for a four-day period to observe recruit training and gain a better understanding of how recruits are transformed into Marines. Filmed February 2020. || Ospreys of the 352nd SOW from RAF Mildenhall fly during Exercise Valiant Liberty || U.S. Marines with 3rd Battalion, 6th Marine Regiment, 2d Marine Division in a live-fire range during a continuation of Mountain Training Exercise 2-20 on Marine Corps Air-Ground Combat Center Twenty-nine Palms, California, March 4, 2020. || B-1B Bomber takeoff from Nellis Air Force Base on January 1, 2020. || U.S. Soldiers assigned to 1st Platoon, Charlie Battery, 2nd Battalion, 8th Field Artillery Regiment, 1st Stryker Brigade Combat Team, 25th Infantry Division, conduct fire mission with M-777 howitzer at Al Asad Air Base, Iraq on March 2, 2020. || B-52 Stratofortress aircrew preflight check before takeoff at Nellis Air Force Base during Red Flag 20-2, March 13, 2020. || B-52 takeoff in operations during Red Flag 20-2 on March 12, 2020.



Film Credits: Video by Capt. Dusty Culpepper, Joint Force Headquarters, Mississippi National Guard -- Video by Lance Cpl. Jacob Wilson, III Marine Expeditionary Force -- Video by Lance Cpl. Dangelo Yanez, 3rd Marine Division -- Video by Staff Sgt. Gustavo Castillo, Air Force Special Operations Command Public Affairs -- Video by Cpl. Aaron Douds, 2nd Marine Division -- Video by Staff Sgt. James Merriman, Air Force Special Operations Command Public Affairs -- Video by Staff Sgt. Austin Berner, 982nd Signal Company (Combat Camera) (Airborne) -- Video by Tech. Sgt. Amy Picard, Alaska National Guard Public Affairs -- Video by Cpl. Cody Ohira, 4th Marine Corps District -- Video by Senior Airman Shanice Williams-Jones, 48th Fighter Wing Public Affairs -- Video by Lance Cpl. Anna Bibbo, 2nd Marine Division -- Video by 2nd Lt. Joshua Sinclair, 28th Bomb Wing Public Affairs -- Video by Staff Sgt. Philip Bryant, Air Force Global Strike Command Public Affairs -- Video by William Lewis, Nellis AFB Public Affairs

205.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15 Eagles fly in formation over parts of Oregon to honor essential workers during the COVID-19 pandemic. Filmed on May 5, 2020. Unit - 142nd Wing.

Film Credits: Video by Master Sgt. Steven Conklin, 142nd Wing Public Affairs

206.description:
Footage from the Spirit of Texoma Flyover in Wichita Falls, TX on May 1, 2020. The flight honored health care workers and essential personnel that continue to work during the COVID-19 crisis, and included T-6A Texan II turboprop planes from the 80th Flying Training Wing, Sheppard Air Force Base, Wichita Falls, TX.

Film Credits: Video by Benjamin Remmert, 82nd Training Wing Public Affairs

207.description:
U.S. Air Force pilots from the 120th Fighter Squadron, 140th Wing, Colorado Air National Guard, fly F-16 Fighting Falcons (Vipers) in formation over Colorado cities and towns as a salute to the men and women who have been on the front lines battling COVID-19. During the nearly 2-hour flight, the jets flew over more than 70 hospitals and healthcare facilities where COVID-19 rates were the highest.

Film Credits: Video by 2nd Lt. Benjamin Kimball, 140th Wing Public Affairs

208.description:
Oregon Air National Guard F-15 Eagles with the 142nd Wing takeoff, along with in-flight footage. Filmed on May6, 2020. 

Film Credits: Video by Master Sgt. Steven Conklin, 142nd Wing Public Affairs

209.description:
U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptors conduct an Elephant Walk and takeoff from Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson, Alaska, on May 5, 2020. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman Johnathon Wines, Airman First Class Mario Calabro, Airman 1st Class Jordan Smith, Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson Public Affairs

210.description:
U.S. Air Force T-38 Talon jets from the 71st Flying Training Wing, Vance Air Force Base, Oklahoma, fly over Oklahoma City as part of the Oklahoma Salute to Service, on May 1, 2020.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Airman 1st Class Octavius Thompson, 71st Flying Training Wing Public Affairs

211.description:
The U.S. Air Force Air Demonstration Team “Thunderbirds” prepare to takeoff for a flyover at NAS Pensacola, FL on May 2, 2020. The flyover was part of America Strong -- a collaborative salute from the Air Force and Navy to recognize healthcare workers, first responders, military, and other essential personnel while standing in solidarity with all Americans during the COVID-19 pandemic.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. Cory W. Bush, Air Force Thunderbirds

212.description:
The 168th Wing, Alaska Air National Guard, ferried two new F-35A Lightning II aircraft from the Lockheed Martin factory in Fort Worth, Texas, to the 354th Fighter Wing, Eielson Air Force Base, Alaska on April 21, 2020.

Film Credits: U.S. Air National Guard Video by Tech. Sgt. Adam Keele, 168th Wing Public Affairs

213.description:
Belgian F-16 Fighting Falcons assigned to NATO’s Baltic Air Policing mission intercept Russian fighter jets as they conducted low passes over a US Navy destroyer in the Baltic Sea on April 17, 2020. The Belgian F-16s launched from Šiauliai Air Base in Lithuania then intercepted the Russian aircraft – two Su-24 Fencer attack jets, one Su-27 Flanker air superiority fighter, and one Su-30 Flanker-C multirole fighter – over the USS Donald Cook, a U.S. Arleigh Burke-class destroyer maneuvering in the Baltic Sea off the coast of Lithuania. Intercepts can be triggered when air traffic (civilian or military) do not respond to hails from air traffic controllers.

Film Credits: Courtesy Video, Natochannel

214.description:
U.S. Army AH-64 Apache Helicopters conduct deck landing qualifications in the Persian Gulf aboard the USS Lewis B. Puller (ESB-3). Puller is the first purposely-built expeditionary mobile base vessel for the United States Navy. The Apache Helicopters belong to Task Force Saber (4th Squadron, 6th Cavalry Regiment). Filmed on April 15, 2020. 

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Sgt. Trevor Cullen, Task Force Spartan

215.description:
U.S. Marines with Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 268 conduct Defensive Weapon System (DWS) training on April 3, 2020. Designed to provide suppressive defensive fire, the DWS is remotely operated and incorporates a gunner station, targeting sensor and the GAU-17 minigun.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Matthew Kirk, Marine Corps Base Hawaii

216.description:
U.S. Navy Blue Angels aerial demonstration ground crew and pilot cockpit video.

Film Credits: Video by Petty Officer 1st Class Jess Gray, Navy Flight Demonstration Squadron

217.description:
U.S. Navy amphibious assault ship USS America (LHA-6) continues flight operations in the South China Sea during the exploding COVID-19 pandemic on March 18, 2020. F-35B Lightning II Joint Strike Fighters, MV-22B Osprey tiltrotors, and CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters are highlighted. Units - Marine Fighter Attack Squadron (VMFA-122) and Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron (VMM-265) (Reinforced) and 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU).

Film Credits: Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Kolby Leger, 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit

218.description:
U.S. Navy aircraft carrier USS Harry S. Truman (CVN-75) conducts a vertical replenishment-at-sea (VERTREP) with USNS Medgar Evers (T-AKE 13) on April 15, 2020. The Harry S. Truman Carrier Strike Group (HSTCSG) remains at sea in the Atlantic in order to protect the crew from COVID-19 and still remain a certified carrier strike group force ready for tasking. Keeping HSTCSG at sea allows the ship to maintain a high level of readiness during the global COVID-19 pandemic.

Film Credits: Video by Seaman Apprentice Samuel Tyson, USS Harry S Truman

219.description:
German Eurofighter Typhoons and Tornadoes, Italian F-35s and Typhoons, and Spanish Typhoon fighter aircraft taxi, takeoff and land during Exercise Red Flag 20-2 at Nellis Air Force Base, NV, March 2020.

Film Credits: Video by William Lewis, Nellis AFB Public Affairs

220.description:
52nd Fighter Wing F-16 Fighting Falcons operate out of Spangdahlem Air Base, DE, on March 25, 2020.

Film Credits: Courtesy Video, 52nd Fighter Wing Public Affairs

221.description:
Spanish Air Force Eurofighter Typoon pre-flight check at Red Flag Exercise, Nellis Air Force Base in March, 2020.

Film Credits: Video by William Lewis, Nellis AFB Public Affairs -- Video by Staff Sgt. Philip Bryant, Air Force Global Strike Command Public Affairs

222.description:
Amphibious Assault Ship USS America (LHA-6) conducts flight operations in March and April of 2020 during the raging COVID-19 pandemic. This video shows that the U.S. Navy is still capable of conducting operations, even as the USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) aircraft carrier has been sidelined by the COVID-19 infection. Editorial: Who is the dimwit that thought it was a good idea to let the Roosevelt have a shore-leave in Vietnam, as the coronavirus was starting to spread worldwide? That guy should have his head examined! In my mind, humankind has underestimated this virus from day one. And now humans are scrambling to save the world as we know it. Am I being overdramatic, yes, no? Leave a comment...

Film Credits: Video by Petty Officer 3rd Class Vincent Zline, USS America (LHA-6) -- Video by Seaman Jonathan Berlier, USS America (LHA-6) -- Video by Seaman Jomark Almazan, USS America (LHA-6) -- Video by Seaman Theodore Lee, USS America (LHA-6)

223.description:
U.S. Air Force technicians test an F-22 Raptor engine in the "Hush House" at Joint Base Elmendorf–Richardson, AK. The hush house is an enclosed, noise-suppressed facility used for testing aircraft systems, including propulsion, mechanics, electronics, pneumatics, and at full power.

Film Credits: Video by Airman Mario Calabro, Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson Public Affairs

224.description:
In these hard times, here are some examples of the U.S. Military on duty delivering life saving resources to the American people. Video order of presentation: 

(1) Airmen from the California Air National Guard's 146th Airlift Wing set up a Federal Medical Station, March 29, 2020, inside the Los Angeles Convention Center in Los Angeles, as part of California's statewide COVID-19 response effort. 

(2) Members of the West Virginia National Guard (WVNG) assist volunteers and staff of the Facing Hunger Foodbank, located in Huntington, West Virginia, to package and prepare food distribution boxes for the elderly as a part of the ongoing state of West Virginia COVID-19 pandemic outbreak response, March 31, 2020. 

(3) Rhode Island National Guard is training to administer Covid-19 tests to the public. These tests will be administered to people in the state of Rhode Island who have been refered by their primary care providers to recieve a Covid-19 test. On Monday March 30th Soldiers from the RI National Guard began setting up a testing station at Community College of Rhode Island, Warwick.

(4) The hospital ship USNS Comfort (T-AH 20) prepares the intensive care unit (ICU) to admit patients in support of the United States COVID-19 response efforts.

(5) USNS Mercy (T-AH 19) support of national COVID-19 response efforts. Serving as a referral hospital for non-COVID-19 patients currently admitted to shore-based hospitals. This allows shore base hospitals to focus their efforts on COVID-19 cases.

Film Credits: California State Guard Video by Sgt. Zak Lara, California National Guard -- Video by Edwin Wriston, West Virginia National Guard -- Air National Guard Video by Staff Sgt. John Vannucci, Joint Force Headquarters, Rhode Island National Guard -- U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 1st Class Scott Bigley, Commander, U.S. 2nd Fleet -- U.S. Navy video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Erwin Jacob Miciano, Commander, U.S. 3rd Fleet

225.description:
The USNS Mercy Hospital Ship Docks at Port of Los Angeles, CA on March 27, 2020 amid the COVID-19 pandemic. USNS Mercy is a Military Sealift Command hospital ship with 1000 hopital beds, state-of-the-art equipment, and top-notch medical staff. The deployment of Mercy at this time is designed to provide a "relief valve" to make beds available for an overflow of Los Angeles area hospitals, in the event those hospitals cannot handle the crush of Coronavirus cases that may be expected in the coming days and weeks. Filmed on March 27, 2020. Unit - USNS Mercy (T-AH-19).

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Natalie M. Byers, Commander, U.S. 3rd Fleet -- U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Jacob Yost, Commander, U.S. 3rd Fleet -- U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Ryan M. Breeden, Commander, U.S. 3rd Fleet

226.description:
The NASA Super Guppy (B-377-SGT Super Guppy Turbine) transport plane lands at Mansfield-Lahm Regional Airport, OH on March 22, 2020, to load the Orion Space Capsule/NASA Artemis Mission, bound for the Kennedy Space Center, FL.

Film Credits: Ohio Air National Guard Video by Senior Airman Marc Wilson - Released, 179th Airlift Wing

227.description:
Military Sealift Command hospital ship USNS Mercy (T-AH 19) navigates the San Diego channel on March 23, 2020. Mercy was deployed in support of the nation’s COVID-19 response efforts, and will serve as a referral hospital for non-COVID-19 patients currently admitted to shore-based hospitals. This allows shore base hospitals to focus their efforts on COVID-19 cases. One of the Department of Defense’s missions is Defense Support of Civil Authorities. DOD is supporting the Federal Emergency Management Agency, the lead federal agency, as well as state, local and public health authorities in helping protect the health and safety of the American people. 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Jasen Moreno-Garcia - Released by Commander, U.S. 3rd Fleet

228.description:
The USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN-69) and USS Harry S. Truman (CVN-75) carrier strike groups conduct dual carrier and joint air wing operations with a B-52H Stratofortress in the Arabian Sea/Persian Gulf on March 21, 2020. 

Film Credits: Courtesy Video, Video by Petty Officer 1st Class Keith Simmons, USS Harry S Truman

229.description:
Helicopter view of U.S. Naval Base Guam, with USS America (LHA-6), USS Green Bay (LPD-20) and USS Germantown (LSD-42) docked, as part of America Expeditionary Strike Group (America ESG). Also operating from Naval Base Guam are USNS Rappahannock (T-AO-204) and USS Frank Cable (AS-40). Operating in the U.S. 7th Fleet area of operations, the America ESG-31st Marine Expeditionary Unit team of 4,500 Sailors and Marines is prepared to conduct missions across the full spectrum of military operations. Filmed on March 21, 2020. 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist Seaman Jonathan Berlier, USS America (LHA-6)

230.description:
Combat Air Force Exercise Red Flag (long version) includes footage of maintenance crew-members performing pre-flight checks on a B-52 Stratofortress prior to takeoff at Nellis. German Tornados, Italian Eurofighters, and Spanish Eurofighters, and U.S. B-52 Bombers prepare for takeoff at Nellis. F-35 Lightning II strike fighters and U.S. Aggressor force F-16s, Eurofighters, German Tornados, and U.S. B-52 Stratofortresses takeoff and land at Nellis Air Force Base. Filmed in March 2020.  

Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Philip Bryant, Air Force Global Strike Command Public Affairs

231.description:
Senior Airman Mathieu Cyrus, F-35A Lightning II Demonstration Team avionics specialist, received a familiarization ride in an F-16 Viper fighter jet (aka F-16 Fighting Falcon) and goes supersonic. At one point during the ride he undergoes a 9G, 180 degree turn and takes it like a champ. Filmed on February 28, 2020 during the annual Air Force Heritage Flight Training Conference at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base, Arizona. 

Film Credits: Video by Capt. Kippun Sumner, F-35A Demo Team Public Affairs

232.description:
GoPro video of takeoff and landing from the cockpit of an F-15C Eagle fighter jet out of RAF Lakenheath, UK. Unit - 48th Fighter Wing. Filmed on March 17, 2020.

Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class Anthony Clingerman, 48th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

233.description:
U.S. Marine Corps M1A1 Abrams main battle tanks maneuver and fire on a range at Camp Lejeune, North Carolina on March 12, 2020. Tank table 12 integrates fire and maneuver tactics with offensive and defensive scenarios during day and night, to test and enhance the Marines' abilities. Unit - 2nd Tank Battalion, 2d Marine Division.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Ashley McLaughlin, 2nd Marine Division

234.description:
U.S. Air Force C-17 Globemaster III assigned to the 816th Expeditionary Airlift Squadron conducts a cargo and personnel transportation in the U.S. Central Command Area of Responsibility (AOR) on February 13, 2020. The 816th EAS, deployed with U.S. Air Forces Central Command, is responsible for delivering cargo and passengers to U.S. and coalition forces' bases, enabling a constant presence in the area.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman Brandon Cribelar, U.S. Air Forces Central Command Public Affairs

235.description:
U.S. Air Force B1-B Lancer Bombers takeoff at night with Las Vegas in the background.

Film Credits: Video by 2nd Lt. Joshua Sinclair, 28th Bomb Wing Public Affairs

236.description:
Various shots of Red Flag air combat exercise at Nellis AFB, NV. Filmed in January-March 2020.

Film Credits: Video by 2nd Lt. Joshua Sinclair, 28th Bomb Wing Public Affairs -- William Lewis, Nellis AFB Public Affairs

237.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a live-fire, vehicle mounted weapons training exercise at Camp Pendleton, CA on February 27, 2020. Unit - Ordnance Maintenance Company, 1st Maintenance Battalion, 1st Marine Logistics Group.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by LCpl. Kevin Seidensticker, 1st Marine Logistics Group

238.description:
Norway has sent four F-35 Lightning II fighters to police Iceland’s airspace, marking the first deployment abroad for the Royal Norwegian Air Force’s most advanced fighter jet. NATO’s Air Policing mission in Iceland, formally called - Airborne Surveillance and Interception Capabilities to meet Iceland’s Peacetime Preparedness Needs - is responsible for monitoring the airspace in and around Iceland while ensuring that all air traffic is identified. Because Iceland has no military, Allies provide this service on a rotating basis. Filmed on March 5, 2020.

Film Credits: Courtesy Video, Natochannel - Public Domain

239.description:
B-52H Stratofortress bombers takeoff from Barksdale Air Force Base, LA, en route to Nellis Air Force Base, NV, on March 5, 2020.

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Lillian Miller, 2nd Bomb Wing Public Affairs

240.description:
Explosive Ordnance Disposal (EOD) personnel conduct a joint training exercise with Pararescuemen (PJs) at Al Udeid Air Base, Qatar on February 12, 2020. This exercise simulated convoy operations striking an improvised explosive device (IED), to allow EOD members and Pararescuemen to practice caring for casualties until medically evacuated. Units - 48th ERQS, 379th AEW.

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Olivia Grooms, 379th Air Expeditionary Wing Public Affairs

241.description:
A New York Air National Guard LC-130H "Skibird" assigned to the 139th Airlift Squadron, executes a resupply mission at Camp Rockwell, Alaska in support of Exercise Arctic Edge 2020 on March 1, 2020. Arctic Edge is a biennial U.S. Northern Command homeland defense exercise designed to provide high quality and effective training in the extreme cold-weather conditions found in Arctic environments.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman Xavier Navarro, Alaskan NORAD Region/Alaskan Command/11th Air Force

242.description:
U.S. Air Force A-10 Thunderbolt II and F-16 Fighting falcon aircraft crew-members work in conjunction with Royal Thai Air Force members during exercise Cobra Gold 2020 at Korat Royal Thai Air Force Base, Nakhon Ratchasima province, Kingdom of Thailand on March 2, 2020. Exercise Cobra Gold is the largest theater security cooperation exercise in the Indo-Pacific and is an integral part of the U.S. commitment to strengthen engagement in the region. Units - 25th Aircraft Maintenance Unit and 25th Fighter Squadron (A-10s) -- 36th Fighter Squadron (F-16s).

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Sgt. Austin Fox, U.S. Army Pacific Public Affairs Office

243.description:
Amphibious assault ship USS America (LHA-6) conducts F-35B Lightning II strike fighter operations during Exercise Cobra Gold 2020 in the Gulf of Thailand, February, 2020. 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist Seaman Jomark A. Almazan, USS America (LHA-6) -- Video by Petty Officer 1st Class Rufus Hucks, USS America (LHA-6) -- U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist Seaman Apprentice Theodore Lee, USS America (LHA-6)

244.description:
U.S. Soldiers from the Illinois Army National Guard, 106th Aviation Battalion, conduct door gunnery training aboard UH-60 Blackhawk helicopters at Range 29, Fort McCoy in Wisconsin. Filmed on January 10, 2020.

Film Credits: Video by Greg Mason, Fort McCoy Multimedia Visual Information Branch

245.description:
U.S. Air Force Base Nellis, north of Las Vegas, is home to Red Flag exercises every year. Red Flag is an air combat exercise, divided into 4 times per calendar year. It includes aircraft from not only all the U.S. services, but also from multi-national countries allied to the U.S. This video is from Red Flag 20-1, filmed during February, 2020.

Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class Bryan Guthrie, Nellis AFB Public Affairs -- Video by Ronald Bradshaw, 388th Fighter Wing -- Video by William Lewis, Nellis AFB Public Affairs

246.description:
U.S. Air Force AC-130J Ghostrider aircrews fire on targets during exercise Emerald Warrior 20-1 at Alpena Combat Readiness Training Center, Michigan, January, 2020. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Airman 1st Class Hannah Strobel and U.S. Air Force Video by Airman 1st Class Victoria Hadden, Air Force Special Operations Command Public Affairs

247.description:
8th Special Operations Squadron CV-22 Osprey transports U.S. Navy SEALs during exercise Emerald Warrior 20-1 on January 21, 2020, at Alpena Combat Readiness Training Center in Michigan. Emerald Warrior provides annual, realistic pre-deployment training, including multiple joint operating areas to prepare special operations forces to sharpen their abilities to engage around the globe. 

Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. James Merriman, Air Force Special Operations Command Public Affairs

248.description:
First Person point-of-view (POV), as a USAF Crew Chief makes pre-flight checks on an F-16 Fighting Falcon prior to takeoff at Monte Real Air Base (Air Force Base No. 5) in Portugal, during a U.S. flying training deployment (FTD). Filmed on February 17, 2019. Units - 480th Expeditionary Fighter Squadron and the Portuguese Air Force.

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Chanceler Nardone, 52nd Fighter Wing Public Affairs

249.description:
U.S. Marines, 3rd Assault Amphibian Battalion and 2nd Battalion, 1st Marine Regiment, 1st Marine Division, drive assault amphibious vehicles to a beach landing on Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton, and back to the San Antonio-class amphibious transport dock ship, USS Portland (LPD-27), during Exercise Iron Fist 2020. Filmed in February, 2020.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. David Luckey and Cpl. Anabel Abreu Rodriguez, 15th Marine Expeditionary Unit

250.description:
Air Force Special Operations Command (AFSOC) Airmen support F-22 Raptors with forward air refueling point (FARP) training on Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson on January 29, 2020, during exercise Emerald Warrior 20.1. Source: https://www.afsoc.af.mil/News/Article-Display/Article/2079112/special-tactics-operators-simulate-first-ever-extreme-cold-weather-farp-with-ne/

Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Gustavo Castillo, Air Force Special Operations Command Public Affairs

251.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers conduct team-live fire drills at Al Asad Air Base in Iraq on February 5, 2020. Unit - 1st Battalion, 5th Infantry Regiment (Charger Company), 1st Brigade Combat Team, 25th Infantry Division.

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Spc. Derek Mustard, Combined Joint Task Force - Operation Inherent Resolve

252.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcon (Viper) fighter jets takeoff, over a 3 day period from February 10-13, 2020,  from Kunsan Air Base in South Korea. Unit - 8th Fighter Wing "Wolfpack".  

Film Credits: Video by Tech. Sgt. Joshua Arends, 8th Fighter Wing Public Affairs -- Video by Staff Sgt. Anthony Hetlage, 8th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

253.description:
F-35A Lightning II strike fighters from the 421st Fighter Squadron, launch and land at Nellis Air Force Base during exercise Red Flag 20-1, on February 7, 2020. Red Flag 20-1, from January 27 to February 15, is meant to give at least 10 combat-representative sorties to younger pilots to better prepare them for real combat against neer-peer adversaries. 

Film Credits: Video by Ronald Bradshaw, 388th Fighter Wing

254.description:
Various aircraft takeoff from Nellis Air Force Base during night operations at exercise Red Flag 20-1 on February 10, 2020 . Aircraft include: B-1B Lancer, E-3 Sentry AWACS, F/A-18F Super Hornet, EA-18G Growler, F-16 Fighting Falcon, F-35A Lightning II and F-35B Lightning II. 

Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class Bryan Guthrie, Nellis AFB Public Affairs -- Video by William Lewis, Nellis AFB Public Affairs

255.description:
Opening footage - the amphibious assault ship USS America (LHA-6) maneuvers in formation with amphibious dock landing ship USS Germantown (LSD-42), amphibious transport dock ship USS Green Bay (LPD-20) and U.S. 7th Fleet flagship USS Blue Ridge (LCC-19), in the Philippine Sea on January 1, 2020. Following footage - flight deck operations aboard USS America in East China Sea, January, 2020. 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 1st Class Chris Krucke, Released Commander, U.S. 7th Fleet -- U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication 3rd Class Vincent E. Zline, Released USS America (LHA-6) -- U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Vance Hand, Released USS America (LHA-6) -- U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Seaman Jonathan Berlier, Released USS America (LHA-6)

256.description:
