Continuous GoPro shot from under a KC-135 Stratotanker as it lands at the Gulfport Combat Readiness Training Center. Filmed on February 2 during exercise Southern Strike 2020. Unit - 186th Air Refueling Wing, Mississippi Air National Guard.  

Film Credits: Video by Capt. Dusty Culpepper, Joint Force Headquarters, Mississippi National Guard

257.description:
U.S. Marines with 3rd Battalion, 6th Marine Regiment, 2nd Marine Division, test the stopping power of bullets on snow-blocks during Mountain Training Exercise (MTX) 2-20 at Marine Corps Mountain Warfare Training Center, Bridgeport in California on February 6, 2020. The Marines opened fire on blocks of Snowcrete, a mixture of snow and water frozen in cardboard boxes to see how far the bullets would penetrate.  

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Anna Bibbo, 2nd Marine Division

258.description:
Two U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcons assigned to the 480th Expeditionary Fighter Squadron fly in formation with a Portuguese Air Force C-295 aircraft and two Portuguese F-16s over Monte Real Air Base, Portugal on February 5, 2020. 

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Chanceler Nardone, 52nd Fighter Wing Public Affairs

259.description:
A U.S Marine fires an FGM-148 Javelin at Yausubetsu Training Area, Hokkaido, Japan on February 2, 2020. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Gunner Thomas Johnson

260.description:
U.S. Navy Destroyer USS Paul Hamilton (DDG-60) fires various weapons systems during training exercises, including the Close-In Weapons System (CIWS), 5-inch Main Naval gun, 25mm Bushmaster cannon, and an SM-2 vertical launched missile. Filmed in July 2019.  

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Austin Rooney and Jonathan Snyder, Defense Media Activity - Navy Production - Released

261.description:
U.S. Marines training during Exercise Steel Knight 20 (SK20) at Marine Corps Air-Ground Combat Center, Twentynine Palms, California in December 5-12, 2019. SK20 is an annual training exercise with about 13,000 Marines and is designed to improve the 1st Marine Division's ability to fight and win against a near-peer force. Units - 7th Marine Regiment, 1st Marine Division and Company C, 3rd Light Armored Reconnaissance Battalion, 1st Marine Division  

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Courtney G. White; U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Benjamin Aulick

262.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers fire the M-777 Howitzer during a culminating field artillery exercise at Fort Sill, Oklahoma on July 18, 2019.  

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Sgt. Geradine Cadet-Smith, Defense Media Activity - Army

263.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcons take-off during routine training flight operations at Kunsan Air Base in South Korea, January, 2020.  

Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Anthony Hetlage, 8th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

264.description:
Military Working Dog (MWD) Max attached to 1st Special Operations Security Forces Squadron, at Hurlburt Field, FL, is bitten by a Brown Recluse Spider. Through long odds, with major damage to his leg, and under the care of Military veterinarians... MWD Max makes a full recovery. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman Joseph P. Leveille, 1st Special Operations Wing Public Affairs

265.description:
U.S. Marine Corps CH-53E Super Stallion transport helicopters from Marine Heavy Helicopter Squadron 461 (HMH-461) conduct field exercises during deployment for training (DFT) at Colorado Springs, Colorado in January, 2020. The goals of this deployment are to increase the squadron’s proficiency in cold weather and high altitude aviation operations and to improve overall combat readiness.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Elias E. Pimentel III, 2nd Marine Aircraft Wing

266.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15E Strike Eagles execute an aerial refueling mission over parts of the Middle East, as seen through the lens of Combat Camera on January 15, 2020. Units - F-15E Strike Eagles, 494th Expeditionary Fighter Squadron -- KC-10 Extender, 908th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman Brandon Cribelar, U.S. Air Forces Central Command Public Affairs

267.description:
U.S. Marines board CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters during exercise Steel Knight on Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton in California on December 6, 2019.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Mark A. Lowe II

268.description:
USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78), the Navy's newest aircraft carrier, conducts flight operations in the Atlantic Ocean. EA-18G Growlers get fueled and then take-off and land on the USS Ford to test the Electromagnetic Aircraft Launch Systems (EMALS) and Advanced Arresting Gear (AAG) on January 19, 2020.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist Seaman Jesus O. Aguiar

269.description:
1st Battalion, 9th Cavalry Regiment, 2nd Armored Brigade Combat Team, 1st Cavalry Division conducts a live-fire exercise in Pabradé, Lithuania, January 2020. In Vietnam, it is estimated that the 1st Squadron, 9th Cavalry was responsible for 50 percent of all enemy soldiers killed by the 1st Cavalry Division during the war. It was for this reason that the Squadron earned the nickname The Headhunters.

Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Scott Longstreet, 241st Mobile Public Affairs Detachment

270.description:
T-45 Goshawk, assigned to Air Test and Evaluation Squadron (VX-23), takeoff and land on the aircraft carrier USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78) during sea trials and testing the Electromagnetic Aircraft Launch Systems (EMALS) and Advanced Arresting Gear (AAG). Filmed January 18, 2020.

Film Credits: Video by Petty Officer 3rd Class Connor Loessin, USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN 78)

271.description:
The U.S. Air Force E-4B "Nightwatch" plane (aka Doomsday Plane) is designed to ensure continuity of government in the event of a surprise nuclear attack on the United States. In case of attack, the President, Vice President, and the Joint Chiefs of Staff would board the E-4B at a secret location to assume control of the remaining American nuclear forces. The E-4B would then fly a top-secret route, and could stay in the air for days with the assistance of aerial refueling tankers. The E-4B is reinforced against the effects of electromagnetic pulse (EMP), so its command and control communications, theoretically would not be cut off by incoming nuclear explosions. Filmed December 2019.
    
Film Credits: Video by Kevin Schwandt, 55th Wing Public Affairs

272.description:
Sentry Aloha is an ongoing series of fighter exercises, hosted by the Hawaii Air National Guard's 154th Wing, involving multiple types of aircraft and services. Sentry Aloha provides tailored, cost effective and realistic combat training for U.S. Air Force, Air National Guard and other Department of Defense services to provide U.S. warfighters with the skill sets necessary to perform their homeland defense and overseas combat missions. This iteration of Sentry Aloha 20-1 consists of approximately 1,000 Airmen from 15 Active Duty, ANG and Air Force Reserve units across eight states. Filmed on January 8, 2020.
    
Film Credits: Video by Tech. Sgt. Christian Jadot, 144th Fighter Wing Public Affairs -- Video by Staff Sgt. Joshua Halverson, 128th Air Refueling Wing Public Affairs

273.description:
B-52H Stratofortress scramble, cart start and MITO take-off. B-2 Spirit take-off and aerial refueling. F-35A Lighting II taxi and take-off, plus aerial footage. All in one video.
    
Film Credits: Courtesy Video clips from Secretary of the Air Force Public Affairs - Released

274.description:
On January 9, 2020, while conducting routine operations in the North Arabian Sea, USS Farragut (DDG-99) was aggressively approached by a Russian Navy ship. Farragut sounded five short blasts, the international maritime signal for danger of a collision, and requested the Russian ship to alter course in accordance with international rules of the road. The Russian ship initially refused but ultimately altered course and the two ships opened distance from one another.
    
Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Petty Officer 3rd Class Dawson Roth, U.S. Naval Forces Central Command / U.S. 5th Fleet - Released

275.description:
A U.S. Air Force KC-135 Stratotanker conducts aerial refueling with a B-52H Stratofortress during Bomber Task Force 20-1 over the Arctic Sea, with air traffic control chatter aboard the KC-135. Filmed on November 4, 2019.
    
Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. James Cason

276.description:
Forward Looking Infrared video (FLIR) shows U.S. Marines landing in MV-22B Osprey aircraft at the U.S. Embassy compound in Iraq as a crisis response force to protect it from protesters during heightened tensions on December 31, 2019. Approximately 100 Marines were deployed to protect the U. S. Embassy in Baghdad, Iraq after protesters stormed the embassy gates trying to get inside the perimeter. The protests are in response to U.S. airstrikes on Iranian backed militia groups. The U.S. airstrikes were a response to earlier rocket attacks by the militia groups which killed an American contractor and injured several U.S. service members.
    
Film Credits: Courtesy Video, Combined Joint Task Force - Operation Inherent Resolve

277.description:
U.S. Marines assigned to Special Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force-Crisis Response-Central Command (SPMAFTF-CR-CC) 19.2, prepare to deploy from Kuwait in support of a crisis response mission on December 31, 2019. Approximately 100 Marines were deployed to protect the U. S. Embassy in Baghdad, Iraq after protesters stormed the embassy gates trying to get inside of the perimeter. The protests are a reaction to U.S. airstrikes on Iranian backed militia. The U.S. airstrikes were a response to earlier rocket attacks by the militia which killed an American contractor and injured several U.S. service members.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Robert Gavaldon and Sgt. David Bickel, Special Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force Crisis Response - Central Command

278.description:
U.S. Air Force Global Strike Command named the MH-139A helicopter, “Grey Wolf” during a naming ceremony at Eglin AFB, Florida on December 19, 2019. The Grey Wolf will primarily be used by Air Force security teams to guard ICBM sites. The Air Force plans to buy up to 84 of the aircraft at a cost of $2.4 billion.
    
Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Philip Bryant, 2nd Bomb Wing Public Affairs

279.description:
U.S. Marines have a number of ways to destroy enemy ground troops. Helicopter gunships are one of the most effective and efficient ways of achieving that objective. Video shows various U.S. Marines training exercises with UH-1Y Venom and AH-1Z Viper attack helicopters at Chocolate Mountain, Aerial Gunnery Range in California.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Jeremiah O. Naranjo, U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Aaron James Vinculado, U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Daniel D. Kujanpaa, Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1)

280.description:
F-35A Lightning II aircraft from the 158th Fighter Wing, Vermont Air National Guard base in South Burlington, nicknamed "The Green Mountain Boys", takeoff and land during routine flight operations. Filmed over October - December, 2019.
    
Film Credits: Video by Master Sgt. Michael Davis, 158th Fighter Wing

281.description:
U-2 pilots reach an average altitude of 70,000 feet to perform reconnaissance missions. Without suiting up, the air pressure changes would make their blood boil and cause blood vessels to pop. 
    
Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Benjamin Bugenig and Senior Airman Darien Perez, 51st Fighter Wing Public Affairs

282.description:
U.S. Air Force KC-10 Extender from 908th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron refuel USAF F-35 Lightning II strike fighters over United Arab Emirates on November 23, 2019. 
    
Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. Bethany La Ville, U.S. Air Forces Central Command Public Affairs

283.description:
A USAF C-130 Hercules from the 153rd Airlift Wing, Wyoming Air National Guard, fires flares at sunset over Camp Guernsey Joint Training Center during a training mission on Sept. 24, 2019. 
    
Film Credits: U.S. Air National Guard Video by Tech. Sgt. Jacqueline Marshall, 153rd Airlift Wing, Wyoming National Guard

284.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15E Strike Eagles refuel to stay on station over the Middle East on December 1, 2019. 
   
Film Credits: Video by Tech. Sgt. Joshua Williams, 380th Air Expeditionary Wing Public Affairs

285.description:
Mezzo-soprano vocalist, Gunnery Sergeant Sara Sheffield, member of "The President's Own" United States Marine Band, sings "God Rest Ye Merry Gentlemen" in Washington DC on December 12, 2019. More info on the United States Marine Band and Sara Sheffield here:
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Marine_Band
https://www.marineband.marines.mil/Members/Musicians/Vocalists/
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sara_Sheffield 

Film Credits: Courtesy Video, "The President's Own" U.S. Marine Band

286.description:
U.S. Coast Guard Cutter Bertholf (WMSL-750) boarding teams interdict a low-profile go-fast boat while patrolling international waters in the Eastern Pacific Ocean, seizing more than 3,100 pounds of suspected cocaine on November 4, 2019.

Film Credits: Courtesy Video U.S. Coast Guard Pacific Area

287.description:
The 2019 Guardian Angel Military Freefall Jumpmaster Course at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base in Tucson, AZ, is a U.S. DoD Special Operations Command accredited freefall jumpmaster course designed to train senior military parachutists on running a military parachute operation. The training includes teaching different jumping techniques, familiarizing jumpers with different pieces of equipment, executing the directing of jumpers to a designated release point and accomplishing two live jumps. Filmed in October 2019. More info about 2019 Guardian Angel Military Freefall Jumpmaster Course here: https://www.dm.af.mil/Media/News/Article/1981513/falling-with-style/     

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Blake Gonzales, 355th Wing

288.description:
5th Special Forces Group (Airborne) Green Berets conduct breaching and room clearing training at Fort Campbell, KY on April, 16 2019.     

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Staff Sgt. Iman Broady-Chin, 5th Special Forces Public Affairs Office

289.description:
U.S. Air Force A-10 Thunderbolt II and F-16 Fighting Falcon fighter jets receive fuel over Afghanistan during ongoing combat operations on November 12, 2019. Unit - 340th Expeditionary Aerial Refueling Squadron.   

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Airman 1st Class Brandon Cribelar, 455th Air Expeditionary Wing Public Affairs

290.description:
A U.S. Air Force C-130J Super Hercules aircrew execute two combat airdrops over undisclosed locations in Afghanistan on December 9, 2019. Unit - 774th Expeditionary Airlift Squadron.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Airman 1st Class Brandon Cribelar, 455th Air Expeditionary Wing Public Affairs

291.description:
The U.S. Air Force - 11th Bomb Squadron, located at Barkdale AFB, is the only unit in the world providing all aspects of B-52 aircrew training. This brief video shows scenes of an instructor flight over Louisiana on December 5, 2019.

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Stuart Bright, 2nd Bomb Wing Public Affairs

292.description:
U.S. Air Force F-35A strike aircraft integrate with U.S. Army artillery during a live-fire exercise at Fort Bliss, TX on November 6, 2019. Interviews with Military personnel explaining the exercise. 

Film Credits: Video by Sgt. Dontavian Harrison, 24th Theater Public Affairs Support Element -- Air Force Staff Sgt. Tarelle Walker, 33rd Fighter Wing Public Affairs -- Interviews with U.S. Army Maj. William O'Neill, Operations Officer with 1st Armored Division, Division Artillery, and U.S. Air Force Cpt. Patrick Burns, Intelligence Officer with 7th Air support Operations Squadron, based out of Fort Hood, Texas

293.description:
U.S. Soldiers from the 300 Military Police Brigade conduct crew gunnery, firing 50 Caliber, M249 machine gun and CROW on Range 26 at Fort McCoy, WI.

Film Credits: Video by Greg Mason, Fort McCoy Multimedia Visual Information Branch

294.description:
U.S. Marines shoot a stationary marksmanship target range as part of cold-weather training in Setermoen, Norway on November 27, 2019. Unit - Marine Rotational Force-Europe 20.1, Marine Forces Europe and Africa.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Menelik Collins, U.S. Marine Corps Forces, Europe and Africa

295.description:
U.S. Marines assigned to Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 161 (VMM-161), conduct MV-22B Osprey deck landing qualification aboard the expeditionary staging base USS Lewis B. Puller (ESB-3) in an undisclosed location on October 28, 2019.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl Rhita Daniel, Special Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force Crisis Response - Central Command

296.description:
U.S. Marines conduct training exercises at Marine Corps Air-Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms (MCAGCC) in California. MCAGCC has the nickname "29 Stumps" or just "The Stumps", because it's in the middle of the desert and there is not a palm tree to be found. Marines with 2d Light Armored Reconnaissance Battalion, 2nd Marine Division conduct a Regimental Assault Course (RAC), and convoy/patrol operations during Integrated Training Exercise (ITX) 1-20. Filmed in October, 2019.  

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Ashley McLaughlin, 2nd Marine Division

297.description:
U.S. Military personnel share a Thanksgiving Day feast at Ali Al Salem Air Base in Kuwait. Base leadership took turns serving the meals to make sure everyone had a full plate during their deployment over the 2019 Thanksgiving holiday. Make a comment to the thousands of U.S. men and women who are serving today, far away from their homes, family, and friends. They deserve your respect.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Tech. Sgt. Michael Mason, 386th Air Expeditionary Wing Public Affairs

298.description:
Air defense exercise Amalgam Dart on November 21, 2019, over Knoxville, TN... a few F-16 Fighting Falcons intercept a plane in the restricted airspace and escort a Cessna-type aircraft out of the area.
 
Film Credits: Video by Lt. Col. CONR NORAD, North American Aerospace Defense Command

299.description:
The NASA Super Guppy, wide-bodied cargo aircraft, landed at Mansfield-Lahm Regional Airport on November 24, 2019 while transporting the Orion space capsule. The Orion vehicle is set to be tested in Ohio and the 179th Airlift Wing of the Ohio Air National Guard provided airlift and ground support to NASA during this phase of the mission. Thank you for your hard work. 
 
Film Credits: U.S. Air National Guard Video by Senior Airman Marc Wilson - released - 179th Airlift Wing

300.description:
U.S. Marines with Marine Rotational Force-Europe 20.1 (MRF-E), conduct ice-breaking drills during cold-weather training at Setermoen, Norway on November 22, 2019. MRF-E focuses on regional engagements throughout Europe by conducting various exercises, arctic cold-weather and mountain-warfare training, and military-to-military engagements, which enhance overall interoperability of the U.S. Marine Corps with allies.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Menelik Collins, U.S. Marine Corps Forces - Europe and Africa

301.description:
Aircrew from the 4th Special Operations Squadron fly a training sortie on an AC-130U Spooky Gunship over Navarre, Florida on November 4, 2019. During the flight they fired 105mm, 40mm and 25mm rounds at targets to train and enhance their capabilities in preparation for deployment.
 
Film Credits: Video by Master Sgt. Jeffrey Curtin, 1st Special Operations Wing Public Affairs

302.description:
U.S. Marines with Charlie Company, 1st Battalion, 3rd Marine Regiment, conduct a live-fire platoon attack on Range 10 during Exercise Bougainville II at Pohakuloa Training Area, Hawaii on October 22, 2019. Bougainville II is the second phase of pre-deployment exercise conducted by the battalion to enhance unit combat readiness.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Eric Tso, III Marine Expeditionary Force

303.description:
Cockpit video from a U.S. Air Force T-38 Talon training flight at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base, AZ on November 11, 2019. The T-38s are based at Sheppard Air Force Base, TX and were conducting training directed by Luke Air Force Base, AZ.
 
Film Credits: Footage by Senior Airman Mya Crosby and Airman 1st Class Blake Gonzales. Edited by Airman 1st Class Blake Gonzales, 355th Wing

304.description:
Two U.S. Air Force B-1B Lancer bombers land at Prince Sultan Air Base (PSAB), in Saudi Arabia on October 25, 2019. This marks the first time B-1B aircraft have been deployed to Saudi Arabia. 
 
Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman Matthew Zakrzewski, U.S. Air Forces Central Command Public Affairs

305.description:
U.S. Soldiers conduct a live-fire exercise during exercise Dragoon Ready 20 at Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany on October 30, 2019. Unit - 3rd Squadron, 2d Cavalry Regiment.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Christoph Koppers, Training Support Activity Europe

306.description:
U.S. Marine Pilots with Marine All Weather Fighter Attack Squadron 224 (VMFA(AW)-224) get ready for flight training with the Japanese Air Self Defense Force (JASDF) during an aviation training relocation (ATR) to Misawa Air Base, Japan during October, 2019. VMFA(AW)-224 is an F/A-18 Hornet squadron home-based at Marine Corps Air Station Beaufort, South Carolina.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Jaxson Fryar, American Forces Network Iwakuni

307.description:
B-52 Stratofortresse bombers deployed from Barksdale Air Force Base take off from RAF Fairford, England, November 8, 2019... B-52H from 20th Bomb Squadron in training at the Joint Pacific Alaska Range Complex, November 11, 2019 ... USAF B-52H Stratofortress assigned to the 20th Expeditionary Bomb Squadron lands at Al Udeid Air Base, Qatar, May 8, 2019.
 
Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Philip Bryant, 2nd Bomb Wing Public Affairs -- Video by Airman 1st Class Lillian Miller, 2nd Bomb Wing Public Affairs -- Video by Senior Airman Jourdan Barrons, U.S. Air Forces Central Command Public Affairs

308.description:
An F-16 Fighting Falcon from the 138th Fighter Wing flies through another jets contrail at the Pacific Missile Range Facility near the island of Kauai, Hawaii.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Air National Guard Video by TSgt. Phillip Cowen, 138th Fighter Wing

309.description:
Polish Air Force F-16C Fighting Falcons engage in a planned intercept and escort of a U.S. Air Force B-52H Stratofortress over Poland during exercise Bomber Task Force Europe 20-1, on October 28, 2019.
 
Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class Duncan Bevan, 1st Combat Camera Squadron

310.description:
U.S. Air Force B-52H Stratofortress bombers take part in exercise Bomber Task Force 20-1 (Oct-Nov 2019). Scenes include: B-52H Stratofortress from 2nd Bomb Wing flies a sortie from Souda Bay, Greece back to Fairford, England on November 4, 2019... B-52H Stratofortress flies a sortie from RAF Fairford over Saudi Arabia on November 1, 2019... B-52H Stratofortress refuels with a 100th Air Refueling Wing KC-135 Stratotanker and flies a sortie over the Arctic Sea on November 4, 2019... Two B-52H bombers assigned to the 96th Bomb Squadron fly in formation over the Baltic Sea on October 23, 2019... B-52H Stratofortress aircraft from Barksdale Air Force Base fly a sortie with the Royal Norwegian Air Force over Norway on October 30, 2019.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Tech. Sgt. Christopher Ruano/1st Combat Camera Squadron  --  U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. James Cason, 1st Combat Camera Squadron  --  U.S. Air Force Video by Airman 1st Class Duncan C. Bevan, 1st Combat Camera Squadron

311.description:
Backseat cockpit GoPro video of the Weapons Systems Officer (WSO) in a U.S. Air Force F-15E Strike Eagle, 492nd Fighter Squadron, out of RAF Lakenheath on November 7, 2019.
 
Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class Anthony Clingerman, 48th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

312.description:
U.S. Marines with Combined Anti-Armor Team, 1st Battalion, 3rd Marine Regiment, conduct a Convoy live-fire movement at Range 20A during Exercise Bougainville II at Pohakuloa Training Area, Hawaii on October 18, 2019.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Eric Tso, III Marine Expeditionary Force

313.description:
Follow the crew of USS Paul Hamilton (DDG-60) underway in the Pacific, as the crew talks about life on a USN Destroyer - from what they do for work, to where they eat, sleep, and work out. Filmed in July 2019.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Austin Rooney, Defense Media Activity-Navy Production - released

314.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a Regimental Assault Course during Integrated Training Exercise (ITX 1-20) on Marine Corps Air-Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms, California on October 28-30, 2019.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corp Video by Lance Cpl. Sydney Smith, and Sgt. Sylvia L. Tapia

315.description:
U.S. Marines with 3rd Reconnaissance Battalion, 3rd Marine Division conduct parachute operations from a KC-130 Hercules and a UH-1N Huey on Ie Shima, Okinawa, Japan in October 2019. This training included Marines from 3rd Transportation Support Battalion and 3rd Marine Logistics Group.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Josue Marquez, 3rd Marine Division

316.description:
B-52H Stratofortress bombers from Barksdale Air Force Base takeoff during exercise Global Thunder 2019. Over Europe B-52s train together on bomb runs with the French Air Force during Bomber Task Force Europe 20-1. Filmed on October 24-25, 2019. Unit - 2nd Bomb Wing, USAF.
 
Film Credits: Video by Tech. Sgt. Mike Meares and Tech. Sgt. Christopher Ruano

317.description:
Scenes from Integrated Training Exercise (ITX) 1-20 at Twentynine Palms, California, in October 2019. The purpose of ITX 1-20 is to create a challenging, realistic training environment that produces combat ready forces capable of operating as an integrated Marine Air-Ground Task Force (MAGTF).
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Andrew Smith, and Sgt. Sylvia L. Tapia

318.description:
View from cockpit as U.S. Air Force B-52H Stratofortress bombers takeoff from RAF Fairford, England, during exercise Bomber Task Force Europe 20-1. Also, view the weapon systems officers performing duties. Filmed on October 21, 2019.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. Philip Bryant, 2nd Bomb Wing Public Affairs, and Tech. Sgt. Christopher Ruano, 1st Combat Camera Squadron

319.description:
U.S. Air Force 15E Strike Eagles assigned to the 494th Fighter Squadron takeoff at night from RAF Lakenheath, England on October 18, 2019.
 
Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Rachel Maxwell, 48th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

320.description:
Aerial footage of a B-2 Spirit bomber from the 509th Bomb Wing at Whiteman Air Force Base, MO. Filmed March 2019.
 
Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Matthew Hester, 3d Audiovisual Squadron

321.description:
U.S. Marines with Alpha Company, 2d Light Armored Reconnaissance Battalion, 2nd Marine Division, conduct platoon attacks during Integrated Training Exercise (ITX) 1-20, at Marine Corps Air-Ground Combat Center, Twentynine Palms, California, October 6, 2019.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Ashley McLaughlin, 2nd Marine Division

322.description:
A U.S. Air Force B-52H Stratofortress conducts a training mission out of RAF Fairford, England, during Bomber Task Force Europe 20-1, October 22, 2019. Video shows views of pilot-cockpit and combat systems officers during takeoff, in-flight and landing. Bomber Task Force Europe 20-1 is an exercise designed to familiarize aircrew with European airspace and reassure allies in the region. Unit - 96th Bomb Squadron, Barksdale Air Force Base, Louisiana.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. James Cason, 1st Combat Camera Squadron

323.description:
A U.S. Air Force B-52 Stratofortress conducts a training mission in support of Bomber Task Force Europe 20-1 on October 15, 2019, at RAF Fairford, England. Unit - 2nd Bomb Wing, Barksdale Air Force Base, Louisiana.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. Philip Bryant, 2nd Bomb Wing Public Affairs, and Tech. Sgt. Christopher Ruano, 1st Combat Camera Squadron

324.description:
U.S. Marines conduct an MV-22B Osprey aircraft tail gunnery certification during Weapons and Tactics Instructor (WTI) course 1-20 inside Shade Tree Range, California on October 8, 2019. WTI is a seven-week training event hosted by Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1), which emphasizes operational integration of the six functions of Marine Corps aviation in support of a Marine Air Ground Task Force. WTI also provides standardized advanced tactical training and certification of unit instructor qualifications to support Marine aviation training and readiness, and assists in developing and employing aviation weapons and tactics.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Lauren Brune, Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One

325.description:
Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Timothy Schumaker, assigned to The U.S. Navy Flight Demonstration Squadron, the Blue Angels, films a joint flight with the World War II era B-29 Superfortresss “Doc” from the backseat of an F-18 Hornet flown by Lt. Cmdr Cary Rickoff during the 2019 California Capital Air Show in Sacramento on October 10, 2019. 
 
Film Credits: Video by Petty Officer 2nd Class Timothy Schumaker, Navy Flight Demonstration Squadron

326.description:
U.S. Air Force C-17 Globemaster III transport jets are the backbone of U.S. Military air mobility. The United States currently (2019) has over 200 C-17s in service. 
 
Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Nicholas Brown, 15th Wing Public Affairs

327.description:
U.S. Navy Blue Angels demonstration team F/A-18 Hornets conduct aerial refueling with a KC-10 Extender over Arizona, on their way to Kelly Field, San Antonio, Texas on October 14, 2019. KC-10 Extender Unit - 9th Air Refueling Squadron, Travis Air Force Base, CA.
 
Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class Amy Younger, 60th Air Mobility Wing Public Affairs

328.description:
U.S. Marines with Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron (VMM-262) conduct flight operations during exercise KAMANDAG 3 over Subic Bay, Philippines on October 12, 2019. KAMANDAG is an acronym for the Filipino phrase “Kaagapay Ng Mga Manirigma Ng Dagat,” which translates to “Cooperation of the Warriors of the Sea,” highlighting the partnership between the U.S. and Philippine militaries.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Seth Rosenberg, 3rd Marine Expeditionary Brigade

329.description:
U.S. Air Force Fighting Falcon fighter jets takeoff at sunset on Kunsan Air Base, South Korea, October 10, 2019. Unit - 8th Fighter Wing. 
 
Film Credits: Video by Tech. Sgt. Joshua Arends, 8th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

330.description:
U.S. Marine Corps MV-22B Osprey crew-members conduct training exercises during Weapons and Tactics Instructor (WTI) course 1-20 in Yuma, Arizona, on October 5, 2019.  
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Cody Rowe, Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One

331.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 8th Fighter Wing "Wolf Pack", taxi and takeoff during routine training operations at Kunsan Air Base, South Korea, on October 10, 2019. 
 
Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Anthony Hetlage, 8th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

332.description:
U.S. Navy Operations Specialist "A" School is a 10 week enlisted course located at the Naval Training Center (NTC) Great Lakes, Illinois. Filmed on August 1, 2019. More information about USN Operations Specialist here: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operations_specialist_(United_States_Navy) and here: https://www.cool.navy.mil/usn/enlisted/rating_info_cards/os.pdf
 
Film Credits: Video by Petty Officer 3rd Class Joshua DuFrane, Defense Media Activity-Navy Production

333.description:
U.S. Airmen perform maintenance and pre-flight checks prior to launching F-22 Raptor fighter jets in a simulated biological/chemical attack scenario during Exercise Polar Force 2019 at Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson, Alaska in October 2019.
 
Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Johnathon Wines, Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson Public Affairs

334.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers with Alpha Battery, 3rd Battalion, 29th Field Artillery Regiment, 4th Infantry Division, fire a M109A6 Paladin in support of joint training exercise Eager Lion 2019 at Training Area 1 in the country of Jordan on August 27, 2019. 
 
Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Sgt. Samantha Lewis, 55th Combat Camera

335.description:
A U.S. Air Force C-5M Super Galaxy transport plane takes-off from Marine Corps Air Station Camp Pendleton, California on October 4, 2019.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Andrew Cortez, Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton

336.description:
A U.S. Air Force C-5M Super Galaxy lands at Marine Corps Air Station (MCAS) Camp Pendleton on October 2, 2019. The C-5M is capable of embarking almost any piece of Marine Corps combat equipment and delivering it to any location in the world.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Lisa Collins, Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One

337.description:
U.S. Marines aboard UH-1Y Venom helicopters assigned to Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1), conduct an offensive air support exercise during Weapons and Tactics Instructor (WTI) course 1-20 at Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range, California on September 30, 2019. WTI is a seven-week training event hosted by MAWTS-1, which emphasizes operational integration of the six functions of Marine Corps aviation in support of a Marine Air Ground Task Force. More info on the six functions of Marine Corps aviation: https://www.trngcmd.marines.mil/Portals/207/Docs/TBS/W280011XQ-DM%20Six%20Funtions%20of%20Marine%20Aviation.pdf?ver=2017-01-24-160308-980
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Lisa Collins, Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One

338.description:
U.S. Marines with 2nd Battalion, 5th Marine Regiment, 1st Marine Division, participate in a Marine Corps Combat Readiness Evaluation (MCCRE) on Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton, California on September 23, 2019. A breakdown of MCCRE: https://www.marines.mil/Portals/1/MCO%203501.1D.pdf
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Joseph Prado, 1st Marine Division

339.description:
U.S. Air Force B-2 Stealth Bombers land at RAF Fairford, England during exercise Bomber Task Force on September 11, 2019.
 
Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Kristin Cerri, 509th Bomb Wing Public Affairs, USAFE Public Affairs

340.description:
Exercise Mobility Guardian is a large scale USAF exercise at Fairchild Air Force Base designed to simulate the need to move war assets into position in short notice. Filmed September 27, 2019.
 
Film Credits: Video by Tech. Sgt. Esteban Esquivel, 436th Airlift Wing Public Affairs and Video by Staff Sgt. Heather Fejerang, 6th Air Mobility Wing Public Affairs

341.description:
A U.S. Air Force HC-130J Combat King II aircraft refuels HH-60G Pave Hawk helicopters during a Hurricane Dorian relief flight to the Bahamas on September 9, 2019. Unit - 334th Air Expeditionary Group, Patrick AFB.

Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class Hayden Legg, 2019 Hurricane Season DoD Response

342.description:
Three different Hi-Definition aerial refueling clips from 2019, featuring USAF aircraft: (1) A KC-135 Stratotanker refuels a B-2 Spirit bomber, 509th Bomb Wing, Whiteman AFB, Missouri, and flies in formation with F-15s from the 48th Fighter Wing, RAF Lakenheath, and Royal Air Force F-35s from RAF Marham on September 16, 2019. (2) A-10 Thunderbolt II "Warthogs" conduct inflight refueling with a KC-135 from the 28th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron, over an undisclosed location on September 14, 2019. (3) A KC-135 Stratotanker from the 92nd Air Refueling Wing assigned to Fairchild Air Force Base, Washington, refuels a B-52H Stratofortress during Exercise Mobility Guardian 2019 on September 19, 2019. 

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Kelly OConnor, 100th Air Refueling Wing Public Affairs -- Video by Senior Airman Roslyn Ward, U.S. Air Forces Central Command Public Affairs -- Video by Senior Airman Xavier Navarro, 1st Combat Camera Squadron

343.description:
The first two (of 20 scheduled) F-35 Lightning II strike fighters arrive at Vermont Air National Guard Base, South Burlington, Vermont on September 19, 2019. Plus, a promo clip of F-35 demo team over Oregon International Airshow on September 21, 2019

Film Credits: Video by Master Sgt. Michael Davis, 158th Fighter Wing -- Video by Senior Airman Alexander Cook, F-35A Demo Team Public Affairs

344.description:
Royal Air Force F-35 Lightning II strike fighters conduct aerial refueling training (probe and drogue method) with a U.S. Air Force KC-135 on September 16, 2019. The RAF F-35s are based at RAF Marham and the KC-135 is based at RAF Mildenhall.

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Kelly OConnor, 100th Air Refueling Wing Public Affairs

345.description:
U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptor fighter jets takeoff at Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson, Alaska on June 5, 2019.

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Johnathon Wines, Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson Public Affairs

346.description:
While the C-17 Globemaster III (233 in service - 2019) is smaller than the C-5 Galaxy (56 in service - 2019) and cannot transport as much cargo per plane than the C-5, the C-17 is the backbone of U.S. Military cargo transport. The C-17 is capable of carrying an M-1 Abrams tank. This video is footage of Exercise Mobility Guardian 2019. Units - 16th Airlift Squadron, from Joint Base Charleston - 517th Airlift Squadron from Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson - 92nd Air Refueling Squadron from Fairchild Air Force Base - 437th Airlift Wing from Charleston Air Force Base. More info about the C-17 vs C-5 from these links:
https://www.af.mil/About-Us/Fact-Sheets/Display/Article/1529726/c-17-globemaster-iii/
https://www.popularmechanics.com/military/aviation/a26716/air-force-reactivating-c-5-galaxy/

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sergeant Shawn White, Senior Airman Xavier Navarro

347.description:
U.S. Marines with Golf Company, Battalion Landing Team, 2nd Battalion, 1st Marines, 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit, execute launch and recovery of Combat Rubber Raiding Craft (CRRC) aboard the dock landing ship USS Ashland (LSD-48), underway in the Coral Sea on July 18, 2019 

Film Credits: Official U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Brennan Priest

348.description:
U.S. Marines conduct semi-annual live-fire qualifications with M1A1 main battle tanks at Camp Buehring, Kuwait on August 19, 2019. Unit - India Company, Battalion Landing Team 3/5, 11th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU). 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Israel Chincio - Released

349.description:
U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptors conduct an evacuation in preparation for Hurricane Dorian at Joint Base Langley-Eustis, Virginia on September 4, 2019. F-22's and T-38 Talons flew to Rickenbacker Air National Guard Base, Ohio so they would be safe from the storm. 

Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class John Foister, 633rd Air Base Wing Public Affairs

350.description:
U.S. Marines practice combat beach assault techniques from the San Antonio-class amphibious transport dock ship - USS Somerset (LPD-25). Filmed in August and September 2019.

Film Credits: Video by Sgt. Tyler Harrison and Sgt. Conner Robbins, 1st Marine Logistics Group

351.description:
U.S. Marine Corps CH-53E Super Stallions land aboard USS Somerset (LPD-25) during Arctic Expeditionary Capabilities Exercise 2019 (AECE 19) on September 7, 2019. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Conner Robbins, 1st Marine Logistics Group

352.description:
U.S. Air Force, 2nd Aerial Refueling Squadron, KC-10 Extender refuels Navy EA-18 Growlers, Navy F/A-18 Super Hornets, and a USAF B-2 Spirit during exercise Northern Edge on May 23, 2019.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by SSgt Bethany La Ville, Pacific Air Forces Public Affairs

353.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15C Eagle and two F-15E Strike Eagles assigned to the 48th Fighter Wing painted with their respective squadron heritage color scheme, rendezvous with a KC-135 Stratotanker assigned to the 100th Air Refueling Wing in support of a fly-over the MSPO Expo (International Defense Industry Exhibition) at Kielce, Poland Sept. 3, 2019.

Film Credits: Video by Capt. Scott Kuhn, 3rd Armored Brigade Combat Team, 1st Cavalry Division

354.description:
Live-Fire room clearing training by A Company, 2nd Battalion, 7th Cavalry Regiment, 3rd Armored Brigade Combat Team, 1st Cavalry Division in South Korea on August 16, 2019.

Film Credits: Video by Capt. Scott Kuhn, 3rd Armored Brigade Combat Team, 1st Cavalry Division

355.description:
U.S. Marines with Marine Rotational Force - Darwin (MRF-D), conduct a fire-mission with M-777 Howitzers during Exercise Koolendong at Mount Bundey Training Area, NT, Australia. Koolendong is a high-end war-fighting exercise designed to increase inter-operability between U.S. Marines and the Australian Defense Force. Filmed in August 2019. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Kallahan Morris and Lance Cpl. Brandon Salas, Marine Rotational Force Darwin

356.description:
U.S. Air Force Special Tactics Operators secure and open a forward arming and refueling point (FARP) from an MC-130J Commando II aircraft for two F-35A Lightning II and two F-15E Strike Eagle fighter jets during Operation Rapid Forge at Ämari Air Base in Estonia on July 25, 2019. The MC-130J Commando II, and aircrew, are able to execute refueling missions in austere, sensitive or hostile territories. AFSOC (Air Force Special Operations Command) operators are the U.S. Air Force's special operations ground force, leading global access, precision strike, personnel recovery, and surgery operations on the battlefield. Operation Rapid Forge integrates NATO nations to enhance readiness and improve interoperability between U.S. Allies and partners in Europe.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. Rose Gudex, 24th Special Operations Wing Public Affairs

357.description:
U.S. Marines with the Ground Combat Element, Marine Rotational Force – Darwin (MRF-D), participate in Exercise Tafakula at Taliai Military Camp, Tonga on August 12-23, 2019. Tafakula is a multilateral exercise hosted by His Majesty’s Armed Forces of Tonga, which includes MRF-D Marines and service members from the New Caledonian Armed Forces, the New Zealand Defense Force, the Australian Defense Force and the Nevada National Guard. This exercise provides an great opportunity to develop relationships, learn about each other's cultures, and share military capabilities.


Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Staff Sgt. Jordan Gilbert, Marine Rotational Force Darwin

358.description:
A U.S. Air Force B-2 Spirit bomber flies with two U.K. Royal Air Force F-35 Lighting II fighter jets while on a Bomber Task Force training exercise over England on August 29, 2019. B-2 Unit - 509th Bomb Wing.


Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman James Merriman, 1st Combat Camera Squadron

359.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15C/D Eagle fighter jets land at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base, Ohio after evacuating from Jacksonville Air National Guard Base, Florida, in advance of Hurricane Dorian on August 30, 2019.


Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Phil Cowen, 88th Air Base Wing Public Affairs

360.description:
The U.S. Missile Defense Agency, Ballistic Missile Defense System Operational Test Agency, and U.S. Army soldiers of the E-62 Battery, 11th Air Defense Artillery Brigade, conducted an intercept test of the Terminal High Altitude Area Defense (THAAD) element of the U.S. Ballistic Missile Defense System. This was flight test THAAD-23 on August 30, 2019.


Film Credits: Missile Defense Agency, Approved for Public Release 19-MDA-10187

361.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcons takeoff on a routine training flight at Kunsan Air Base in South Korea on August 26, 2019. Unit -  Gold tail stripe 80th Fighter Squadron. Blue tail stripe 35th Fighter Squadron.


Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Anthony Hetlage, 8th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

362.description:
The U.S. Army conducted a live-fire range with Abrams Tanks and Bradley Fighting Vehicles as part of exercise Eager Lion 2019 in Jordan on August 26. Unit - C Company, 1st Battalion, 68th Armor Regiment, 3rd Armored Brigade Combat Team, 4th Infantry Division.


Film Credits: Video by Maj. Jason Koontz, 3rd Brigade Combat Team, 4th Infantry Division

363.description:
Cockpit video from the U.S. Air Force F-35A Lightning II Demo Team during a multinational flyover of the Hudson River in Manhattan and West Point, New York on August 23, 2019. The formation included the F-22 Demo Team, Thunderbirds & Royal Air Force Red Arrows.


Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Alexander Cook, F-35A Demo Team Public Affairs

364.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers from the Headquarters and Headquarters Troop, 4th Squadron, 2nd Cavalry Regiment, fire AT4-CS confined space light anti-armor weapons at the 7th Army Training Command’s Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany, August 22, 2019.


Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Spc. Rolyn Kropf, Training Support Activity Europe

365.description:
U.S. Army helicopter pilots from the 3rd Assault Helicopter Battalion, 1st Aviation Regiment, 1st Infantry Division, train and fly over the Romanian coast on August 23, 2019.


Film Credits: Video by Pfc. Laurie Ellen Schubert, 5th Mobile Public Affairs Detachment

366.description:
Polish Air Force F-16s join U.S. Air Force F-15E Strike Eagles in formation flight over Warsaw, Poland, in honor of Polish Armed Forces Day on August 15, 2019.


Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Rachel Maxwell, 48th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

367.description:
The U.S. Navy Blue Angels perform aerobatic maneuvers over Seattle during the 2019 Boeing Seafair Air Show on August 3rd.


Film Credits: Video by Petty Officer 2nd Class Jess Gray, Navy Flight Demonstration Squadron

368.description:
U.S. Marine Corps CH-53E Super Stallions with Marine Heavy Helicopter Training Squadron (HMHT-302) take-off to transport members of the 2nd Battalion, 6th Marine Regiment during a Regimental Field Exercise. Filmed at Marine Corps Air Station New River, North Carolina on August 1, 2019.


Film Credits: Video by Pfc. Gavin Umboh, 2nd Marine Aircraft Wing

369.description:
Exercise Red Flag-Alaska is a series of air exercises led by the U.S. Air Force, focusing on joint offensive counter-air, interdiction, close air support, and large force employment training in a simulated combat environment. Video shots include Canadian CF-18 Hornets - U.S. F-16 Fighting Falcons, EA-18G Growlers, F-16 Fighting Falcon Aggressors and F-15C Eagles. Filmed in August 2019. 

Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class Aaron Guerrisky and Senior Airman Kahdija Slaughter, 354th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

370.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15E Strike Eagles conduct aerial refueling over the Middle East on August 8, 2019, and finish with a couple of barrel rolls. Refueling Unit - KC-135 from the 28th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron.

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Roslyn Ward, U.S. Air Forces Central Command Public Affairs

371.description:
Exercise Northern Lightning 2019 at Volk Field, WI, features a variety of aircraft. Included in this video are F-35A & F-35B Lightning IIs, Draken International L-159s, T-38 Talons, F-16 Fighting Falcons and F-22 Raptors. Filmed on August 13, 2019. More info about Northern Ligtning: https://dma.wi.gov/DMA/news/2019news/19112

Film Credits: Video by Senior Airman Cassidy Woody, 33rd Fighter Wing Public Affairs

372.description:
U.S. Marines with 2nd Tank Battalion, 2nd Marine Division conduct a course-of-fire during a gunnery range at Camp Lejeune, North Carolina on August 5, 2019. This exercise is designed to maintain combat effectiveness of tank crews on the M1A1 Abrams main battle tank.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Aaron Douds, 2nd Marine Division

373.description:
United States Army Soldiers from the 3rd Battalion, 66th Armored Regiment, 1st Armored Brigade Combat Team, 1st Infantry Division based out of Fort Riley, Kansas, conduct combined arms live-fire training at Grafenwohr Training Area, Germany on August 8, 2019.

Film Credits: Video by Sgt. 1st Class Thomas Cornaby, 358th Public Affairs Detachment

374.description:
U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptor fighter jets conduct in-flight refueling with a KC-135 Stratotanker from the 28th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron over undisclosed locations in Middle Eastern airspace on August 1, 2019. The F-22s are deployed to Al Udeid Air Base, Qatar, from the 1st Fighter Wing, Joint Base Langley-Eustis, Virginia, to defend American forces and interests in the U.S. Central Command area of responsibility.

Film Credits: U.S Air Force Video by Senior Airman Roslyn Ward, U.S. Air Forces Central Command Public Affairs

375.description:

383.description:
Crew-members from the Coast Guard Cutter Steadfast (WMEC-623) interdict a go-fast vessel in international waters in the eastern Pacific Ocean on July 18, 2019. The crew-members apprehended the suspected smugglers and seized approximately 2,300 pounds of cocaine from the vessel.

Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class Alex Miller, 52nd Fighter Wing Public Affairs -- Video by Airman 1st Class Chanceler Nardone, 52nd Fighter Wing Public Affairs -- Video by Airman 1st Class Alex Miller, 52nd Fighter Wing Public Affairs

385.description:
Callie is a 26-month-old Dutch Shepherd, and is one of the newest additions to the 123rd Special Tactics Squadron in Louisville, Ky. She is the Kentucky Air Guard's first member of the 123rd Search and Rescue K-9 program, making her the only search and rescue dog in the entire U.S. Department of Defense. Filmed in 2019.

386.description:
An MQ-8B Fire Scout unmanned aerial vehicle assigned to the Sea Knights of Helicopter Sea Combat Squadron (HSC-22) conducts flight operations during an underway with the Freedom-class littoral combat ship USS Milwaukee (LCS-5) on June 26, 2019. The MQ-8B is an unmanned autonomous helicopter developed by Northrop Grumman, designed to provide reconnaissance, situational awareness, aerial fire support and precision targeting support for ground, air and sea forces. As of February 2018, 23 MQ-8B variants were in service with the U.S. Navy.

414.description:
A USAF B-52 Stratofortress deploys four QS64-ER 2000lb mines (Quickstrike-ER Winged Standoff Naval Mines) during an operational demonstration at the Pacific Missile Range Facility on May 29, 2019. The QS64-ER combines Joint Direct Attack Munitions (JDAM) technology and an additional wing kit and battery section to allow it to be delivered from long-range and high-altitude, with pinpoint accuracy, which significantly reduces risk to the aircraft. This aerial naval mine is compatible, inter-operable, and can be employed by virtually any JDAM enabled aircraft, including foreign partners. Unit - 49th Test and Evaluation Squadron from Barksdale Air Force Base. More info about Quickstrike-ER Naval Mine: https://www.navalnews.com/naval-news/2019/06/u-s-indo-pacific-command-tests-quickstrike-er-naval-mine-from-b-52-bomber/  --  https://www.thedrive.com/the-war-zone/23705/b-52-tested-2000lb-quickstrike-er-winged-standoff-naval-mines-during-valiant-shield

Film Credits: Video by Petty Officer 1st Class Robin Peak, U.S. Indo-Pacific Command

The GBU-57A/B Massive Ordnance Penetrator (MOP) is a precision-guided, 30,000-pound (14,000 kg) "bunker buster" bomb used by the United States Air Force. This is substantially larger than the deepest penetrating bunker busters previously available, the 5,000-pound (2,300 kg) GBU-28 and GBU-37.

WTI is a seven-week training event hosted by Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1), which emphasizes operational integration of Marine Corps aviation in support of a Marine Air Ground Task Force. WTI also provides standardized advanced tactical training and certification of unit instructor qualifications to support Marine aviation training and readiness, and assists in developing and employing aviation weapons and tactics.

474.description:
The United States conducted a test of it's Ground-based Midcourse Defense System, downing an ICBM. A test ICBM (Intercontinental Ballistic Missile) was fired from Reagan Test Site, Kwajalein Atoll in the Pacific Ocean and it was successfully shot down by two Ground Based Interceptor missiles launched from Vandenberg Air Force Base in California on March 25, 2019. This test was the first salvo engagement of an ICBM target by two Ground Based Interceptors (GBI), which were designated GBI-Lead, and GBI-Trail for the test. The GBI-Lead destroyed the reentry vehicle, as it was designed to do. The GBI-Trail then looked at the resulting debris and remaining objects and looked for reentry vehicles, selected the next ‘most lethal object’ it could identify, and struck that, precisely as it was designed to do. Units - U.S. Missile Defense Agency, Joint Functional Component Command for Integrated Missile Defense, U.S. Northern Command, and elements of the U.S. Air Force Space Command, 30th, 50th, and 460th Space Wings.   

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by SrA Latonya Kim, 30th Space Wing Public Affairs

482.description:
USS Green Bay test fires the RIM-116 Rolling Airframe Missile (RAM). The RAM is designed to defeat incoming anti-ship missiles. Filmed March, 2019. 

From the Ratheon website https://www.raytheon.com/capabilities/products/ram - The RAM™ guided missile weapon system is the world's most modern ship self-defense weapon and is designed to provide exceptional protection for ships of all sizes. It's currently deployed on more than 165 ships from eight countries, ranging from 500-ton fast attack craft to 95,000-ton aircraft carriers.

A supersonic, lightweight, quick-reaction, fire-and-forget weapon, the RAM system is designed to destroy anti-ship missiles. Requiring no additional direction upon launch, its passive radio frequency and infrared guidance design provide high-firepower capability for engaging multiple threats simultaneously. The missile is continually improved to stay ahead of the ever-evolving threat of anti-ship missiles, helicopters, aircraft and surface craft.

Film Credits: Official U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Anaid Banuelos Rodriguez, Information Specialist 1st Class Matthew Bender

499.description:
In-flight cockpit and aerial footage of U.S. Air Force F-15 Strike Eagles during the 75th Commemorative Flyover for 10 crew members of the WWII U.S. B-17 Flying Fortress "Mi Amigo". The flyover was conducted over Sheffield, England on February 22, 2019. The story of the Mi Amigo in a nutshell: The badly damaged Mi Amigo was returning from a bombing run over Nazi occupied Denmark on February 22, 1944 when it crashed into a wooded area near Sheffield, killing all 10 crew members. An eyewitness account says he thinks the crew could have saved themselves, because the plane circled 3 times over a green field where children were playing. But as the Mi Amigo's one last engine failed, the pilot chose to avoid the green field and the children. Instead he crashed into the woods and the plane exploded. 
More info about the B-17 Mi Amigo: 
https://www.stripes.com/news/they-could-have-saved-themselves-flyover-in-england-honors-memory-of-wwii-aircrew-credited-with-saving-british-kids-1.569744
https://www.historyextra.com/period/second-world-war/mi-amigo-b-17-bomber-plane-crash-sheffield-park-history/

Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class Gaspar Cortez, 48th Fighter Wing Public Affairs

The flyover was conducted over Sheffield, England on February 22, 2019. The badly damaged Mi Amigo was returning from a bombing run over Nazi occupied Denmark on February 22, 1944 when it crashed into a wooded area near Sheffield, killing all 10 crew members. An eyewitness account says he thinks the crew could have saved themselves, because the plane circled 3 times over a green field where children were playing. But as the Mi Amigo's one last engine failed, the pilot chose to avoid the green field. Instead he crashed into the woods. 
More info about the B-17 Mi Amigo:

Video shows training mission of an AC-130W Stinger II gunship from the 16th Special Operations Squadron at Cannon Air Force Base firing the 105mm gun, and footage of 4th Special Operations Squadron Airmen firing the 105 from an AC-130U Spooky.

542.description:
An F-35A and F-16 from Edwards AFB join an F-15E and F-22 from the 422nd Test and Evaluation Squadron out of Nellis AFB, and an F-18 from Air Test and Evaluation Squadron 31 out of Naval Air Weapons Station China Lake, to fly in a formation flight during exercise Orange Flag on December 13, 2018. Orange Flag was developed by the 412th Operations Group to evaluate teamwork across the separate United States services to integrate joint forces across a wide range of mission areas. The events enable the test community to capture data to assess the interoperability of multiple aircraft platforms in an environment outside of traditional Edwards testing. In addition to the fighter jets, B-52, B-2 and B-1 bombers participated in Orange Flag along with KC-135 and KC-10 aerial refueling tankers. “The latest event involved a total of 18 aircraft in six combat-relevant test tasks and experiments.” said Maj. Christopher Campbell, Air Force Test Center, Orange Flag Evaluation Director. Campbell said the team will analyze the data collected and apply it to develop new air power capabilities.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Ethan Wagner

Forward deployed Navy personnel typically advance at a higher rate than the rest of their Navy peers. https://www.navytimes.com/news/your-navy/2017/12/18/forward-deployed-sailors-advance-faster-than-their-stateside-peers/

565.description:
U.S. Air Force T-6A Texan II training aircraft from the 559th and 39th Flying Training Squadrons join together to conduct an "Elephant Walk" at Joint Base San Antonio-Randolph, TX.  The term elephant walk dates to World War II when large fleets of allied bombers would conduct attacks in missions containing hundreds of aircraft. Those who observed this said that the taxiing of these large numbers of aircraft to takeoff in single file in nose-to-tail formations said that they looked like elephants walking to the next watering hole. Over time, it was incorporated into the lexicon of the United States Air Force to identify a "maximum sortie surge".

Film Credits: Sean Schroeder, 502nd Air Base Wing Public Affairs

Truman (CVN-75) plays a part in the largest NATO military exercise in recent years, Trident Juncture 18, off the coast of Norway during October and November of 2018. 578.description:
Special Warfare Combatant Craft Crewmen (SWCC) are some of the most highly trained enlisted personnel in the U.S. Navy. Providing critical support to Naval Special Warfare SEALs and other military special operations forces, SWCC are specially trained to operate on and around rivers and coastal regions around the world while wielding extreme firepower and a deadly skill set. SWCC operators also conduct direct action and special reconnaissance missions on their own.
As a SWCC, you may very likely:
 •Insert and extract SEALs and other Special Operations personnel from a variety of Naval Surface Warfare vessels
 •Collect important data about enemy military installations and shipping traffic in coastal areas
 •Assist other military and civilian law enforcement agencies  

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Austin Rooney - Released, Courtesy of All Hand Magazine - https://www.navy.mil/ah_online/ and Courtesy Video: Marine Corps Base Quantico - https://www.dvidshub.net/video/410047/swcc-hd

The precision strike packages consist of a 30 mm gun and several precision guided munitions (PGMs). Rails are mounted on the out-board pylon of the wing for four Hellfire missiles, SDBs, or SDB IIs under each. 10 Common Launch Tubes (CLTs) are mounted on the rear ramp to fire Griffin A missiles and additional missiles are stored in the aircraft that can be reloaded in flight. CLTs are able to fire other small munitions able to fit inside the 6 inch diameter, 48 inch long tubes. On this mission, you are not going to get to see a bunch of killing. The U.S. Armed Forces does not show that anymore. Although they are the best at it.

651.description:
The Automatic Air Collision Avoidance System (Auto ACAS) is explained by USAF fighter pilots and other technical experts. The Auto ACAS is designed to protect fighter pilots from mid-air collisions. 
System Capabilities:
 • Does not interfere with air combat training, rejoins or close-in formation flight.
• Adapts to quickly changing collision geometries from multiple threats.

System Description:
• F-16 initial integration uses modified Air Combat Maneuvering Instrumentation (ACMI) pods for aircraft-to-aircraft communication.
• Aircraft fire control radar can also be used if ACMI data is not available.
• If a collision avoidance maneuver is required, Auto ACAS takes control of the aircraft via its digital flight control system.
• Auto ACAS-equipped aircraft on a potential collision course with other aircraft select three top avoidance maneuvers from nine possible options:
1) Maintain current maneuver
2) Bunt
3) Roll and pull to one of 7 different bank angles
• Maneuvers are selected based on aircraft state, collision geometry, and accepted pilot “rules of the road”.
For non-Auto ACAS equipped aircraft, the system generates a track file from ACMI pod or radar data and the Auto ACAS equipped aircraft alone will maneuver to avoid the threat aircraft.
• System returns aircraft control to the pilot when flight paths are clear.

Fielding and Performance:
• Auto ACAS was successfully tested through 10 simulation events, 2 Test Pilot School Test Management Projects in FY12 & FY13 and through a flight test conducted by the Air Force Test Center in Summer 2014.

Film Credits: Bryan Ripple, 88th Air Base Wing Public Affairs

U.S. Air Force B-1B bomber aircraft takeoff at RAF Fairford, Great Britain on June 2, 2018 as part of exercise Trojan Footprint 18.

678.description:
Members of the Colorado Air National Guard, 140th Wing Maintenance Group, load MK-82 500 pound bombs onto an F-16 Fighting Falcon in support of live ammunition drops during Exercise Saber Strike 18 at Ämari Air Base in Estonia on June 14, 2018. Saber Strike 18 is the eighth annual installment of the U.S. Army Europe-led cooperative training exercise designed to enhance interoperability among allies and regional partners. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air National Guard Video by Master Sgt. Wolfram M. Stumpf

679.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers fire M109A6 Paladin self-propelled howitzers during exercise Operation Western Strike at Camp Guernsey, Wyoming on June 6, 2018. Unit - 2nd battalion, 142 Field Artillery, Arkansas National Guard, U.S. Army.

Film Credits: U.S. Army National Guard Video by Spc. Stephen M. Wright

680.description:
Range 410A at Twentynine Palms is a large live-fire training range where Marines conduct platoon-sized drills to sharpen their unit attack skills. U.S. Marines with Alpha Company, 1st Battalion, 23rd Marine Regiment, 4th Marine Division, conduct operations on range 410A during Integrated Training Exercise 4-18 (ITX 4-18) at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms, California on June 11, 2018. ITX evaluates and trains Marine Corps infantry units in service-level core competencies that are essential to expeditionary, forward-deployed operations. 

Film Credits: Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Daniel R. Betancourt Jr.

681.description:
U.S. Air Force aircraft (F-16, F-15, and B-1B in this video) have joined military exercises in Europe as part of Baltops-18 and Saber Strike-18 and Trojan Footprint-18. Baltops is an annual multinational exercise designed to enhance interoperability between NATO nations in the Baltic region. Saber Strike is a U.S. Army Europe-led cooperative training exercise to improve land and air operational capabilities on the NATO forward front in Europe. Trojan Footprint is a U.S. Special Operations Command Europe-led exercise over land, sea and air that rapidly deploys NATO and partner nation Special Operations Forces from 13 nations to the Baltic region. All footage filmed in May and June, 2018.

Film Credits: TSgt Roidan Carlson, Master Sgt. Wolfram M. Stumpf

682.description:
U.S. and British Army Paratroopers perform in-flight rigging and static-line jump over Unity crop zone, Latvia from a U.S. Air Force C-17 Globemaster III during Exercise Swift Response 2018 (SR18) on June 9, 2018. Exercise SR18 is one of the premier military crisis response training events for multinational airborne forces in the world that demonstrates the ability of America's Global Response Force to work hand-in-hand with joint and total force partners. U.S. Army unit - 1st Battalion, 508th Parachute Infantry Regiment, 3rd Brigade Combat Team, Fort Bragg, NC. British Army unit - 3rd Battalion, Parachute Regiment, C Company, Colchester, England. U.S. Air Force unit - Joint Base Lewis-McChord.

683.description:

686.description:
Tanks from Austria (Leopard 2A4), Poland (Leopard 2A5), United Kingdom (Challenger 2), and United States (M1A2 SEP v2) drive over cars and flatten them on the precision driving course during the Strong Europe Tank Challenge 2018 (SETC-18) at Grafenwöhr Training Area, Germany. SETC is an annual, multinational tank platoon competition held since 2016 and hosted by the U.S. Army Europe and the German Army. Crews from NATO and non-NATO partners compete in defensive/offensive mounted and dismounted operations. 

The 3rd annual installment of the SETC takes place from June 3 – 8, 2018 with 8 countries competing. SETC-18 countries include: Austria - Leopard 2A4, France - AMX Leclerc, Germany - Leopard 2A6, Poland - Leopard 2A5, Sweden - Stridsvagn 122, Ukraine - T-84 Oplot, United Kingdom - Challenger 2, and United States - M1A2 SEP v2. Past winners: Germany in 2016 and Austria in 2017. Filmed in June 2018.

The Strong Europe Tank Challenge (SETC) is an annual, multinational tank platoon competition held since 2016 at Grafenwöhr Training Area in Germany and hosted by the U.S. Army Europe and the German Army. Crews from NATO and non-NATO partners compete in defensive/offensive mounted and dismounted operations. 

The 3rd annual installment of the SETC is underway now (June 2018) with 8 countries competing this year. SETC-18 countries include: Austria - Leopard 2A4, France - AMX Leclerc, Germany - Leopard 2A6, Poland - Leopard 2A5, Sweden - Stridsvagn 122, Ukraine - T-84 Oplot, United Kingdom - Challenger 2, and United States - M1A2 SEP v2. 722.description:
A fully loaded U.S. Air Force C-17 Globemaster III aircraft from McChord Air Force Base, WA lands, drops off cargo, and then takes-off at Phoenix Airfield in Antarctica. The Army Corps of Engineers built the compacted-snow runway after 16 continuous months of construction. The runway was designed using a compaction technique to modify the deep snow using heavy rollers weighing up to 160,000 pounds, to change the snow’s strength properties from its natural state creating a denser, higher strength snow foundation (32 inches deep) that can withstand the impact of a C-17 landing. And, in this particular case, the Phoenix runway was designed to withstand approximately 60 wheeled flights a year.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Cosmo Walrath - Released

723.description:
Amphibious Assault Ship USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6) arrives at Pearl Harbor for a scheduled port visit on April 27, 2018 and Renders Honors to the Battleship Missouri Memorial and the USS Arizona Memorial.
