754.description:
Restored WWII B-17F Memphis Belle (tail 124485) and B-17G Shoo Shoo Shoo Baby (tail 232076) are moved into positions at the National Museum of the U.S. Air Force in Dayton, OH on March 14, 2018. The Memphis Bell will go on permanent display at the National Museum of the USAF in May 2018, while the Shoo Shoo Shoo Baby will be put into storage awaiting transport to the National Air and Space Museum of the Smithsonian Institution in Washington DC.

Film Credit: Ken LaRock

755.description:
U.S. Army CH-47F Chinook helicopters assigned to Task Force Brawler transport U.S. Air Force pararescuemen (PJs) from the 83rd Expeditionary Rescue Squadron during a training mission in the mountains of Afghanistan on March 15, 2018.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman Nathaniel Stout

756.description:
U.S. Navy guided-missile cruiser USS Antietam (CG-54) fires a standard missile two (SM-2) during a missile exercise in the Philippine Sea on March 17, 2018. More info about SM-2: https://www.globalsecurity.org/military/systems/munitions/sm-2.htm

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video, Public Domain - https://www.dvidshub.net/video/590139/uss-antietam-launches-sm-2-missile

757.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers, Marines, and Special Forces conduct cold weather training at Fort Greely, Alaska and Utqiagvik, Alaska during Exercise Arctic Edge 18. Arctic Edge is a biennial, large-scale, joint-forces training exercise that prepares and tests the U.S. military’s ability to operate tactically in extreme cold-weather conditions found in Arctic environments. Filmed in March 2018.  

Film Credits: SrA Steven Ortiz, TSgt Jeffry Howerton, SrA Joshua Weaver, Mass Communication Specialist 1st Class John Banfield

758.description:
U.S. Marines live-fire training scenes at Fort Bragg, North Carolina: squad level contact and bounding - plus artillery battery with M-777 howitzers. Filmed March 2018.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Samuel Taylor

759.description:
The U.S. Air Force holds a monthly air exercise at Seymour Johnson Air Force Base in North Carolina. Exercise Razor Talon is a large scale, fighter driven training exercise that integrates aircraft from the USAF, Navy, and Marine Corps in air-to-air and air-to-ground attack scenarios. 

Film Credits: A1C Shawna Keyes

760.description:
U.S. Marine Corps F-35B Lightning II aircraft assigned to Marine Fighter Attack Squadron (VMFA) 121 conduct a series of  take-offs and landings aboard the U.S. Navy amphibious assault ship USS Wasp (LHD-1) on March 3, 2018. This marks the first time the F-35B has deployed aboard a U.S. Navy ship with a Marine Expeditionary Unit (31st MEU). The Wasp will provide a rapid-response capability and advance the Up-Gunned ESG concept - https://www.dvidshub.net/video/588699/pac-fleet-commander-talks-about-up-gunned-esg-concept 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 1st Class Alexandra Seeley - Released

761.description:
France, United Kingdom, Germany, and United States artillery units fire various artillery systems during Exercise Dynamic Front 18 at Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany in March 2018. Dynamic Front is an annual exercise focused on the interoperability of U.S. Army, joint service and allied nation artillery units in a multinational environment for field artillery gun crews.

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Spc. Craig Carter, SSG Michael Sword, Christoph Koppers, SFC Jason Duhr, Markus Rauchenberger, Christian Marquardt

762.description:
U.S. Marine Corps infantry train at Range G29 on Camp Lejeune, North Carolina. Filmed March 2018.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Williams O. Quinteros and Lance Cpl. Samuel Taylor

763.description:
German Army Panzerhaubitze 2000 Self Propelled Howitzers fire mission during Exercise Dynamic Front 2018 at Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany. Filmed on March 6-7, 2018. Unit - 4th Battery, 131st Field Artillery Battalion, German Army. 

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Markus Rauchenberger, SSG Michael Sword

764.description:
U.S. Marine Corps MV-22B Osprey tiltrotors conduct an aerial refueling training flight with a USAF KC-10 Extender air tanker over Hawaii on February 24, 2018. Units - Ospreys from Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 268 (VMM-268). KC-10 from the 514th Air Mobility Wing. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Brendan Custer

765.description:
U.S. Field Artillery Unit fires M109A6 Paladin Self-Propelled Howitzers during training exercises at Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany. Unit - 1st Battalion, 7th Field Artillery Regiment, 2nd Armored Brigade Combat Team, 1st Infantry Division based at Fort Riley, Kansas. Filmed in early 2018 (Jan-Feb-Mar).  

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Gertrud Zach, Staff Sgt. Sharon Matthias / 22nd Mobile Public Affairs Detachment, SPC Dustin Biven

766.description:
The U.S. Air Force A-10 Thunderbolt Demonstration Team conducts precision preflight operations, and the pilot performs aerobatics in his A-10C Warthog aircraft. Filmed during Heritage Flight 2018 at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base, March 1-4, 2018. 

Film Credits: A1C Christina Rios, A1C Kayla Palmer, SrA Betty Chevalier, SSgt Eric E Flores

767.description:
The U.S. Marines F-35B Lightning II fighter jet makes its first operational deployment aboard the amphibious assault ship USS Wasp (LHD-1), as part of the 31st MEU. Filmed during Spring Patrol 2018 on March 5, 2018.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Bernadette Wildes

768.description:
Two P-51 Mustangs fly with an F-22 Raptor, and an F-86 Sabre flies with an F-35 Lightning II and a P-51 Mustang during 2018 Heritage Flight Training and Certification Course (HFTCC) at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base in Tucson, Arizona on March 1-2, 2018. HFTCC certifies civilian pilots of historic aircraft and U.S. Air Force pilots to fly in formation together during the upcoming air show season. 

Film Credits: Airman Blake Gonzales

769.description:
U.S. Marines with Maritime Raid Force (MRF), 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU), conduct a night vision live-fire range aboard the amphibious assault ship USS Iwo Jima (LHD-7) at sea on February 24, 2018.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Sylvia L. Tapia - Released

770.description:
Newly commissioned and appointed (warrant officers) U.S. Marine Corps officers conduct table 1,2 and 5 courses of fire with rifles at The Basic School (TBS), Quantico, VA. TBS is where all new USMC officers are taught the basics of being an "Officer of Marines". Filmed February, 2018.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine corps Video by Cpl. Preson A. Shay

771.description:
USMC Force Reconnaissance Marines - Special Operations Capable (SOC) - with Maritime Raid Force, 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU). Filmed in January - February, 2018. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Bernadette Wildes

772.description:
U.S. Air Force members of the 36th Contingency Response Group set up a forward refueling point on Tinian Island and refuel two Navy MH-60S Seahawk helicopters during exercise Cope North 18 on February 26, 2018. Tinian is a U.S. Commonwealth of the Northern Marianas Islands, located near Guam. The Navy helicopters are from Helicopter Sea Combat Squadron 25.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. John Raven

773.description:
USAF Capt Cody Wilton, A-10C Thunderbolt II Demonstration Team pilot, performs a Double Aileron Roll and a Vertical 540 maneuver during practice flights at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base in Arizona.

Film Credits: SrA Betty Chevalier

774.description:
An MQ-9 Reaper unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) assigned to the 62nd Expeditionary Reconnaissance Squadron takes-off at Kandahar Air Base, Afghanistan armed with GBU-38 joint attack munitions on February 22, 2018.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by SSgt. John McRell

775.description:
USAF Senior Airman Jordan Smith, a KC-10 Extender crewmember deployed from Travis Air Force Base, makes homemade pizza while on refueling missions to help break up a flight menu which can become at times monotonous. Filmed February 24, 2018.

Film Credits: TSgt Lynette Hoke

776.description:
U.S. Marines with the Maritime Raid Force, 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU) conduct a live-fire marksmanship range aboard the amphibious assault ship USS Iwo Jima (LHD-7) at sea on February 17, 2018. 

Film Credits:  U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Sylvia L. Tapia

777.description:
U.S. Marines, Republic of Korea Marines (South Korea), and Royal Thai Marines conduct an amphibious landing during Exercise Cobra Gold 18 at Hat Yao Beach in Rayong, Thailand on February 17, 2018. 

Film Credits:  U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Scott P. Smolinski, Sgt. Rebecca L. Floto, and U.S. Air Force Video by Airman Timothy J. Tweet

778.description:
Various footage from the Portuguese led air exercise Real Thaw 2018 which took place early in February, 2018. The exercise featured 35 aircraft and 1,500 personnel from the Portuguese Air Force, Army and Navy as well as military forces from Denmark, France, the Netherlands, Spain, the United States and NATO (E-3A AWACS and DA-20). Real Thaw 2018 included air defense, convoy protection in humanitarian missions, close air support to ground forces and special operations, extraction of military and civilian elements, cargo and paratroopers drops, combat search and rescue, aero-medical evacuations, civil-military cooperation, conventional guided and high-accuracy ordnance attacks and conventional attacks on maritime forces. Footage includes go-pro shots from the cockpit of a Spanish F-18 performing a parallel take-off with another Spanish F-18, paratroopers dropping from a C-130 aircraft, as well as shots of a NATO AWACS plane.

Film Credits: https://www.dvidshub.net/unit/NATOTV

779.description:
U.S. Service Members and Royal Thai Air Force conduct a pre-flight brief and flying operations as part of joint-aviation training during Exercise Cobra Gold 18 at Korat Air Force Base, Kingdom of Thailand on February 14, 2018. Cobra Gold is an annual exercise conducted in Thailand. 

Film Credits:  U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Zachery C. Laning

780.description:
Footage of Army air assault training with the 101st Combat Aviation Brigade at Fort Campbell, KY-TN. Filmed in 2018.

Film Credits:  SGT Marcus Floyd

781.description:
Cockpit video of two jets launching from the aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71). 1st clip - An EA-18G Growler, assigned to Electronic Attack Squadron (VAQ-139), filmed on January 1, 2018. 2nd clip - An F/A-18F Super Hornet, assigned to Strike Fighter Attack Squadron (VFA-22), filmed on December 17, 2017. USS Theodore Roosevelt is currently deployed to the U.S. 5th Fleet area of operations. 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video courtesy of Electronic Attack Squadron 139 - Released. U.S. Navy Video courtesy of Strike Fighter Attack Squadron 22 - Released. CPO Jay Pugh, LCDR Beth Teach

782.description:
The flightline at Nellis Air Force Base in Nevada during exercise Red Flag 18-1, shows footage of F-16 Fighting Falcons and Aggressor Squadron fighter jets preparing for takeoff. Filmed on February 9, 2018.

Film Credits: A1C Christina Ensley, SrA Mychal Fox, A1C Stephanie Gelardo, A1C Olivia Grooms, A1C Julian Kemper and William Lewis

783.description:
U.S. Air Force A-10C Thunderbolt II (Warthogs) taxis and takeoff during exercise Bushwhacker 18-02 Cactus Flag at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base in Tucson, AZ on February 11, 2018.  Exercise Cactus Flag is designed to test Davis-Monthan AFB's ability to deploy attack aircraft around the world. Unit - 355th Fighter Wing.  

Film Credits: A1C Christina Rios, A1C Kayla Palmer, SSgt Eric E Flores

784.description:
Marine Light Attack Helicopter Training Squadron (HMLAT) 303 from Camp Pendleton sent it's last AH-1W Super Cobra helicopter to the Aerospace Maintenance and Regeneration Group (the boneyard) at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base, AZ on February 6, 2018. HMLAT-303 is transitioning from the AH-1W to the AH-1Z Viper helicopter.   

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Rachael E. Zilliox - Released

785.description:
GoPro cockpit footage from the F-16 Fighting Falcon during Super Bowl LII Heritage Flight flyover of U.S. Bank Stadium in Minneapolis, Minnesota on February 4, 2018. Eagles beat the Patriots 41-33. Congrats Philadelphia on your first Super Bowl win!  

Film Credits: SrA Sean Sweeney

786.description:
An FBI SWAT team practices room clearing techniques in the shoot-house at Fort McCoy, WI. 

Film Credits: Greg Mason, Fort McCoy Public Affairs

787.description:
F-22 Raptor, E-3 Sentry, and C-17 Globemaster III takeoff from Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson, AK in the morning on February 2, 2018. 

Film Credits: SSgt Carly Kavish

788.description:
Multiple U.S. Air Force C-130J Super Hercules aircraft from the 317th Airlift Wing performed a Minimum Interval Takeoff (MITO) as part of Operational Readiness Exercise (ORE 18-1) at Dyess Air Force Base in Texas on February 2, 2018. 

Film Credits: A1C Susan Roberts

789.description:
A compilation video of Gung Ho Vids footage with music. 

Film Credits: U. S. Department of Defense
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids 
Music by AudioBlocks

790.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcons and A-10 Thunderbolt II (Warthogs) conduct aerial refueling while on patrol over Afghanistan in January 2018.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by SSgt. John McRell

791.description:
U.S. Air Force pararescue trainees go through training evolutions with Pave Hawk helicopters in the New Mexico desert. Filmed on January 26, 2018.

Film Credits: Peter Ising

792.description:
Cockpit view of a USAF C-130 transport plane dropping U.S. Army Paratroopers over Juliet drop zone, Aviano, Italy. Units - 1st Battalion (Airborne), 503rd Infantry Regiment, 173rd Airborne Brigade, U.S. Army --- 37th Airlift Squadron, U.S. Air Force. Filmed on January 1, 2018.

Film Credits: Staff Sgt. Alexander Henninger

793.description:
U.S. Navy multimedia piece aboard the aircraft carrier USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78) as she prepares to go to operational condition. Filmed January 2018.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Kiana Raines and Sean A Elliott

794.description:
AV-8B Harriers from Marine Attack Squadron 231 join F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 180th Fighter Wing for cold-weather training and joint air-to-air training at Toledo Air National Guard Base, OH on January 17-19, 2018.

Film Credits: AB Kregg York

795.description: The F-35 Patuxent River Integrated Test Force team tests the U.S. Marine Corps F-35B STOVL capabilities with sloped surface vertical landing at Marine Corps Auxiliary Landing Field Bogue, N.C. The testing goal is to expand the F-35B envelope for vertical landings with relaxed sloped surface requirements. Video courtesy of Lockheed Martin.

796.description:
The U.S. Navy's newest littoral combat ship, the future USS Omaha (LCS-12), transits the Panama Canal and arrives at its new homport of San Diego Naval Base. The future USS Omaha is scheduled to be commissioned on February 3, 2018. The Omaha is the sixth ship in the LCS Independence class.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Lt. Chris Krokus and Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Kelsey J. Hockenberger - Released

797.description:
Footage of the 18th Aggressor Squadron from Eielson Air Force Base, AK during Exercise Sentry Aloha 18-1. Filmed at Joint Base Pearl Harbor Hickam, HI on January 17, 2018.

Film Credits: SrA Joshua Weaver

798.description:
U.S. Army and Polish Paratroopers conduct a joint air assault exercise on Camp Bondsteel, Kosovo on January 1, 2018. The troops are part of Multinational Battle Group-East (MNBG-E), under NATO command.

Film Credits: SGT Michael A Parker

799.description:
U.S. Marines with 1st Tank Battalion, 1st Marine Division conduct training operations with M1A1 main battle tanks during Exercise Steel Knight 18 at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms, December 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Christopher D. Thompson

800.description:
Scenes of Exercise Sentry Aloha 18-1 in Hawaii featuring U.S. Air Force F-15C Eagle, F-22 Raptor, and F-16 Aggressor jets taking-off at Joint Base Pearl Harbor-Hickam. Filmed January, 2018.

Film Credits: SSgt Christian Jadot

801.description:
B-52H Stratofortress bombers conduct touch-and-go and landing operations at RAF Fairford, England on January 10, 2018. The USAF 5th Bomb Wing is deployed to RAF Fairford in support of bomber assurance and deterrence operations. Filmed in January, 2018.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. James Cason

802.description:
U.S. Army, 3rd Infantry Division tank crews conduct training at Fort Stewart, GA with M1A2 Abrams main battle tanks.

Film Credits: Lance Milsted, Defense Media Activity

803.description:
U.S. and German paratroopers conduct a static line jump from a USAF C-130J Super Hercules out of Ramstein Air Base in Germany. The re-certification jump, over the Alzey Drop Zone was part of Operation Toy Drop 2017 on December 6, 2017. More info about Operation Toy Drop here: https://www.army.mil/article/160297/operation_toy_drop_2015_provides_gifts_from_above

Film Credits: SSgt Tory Patterson

804.description:
Compilation video featuring MV-22B Ospreys transporting U.S. Marines during various training exercises. The MV-22B tilt-rotor has a maximum speed of 315 mph. It can carry 24 Marines with a combat range of 400 miles, and it can be refueled in-flight.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl Calvin Hilt, LCpl. Kristiana Gehly, Sgt Lucas Hopkins, LCpl Tucker Wolf, TSgt Michael Cowley, Cpl. Anna Albrecht

805.description:
F-15C Eagle fighter jets takeoff from Fresno Air National Guard Base on a night mission. Filmed on December 2, 2017.

Film Credits: SSgt Nicole Wright

806.description:
U.S. Air Force Special Tactics Airmen from the 15th Special Operations Squadron conduct a High Altitude Low Opening (HALO) jump over Smyrna, Tennessee on July 8, 2017.

Film Credits: TSgt Jeffrey Curtin

807.description:
The first segment of the video is from a USAF scramble drill filmed in Lithuania in 2014... the aerial segment of the video is U.S. Air Force F-15 Eagles from the 493d Fighter Squadron (Grim Reapers), conduct 2 intercepts of Russian SU-30 Flankers in international airspace near the Baltics during Baltic Air Policing mission, November 23 and December 13, 2017. The intercepts were initiated because the Russian aircraft did not broadcast the appropriate codes required by air traffic control and had no flight plan on file. The U.S. Air Force deployed Airmen and aircraft from RAF Lakenheath to Šiauliai Air Base, Lithuania, for approximately four months to conduct the NATO air policing mission.

Film Credits: Video Courtesy of NATO TV - Luca Fazzuolli and 48th Fighter Wing and Staff Sgt. Taylor West

808.description:
U.S. Air Force tested the A-29 Super Tucano and AT-6 Texan II aircraft landing and takeoffs on a dirt runway at Melrose Air Force Range, Cannon Air Force Base, NM. Filmed on July 26, 2017.

Film Credits: Video by A1C Jerreht Harris, 27th Special Operations Wing Public Affairs

809.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers from Battle Company, 1-32 Infantry, 1st Brigade Combat Team, 10th Mountain Division, assigned to Combined Joint Task Force-Horn of Africa's (CJTF-HOA) East African Response Force (EARF), conduct team maneuvers through mountainous terrain during live-fire training exercises, both day and night, on December 27, 2017 in Djibouti, Africa. The purpose of the EARF is to rapidly provide adaptable packages of forces to protect American interests on the continent of Africa should any threats arise. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. Shellby Matullo

810.description:
U.S. Marines with the 15th MEU and French Military Forces with Task Force 51/ 5th Marine Expeditionary Brigade conduct various bi-lateral training operations during Exercise Alligator Dagger 2017 in Djibouti, Africa. Alligator Dagger is a joint combat rehearsal that combines U.S. and French forces to practice integrated capabilities. Filmed December 17-19, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Jessica Y. Lucio, Staff Sgt. Vitaliy Rusavskiy

811.description:
USAF Air Commandos with the 7th Special Operations Squadron performed tilt-rotor air to air refueling (TAAR) during an ability to survive and operate (ATSO) exercise over southern England. Air Commandos with the 67th Special Operations Squadon, 352d Special Operations Wing, executed a routine training mission with emergency response procedures for chemical warfare. The integrated ATSO and chemical, biological, radiological and nuclear (CBRN) readiness exercise allowed Airmen to maintain currency on protective measures for CBRN defense. Filmed on December 6, 2017.

Film Credits: SrA Kelly OConnor

812.description:
Scenes from inside a U.S. Air Force Intercontinental Ballistic Missile Silo (Minuteman III ICBM) and the Launch Control Room. This missile was pulled at random from a silo on F.E. Warren Air Force Base, WY and transported to Vandenberg Air Force Base, CA for a test launch. After launching the missile traveled about 4200 miles to a test range near Kwajalein Atoll in the Marshall Islands. Successful test filmed August, 2017.

Film Credits: TSgt Aaron Drobnack, SSgt Kaleb Mayfield, TSgt Kurt Villavicencio

813.description:
U.S. Air Force loadmasters with the 15th Special Operations Squadron watch over Special Tactics Airmen as they perform a HALO jump over Smyrna, Tennessee during Exercise Total Force on July 8, 2017.

Film Credits: TSgt Jeffrey Curtin

814.description:
Compilation video of the U.S. Army's CH-47F Chinook, the world's fastest military helicopter (as of 2017) with a maximum speed of 315 km/hr (196 mph). The CH-47F is powered by two Lycoming T55-GA-714A turboshaft engines, produced by Honeywell Aerospace. Each engine is capable of delivering 4,733 horsepower. CH-47F Chinook specs: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boeing_CH-47_Chinook#Specifications_(CH-47F)

Film Credits: SGT Bryan Spradlin, Minnesota National Guard, SGT Sam Dillon, SSG Lyndsey Prax, SFC Eric Pahon, Massimo Bovo, SrA Natalie Plas

815.description:
U.S. and Estonian Special Operations Forces use the Fast Rope Insertion Extraction System (FRIES) and hoist during training exercises at Ämari Air Base, Estonia in December, 2017. 

Film Credits: SPC Liem Huynh

816.description:
U.S. Air Force Tactical Air Control Party specialists (TACP) join their German counterparts to direct strike aircraft in a close air support training exercise. Filmed at Camp Grayling, MI on April 13, 2017. 

Film Credits: SrA Kyle Saunders

817.description:
Cockpit video of F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 8th Fighter Wing, Kunsan Air Base, South Korea, conducting aerial refueling with a KC-135 Stratotanker on December 20, 2017.

Film Credits: TSgt Joshua Rosales

818.description:
U.S. Marine Corps AH-1Z Viper Helicopters arrive at Marine Corps Air Station, Kaneohe Bay on December 19, 2017. Unit - Marine Light Attack Helicopter Squadron 367 (HMLA-367), Marine Aircraft Group 24, 1st Marine Aircraft Wing.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Aaron Patterson and Cpl. Brendan Custe

819.description:
U.S. Marines with Company A, 15th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU),  Battalion Landing Team, conduct marksmanship training on a fire-and-maneuver range in Kuwait on December 19, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Timothy Valero

820.description:
Razor Talon is a monthly aerial warfare exercise out of Seymour Johnson Air Force Base in North Carolina. F-15E Strike Eagles from the 335th Fighter Squadron fly in this video on December 15, 2017. 

Film Credits: A1C Shawna Keyes

821.description:
F-22 Raptor Pilots and maintainers at Joint Base Langley-Eustis prepare for a night-flight mission. Filmed on July 7, 2017.

Film Credits: SrA Nicolas Myers

822.description:
USAF KC-135 Stratotankers scramble during Exercise Global Thunder 2018 at MacDill Air Force Base, FL. Filmed in November 2017.

Film Credits: A1C Heather Fejerang, SrA Courtney Chapa

823.description:
U.S. Air Force personnel from the 823rd Base Defense Squadron (BDS) shoot Browning M2 .50 Caliber Machine Guns for training and qualification at Camp Blanding, FL. Filmed December 2017.

Film Credits: SrA Kyle Saunders

824.description:
This is a music video that I uploaded in 2014 and then I stupidly deleted it. I can't remember why... So I am reuploading it now. It shows Marine Medium Helicopter Squadron (HMM-364) flying out of Camp Pendelton and over parts of San Diego, CA. Original file here: https://www.dvidshub.net/video/326695/hmm-364-fly-barn
Music Licensed from AudioBlocks: https://www.audioblocks.com/stock-audio/dangerous-full-1.html

Film Credits: Sgt Megan Scullin

825.description:
F-35A Strike Fighters from the 33rd Fighter Wing join E/A-18 Growler electronic warfare jets in Exercise Red Flag 17-3 at Nellis Air Force Base, NV on July 18, 2017.

Film Credits: SrA David Scott-Gaughan

826.description:
Various footage of USMC pugil stick fights at boot camp Parris Island and boot camp San Diego and Camp Pendleton Marine Corps Base. Pugil Sticks are padded poles used since the early 1940s by U.S. Military in training for rifle and bayonet combat.

Film Credits: Lance Cpl. Carlin Warren, Lance Cpl. Daniel A. Lobo, Sgt. John C. Lamb, Cpl Timothy Childers

827.description:
Short documentary highlighting the evolution of one of America's nuclear triad deterrent, the intercontinental ballistic missile (ICBM). The U.S. nuclear triad consists of three elements... Intercontinental Ballistic Missile, Submarine Launched Ballistic Missile, and Nuclear Strategic Bomber Aircraft.

Film Credits: Video by Airman 1st Class Cory Kuttler - Released by Defense Media Activity Air Force

828.description:
U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptors takeoff from Tyndall Air Force Base in Florida during Exercise Stealth Guardian on August 16, 2017. Unit - 325th Fighter Wing.

Film Credits: A1C Tybee Hurst

829.description:
The Tuskegee Airmen were the first black servicemen to serve as Military Aviators in the U.S. Armed Forces, flying with distinction during World War II. Filmed at Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson, AK on October 10, 2017.

Film Credits: A1C Austin Johnson-Harper

830.description:
The USN aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) conducted a Replenishment At Sea (RAS) with the dry cargo and ammunition ship USNS Matthew Perry (T-AKE 9) in the Persian Gulf on December 7, 2017. Part of the RAS was a vertical replenishment (VERTREP), where an MH-60S Sea Hawk helicopter transported cargo to the carrier.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Anthony J. Rivera and Mass Communication Specialist Seaman Michael A.Colemanberry - Released

831.description:
U.S. Navy MH-60 Seahawk helicopter crewmembers assigned to the "Black Jacks" of Helicopter Sea Combat Squadron (HSC-21) assist in fighting California wildfires in San Diego County, CA on December 8, 2017. HSC-3 and HSC-21 are assisting the California Department of Forestry and Fire Protection by providing aircrews flying specially-equipped MH-60S helicopters to conduct aerial water drops on the fires.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 1st Class Paolo Bayas - Released

832.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers from the 101st Airborne Division test fire the M17 pistol at a target range. The M17 Modular Handgun System replaces the M9 pistol, the standard Army sidearm since 1986. The M-17 is a Military version of the SIG Sauer P320 pistol. The new handgun has an external safety, self-illuminating sights for low-light conditions, an integrated rail for attaching enablers and an Army standard suppressor conversion kit to attach an acoustic/flash suppressor. There is also an M18 version which is a compact version of the M17. These Soldiers are among the first to fire the Army's new handgun. Sig Sauer beat out Glock for the $580 million contract to produce the weapons after winning the Army and Air Force modular handgun competition. Filmed at Fort Campbell on November 27 and December 5, 2017.

Film Credits: SSG Jesse Anderla

833.description:
U.S. Army Field artillery Soldiers conduct M109A6 Paladin crew qualifications near Torun, Poland on December 6, 2017. Unit - Battery B, 1st Battalion, 7th Artillery Regiment, 2nd Armored Brigade Combat Team, 1st Infantry Division.  

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Sgt. Gregory T. Summers / 22nd Mobile Public Affairs Detachment

834.description:
USS Coronado (LCS-4), a U.S. Navy Independence-class littoral combat ship, returns to homeport Naval Base San Diego after being deployed for 18 months. Good job, and you earned a well-deserved rest. Merry Christmas to the crew members of the USS Coronado. Coronado operated in Southeast Asian waters for 14 months and worked with 16 navies, participated in 11 exercises, made 10 strategic port visits and successfully fired a Harpoon surface-to-surface missile, striking a target beyond visual range. Filmed on December 5, 2017.  

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist Seaman Apprentice Lasheba M. James

835.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15C Eagle and F-22 Raptor fighter jets are prepped on the flight line at Gwangju Air Base, South Korea prior to taking-off on training sorties during exercise Vigilant Ace 18. Filmed on December 5, 2017. Units - F-15Cs from the 18th Wing, Kadena Air Base, Japan. F-22s from the 90th Fighter Squadron, Joint Base Elmendorf -Richardson, Alaska. 

Film Credits: MSgt Burt Traynor

836.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers from the 10th Mountain Division take-on the French Desert Commando Course in Djibouti, Africa on December 3, 2017. Unit - Battle Company, 1-32 Infantry, 1st Brigade Combat Team, 10th Mountain Division, assigned to Combined Joint Task Force-Horn of Africa's (CJTF-HOA) East African Response Force (EARF). 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. Shellby Matullo

837.description:
GoPro footage of U.S. Air Force pararescuemen (PJs) assigned to the 212th Rescue Squadron showcasing their capabilities of long-range search and rescue during training operations. The 212th Rescue Squadron (212 RQS) is a unit of the Alaska Air National Guard stationed at Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson in Anchorage, Alaska. Filmed in December 2017.

Film Credits: Courtesy of MSgt. Michael Sullivan, 212th Rescue Squadron and A1C Kelly Willett

838.description:
The aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) launches F/A-18 Hornet and Super Hornet strike fighters and E-2C Hawkeye early warning aircraft in the U.S. 5th Fleet area of operations on November 30 to December 2, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist Third Class Janine F. Jones and Mass Communication Specialist Seaman Michael A. Colemanberry

839.description:
"Hot Pit" refueling F-22 Raptors and AH-64 Apache helicopters during Arctic ACE 2017 - Forward Arming and Refueling Point (FARP). Filmed July 12-13, 2017.

Film Credits: SSgt Carly Kavish

840.description:
U.S. Air Force Special Missions Aviation Airmen inspect and prepare a HH-60G Pave Hawk helicopter before a routine training flight at Moody Air Force Base, GA on November 30, 2017. More info about Special Missions Aviation Airmen here: https://www.airforce.com/careers/detail/special-missions-aviation

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by SrA Kyle Saunders

841.description:
U.S. Army helicopters assigned to 1st Air Cavalry Brigade, 1st Cavalry Division, take-off from Chièvres Air Base, Belgium headed for various NATO bases in Germany, Latvia, Romania and Poland. 45 UH-60 Black Hawk, 12 CH47 Chinook and 20 AH-64 Apache helicopters deployed in October 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Visual Information Specialist Pascal Demeuldre

842.description: Operation Deep Freeze (ODF) is the code-name for a series of United States research missions to Antarctica, beginning with "Operation Deep Freeze I" in 1955. ODF has since made regular missions to resupply U.S. Antarctic bases, coordinated by the United States Military. This video highlights various footage of ODF 2017, released by Pacific Air Forces Public Affairs on November 22, 2017 - produced by SSgt Jamie Spaulding.

843.description:
U.S. Army helicopters assigned to the 1st Cavalry Division are staged at Chièvres Air Base, Belgium. Forty-five UH-60 Black Hawks, twelve CH47 Chinooks and twenty AH-64 Apaches took-off headed for Germany, Latvia, Romania and Poland in support of Operation Atlantic Resolve on October 25, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Visual Information Specialist Pascal Demeuldre

844.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 77th Expeditionary Fighter Squadron "Gamblers" takeoff from Bagram Airfield, Afghanistan and conduct combat flight operations. Filmed November 19-21, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Tech. Sgt. Justin Jacobs, Senior Airman Ryan Green

845.description:
The U.S. Navy submarine USS Illinois (SSN-786) arrives at Pearl Harbor Naval Base, HI on November 22, 2017, following a change of homeport from Groton, CT. USS Illinois is a Virginia-Class nuclear powered fast-attack submarine with 134 Navy personnel aboard, commissioned on October 29, 2016.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by PO1 Daniel Hinton

846.description:
A U.S. Navy C-2A Greyhound Carrier Onboard Delivery (COD) plane takes off and lands aboard the aircraft carrier USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN-69) on October 26, 2016. In recent news, a C-2A assigned to the VRC-30 “Providers” apparently has crashed into the sea off Okinawa, Japan with 11 crew and passengers. The crash happened on November 22, 2017 while the aircraft was en-route to the aircraft carrier USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76). A search-and-rescue (SAR) operation by the “Golden Falcons” of U.S. Navy Helicopter Sea Combat Squadron (HSC-12) from the USS Reagan has recovered 8 survivors, which were reportedly in good condition. Sadly, 3 crew members perished. God Bless Them.This is the 6th C-2 crash since this type aircraft entered active service in 1966. Learn more about the crash here: https://theaviationist.com/2017/11/22/u-s-navy-aircraft-carrying-11-crew-and-passengers-crashed-in-the-ocean-southeast-of-okinawa/
C-2 Unit In The Video: Horsemen of Detachment IV, Fleet Logistics Support Squadron (VRC-40).

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Petty Officer 2nd Class Michael R. Gendron

847.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcon Pilots from the 77th Fighter Squadron, Shaw Air Force Base, SC deploy to Southwest Asia on October 21, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by A1C Sean Sweeney

848.description:
A B-52 Stratofortress bomber assigned to the 379th Air Expeditionary Wing, Al Udeid Air Base, Qatar takes-off on a mission over Afghanistan on November 19, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Air National Guard Video by Staff Sgt. Aubrey Griffin

849.description:
Compilation video of C-130 Hercules and C-17 Globemaster III transport planes taking-off and landing on improvised dirt runways, simulating combat situations.

Film Credits: William Lewis, SSgt Nicholas Priest, A1C Rachel Webster, MSgt Shane Cronin, SrA Aaron Hauser, SrA Rachel Maxwell

850.description:
Scenes of U.S. Military firing the M2 Browning .50 caliber machine gun in various training exercises. The "Ma Deuce" has been used by the U.S. Military in every war or conflict from WWII to the present day.

Film Credits: SA Edward Guittierrez III, SSgt Brandon M. Owen, SGT Arthur Haring, Cpl Jordan Walker, LCpl. Zachary W. Montgomer

851.description:
U.S. Air Force Physiology Technicians (PT) from the the 19th Aerospace Medicine Squadron, High Altitude Airdrop Mission Support unit (HAAMS) explain the purpose of HAAMS. These Airmen are specially trained to provide in-flight physiological support to aircrews, special operations forces, high altitude parachutists, and other military units that perform unpressurized airdrop operations at 20,000 feet or above. The 19th Aerospace Medicine Squadron is stationed at Little Rock Air Force Base, Arkansas.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by SSgt Kenny Holston

852.description:
A brief overview documentary of the training that takes place at School of Infantry West (SOI) at Camp Pendleton, CA. This video shows you the basics of how the School of Infantry West integrates and trains different Military Occupational Specialties (MOS) of the U.S. Marines.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl Manuel Serrano

853.description:
U.S. Marine Corps F-35B Lightning II fighter jets land at Marine Corps Air Station Iwakuni, Japan on November 15, 2017. The remaining aircraft represent the last installment of F-35B Lightning II aircraft assigned to Marine Fighter Attack Squadron 121 (VMFA-121).

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Staff Sgt. William Faffler

854.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Viper Demonstration Team performs at the 2017 Dubai Airshow, flying an F-16 Fighting Falcon.

Film Credits: SSgt BreeAnn Sachs

855.description:
Extensive video of B-1B Lancer "BONE" bomber jet pilots being prepped, aircraft being loaded with cruise missiles and bombs by ordnance ground-crew, then taxis and takeoff, day and night operations during Exercise Global Thunder 18 at Dyess Air Force Base in Texas. Filmed November 2017.

Film Credits: SrA Draeke Layman, A1C Susan Roberts, A1C ShaMar Smith

856.description:
Sea level view, closeups, and aircraft flyover during three U.S. Aircraft Carrier Strike Groups operating in the Sea of Japan and East China Sea (with escort ships from Japan). The three carrier strike groups are sailing closer to North Korea as tensions are mounting between North Korea and the U.S. The three U.S. Navy aircraft carriers are: USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76), USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71), and USS Nimitz (CVN-68). Filmed on November 11, 2017.

Film Credits: SN Cody Deccio, PO3 Chad Anderson, CPO Jay Pugh, PO3 Jamaal Liddell, PO1 Glenn Slaughter, PO3 Janine F. Jones

857.description:
Three U.S. Aircraft Carrier Strike Groups are operating in the Sea of Japan and East China Sea (with ships from Japan) as a warning to North Korea. The three carrier strike groups are: USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76), USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71), and USS Nimitz (CVN-68). Filmed on November 11, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by PO3 Deanna Gonzales, SN Cody Deccio, CPO Porter Anderson

858.description:
For the first time in 10 years three U.S. Aircraft Carrier Strike Groups have combined for military exercises, joining forces in the Sea of Japan and East China Sea (with ships from Japan), presenting a warning to North Korea. The three carrier groups are: USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76), USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71), and USS Nimitz (CVN-68). 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by CPO Jay Pugh, PO2 Conor Minto, PO3 Anthony Rivera

859.description:
The Prowlers of the Pacific airshow team performed at the Thunder Over South Georgia Air Show 2017 on November 9, 2017. The team includes four vintage WWII aircraft: Curtiss SB2C Helldiver (marked with number 32 on the tail section), Douglas SBD-5 Dauntless Dive Bomber (marked with number 5 on the mid-section), Goodyear FG-1D Corsair (marked with number 530 on the mid-section and checkered tail-section), and the Japanese Nakajima B5N “KATE” Torpedo Bomber (with a torpedo attached underneath). More info about the Prowlers of the Pacific here: http://dixiewing.org/airshows/prowlers-of-the-pacific/

Film Credits: SrA Kyle Saunders
Photo Credits:
https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Curtiss_SB2C_Helldiver_CAF.jpg
https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Goodyear_FG-1D_Corsair,_Commemorative_Air_Force_JP7434664.jpg
https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=File:Dauntless_Dive_Bomber.JPG

860.description:
The newest U.S. Navy aircraft carrier, USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78), launches and recovers F/A-18 Super Hornet fighter jets during testing and evaluation operations in the Atlantic Ocean. Filmed November 2-4, 2017.  

Film Credits: Joshua Sheppard, PO2 Kristopher Ruiz, PO3 Sean Elliott, SA Connor Loessin, PO3 Gitte Schirrmacher

861.description:
U.S. Army, 3rd Brigade Combat Team, 25th Infantry Division conducts Common Remotely Operated Weapon Station (CROWS) training with their M115A1 HMWVVs at the Battle Area Complex, Schofield Barracks, Hawaii, on November 7, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Staff Sgt. Armando R. Limon

862.description:
U.S. Marines with 1st Battalion, 6th Marine Regiment, Marine Air-Ground Task Force-5 (MAGTF), conduct the Final Exercise (FINEX) during Integrated Training Exercise 1-18 (ITX) at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms, CA on November 5, 2017. The purpose of ITX is to create a challenging, realistic training environment to produce combat-ready forces capable of operating as an integrated MAGTF.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Dani A. Zunun

863.description:
German Patriot missile systems join American Avenger systems and Stinger MANPADS at a live-fire exercise at the NATO Missile Firing Installation (NAMFI) at Chania, Greece from October 31 - November 9, 2017. More than 200 U.S. soldiers and approximately 370 German soldiers will fire live Patriot, Avenger, and Stinger missiles during a German-led, tactical live-fire exercise at NAMFI. The combined exercise, referred to as Artemis Strike by U.S. participants, will provide realistic training, require participants to overcome the challenges associated with force projection, and educate operators on their air missile defense systems. Additionally, it will require the 10th AAMDC to deploy, operate and fire live missiles within a tactical scenario, under Supreme Headquarters Allied Powers Europe (SHAPE) operational readiness evaluation criteria.

Film Credits: Anthony Sweeney, SFC Jason Epperson

864.description:
U.S. Marines with 3rd Battalion, 1st Marine Regiment, 1st Marine Division conduct a low-light air assault exercise during Weapons and Tactics Instructors Course (WTI) 1-18 at Twentynine Palms, California on October 17, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sergeant Daniel Kujanpaa

865.description:
F/A-18 Super Hornets launch and land during night flight operations aboard the newly commissioned aircraft carrier USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78) on November 4, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by SN Gitte Schirrmacher

866.description:
F/A-18 Super Hornets conduct landing operations aboard the U.S. Navy's newest aircraft carrier, USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78), during testing operations on November 1, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Ruben Reed, Joshua Sheppard

867.description:
U.S. Air Force Tactical Air Control Party (TACP) - Joint Terminal Attack Controllers (JTAC) conduct close air support operations during Exercise Razor Talon (April 2017). Interview with SSgt Houston Thomas, the lead TACP on the ground, describes this month's Razor Talon as well as explaining his favorite part of being TACP and what it takes to get there.

Film Credits: SSgt Patrick Cole

868.description:
U.S. Marines launch from USS Ashland (LSD-48) in amphibious assault vehicles and conduct a simulated combat beach landing during Exercise Blue Chromite in Okinawa, Japan on November 2, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Jonathan Clay and U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Allison Beiswanger and Lance Cpl. Charles Plouffe - Released

869.description:
U.S. Marines fire the Carl Gustaf M4 Rocket System on a training range at Camp Hansen, Okinawa, Japan on October 25, 2017. Unit- 31st MEU.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Garett Burns - Released

870.description:
Panzerhaubitze 2000, 155mm self-propelled howitzers fire rounds downrange during exercise Iron Wolf II in Lithuania, October 2017. The German artillery gun is able to shoot three rounds in 10 seconds and up to 10 rounds in one minute. Exercise Iron Wolf II involved 2,300 troops from 12 NATO Allies. More info here: https://kam.lt/en/news_1098/current_issues/minister_of_national_defence_will_attend_media_and_distinguished_visitors_day_of_multinational_exercise_iron_wolf_ii.html?pbck=0  

Film Credits: NATOTV

871.description:
U.S. Army Paratroopers assigned to the 173rd Airborne Brigade conduct a live fire training exercise as part of Eagle Strike 17 at Range 118, Grafenwoehr, Germany on October 23rd, 2017. Unit - 2nd Battalion, 503rd Infantry Regiment (Airborne), 173rd Airborne Brigade.  

Film Credits: Staff Sgt. Alexander C. Henninger

872.description:
B-2 Spirit Bombers takeoff from Whiteman Air Force Base, Missouri on a long-range mission to the Pacific Command Area Of Responsibility to demonstrate commitment to U.S. allies. Filmed on October 28, 2017.  

Film Credits: SSgt Scott Fremming

873.description:
HD compilation of MV-22 and CV-22 Osprey Tiltrotor aircraft on takeoff, landing, and inflight refueling.   

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Evan R. White - Released and A1C Joseph Pick, A1C Caleb Pavao, PO1 Mark Logico, U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. AaronJames B. Vinculado, U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. James R. Skelton, Lance Cpl. Gregory D. Boyd, Sgt Chris Stone
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

874.description:
A U.S. Air Force Special Operations CV-22 Osprey conducts hoist training at Cannon AFB in New Mexico. Filmed in 1st person point-of-view with a helmet camera. Unit - 27th Special Operations Wing. 

Film Credits: Amn Marcel Williams

875.description:
A Retired U.S. Air Force navigator and bombardier talks about the Convair B-58A Hustler at the National Museum of the U.S. Air Force in Dayton, OH. The B-58 was the first supersonic bomber of the USAF. Narrator - Col. (Ret.) Chuck Jones.

Film Credits: Ken LaRock

876.description:
U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptors and T-38 Talons taxi and takeoff at Langley Air Force Base, VA on September 11, 2017.

Film Credits: SSgt Ben Wocken

877.description:
Battlefield Airmen are USAF Special Tactics Operators which include Combat Controllers, Pararescuemen, Tactical Air Control Party members, and Special Operations Weather Technicians. Candidates for these highly skilled and physically demanding positions must complete a 2 year training pipeline that typically has a washout rate between 70-90 percent. Video shows footage of the 350th Battlefield Airmen Training Squadron, Battlefield Airmen Training Group, 37th Training Wing, Air Education and Training Command at Joint Base San Antonio - Medina, TX during September, 2017.

Film Credits: Jose Sanchez Alonso, Ruth Medinavillanueva
Derivative Work: Gung Ho Vids

878.description:
Platoon live-fire exercise at Range 307, Grafenwoehr, Germany on October 22, 2017. Unit - Charlie Company (MOD), 1st Battalion, 503rd Infantry Regiment (Airborne), 173rd Airborne Brigade. 

Film Credits: Staff Sgt. Alexander C. Henninger

879.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers conduct a live-fire training evolution with the M252A1 81mm Mortar system at Range 117 in Grafenwoehr, Germany on October 20, 2017. Unit - Headquarters and Headquarters Company (HHC), 2nd Battalion, 503rd Infantry Regiment (Airborne), 173rd Airborne Brigade.

Film Credits: Sgt. Rodolfo Rojas, Spc. Markus Caver, Pfc. James West, Pvt. William Hall
Attribution: Staff Sgt. Alexander C. Henninger

880.description:
U.S. Marine Corps F-35B Lighting II fighter jets are training at Air Station Iwakuni, Japan in a bilateral show-of-force. The deployment is designed to reassure U.S. allies in the region against threats of nuclear war from North Korean leader Kim Jong Un. Filmed October 18-20, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Staff Sgt. William Faffler, Cpl. Joseph Abrego. Cpl. Waiyan Tin, Cpl. Carlos Jimenez

881.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15 Strike Eagles and A-10C Thunderbolt II (Warthogs) execute aerial refueling with a KC-135 Stratotanker from the 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron somewhere over Iraq on October 6, 2017. The F-15s are from the 336th Fighter Squadron, Seymore Johnson AFB and the A-10s are from the 23rd Fighter Group, Pope AFB.

Film Credits: U.S Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. John Raven

882.description:
U.S. Marines and Sailors conduct training operations during exercise Alligator Dagger, which was a 2 week combat rehearsal in Djibouti, AF, September 2017, to increase readiness in the 15th Marine Expeditionary Unit over the United States 5th Fleet area of operation.

Film Credits: Cpl Timothy Valero, LCpl Jacob Pruitt

883.description:
The U.S. Navy successfully conducted a demonstration with the Laser Weapon System (LaWS) aboard Afloat Forward Staging Base (Interim) USS Ponce (AFSB(I) 15), shooting down an unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) in the Persian Gulf on July 14, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by MC1 Joshua Bryce Bruns

884.description:
U.S. Marine Corps CH-53E Super Stallion and U.S. Army MH-60M Black Hawk helicopters conduct aerial refueling during training at Weapons and Tactics Instructor course (WTI) 1-18 in Yuma, AZ on October 6, 2017. Slow Motion filmed at 120 fps.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Ben Drake
Music Licensed From AudioBlocks - https://www.audioblocks.com/stock-audio/it-happens-to-be.html

885.description:
U.S. Marines with Marine Unmanned Aerial Vehicle Squadron 2 (VMU-2) launch a RQ-21A Blackjack surveillance drone during assault support tactics 3 (AST-3) in support of Weapons and Tactics Instructors course (WTI) 1-18 at Canon Air Defense Complex (P111), Yuma, AZ on October 13, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. AaronJames Vinculado

886.description:
A U.S. Air Force F-35A Lightning II fighter jet lands at Eielson Air Force Base, Alaska on October 12, 2017 to conduct cold weather testing. The tests are being done to ensure the fifth generation multi-role fighter aircraft performs optimally in Alaska's harsh weather conditions.

Film Credits: SrA Joshua Weaver

887.description:
U.S. Marines with 2nd Low Altitude Air Defense (LAAD) Battalion fire FIM-92 Stinger Missiles and M240B machine guns during a live-fire training exercise at Camp Lejeune, NC on October 10, 2017.

Film Credits: LCpl Luisa Torres

888.description:
U.S. Air Force A-10 Thunderbolt II (Warthogs) conduct aerial refueling with a KC-135 Stratotanker somewhere over Syria on July 6, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Tech Sgt. Micah Theurich

889.description:
A U.S. C-17 Globemaster III transport plane landed at Kunsan Air Base, South Korea on September 20, 2017 with two M142 High Mobility Artillery Rocket Systems (HIMARS) aboard. The 18th Field Artillery Brigade, Fort Bragg, NC conducted a live-fire exercise the following day at Daecheon, South Korea. 

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Sgt. Ashley Marble and Spc. Ian Ryan

890.description:
Parade Of Ships during San Francisco Fleet Week 2017. The Wasp-class amphibious assault ship USS Essex (LHD-2), avenger-class mine countermeasures ship USS Champion (MCM-4), Legend-class cutter USCGC Stratton (WMSL-752), Halifax-class frigate HMCS Winnipeg (FFH-338), Army Corps of Engineers Drift Collector John A. B. Dillard, and San Francisco Fire Boat St. Francis sail through the San Francisco Bay, under the Golden Gate Bridge and past Alcatraz Island. Filmed on October 6, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Donavan K. Patubo, Sgt Annika Moody, LCpl Samantha Bray, PO1 Jason Graham

891.description:
The U.S. Navy's newest aircraft carrier USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78) is underway conducting testing and evaluation operations with F/A-18F Super Hornets assigned to Air Test and Evaluation Squadron (VX-23). Filmed September 29 to October 2, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Joshua Murray, Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Connor D. Loessin, Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Ruben Reed, Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Sean Elliott

892.description:
U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptors from Joint Base Langley-Eustis, VA arrive at RAF Lakenheath in the UK for a flying training deployment with NATO Allies and European partners. They will also forward deploy to other NATO bases as a demonstration of the United States commitment to NATO partners. Filmed on October 8, 2017.

Film Credits: SSgt Armando Aparicio

893.description:
U.S. Marine Corps snipers with Regimental Surveillance And Target Acquisition Company (RSTAC) practice their deadly craft during a field training exercise at Fort Irwin National Training Center, CA on October 2-3, 2017. RSTAC is an experimental company designed to build proficiency in USMC Scout Sniper operations.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Antonio Campbell

894.description:
U.S. Marine Corps snipers with Regimental Surveillance And Target Acquisition Company (RSTAC) participated in a field training exercise at Fort Irwin National Training Center, CA on October 2, 2017. RSTAC is an experimental company designed to build proficiency in USMC Scout Sniper operations.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Antonio Campbell

895.description:
U.S. Marine Corps Joint Terminal Attack Controllers (JTAC) call in close air support aircraft during a training exercise at Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range, CA on September 22, 2017. The training was part of Weapons and Tactics Instructor Course 1-18 (WTI). WTI is a seven week training event hosted by Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1) at Marine Corps Air Station Yuma, AZ. Some basic info about JTAC: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joint_terminal_attack_controller

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Daniel Kujanpaa

896.description:
CV-22 Osprey tiltrotor aircraft from U.S.Special Operations Command Europe participated in Exercise Aurora 17, the largest military exercise in Sweden over the last 20 years. More than 19,000 personnel from Sweden participated in the exercise alongside an estimated 1,500 personnel from Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Lithuania, Latvia, Norway, and the United States. Filmed out of Satenas Airbase, Sweden in September, 2017.

Film Credits: SSG Henry Gundacker

897.description:
U.S. Marines assault amphibious vehicle crewmembers train with the Philippine Navy's BRP Tarlac (LD-601) at Subic Bay, Philippines on October 3, 2017. Unit - Amphibious Assault Company, Combat Assault Battalion, 3rd Marine Division, III Marines Expeditionary Force.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Averi M. Coppa, Cpl. David A. Diggs

898.description:
The Belgium sniper squad won 1st place in the 2017 European Best Sniper Squad competition, September 24-28 at the Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany. Sixteen squads participated in the competition, including two U.S. teams. The U.S. Army Europe competition, organized by the 7th Army Training Command, was the second annual European Best Sniper Squad Competition. The sniper squad from Sweden took 2nd place and the squad from Czech Republic took 3rd place. Countries that participated: Belgium, Bulgaria, Canada, Czech Republic, Germany, Italy, Latvia, Lithuania, Netherlands, Poland, Portugal, Spain, Sweden and the United Kingdom. The U.S. squads were: 173rd Airborne Brigade, Vicenza, Italy and 2nd Cavalry Regiment, Vilseck, Germany.

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Specialist Craig Carter, Specialist Christoph Koppers, Markus Rauchenberger, Specialist Emily Houdershieldt

899.description:
U.S. Marine Corps UH-1Y Venom helicopter crewmembers execute a training exercise over a simulated enemy area during Weapons and Tactics Instructors Course (WTI) 1-18 at Yuma, Arizona on September 28, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Charnelle Smith

900.description:
C-5M Super Galaxy transport planes load supplies and takeoff to Puerto Rico to help citizens after two hurricanes hit the island in September, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by SSgt Traci Keller, David Cushman, Staff Sgt. Robert Hicks

901.description:
Aircraft maintainers from the 165th Airlift Wing, Georgia ANG, conduct an operational check on engines for a C-130 Hercules at the Air Dominance Center in Savannah, GA on September 29, 2017. The 165th Airlift Wing is serving as a hub and spoke operation for aircraft flying to and from Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands providing vital supplies and personnel needed for hurricane relief and recovery efforts.

Film Credits: U.S. Air National Guard Video by Tech. Sgt. Jeremy Farson

902.description:
A U.S. Air Force B-52H Stratofortress takes-off from RAF Fairford, England and conducts aerial refueling with a French Air Force C-135FR air tanker. B-52 bombers from the 2 Bomber Wing, USAF are on deployment to England for 3 weeks to support Bomber Assurance and Deterrence operations (BAAD). U.S. Strategic Command bomber forces regularly conduct combined theater security cooperation engagements with allies and partners, demonstrating the U.S. capability to command, control and conduct bomber missions across the globe. Filmed September 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman James Merriman

903.description:
U.S. Marines with 3rd Light Armored Reconnaissance Battalion (3rd LAR), conduct a live-fire exercise at Twentynine Palms, CA on September 12, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Jeremiah Naranjo

904.description:
Cockpit view of A-10 Thunderbolt II (Warthog) during Takeoff, In-flight, and Landing. Filmed at Nellis Air Force Base, NV on September 21, 2017.

Film Credits: A1C Stephanie Gelardo

905.description:
U.S. Marines with 1st Light Armored Reconnaissance (LAR) Battalion, 1st Marine Division, cross Colorado River with light armored vehicles (LAV) as part of Operation Deep Strike II, in Blythe, AZ. Then they conduct target training with the M242 Bushmaster Chain Gun. Filmed during Exercise Deep Strike II on September 13, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Justin Huffty

906.description:
U.S. Air Force 379th Air Expeditionary Wing aircraft takeoff and land at Al Udeid Air Base, Qatar on Sept. 7, 2017. Aircraft --  C-17 Globemaster III, E8-C JSTARS, KC-135 Stratotanker, and B-52 Stratofortress.

Film Credits: MSgt Andrew Moseley

907.description:
U.S. Soldiers from 5th Squadron, 4th Cavalry Regiment, 2nd Armored Brigade Combat Team, 1st Infantry Division conducts a combined live-fire exercise at Presidenski Range, Poland on September 25, 2017.

Film Credits: SGT Mark Brejcha

908.description:
U.S. Marines with Marine Rotational Force-Europe join together with Swedish and Finnish Army Forces in Exercise Aurora 17, the largest Swedish led military exercise in more than 20 years. Filmed on Gotland Island, Sweden on September, 19 2017.

Film Credits: SSgt Emma Mayen

909.description:
U.S. and Polish air force F-16 Fighting Falcons conduct flight operations together at Krzesiny Airbase, Poland as part of Aviation Rotation 17-4 (Operation Atlantic Resolve). USAF Unit - 480th Fighter Squadron. Filmed on September 11-12, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by TSgt Anthony Plyler

910.description:
U.S. Army Troops use the M240B machine gun. Units - Delta Company, 1st Battalion, 503rd Infantry Regiment, 173rd Airborne Brigade - 1st Battalion, 158th Infantry - 173rd Brigade Support Battalion, 173rd Airborne Brigade.

911.description:
U.S. Marines assigned to Marine Aerial Refuel and Transport Squadron (VMGR) 252 conduct aerial refuel exercises above Marine Corps Air Station Cherry Point, NC on September 19, 2017. VMGR-252 participated in refueling AV-8B Harriers and F-35B Lightning II aircraft. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Jonathon Wiederhold - Released

912.description:
B-52 Stratofortess takeoff and landing at Royal Air Force Fairford airfield on September 19, 2017. The airmen are from 2nd Bomb Wing, deployed to RAF Fairford for 3 weeks supporting Bomber Assurance and Deterrence operations. USAF Strategic Command bomber forces regularly conduct combined theater security cooperation engagements with allies and partners, demonstrating the U.S. capability to command, control and conduct bomber missions across the globe. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman James Merriman

913.description:
India and USA conducted exercise Yudh Adhyas 2017 at Joint Base Lewis McChord, WA from September 14-17. Yudh Abhyas is a large scale bi-lateral training exercise to learn to operate together.

Film Credits: Songho Yun

914.description:
U.S. Army, 210th Field Artillery, 2nd Infantry Division holds a live-fire exercise with M270 Multiple Launch Rocket System at Pocheon, Gyeonggi - Do, South Korea on September 15, 2017.

Film Credits: Songho Yun

915.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15C Eagles from the 493rd Expeditionary Fighter Squadron conduct NATO Baltic Air Policing at Šiauliai Air Base, Lithuania on September 13, 2017. The Baltic Air Policing mission is a NATO air defense Quick Reaction Alert (QRA) in order to guard airspace over the three Baltic states of Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania. 

Film Credits: SrA Elizabeth Taranto

916.description:
U.S. Marine Corps F-35B Lightning II aircraft with Marine Fighter Attack Squadron (VMFA) 121 takeoff from Marine Corps Air Station Iwakuni, Japan for a show-of-force against North Korea on September 18, 2017. The F-35B strike fighters joined U.S. Air Force, Japan and Republic of Korea Air Force aircraft in a sequenced show-of-force over the Korean peninsula.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Waiyan Tin and Cpl. Carlos Jimenez

917.description:
U.S. Army and Egyptian Military conduct a live-fire armored assault during Exercise Bright Star on 15 September, 2017 at Mohamed Naguib Military Base, Egypt. U.S. Army unit - 2nd Battalion, 7th Cavalry Regiment, 3rd Armored Combat Team, 1st Cavalry Division.

Film Credits: US Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. John Raven

918.description:
U.S. Air Force B-52H Stratofortress bombers land at RAF Fairford in Gloucestershire, England on September 14, 2017, to support bomber assurance and deterrence operations - U.S. Strategic Command, 2nd Bomb Wing.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force video by Senior Airman James Merriman

919.description:
U.S. and Egyptian armed forces members conduct exercise Bright Star at Mohamed Naguib Military Base, Egypt. Filmed September 2017.

Film Credits: US Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. John Raven - U.S. Army Video by Staff Sgt. Leah R. Kilpatrick

920.description:
A U.S. Air Force KC-10 Extender conducts an aerial refueling mission with British Royal Air Force Typhoon FGR4 fighter jets over Syria on August 10, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Tech Sgt. Micah Theurich

921.description:
C-17 Globemaster III aircrews from the 14th Airlift Squadron - Joint Base Charleston, SC deliver hurricane relief to Saint Thomas International Airport, U.S. Virgin Islands. A fleet of C-17 Globemaster III from Joint Base Charleston relocated to Scott AFB, IL in advance of Hurricane Irma, to be staged and ready to deliver aide, equipment, and personnel to the areas affected by the hurricane. Filmed on September 10, 2017. 

Film Credits: TSgt Jose Rodriguez

922.description:
Buckley Air Force Base in Colorado celebrated the 70th Anniversary of the U.S. Air Force with a "Combat Dinning Out Event." Base personnel got crazy and had a good time. Filmed on July 14, 2017.

Film Credits: SrA Madison Ratley

923.description:
Ten A-10 Thunderbolt II Warthogs and approximately 270 Airmen from the U.S. Air Force have been deployed to Amari Air Base, Estonia for a Foward Training Deploymen  (FTD). This training will focus on maintaining joint readiness while building interoperability capabilities between NATO countries. Filmed September 5, 2017.
 Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by SSgt Shellby Matullo 

DOD_104820207-DOD_104820192

924.description:
The Paladin M109A6 is designed to obliterate enemy positions as a howitzer from miles away. But it can fire directly on targets if the situation should be needed. U.S. Soldiers conduct a direct fire exercise with M109A6 Paladin howitzers at the 7th Army Training Command’s Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany, Sept. 12, 2017. Unit - 3rd Battalion, 29th Field Artillery Regiment, 3rd Armored Brigade Combat Team, 4th Infantry Division. Filmed on September 11, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Gertrud Zach

925.description:
Hurricane Harvey flood waters stranded 17,000 cattle with very little food. National Guard members from Ohio, Texas and Utah drop bales of hay from a Chinook Helicopter to cows in the Beaumont, TX area on September 9, 2017.

Film Credits: SSG Cahugh Giles

926.description:
U.S. Air Force aircraft assigned to the 1st Special Operations Wing evacuate from Hurlburt Field, FL in advance of Hurricane Irma on September 9, 2017. Video shows an AC-130 Spooky Gunship, MC-130H Combat Talon II, and CV-22 Osprey tiltrotor aircraft taking-off.

Film Credits: A1C Joseph Pick, A1C Caleb Pavao

927.description:
U.S. Army Paratroopers from the 4th Brigade Combat Team (Airborne), 25th Infantry Division conduct day and night jumps from C-17 Globemaster III aircraft to maintain qualifications. Filmed over the Malamute Drop Zone - Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson, AK on September 9, 2017.

Film Credits: SrA Joshua DeGuzman

928.description:
The last operational C-5A Galaxy airlifter in the U.S. Air Force inventory - takeoff at Westover Air Reserve Base, MA - landing, taxi, and parking at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base, AZ to be retired to the Aircraft Boneyard (309th Aerospace Maintenance and Regeneration Group) - ARMAG. Filmed on September 7, 2017. Westover Air Reserve Base now operates the upgraded C-5M Super Galaxy: http://www.westover.afrc.af.mil/News/Article-Display/Article/1299209/westover-c-5m-noses-out-on-flightline/

Film Credits: MSgt W.C. Pope, A1C Christina Rios

929.description:
The U.S. Air Force EC-130J Commando Solo is a specially-modified four-engine Hercules transport plane designed to conduct Military Information Support Operations (MISO), psychological operations (PSYOPS) and civil affairs broadcasts in AM, FM, HF, TV and military communications bands. The 193rd Special Operations Wing, Middletown, Pennsylvania is the only Air Force unit that operates the EC-130J. KC-135 Stratotanker unit from the 916th Air Refueling Wing, Air Force Reserve, Seymour Johnson Air Force Base. Filmed on August 16, 2017. 

Film Credits: MSgt Matt Schwartz

930.description:
Aerial footage of U.S. Marine Corps F-35B Lighting II fighter jets, U.S. Air Force B-1B Lancer bombers, and South Korean Air Force F-15K Slam Eagles releasing bombs. Ground footage of bombs detonating at Pilsung Range in South Korea. Show of Force in response to North Korea launching a missile over Japan. Filmed on August 31, 2017.  

Film Credits: SSgt Alex Echols, SSgt Michael Kantack

931.description:
The U.S. Air Force X-37B Orbital Test Vehicle (OTV-5) is being staged in preparation for its upcoming launch on September 7, 2017. Filmed on September 5, 2017.  

Film Credits: Video courtesy of Boeing, SrA Timothy Kirchner

932.description:
U.S. Air Force C-17 Globemaster III aircraft operated by the 517th Airlift Squadron conduct flight operations, refueling, and a mass jump of 4th Brigade Combat Team (Airborne), 25th Infantry Division. The jump was part of a sustainment field exercise in order to maintain jump qualifications. Filmed out of Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson, Alaska on August 28, 2017.

Film Credits: SrA Javier Alvarez, SrA Joshua DeGuzman, Amn Austin Johnson-Harper

933.description:
A U.S. Air Force B-52H Stratofortress bomber takes-off and lands during exercise Ample Strike 2017 at RAF Fairford in England on August 28, 2017. 

Film Credits: A1C Draeke Layman

934.description:
Flyover view of 309th Aerospace Maintenance and Regeneration Group (aka AMARG or The Aircraft Boneyard) at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base, AZ. The Boneyard contains about 5,000 retired military aircraft over 2,600 acres. Crews at the Boneyard preserve aircraft for possible future use, pull aircraft parts to supply to the field and perform depot-level maintenance and aircraft regeneration in support of Air Force operations. Filmed on July 27, 2017.   

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Andrew Breese

935.description:
Flyover footage of Rockport, TX in the aftermath of Hurricane Harvey. The small town of Rockport, TX was ground zero when category 4 Hurricane Harvey hit the Texas Gulf Coast on August 25, 2017.  

Film Credits: U.S. National Guard Video by John Thibodeau

936.description:
U.S. Military Forces mobilize to help Hurricane Harvey victims in Texas. Filmed August 2017.

Film Credits: Amn Richard Hayes, 1LT Zachary West, PO1 Robert Simpson, PO3 Johanna Strickland, Alana Miller, TSgt Karl Schwach

937.description:
U.S. Air Force B-1B Lancer and B-52 Stratofortress bomber aircraft takeoff and land at RAF Fairford in England during exercise Ample Strike 17. Filmed on August 27-28, 2017. 

Film Credits: A1C Draeke Layman

938.description:
U.S. Marines get ready to deploy. Marines are always ready to jump in the whirlwind-of-fire and defend the United States... U.S. Marines always conduct live-fire drills prior to a Deployment for Training (DFT). This DFT was on Fort A.P. Hill, VA in August 2017. Unit- 3rd Battalion, 2nd Marine Regiment, 2nd Marine Division (2d MARDIV).

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Jaycee Littleton

939.description:
Two USAF KC-10 Extender air tanker missions to refuel F-22 Raptors over undisclosed locations, keeping the fighter jets patrolling the skies and ready for strike operations. KC-10 Unit - 908th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron, U.S. Air Force Central Command. Filmed on August 7-9, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Tech Sgt. Micah Theurich

940.description:
F-15E Strike Eagle pilots and groundcrews from the USAF 334th and the 336th fighter squadrons prepare their fighter jets for flight at Seymour Johnson Air Force Base, NC. 

Film Credits: SrA Carly Thompson, SrA Gabriela Keiser, TSgt Larry Reid Jr.

941.description:
U.S. Marines practice external lift operations with CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters lifting LAV-25 light armored vehicles at Camp Pendleton, CA. Units - Landing Support Company, 1st Transportation Support Battalion (1st TSB), Combat Logistics Regiment 1, 1st Marine Logistics Group. Filmed on August 22, 2017.

Film Credits: Cpl James Trevino

942.description:
The aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) conducts flight operations, launching F/A-18 Super Hornet fighter jets during composite training unit exercise (COMPTUEX) in preparation for an upcoming deployment. COMPTUEX tests a carrier strike group's mission readiness and ability to perform as an integrated unit through simulated real world scenarios. Filmed August 11-19, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Victoria Galbraith and Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Alex Millar -- Released

943.description:
E-2D Advanced Hawkeye airborne early warning aircraft land at Marine Corps Air Station Iwakuni, Japan, after a deployment aboard the USS Ronald Reagan aircraft carrier. Unit - Carrier Airborne Early Warning Squadron 125. Filmed on August 14, 2017.

Film Credits: Cpl Sara Abrego

944.description:
North Korea (NK) threatened to launch a nuclear strike at Guam in August 2017. After thinking about it longer, the NK leadership realized U.S. Air Force B-1B Lancer bombers would be in the air, able to retaliate and decimate Pyongyang. So the NK leadership decided to abort the ill conceived plan of nuking Guam. USAF B-1B unit from Andersen Air force Base, 37th Expeditionary Bomb Squadron, deployed from Ellsworth Air Force Base, SD.

Film Credits: U.S Air Force Video by Amn Audra Young, SSgt Mariko Frazee

945.description:
Soldiers from 2nd Calvary Regiment fire M777 Howitzers at Vaziani Training Area in the country of Georgia during exercise Noble Partner 17 on August 10, 2017.

Film Credits: SGT Dani White, SGT Taylor Hoganson

946.description:
USS Nimitz (CVN-68) is a nuclear powered supercarrier of the U.S. Navy and the lead ship of her class. It is one of the largest warships in the world, with a total displacement of 110,250 tons. "Supercarrier" is an unofficial term for the largest aircraft carriers, typically those displacing over 70,000 tons. Supercarriers are the largest warships ever built. The U.S. Navy currently has 11 Supercarriers in service - 10 Nimitz Class carriers, and the USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78) which is the lead ship of the Ford Class. More info: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supercarrier#Supercarriers_in_service

Film Credits: PO1 Daniel Barker, PO1 Jose Hernandez, SN Cody M. Deccio, PO3 Joshua Haiar, 2nd Class Holly L. Herline

947.description:
U.S. Air Force, Royal Australian Air Force and Canadian Air Force C-17 Globemaster III and C-130 transport planes conduct an Elephant Walk and Minimum Interval Takeoff (MITO) at Joint Base Lewis–McChord, WA during exercise Mobility Guardian on August 2, 2017. Elephant Walk is a USAF term referring to a mass aircraft launch.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by SrA Megan Mallory, SSgt Traci Keller, SrA Izabella Sullivan, Tech. Sgt. Jodi Martinez

948.description:
U.S. Air Force B-1B Lancer bombers filmed at Nellis Air Force Base in Nevada. The Lancer is nicknamed "Bone" from B-One.

Film Credits: 99th Air Base Wing Public Affairs Video by William Lewis

949.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcon maintainers and pilots make a formidable team at Red Flag 17-3 aerial combat exercise on Nellis Air Force Base, July 24, 2017. Unit - 55th Fighter Squadron, Shaw Air Force Base, South Carolina.

Film Credits: A1C Christina Ensley

950.description:
U.S. Air Force B-1B Lancer bomber jets assigned to the 37th Expeditionary Bomb Squadron, deployed from Ellsworth Air Force Base, South Dakota, takeoff from Andersen Air Force Base, Guam, for a training mission on August 11, 2017.  

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman Robert Mason and Airman Audra Young

951.description:
U.S. Marines with 2nd Amphibian Assault Battalion, 1st Battalion, 1st Marine Regiment, and 1st Tank Battalion Marine Air Ground Task Force-8 (MAGTF-8) conduct the Mechanized Assault Course (MAC) at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center, Twentynine Palms, California on August 9, 2017.  

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Kassie L. McDole

952.description:
U.S. Air Force air tankers refuel various allied fighter jets inflight.  

Film Credits: US Air Force Video by 2nd Lt. Nathanael Callon and Staff Sgt. John Raven

953.description:
U.S. Air Force A-10 Thunderbolt II squadron deployed to Estonia, flight line footage at Amari Air Base. Filmed on August 8, 2017.

Film Credits: SGT Anri Baril

954.description:
Two U.S. Air Force B-1B Lancer bombers and two KC-135 Statotankers takeoff from Andersen Air Force Base, Guam, for a 10-hour mission, flying in the vicinity of Kyushu, Japan, the East China Sea, and the Korean peninsula on August 7, 2017. B-1 Bomber Unit - 37th Expeditionary Bomb Squadron, deployed from Ellsworth Air Force Base, South Dakota.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Tech. Sgt. Richard P. Ebensberger

955.description: The World's Greatest Air Show at RAF Fairford. Filmed on July 15, 2017.

956.description:
Royal Air Force A400M Atlas - No. 70 Squadron-LXX Squadron, RAF lands at Mcallister Airport, WA. The A-400M Atlas makes its large-scale, international exercise debut at exercise Mobility Guardian. Both the Royal Air Force and French Air Force have brought this aircraft. It has a range of 4,000 miles and carries 116 passengers. Mobility Guardian is Air Mobility Command's premier exercise, providing an opportunity for the Mobility Air Forces to train with joint and international partners airlift, air refueling, aeromedical evacuation and mobility support.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by SSgt Guy LaPlante, A1C Ryan Baumgart, SSgt Traci Keller, SrA Timothy Kirchner

957.description:
The aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) conducts flight operations during a composite training unit exercise (COMPTUEX). COMPTUEX is a training certification the U.S. Navy performs on ships before deployment. Filmed August 5, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Alex Millar - Released

958.description:
Three UH-60 Black Hawk helicopters practice landing and taking-off together at Fort McCoy, WI on June 5, 2016. Unit - 1st Assault Helicopter Battalion, 106th Aviation Regiment, U.S. Army ANG.

Film Credits: Greg Mason

959.description:
Two F-22 Raptors from the U.S. Air Force 3rd Wing meet up with a new HC-130J Combat King II aircraft inflight from Lockheed Martin in South Carolina and escort it to its new home at Joint Base Elmendorf Richardson, Alaska. The HC-130J crew is from the 176th Wing, Alaska Air National Guard.

Film Credits: A1C Kelly Willett

960.description:
Multiple C-17 Globemaster III air refueling (aka tanking) during exercise Talisman Saber/Ultimate Reach 2017. Video shows KC-10 Air Tanker refueling C-17s inflight from Travis Air Force Base to Hickam Air Force base to Wake Island to Brisbane, Australia on July 12-13, 2017.

Film Credits: SSgt Scott Taylor

961.description:
U.S. Army M1A2 Tanks conduct bounding maneuvers during a live-fire exercise at Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany on August 2, 2017. Unit - Aggressor Company, 1st Battalion, 68th Armor Regiment, 3rd Armored Brigade Combat Team, 4th Infantry Division.  

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Gertrud Zach

962.description:
U.S. Army paratroopers from the 82d Airborne Division jump out of a C-17 Globemaster III assigned to 7th Airlift Squadron during Operation Panther Storm 2017 at Fort Bragg, NC on July 24, 2017. Panther Storm is a deployment readiness exercise used to test the 82nd Airborne Division’s ability to rapidly deploy its global response force anywhere in the world with only a few hours notice. 

Film Credits: US Air Force Video by Tech Sgt Alexander Farver

963.description:
A-10 Thunderbolt II jets from the 422d Test and Evaluation Squadron (422 TES) dropped guided weapons and fired 30mm Gatling cannons during training at Nevada Test and Training Range on July 19, 2017. The Warthog pilots dropped Guided Bomb Unit-12s (GBU-12), Guided Bomb Unit-38s (GBU-38), and Guided Bomb Unit-31s (GBU-31).  

Film Credits: SrA Mychal Fox, William Lewis

964.description:
Range 400 & 410A at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center, 29 Palms are used to train USMC rifle companies in the techniques and procedures for ground attack of enemy fortified compounds. Filmed on July 21-22, 2017. Units - Echo Company, 2nd Battalion, 1st Marine Regiment, Marine Air Ground Task Force-8 (MAGTF-8) and Alpha Company, 1st Battalion, 1st Marine Regiment, Marine Air-Ground Task Force-8 (MAGTF-8).  

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Justin M. Smith and Cpl. Christopher A. Mendoza

965.description:
Multiple views of CBU-105 Sensor Fused Weapons in action. The CBU-105 (cluster bomb unit) is a Precision Guided Munition that can be used to stop enemy armored units such as tanks. It can be used to target SAM sites including radars and support vehicles. Video released by 99th Air Base Wing, Nellis Air Force Base on July 31, 2017. More info about CBU-105 here: https://defencyclopedia.com/2015/06/12/cbu-105-sensor-fuzed-weapon-usafs-ultimate-tank-buster/    

Film Credits: A1C Megan Qualls

966.description:
