U.S. Marines with Marine Air Ground Task Force-8 (MAGTF-8) participate in a Tank Mechanized Assault Course (TMAC) during Integrated Training Exercise (ITX) 5-17 at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center, Twentynine Palms, CA on July 28, 2017. The purpose of ITX is to create a realistic training environment that produces combat-ready forces capable of operating as an integrated MAGTF. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Kassie L. McDole

967.description:
Alpha Battery of 1st Battalion, 147th Field Artillery (MLRS) out of Aberdeen, South Dakota fire MLRS, joined by other NATO rocket launchers during Exercise Saber Guardian 17. Filmed on July 15, 2017 in Cincu, Romania.

Film Credits: SGT Austin Pearce

968.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers from 1-26 Infantry Regiment, 101st Airborne Division, assault through a desert objective in Dona Ana, NM on July 14th 2017.

Film Credits: SGT Devone Collins

969.description:
Logistic convoys are some of the most targeted and deadly places in a combat zone. A convoy must be well armed and protected by trained personnel who know how to target and shoot back at the enemy. U.S. Marines with Combat Logistics Battalion 2, Marine Air Ground Task Force-8 (MAGTF-8) conduct Motorized Fire and Movement Exercises (MFME) during Integrated Training Exercise (ITX) 5-17 at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center, Twentynine Palms, CA on July 23, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Kassie L. McDole

970.description:
U.S. Army paratroopers with 3rd Brigade Combat Team, 82nd Airborne Division, fires weapons at a zero range during deployment readiness at Fort Bragg, NC July 24, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Sgt. Steven Galimore

971.description:
Australian and United States troops fight side-by-side in a mock battle during exercise Talisman Saber 17 at Shoalwater Bay Training Area, July 20, 2017. If the shit ever hits the fan for real, the Aussies will have your back... so likewise you Kangaroos, friends till the end. 

Film Credits: SLCpl Jacob Colvin

972.description:
Marine Corps artillery units report on their experience in Australia... Talisman Saber 2017. 

Film Credits: SLCpl Jacob Colvin

973.description:
U.S. Navy aircraft carrier USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76) is off the Queensland coast, Australia - near Townsville. The ship is conducting air support operations in Exercise Talisman Saber 2017. Filmed on July 14, 2017. 

Film Credits: SSG Tom Conning

974.description:
Saber Guardian 17 is a major military exercise conducted across three Eastern European NATO countries... Bulgaria, Hungary, and Romania. This footage is from a combined arms live-fire exercise at Novo Selo Training Area, Bulgaria on July 20, 2017.

Film Credits: Laurens Vermeire, SPC Rafael Garibay, SSG Zachary Holden, SSG Nicholaus Williams

975.description:
If you want to be a Marine Corps door gunner you must first be a Crew Chief. Being a Crew Chief is not easy. USMC... Semper Fi.

Film Credits: This work, ITX 5-17 UH-1Y Huey Close Air Support Drills, by Sgt Kassie McDole, identified by DVIDS, must comply with the restrictions shown on https://www.dvidshub.net/about/copyright.

976.description:
U.S. Army M109A6 Paladin Howitzer crew fires artillery rounds at National Training Center, Fort Irwin, California on July 20, 2017.

Film Credits: SSG Edward Siguenza - https://www.dvidshub.net/about/copyright

977.description:
U.S. Air Force footage of an F-15 Eagle flight over Crater Lake, OR including crystal clear views of inflight refueling and F/A-18 fighter jets flying in formation and peeling off. The 173rd Fighter Wing aircraft video is attributed to TSgt Jason Van Mourik, produced on July 20, 2017.

Film Credits: https://www.dvidshub.net/about/copyright

978.description:
The Office of Naval Research (ONR) demonstrates the Navy's electromagnetic railgun initial rep-rate fires of multi-shot salvos at the Naval Surface Warfare Center Dahlgren Division. The railgun relies on a massive electrical pulse, rather than gunpowder or other chemical propellants, to launch projectiles at distances over 100 nautical miles – and at speeds that exceed Mach 6. 

Film Credits: John Williams

979.description:
U.S. Marines with the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit (31st MEU) conduct an amphibious landing on Freshwater Beach in the Shoalwater Bay Training Area, Australia during exercise Talisman Saber 2017 on July 19. Exercise Talisman Saber is the largest combined, joint military exercise undertaken by the Australian Defense Force (ADF) and the biennial exercise was conducted for the seventh time in 2017, involving more than 30,000 U.S. and Australian personnel. 

Film Credits: https://www.dvidshub.net/video/539072/31st-meu-beach-assault-b-roll-package

980.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers combine with Romanian Air Defense units in a live-fire exercise on July 19, 2017. The U.S. Soldiers used their mobile Avenger Air Defense Missile Systems to shoot down target drones at Capu Midia, Romania. Unit - Charlie Battery, 2nd Battalion, 263rd Air Defense Artillery Regiment.

Film Credits: SGT Mark Brejcha

981.description:
M41A7 TOW Improved Target Acquisition System (ITAS) provides long-range, lethal anti-armor and precision assault fires capabilities for U.S. Army Infantry. Soldiers from Alpha/Bravo Troop 2-106th CAV, Delta Company 2-130 INF and Delta Company 1-178 INF from the Illinois Army National Guard fire TOW missiles at Range 19, Fort McCoy, WI on March 13, 2017. The 33D IBCT TOW crews conducted training on the M41A7 ITAS system including system descriptions, target engagement, FTL capabilities, Crew Commands, PMCS, and Missile capabilities.

Film Credits: Greg Mason

982.description:
M41A7 TOW Improved Target Acquisition System (ITAS) provides long-range, lethal anti-armor and precision assault fires capabilities for U.S. Army Infantry. Soldiers from Alpha/Bravo Troop 2-106th CAV, Delta Company 2-130 INF and Delta Company 1-178 INF from the Illinois Army National Guard fire TOW missiles at Range 19, Fort McCoy, WI on March 14, 2017. The 33D IBCT TOW crews conducted training on the M41A7 ITAS system including system descriptions, target engagement, FTL capabilities, Crew Commands, PMCS, and Missile capabilities.

Film Credits: Greg Mason

983.description:
South Dakota Army National Guard soldiers from the 1-147th Field Artillery battalion conduct hide and fight maneuvers with the M270A1 Multiple Launch Rocket System (MLRS) during annual training at Fort McCoy, WI on June 23-25, 2017.

Film Credits: Greg Mason

984.description:
U.S. Navy Landing Craft Air Cushion (LCAC) assigned to Naval Beach Unit (NBU-7), conduct 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit (31-MEU) forces and equipment offload on the beach in Australia as part of a large-scale amphibious assault during Talisman Saber 17. LCACs, launched from the amphibious assault ship USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6), enabled movement of 31st MEU forces and equipment ashore in order for the MEU to complete mission objectives in tandem with Australian counterparts. Filmed on July 13, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Diana Quinlan - Released

985.description:
The Australian 5th Aviation Regiment leads Battle Group Pegasus, made up of 24 helicopters from Australia, the U.S. and New Zealand. Filmed on July 11, 2017 as part of exercise Talisman Saber 2017.
Interview with Capt. Joshua Ahrens, B Troop commander, 25th Combat Aviation Brigade, 26th Cavalry, U.S. Army.

Film Credits: SGT Jorge Higuera and SPC Bradey Pettit

986.description:
The land battle phase of Exercise Talisman Saber 2017 was launched on July 13, 2017, with the largest amphibious landing Australian troops have been involved in since WWII. Troops transported ashore from an amphibious readiness element including HMAS Canberra, HMAS Choules and HMNZS Canterbury. Airborne soldiers from the United States, Canada and Australia also parachuted into the Shoalwater Bay Training Area in Central Queensland from six Royal Australian Air Force and United States Air Force C-17 Globemaster aircraft that had started their journey in Alaska.

Film Credits: https://www.dvidshub.net/video/538025/beach-landing-troops-and-equipment-shoalwater-bay-training-area

987.description:
U.S. Navy EA-18G Growlers from Electronic Attack Squadron 132 (VAQ-132) fly training sorties to hone their combat skills. Filmed at RAAF Base Amberley, Australia on July 7, 2017. 

Film Credits: Australian Army Sgt. Michael Bolt and Australian Air Force Sgt. Kirk Peacock

988.description:
U.S. Army air assault training with Black Hawk and Chinook helicopters by the 3rd Battalion, 501st Aviation Regiment at White Sands Space Harbor, NM on June 28, 2017.

Film Credits: John Hamilton

989.description:
U.S. Army TARDEC (Tank Automotive Research, Development and Engineering Center) is testing the Chevrolet Colorado ZH2 to evaluate its off-road capabilities. The Colorado ZH2 is the the most extreme off-road hydrogen fuel-cell electric vehicle ever made by General Motors. Soldiers from the 4th Infantry Division and 10th Special Forces Group exercised the demonstrator to evaluate the ZH2's power (torque) responsiveness, silent mobility, high exportable power, and fuel cell technology. Filmed at Fort Carson, CO - June 27-30.

Film Credits: Kimberly Derryberry, TARDEC Public Affairs

990.description:
The U.S. Missile Defense Agency (MDA), the Ballistic Missile Defense System Operational Test Agency, and U.S. Army Soldiers of the 11th Air Defense Artillery Brigade from Fort Bliss, TX conduct an intercept test of the Terminal High Altitude Area Defense (THAAD) element of the United States Ballistic Missile Defense System. Filmed on July 11, 2017. More info: https://www.mda.mil

Film Credits: Leah Garton

991.description:
Two U.S. Air Force B-1B Lancer bombers takeoff at night, with afterburners blazing, from Andersen Air Force Base, Guam on July 8, 2017. Unit - Deployed from Dyess Air Force Base, TX to the 9th Expeditionary Bomb Squadron, Guam.

Film Credits: A1C Phillip M Guadiana-Gomez

992.description:
New U.S. Marine Corps recruits meet their drill instructors, who give an introductory speech, and will be responsible for transforming them into Marines at Marine Corps Recruit Depot Parris Island. Although the recruits were under the supervision of other drill instructors since their arrival on Parris Island several days earlier, these are the drill instructors who will be with them every moment for the next 12 weeks. Filmed on July 1, 2017.

Film Credits: Video by Lance Cpl. Maximiliano Bavastro and Lance Cpl. Carlin Warren

993.description:
U.S. Navy LCAC (Landing Craft Air Cushion) launch and recovery aboard the amphibious assault ship USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6) during exercise Talisman Saber 17 in the Coral Sea on July 8, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist Specialist 2nd Class Jeanette Mullinax and Seaman Cosmo Walrath - Released

994.description:
U.S. Marine Corps aircrews with VMFA-232, VMFA-251 and VMFA-122 squadrons conduct flight line operations during Red Flag-Alaska 17-2 air combat exercise. F/A-18 Hornet and F-22 Raptor fighter jets takeoff during Red Flag-Alaska 17-2 at Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson, Alaska. Filmed June 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Kowshon Ye

995.description:
U.S. Navy MH-53E Sea Dragons assigned to Helicopter Mine Countermeasures Squadron 14 (HM-14), conduct aerial refueling operations off the coast of NC on June, 21 2017.

Film Credits: LCpl Luisa Torres

996.description:
Military exercises continue in South Korea with U.S. Marines - in the face of continued launching of North Korean nuclear capable missiles. Filmed June 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. David A. Diggs

997.description:
Aerial refueling of French Dassault Rafale fighter jets, U.S. Marine Corps EA-6B Prowler electronic attack jets, and an Australian E-7A Wedgetail combat battle-space management jet over undisclosed locations in June and July 2017.

Film Credits: US Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. John Raven

998.description:
A 17th Special Operations Squadron MC-130J Commando II lands and takes-off on a remote island runway on Okinawa, Japan during a training exercise. Filmed July 4, 2017. MC-130J Commando II fact sheet: http://www.af.mil/About-Us/Fact-Sheets/Display/Article/104510/mc-130j-commando-ii/

Film Credits: A1C Jerome Brackins Jr

999.description:
Compilation video of the C-5 Galaxy and variants, featuring the largest plane in the U.S. Military inventory. Interior and exterior shots, takeoff and landing, loading and unloading, inflight cockpit views and aerial refueling clips are included. Plus music video clip licensed by Gung Ho Vids.

Film Credits: Video clips courtesy of the United States Air Force, Department of Defense - Derivative Works Gung Ho Vids

1000.description:
U.S. Marines conduct the Marine Corps Combat Readiness Evaluation (MCCRE), at Camp Lejeune, NC in June 2017. MCCRE is a pre-deployment training evaluation designed to test Marines in various combat scenarios. Units - 2nd Battalion, 2nd Marine Regiment, 2d Marine Division and 1st Battalion, 8th Marine Regiment, 2nd Marine Division.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Adam D. Edwards and Lance Cpl. Bethanie Ryan

1001.description:
U.S. Marines live-fire exercise with MK19 40mm Grenade Launcher, BGM-71 TOW Missile, and FGM-148 Javelin Missile on June 22, 2017. Unit - 2nd Battalion, 2nd Marine Regiment, 2nd Marine Division. Filmed at Camp Lejeune, NC on June 22, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Dani A. Zunun

1002.description:
Pilots from the 167th Airlift Wing fly a C-17 Globemaster III transport plane on a training flight out of Shepherd Field, WV, with touch-and-go landings and aerial refueling. Filmed on March 4, 2017.

Film Credits: SMSgt Emily Beightol-Deyerle

1003.description:
A U.S. Air Force HC-130P Combat King aircrew from the 81st Expeditionary Rescue Squadron and pararescuemen from the 82nd Expeditionary Rescue Squadron conduct personnel recovery training at an undisclosed location on on April 29, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. Laura Beckley

1004.description:
U.S. Air Force Special Operations Airmen (AFSOC) prepare a dirt runway for a C-130J Super Hercules landing and takeoff at an undisclosed location on June 9, 2017. Imagery has been modified to protect personally identifiable information. Unit - 75th Expeditionary Airlift Squadron.

Film Credits: SSgt Nicholas Priest

1005.description:
SERE - Survival, Evasion, Resistance, and Escape is a program that provides U.S. military personnel, U.S. Department of Defense civilians, and private military contractors with training in evading capture, survival skills, and the military code of conduct. Night jump training filmed over Japan on April 13, 2017. More info here: http://www.businessinsider.com/heres-what-its-like-at-sere-training-2014-12

Film Credits: SrA Katelynn Moeller

1006.description:
U.S. Marine Corps tank crews from 1st Marine Division, (1stMARDIV) - 2d Marine Division, (2DMARDIV) - 4th Marine Division (4thMARDIV) compete in the 14th Annual Tank Gunnery Competition, Tiger Competition (TIGERCOMP) at Camp Lejeune, NC on June 9, 2017. Bravo Company, 1st Tank Battalion, 1st Marine Division (1ST MARDIV) placed 1st in the competition.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by LCpl David Luckey and Cpl Williams Quinteros

1007.description:
HD footage-1080p/60fps of U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptors and F-15 Strike Eagle aerial refueling over undisclosed location, in-combat targeting... probably over Iraq, Syria, or Afghanistan. Filmed on June 21, 2017.  

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Tech Sgt. Micah Theurich

1008.description:
U.S. Air Force Pilot Colonel Fesler conducts a fini flight, or final flight, in a F-22 Raptor fighter jet at Langley Air Force Base, VA. Fini flight is a military aviator tradition which marks retirement, departure from an assigned unit, or the final time he/she will fly a certain aircraft ever again. A fini flight is a celebration and is usually met at the end with water hoses over the aircraft, family members, squadron mates, and friends. Filmed on June 21, 2017.   

Film Credits: A1C Amanda Dole and SSgt Benjamin Wocken

1009.description:
The U.S. Air Force-MQ-9 Reaper unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) is responsible for killing multiple terrorist and other scumbags around the world.  

Film Credits: TSgt. Neil S. Ballecer, SSgt Joseph Orellana, SSgt Erin Mills, SrA William Branch

1010.description:
Pilots and air crew members of the Ohio Air National Guard, 180th Fighter Wing, prepare for F-16 Fighting Falcon fighter jet flight operations. Footage is from Toledo Air National Guard Base and includes shots of: pilot briefing, pilot suit up, ground crew maintenance and munitions activity, Pilot pre-flight prep, F-16 jet takeoffs, and cockpit video. If activated to federal service, the 180th Fighter Wing is gained by the United States Air Force Air Combat Command. Filmed on June 21, 2017.  

Film Credits: SSgt Michael Hughes

1011.description:
Three live-fire exercise by U.S. Marines forward deployed in South Korea. Marines with 3rd Battalion, 8th Marine Regiment, 3rd Marine Division, conduct a live-fire platoon attack at Range Georgia, a live-fire convoy defense exercise at Story Live Fire Complex, and live-fire close-quarter battle drills at New Mexico Range Training Area. Plus testing of the Utility Task Vehicle (UTV) at Eagle Point Training Area. All filmed in South Korea, June 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. David A. Diggs

1012.description:
Historic color footage of the Memphis Belle B-17 bomber with her famous flight crew and other B-17s during WWII. Memphis Belle is the nickname of the Boeing B-17F Flying Fortress that was one of the first B-17 bombers to complete 25 combat missions with her crew intact. The aircraft and crew then returned to the United States to sell war bonds in support of the war effort. Between 1942 and 1945, film director William Wyler volunteered to serve as a major in the United States Army Air Forces and directed "The Memphis Belle: A Story of a Flying Fortress" (1944), a documentary about a Boeing B-17 and its U.S. Army Air Force crew. Wyler filmed the documentary at great personal risk, flying over enemy territory on actual bombing missions in 1943. This footage is Public Domain B-Roll from the National Archives and Records Administration.

Film Credits: William Wyler, National Archives and Records Administration

1013.description: Clips of various U.S. warplanes inflight, aerial refueling, and some cockpit video of T-38 training aircraft. This footage was captured mostly over undisclosed locations, with some training scenes of Red Flag- Alaska, all courtesy of the United States Air Force. The video was shot by USAF and Combat Camera members in June 2017. Anyone can use this footage, as it is Public Domain. All footage was edited and rendered in 1080p-60fps by Gung Ho Vids. Credit to the extraordinary Military videographers who produced this outstanding footage: SrA Joshua DeGuzman, SrA Nicolas Myers, SSgt John Raven, TSgt Micah Theurich

1014.description:
Crew members assigned to the 23rd Expeditionary Aircraft Maintenance Squadron prepare and load munitions onto a 23rd Expeditionary Bomb Squadron B-52H Stratofortress at Al Udeid Air Base on June 15, 2017. 

Film Credits: TSgt Micah Theurich

1015.description:
The 56th Fighter Wing at Luke Air Force Base resumed F-35A Lightning II flight operations after an 11 day pause due to five physiological events that occurred with pilots during flights from May 2-June 8, 2017. Filmed on June 21, 2017. More info here: http://www.af.mil/News/Article-Display/Article/1219526/luke-afb-to-resume-local-f-35a-flying-operations/

Film Credits: SrA Joshua Altice, A1C Heidi Goodsell, A1C Caitlin Gorsi and A1C Caroline Parks

1016.description:
U.S. Marine Corps Gunners are extremely rare. Only 97 Gunners exist in the entire USMC. A USMC Gunner explains how suppressors (silencers) increase lethality, how to properly collimate the rifle, and gives a demonstration of how hot a suppressor can get during firing... by cooking bacon on his rifle suppressor.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by LCpl Timothy Lutz and Cpl. Clarence L. Wimberly

1017.description:
U.S. Marines from Marine Corps Europe participated in BALTOPS 17. Baltic Operations (BALTOPS) is an annual multinational, maritime-focused exercise in the Baltic Sea region, and 2017 is the 45th edition of the exercise involving 4,000 shipboard personnel, 50 ships and submarines, and more than 50 aircraft from 14 countries: Belgium, Denmark, Estonia, France, Germany, Latvia, Lithuania, the Netherlands, Norway, Poland, the United Kingdom, the United States and NATO’s Enhanced Opportunities Partners: Finland and Sweden. BALTOPS, which began in 1972, continues to be an excellent opportunity for NATO and regional partners to strengthen interoperability through a series of combined tactical maneuvers and scenarios. Filmed at Putlos Range, Germany on June 6-7, 2017.

Film Credits: PO2 Kelby Sanders

1018.description:
NATO armored vehicles conduct a river crossing on a constructed pontoon bridge in Rukla, Lithuania on June 19, 2017 as part of Operation Iron Wolf - Saber Strike 17. Iron Wolf is a sub-exercise of Saber Strike 17. Saber Strike is a major NATO Alliance exercise throughout the Baltic region and Poland involving militaries from: Belgium, Canada, Croatia, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Italy, Latvia, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Slovenia, Slovakia, the United Kingdom and the United States.

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Spc. Samuel Brooks and Courtesy Video by Nato TV

1019.description:
U.S. Air force B-1B Lancer bombers assigned to the 9th Expeditionary Bomb Squadron, takeoff from Andersen Air Force Base, Guam, for a 10-hour mission, flying in the vicinity of Kyushu, Japan, the East China Sea, and the Korean Peninsula, June 20, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. Joshua Smoot

1020.description:
Ordnance Airmen deployed from Barksdale Air Force Base, Louisiana load munitions on a B-52H Stratofortress at RAF Fairford, U.K. Filmed on June 4, 2017.

Film Credits: TSgt Sarah Loicano

1021.description:
Footage of NATO Nations conducting a large-scale military exercise in Poland. Operation Saber Strike 2017 is integrated and synchronized deterrence oriented training designed to improve interoperability and readiness. It takes place in multiple locations throughout Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania and Poland May 28 through June 24 and involves Belgium, Canada, Croatia, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Italy, Latvia, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Slovenia, Slovakia, the United Kingdom and the United States. 

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Charles Rosemond, SGT Austin Majors, Staff Sgt. Brian Kohl, Spc. Samuel Brooks, Spc. Stefan English

1022.description:
British Royal Air Force Typhoon FGR4 fighter jets are conducting sorties with Romanian MIGs from Mihail Kogalniceanu Air Base in Romania to police the skies over parts of the NATO Alliance. Filmed on June 14, 2017.

Film Credits: NATO Channel

1023.description:
Navy aircraft carrier USS Abraham Lincoln (CVN-72) has returned to fleet action after completing its 4 year long Refueling and Complex Overhaul (RCOH) carried out at Newport News Shipyard. The Lincoln is currently underway conducting flight deck certification to ensure the ship and air wing are able to safely launch and recover aircraft. Filmed in June 2017.

Film Credits: PO1 Mark Logico, MC3 Clint Davis, MC3 Cody Anderson, MCSN Jeff Sherman

1024.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcon and A-10 Thunderbolt II fighter jets takeoff during aerial combat exercise Red Flag-Alaska 17-2 at Eielson Air Force Base on June 13th, 2017. 

Film Credits: SrA Joshua DeGuzman

1025.description:
Romanian Air Force MIG-21 LanceR fighter jets takeoff at Camp Turzii, Romania during Operation Dacian Viper, training with the USAF 187th Fighter Wing, August 2012. Plus cockpit video. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air National Guard Video by Tech. Sgt. Jeffery Foster

1026.description:
The aircraft carrier USS Abraham Lincoln (CVN-72) performs high-speed turns in the Atlantic Ocean after completing its midlife Refueling and Complex Overhaul (RCOH). Filmed on May 11, 2017.  

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Clint Davis - Released

1027.description:
U.S. Marine Corps F/A-18C Hornet air crews perform pre-flight checks and maintenance prior to takeoff during air combat exercise Red Flag Alaska 17-2 on June 12-13, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Kowshon Ye

1028.description:
Oregon Air National Guard crewmembers with the 142nd Fighter Wing perform pre-flight maintenance, weapons loading, and post-flight maintenance on F-15C Eagle fighter jets at Nellis Air Force Base during Weapons Instructor Course, May 29 to June 16, 2017. 

Film Credits: MSgt John Hughel

1029.description:
U.S. Marine Corps F-35B Lightning II fighter jets with Marine Fighter Attack Squadron (VMFA-121) conduct vertical landings at Marine Corps Air Station Iwakuni, Japan on June 13, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Waiyan Tin, Lance Cpl. Joseph Abrego, Lance Cpl. Mason Roy

1030.description:
A U.S. Air Force C130-J aircrew with the 75th Expeditionary Airlift Squadron supports an East Africa Response Force training exercise and performs dirt landings. Combined Joint Task Force - Horn of Africa (CJTF-HOA) promotes security in East Africa by assisting partner nations with countering violent extremist organizations, fostering regional security cooperation, and by protecting U.S. personnel and facilities in its 10-country area of responsibility. Filmed on May 10, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Technical Sgt. Laura Beckley

1031.description:
USS Zumwalt (DDG-1000) is the U.S. Navy's newest destoyer and is the lead ship of the Zumwalt class. Shots include exterior and interior footage - berthing, head, mess deck, bridge, engineering, medical, and other ships spaces. Filmed on May 8, 2017.

Film Credits: Kevin Dawson

1032.description:
USS Wyoming (SSBN-742) on a regularly-scheduled patrol in the Atlantic Ocean. Shots include exterior, interior, and general life onboard the sub.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Austin Rooney - Released

1033.description:
A restored WWII era Boeing B-29 Superfortress, nicknamed "Doc", takes off from McConnell Air Force Base, Kansas and arrives at Whiteman Air Force Base, Missouri in advance of the Wings Over Whiteman airshow. Filmed on May 9, 2017. The B-29 was the bomber that dropped 2 atomic bombs on Japan during WWII... the "Enola Gay" dropped on Hirosima and the "Bockscar" dropped on Nagasaki.

Film Credits: SrA Darrell Sydnor II, A1C Kristin Cerri

1034.description:
Royal Dutch Marines of 11 Raiding Squadron conduct air assault and combat drills with U.S. Army Chinook helicopters at Cincu training area, Romania, as part of NATO exercise Noble Jump 2017. Filmed on May 8-9, 2017.

Film Credits: NATO, Peter van Bastelaar 
Mediacentrum Defensie (Netherlands)

1035.description:
U.S. Army Air Assault School at Camp Rilea, Oregon is a 10-day course designed to prepare Soldiers for insertion, evacuation, and pathfinder missions that call for the use of multipurpose transportation and assault helicopters. Officially called the Sabalauski Air Assault School (TSAAS), the original school is located at Fort Campbell, Kentucky. But there are also or have been schools at Fort Rucker, Alabama; Schofield Barracks, Hawaii; Fort Hood, Texas; Camp Blanding, Florida; Fort Bliss, Texas; Fort Benning, Georgia; Fort Drum, New York; Fort Ord, California; Fort Richardson, Alaska; Fort Wainwright, Alaska; Fort Belvoir, Virginia; Fort Bragg, North Carolina, Camp Gruber, Oklahoma, and West Point, New York. Male and Female Soldiers of all ranks, from around the nation, go through Air Assault School at Camp Rilea in Warrenton, Oregon. Filmed on June 9, 2017.

Film Credits: SPC Alisha Grezlik

1036.description:
Helicopter view of the amphibious assault ship USS America (LHA-6) during testing of the F-35B Lightning II (short takeoff and vertical landing variant) on November 16, 2016.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Andy Wolfe - Released

1037.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 510th Fighter Squadron train at Krzesiny Air Base, Poland on June 8, 2017 during exercise BALTOPS 2017. The exercise is designed to enhance flexibility and interoperability, to strengthen combined response capabilities to defend the Baltic Sea region.

Film Credits: SSgt Esteban Esquivel

1038.description:
U.S. Air Force B-52H Stratofortress bombers land at RAF Fairford in England to support upcoming military exercises in Europe. Filmed on May 2, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Tech. Sgt. Miguel Lara

1039.description:
British Grenadier Guards conduct air assault exercises, boarding U.S. Army Chinook helicopters during operation NOBLE JUMP 17 in Romania on May 7, 2017. The Grenadier Guards is an infantry regiment of the British Army. It is the most senior regiment of the Guards Division.

Film Credits: NATO

1040.description:
U.S. Marines attached to Advanced Infantry Training Battalion, School of Infantry-East (SOI-E), conduct a combined arms exercise at Camp Lejeune, N.C., April 7, 2017. The mission of SOI-E is to train entry-level and advanced level Marines in the skills required to be an Infantry Marine for the operating forces.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Manuel Serrano

1041.description:
Laughlin AIr Force Base in Texas is the largest primary pilot training base in the USAF. It is used as a first-step for USAF pilots to get hands-on flying training with the T-6A Texan II aircraft. The T-6A Texan II is a single-engine, two-seat plane designed to train Joint Primary Pilot Training students (JPPT) in basic flying skills common to U.S. Air Force and Navy pilots. Filmed on May 31, 2017.

Film Credits: Thomas Moore

1042.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcons from the U.S. Pacific Air Force F-16 Demonstration Team land at Marine Corps Air Station Iwakuni in Japan for hot pit refueling on May 10, 2017. "Hot Pit" is refueling while the jet's engines are still running.

 Film Credits: LCpl Emma Norris

1043.description:
Recent aerial refueling clips of USAF A-10 Thunderbolt II 'Warthogs" and USMC F/A-18 Hornets with KC-10 Extender air tankers. And USAF F-16 Fighting Falcons refueling with a KC-135 Stratotanker. Filmed over undisclosed locations in late May and early June 2017.

Film Credits: US Air Force Video by Tech Sgt. Micah Theurich, Staff Sgt. John Raven, SrA Brandon Gifford

1044.description:
USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70) and USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76) Aircraft Carrier Strike Groups sail together in the Sea of Japan on May 1, 2017. The strike groups include: USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70), Carrier Air Wing (CVW-2), guided-missile cruiser USS Lake Champlain (CG-57) and guided-missile destroyers USS Wayne E. Meyer (DDG-108) and USS Michael Murphy (DDG-112), USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76), Carrier Air Wing (CVW-5), guided-missile cruiser USS Shiloh (CG-67), guided-missile destroyers USS Barry (DDG-52), USS McCampbell (DDG-85), USS Fitzgerald (DDG-62), and USS Mustin (DDG-89) and the Japanese ships JS Hyuga (DDH-181) and JS Ashigara (DDG-178). 

 Film Credits:  U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Sean M. Castellano - Released

1045.description:
Arctic Challenge 2017 is a multinational military air exercise based in Finland, Norway, and Sweden. The purpose of the exercise is to practice mobilizing, evaluate aircraft, personnel and weapons capabilities, and train in multinational operations. In addition to the three host countries - participating this year are: Belgium, the Netherlands, France, Germany, Switzerland, Great Britain, Canada, and the United States. Arctic Challenge Exercise 2017 takes place from May 19 to June 2. The U.S. Air Force participated and deployed 12 F-15Cs and approximately 200 airmen from the 48th Fighter Wing, RAF Lakenheath, England, to Rovaniemi Air Base, Finland. Additionally, two KC-135s from the 100th Air Refueling Wing, RAF Mildenhall, England, deployed to Kallax Air Base, Sweden to support all participating aircraft. 
Part 1 here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SoURUwkU1Zw

 Film Credits:  SSgt Armando Aparicio

1046.description:
Arctic Challenge 2017 is a multinational military air exercise based in Finland, Norway, and Sweden. The purpose of the exercise is to practice mobilizing, evaluate aircraft, personnel and weapons capabilities, and train in multinational operations. In addition to the three host countries - participating this year are: Belgium, the Netherlands, France, Germany, Switzerland, Great Britain, Canada, and the United States. Arctic Challenge Exercise 2017 takes place from May 19 to June 2. The U.S. Air Force participated and deployed 12 F-15Cs and approximately 200 airmen from the 48th Fighter Wing, RAF Lakenheath, England, to Rovaniemi Air Base, Finland. Additionally, two KC-135s from the 100th Air Refueling Wing, RAF Mildenhall, England, deployed to Kallax Air Base, Sweden to support all participating aircraft. 
Part 2 here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kBT5bYDFuYU

 Film Credits:  SSgt Armando Aparicio

1047.description:
Thirty-five years after President Ronald Reagan proposed the anti-missile Strategic Defense Initiative (SDI) (aka Star Wars), an orbital ballistic missile was shot down by U.S. anti-ballistic missile systems during a test shot on May 30, 2017. FTG-15 Flight Test was a missile test fired from Vandenberg Air Force Base, California against an in-coming ballistic missile fired from a U.S. base in the Marshall Islands. It is being described as... hitting a bullet inflight, with another bullet. For more information go here: https://www.mda.mil

 Film Credits: Leah Garton, SSgt Kaleb Mayfield

1048.description:
The Utah Test & Training Range (UTTR) is a military testing and training area located in Utah's West Desert. It is the largest contiguous block of over-land supersonic-authorized restricted airspace in the continental United States. The UTTR is used for training in air-to-air-combat, air-to-ground inert and live practice bombing and gunnery training by Military aircrews. More info here: http://www.hill.af.mil/About-Us/Fact-Sheets/Display/Article/672497/utah-test-and-training-range/

Film Credits: SSgt Erin Mills

1049.description:
A U.S. Air Force B-52H Stratofortress crew performs flight operations over an undisclosed location in Southwest Asia on May 23, 2017. During the mission, they dropped two leaflet bombs, conducted aerial refueling and provided close air support for troops on the ground. Unit - 23rd Expeditionary Bomb Squadron.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. John Raven

1050.description:
Aerial refueling is a key component in keeping U.S. and coalition aircraft over the battlespace and in the fight. No other air force in the world does it with more precision and regularity than the U.S. Air Force. Film clips show KC-135 Stratotankers from the 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron out of Al Udeid Air Base, Qatar - 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by MSgt Andrew Moseley and TSgt. Micah Theurich

1051.description:
The Battle Of Midway was a major sea battle during WWII between Japan and the United States on June 4-6, 1942. The battle was a decisive win for the U.S. Navy and inflicted devastating damage on the Japanese fleet that proved irreparable. Military historian John Keegan called it "the most stunning and decisive blow in the history of naval warfare."

Film Credits: Robert Gensic

1052.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcons with the 180th Fighter Wing, Ohio Air National Guard provides air combat capabilities in Aerospace Control Alert. F-16s launch against aircraft violating U.S. airspace and they are intercepted. Footage shows temporary duty assignment (TDY) at MacDill Air Force Base. FL. Plus, footage over the Alpena Airspace Complex, Michigan, and Buckeye Airspace, Ohio... both are supersonic, chaff/flare capable with full radar ground control intercept, or GCI and Link-16 capable.

Film Credits: MSgt George Wolfe, TSgt Amber Williams

1053.description:
B-1B bomber crew members conduct flight operations at Dyess Air Force Base, TX on May 11, 2017. The B-1B Lancer is nicknamed BONE from B-One.

Film Credits: A1C Draeke Layman

1054.description:
Aircraft from the 23d Wing conducted a surge exercise May 22, 2017, at Moody Air Force Base, GA. The exercise was conducted in order to demonstrate the ability to rapidly deploy combat ready forces across the globe. The 23d Wing maintains and operates A-10C Thunderbolt IIs, HH-60G Pave Hawks, and HC-130J Combat King II aircraft for precision attack, personnel recovery, and combat support worldwide. Elephant Walk is a USAF term for the taxiing of military aircraft right before takeoff, when they are in close formation. The term "elephant walk" dates to World War II when large fleets of allied bombers would conduct attack missions containing hundreds of aircraft to takeoff in single file in nose-to-tail formations that observers said looked like elephants walking to the next watering hole. 

Film Credits: TSgt Timothy Gallagher

1055.description:
U.S. Air Force C-130J Super Hercules aircraft conduct training operations in Israel during exercise Juniper Falcon 2017 on May 14-15, 2017. USAF Unit - 37th Airlift Squadron based out of Ramstein Air Base, Germany.

Film Credits: SSgt Esteban Esquivel

1056.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15E Strike Fighters and Israeli F-15I Ra'am fighter jets work together during exercise Juniper Falcon May 7-8, 2017 at Uvda Air Base, Israel. U.S. Unit - 494th Fighter Squadron. Israeli Unit - 69th Squadron.

Film Credits: SSgt Esteban Esquivel

1057.description:
U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptor flies in formation with a WWII era P-51 Mustang and an A-10 Thunderbolt II. Plus, the F-22 Raptor Demonstration Team performs - both clips filmed during the Wings Over Wayne Air Show 2017 at Seymour Johnson Air Force Base, NC on May 21, 2017.

Film Credits: SSgt Patrick Cole

1058.description:
U.S. Navy aircraft carrier USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76) conducts flight operations en route to The Sea Of Japan on May 21, 2017. The USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70) is already in waters off North Korea, so the Ronald Reagan would make two carrier strike groups in the area when it completes the trip. Info: http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-4525562/USS-Ronald-Reagan-moves-Korean-Peninsula.html

Film Credits: MC3 Jamaal Liddell

1059.description:
U.S. Navy amphibious assault ship USS Bataan (LHD-5) conducts a replenishment-at-sea (RAS) alongside fleet replenishment oiler USNS Laramie (T-AO-203) on May 13, 2017 in the U.S. 5th Fleet Area of Responsibility (AOR). 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialists 3rd Class Kenneth Rodgers and Raymond Minami - Released

1060.description:
The Strong Europe Tank Challenge 2017 (competition) is over (May 7-12, 2017) and the team from Austria won first place. Here you can see footage of all 6 nations who participated. The order in the video is from 1st place to 3rd place, and then in alphabetical order for the final three participating nations. All nations scores where tightly grouped and only a few points separated them in the final tally. The nations that participated: Austria, France, Germany, Poland, Ukraine and the United States. Participating units were tested on offensive and defensive operations as well as tasks including vehicle identification, battle damage assessment and precision maneuvers. The exercise was held at Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany. A comprehensive look at the competition is best explained in this blog post: http://below-the-turret-ring.blogspot.ca/2017/05/austria-wons-strong-europe-tank.html

Film Credits: Christoph Koppers, SGT Austin Majors, Matthew Oldham, Sarah Tate

1061.description:
U.S. M1A2 Tanks and German Marder Infantry Fighting Vehicles practice defensive and counter-attack maneuvers during exercise Panzer Thrust at Bergen-Hohne Training Area in Germany on May 17, 2017. U.S. Unit - B Company, Ist Battalion, 68th Armor Regiment. German Unit - 401st Mechanized Infantry Battalion.

Film Credits: SGT Austin Majors

1062.description:
Marine Fighter Attack Squadron VMFA-314 completes loading ordnance during Integrated Training Exercise (ITX) 3-17 at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms, CA on May 13, 2017. ITX is a combined-arms training exercise enabling Marines to operate as an aviation combat element integrated with ground and logistics combat elements as a Marine air-ground task force.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Mark A. Lowe - Released

1063.description:
U.S. Marine Corps MV-22B Osprey crews conduct a gunnery exercise during Integrated Training Exercise (ITX) 3-17 at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms, CA on May 10, 2017. ITX is a combined-arms training exercise enabling Marines to operate as an aviation combat element integrated with ground and logistics combat elements as a Marine air-ground task force. Unit - Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron (VMM) 363, 3rd Marine Aircraft Wing.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Mark A. Lowe - Released

1064.description:
U.S. Marines conduct bilateral small arms training with French Commandos Marine, swapping and firing weapons aboard the French ship BPC Mistral on May 8-9, 2017. The Marines have joined the amphibious forces of Japan, France, and the United Kingdom to execute Jeanne D’ Arc, an annual French led exercise aimed to strengthen strategic partnerships and exercising freedom of navigation operations across the Indo-Asia-Pacific region.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. David A. Diggs

1065.description:
Austria won the Strong Europe Tank Challenge 2017 with the Leopard 2A4. The competition was held at Grafenwoehr, Germany, May 7-12, 2017. Platoons from six NATO and partner nations participated. The participants: Austria, France, Germany, Poland, Ukraine and the United States. More info: http://below-the-turret-ring.blogspot.ca/2017/05/austria-wons-strong-europe-tank.html

Film Credits: Matthew Oldham

1066.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15 Strike Eagle crews members prepare for the monthly Razor Talon exercise at Seymour Johnson Air Force Base in North Carolina. These airmen are from the 336th Fighter Squadron, nicknamed - "Rocketeers" - Yellow Fin Flash. Filmed May 2017.

Film Credits:  Amn Shawna Keyes

1067.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers with 101st Airborne Division (Air Assault) practice marksmanship with rifles, crew-served weapons and shotguns on May 2, 2017 at Range 11 in Djibouti, Africa. Unit - 2nd Platoon, Bravo Company, 1-327 Infantry, 1st Brigade Combat Team assigned to Combined Joint Task Force-Horn of Africa's (CJTF-HOA) East African Response Force (EARF). The purpose of the East African Response Force is to rapidly provide forces to protect American interests in the area should any threats arise.

Film Credits: US Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. Nicholas A. Priest

1068.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers with Battle Group Poland conduct live-fire demolition training on May 11, 2017 at Bemowo Piskie Training Area, Poland, to reinforce their ability to use demolition in a safe and effective manner on the battlefield. Each explosion taught the soldiers different charges they can use for destroying caches, demolishing a bridge, creating craters and obstacles with explosives.

Film Credits: Video clips courtesy of Sgt. Ethan Pratt, Battle Group Poland's Engineering Squadron

1069.description:
Footage of Exercise Red Flag 17-2, with fighter jet crew members on duty 24/7 at Nellis Air Force Base. Red Flag 17-2 was underway from February 27 to March 10, 2017. Here are some highlights... Red Flag is the U.S. Air Force's premier air-to-air combat training exercise. Participants often include both United States and allied nations' combat air forces. The exercise provides aircrews the experience of multiple, intensive air combat sorties in the safety of a training environment.

Film Credits: MSgt Wolfram M. Stumpf, SSgt Benjamin Kimball

1070.description:
Team Austria loads and fires its tanks during the Strong Europe Tank Challenge (SETC) at Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany, May 9, 2017. The SETC is co-hosted by U.S. Army Europe and the German Army, May 7-12, 2017. The competition is designed to project a dynamic presence, foster military partnership, promote interoperability, and provides an environment for sharing tactics, techniques and procedures. Platoons from six NATO and partner nations are in the competition.

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Visual Information Specialist Christoph Koppers

1071.description:
German Army (Bundeswehr) crews in Leopard 2A6 tanks perform during the Strong Europe Tank Challenge (SETC) at Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany, May 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Visual Information Specialist Gertrud Zach

1072.description:
U.S. Marines execute an exercise aboard CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters as part of pre-deployment training at Camp Lejeune, NC, April 2017.
  
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Serine Farahi - Released

1073.description:
Live-Fire Exercise aboard USS America (LHA-6), in reaction to a hostile small boat advance, destroying it with Mk-38 Mod 2 chain-gun and .50 caliber machine gun. The USS Pearl Harbor (LSD-52) and the amphibious transport dock ship USS San Diego (LPD-22) steam in formation during the exercise, designed to test ship defense capabilities against a small fast-boat attack. More than 1800 sailors and 2600 Marines assigned to the America Amphibious Ready Group (ARG) and 15th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU) are currently conducting a Composite Unit Training Exercise (COMPTUEX) off the coast of southern California in preparation for deployment. Filmed on April 11, 2017.
  
Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Christopher Marshall - Released

1074.description:
Aerial view of the aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) underway in the Pacific Ocean on March 30, 2017. Plus, firing 2 Rolling Airframe Missiles during a training exercise on April 9, 2017. The Roosevelt is underway conducting a Group Sail Training Unit Exercise (GRUSL) with the Carrier Strike Group.
  
Film Credits: CPO Jennifer Roy

1075.description:
German Army Leopard 2A6 Tanks run over some cars during the Strong Europe Tank Challenge (SETC) at Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany on May 8, 2017. Platoons from six NATO and partner nations are scheduled to take part in the challenge from May 7-12, 2017. The participants are: Austria, France, Germany, Poland, Ukraine and the United States.
  
Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Visual Information Specialist Gertrud Zach

1076.description:
U.S. Marine Corps Snipers shoot targets from an MH-60 Seahawk helicopter on March 30, 2017.
  
Film Credits: Sgt Jack Gnosca

1077.description:
A U.S. Navy E-2C Hawkeye attached to Carrier Airborne Early Warning Squadron 117 taking off from Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson, Alaska, for exercise Northern Edge 2017, May 8, 2017.
  
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Andy Martinez

1078.description:
U.S. Army Paratroopers from the 82nd Airborne Division fire M-777 Howitzers near Mosul, Iraq on April 4, 2017.
  
Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Staff Sgt. Jason Hull

1079.description:
This is historical footage of a test drop of an unarmed AGM-86B air-launched cruise missile by a B-52H Stratofortress over the Utah Test and Training Range on September 22, 2014. Twenty nuclear tipped AGM-86B missiles can be deployed by one B-52H. The weapon has a range of 1000 miles, so no B-52 aircraft has to enter enemy territory. The ending footage is Castle Bravo nuclear test. 
Corresponding Air Force fact sheet: http://www.af.mil/About-Us/Fact-Sheets/Display/Article/104612/agm-86bcd-missiles/  
Film Credits: TSgt Roidan Carlson

1080.description:
U.S. Army Military Intelligence Battalion helicopter flyover of the Iron Triangle in the Fort Irwin National Training Center, CA on May 2, 2017.

Film Credits: CPT Albert Jernegan

1081.description:
A simulated special operating forces raid aboard C-130 Hercules and MV-22 Osprey aircraft during Weapons and Tactics Instructor course (WTI) 2-17 near Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range, CA on April 29, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. AaronJames B. Vinculado

1082.description:
Ukrainian Army Soldiers train to fire RPG-7 and RPG-22 rocket-propelled grenades under guidance of U.S. Army instructors from the 45th Infantry Brigade Combat Team at Yavoriv Combat Training Center, Ukraine on May 4, 2017. The Ukrainian Army, 1st Airmobile Battalion, 79th Air Assault Brigade is paired with soldiers from several nations dedicated to improving professionalism within the Ukrainian military.

Film Credits: SGT Anthony Jones

1083.description:
Two U.S. Air Force F-35A Lightning II fighter jets practice aerial refueling on the first-time flight from RAF Lakenheath to Graf Ignatievo Air Base in Bulgaria. Filmed on April 28, 2017. 

Film Credits: NATO TV

1084.description:
Approximately 250 Airmen and twelve F-16 Fighting Falcons with the Colorado Air National Guard deploy from Colorado Air National Guard Base, Buckley Air Force Base, Colorado on May 1, 2017, headed to Kadena Air Base, Japan as part of U.S. Pacific Command - Theater Security Package. COANG 120th Fighter Squadron will become the 120th Expeditionary Fighter Squadron while deployed. The U.S. Air Force routinely deploys fighter aircraft to the region to provide U.S. Pacific Command and Pacific Air Forces with Theater Security Packages, which help maintain a deterrent against threats to regional security and stability.

Film Credits: SSgt Benjamin Kimball

1085.description:
Footage of F-15C fighter jets on the flight-line, plus takeoffs of F-22 Raptors, F-35 Strike Fighters, F-16 Fighting Falcons, and F/A-18 Hornets - from Exercise Northern Edge 2017 at Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson, AK on May 2-3, 2017. 

Film Credits: SrA Joshua DeGuzman, LCpl Andy Martinez

1086.description:
The KRAKEN disorientation device is an advanced motion system with multiple capabilities, operated by the Naval Medical Research Unit Dayton at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base, OH. It replicates the extreme motions of aircraft, sea vessels, and land vehicles. More info on The Kraken here: http://www.etcaircrewtraining.com/spatial-disorientation-training-system-kraken/

Film Credits: Matthew Clouse and John Harrington

1087.description:
U.S. Military jump over Okinawa, Japan, May 1, 2017.

Film Credits: A1C Jerome Brackins Jr

1088.description:
Aircraft takeoffs during exercise Northern-Edge-2017 at Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson, Alaska on May 1, 2017. Northern Edge 2017 is the U.S. Air Force premier joint training exercise in Alaska designed to practice operations, techniques and procedures as well as enhance interoperability among the services.

Film Credits: SrA Joshua DeGuzman

1089.description:
U.S. Air Force and Army special operators conduct training jumps from an MC-130J Commando II aircraft over Karlsborg Air Base in Sweden on April 13, 2017. Unit - Special Operations Command Europe (SOCEUR). 

Film Credits: SSG Henry Gundacker

1090.description:
U.S. Marine Corps MV-22 Ospreys land in Australia, April 28, 2017 after completing their first Trans-Pacific Flight in history from Hawaii to Royal Australian Air Force Base in Darwin. Osprey Unit - Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 268.

Film Credits: Sgt Emmanuel Ramos

1091.description:
U.S. Marines conduct the final exercise (FINEX-2) at Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range, California on April 27, 2017. The FINEX exercise is designed to execute a simulated special operating forces raid while simultaneously supporting regimental combat team objectives and focusing on all six functions of Marine Aviation supplied by Weapons and Tactics Instructor course (WTI) at Yuma, AZ.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. AaronJames B. Vinculado

1092.description:
U.S. Air Force aircraft Combat Search and Rescue (CSAR) training on "Texas Lake" dry lake bed at the Nevada Test and Training Range, April 27, 2017.

Film Credits: A1C Julian Kemper, A1C Megan Qualls

1093.description:
U. S. T-38 Talon Trainers fly with F-35 and F-15 fighter jets during exercise Atlantic Trident 17 at Joint Base Langley-Eustis, Virginia. Filmed April 2017.

Film Credits: SrA Nicolas Myers

1094.description:
The aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70) takes on ordnance during a vertical replenishment-at-sea (VERTREP), as it makes its way to seas near North Korea. The VERTREP was conducted by the “Black Knights” of Helicopter Sea Combat Squadron (HSC) 4 and the Military Sealift Command dry cargo and ammunition ship USNS Richard E. Byrd (T-AKE 4) in the Philippine Sea on April 24, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Z.A. Landers - Released

1095.description:
The aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70) leads the Japan Maritime Self-Defense Force destroyers JS Ashigara (DDG-178) and JS Samidare (DD-106), the guided-missile destroyers USS Michael Murphy (DDG-112) and USS Wayne E. Meyer (DDG-108), and the guided-missile cruiser USS Lake Champlain (CG-57), during a transit of the Philippine Sea on April 27, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Matt Brown - Released

1096.description:
U.S. Air Force dropped a MOAB (Massive Ordnance Air Blast) bomb, nicknamed "Mother of all Bombs", on ISIS insurgents in Afghanistan on April 13, 2017. Footage of strike (FLIR), and ground video of aftermath destruction.

Film Credits: United States Department of Defense, OF-4 Una Sighvatsdottir

1097.description:
Slow motion footage of the U.S. Air Force Thunderbirds demonstration team at the 2017 Gulf Coast Salute (Open House and Air Show) on Tyndall Air Force Base in Florida, April 22, 2017.

Film Credits: SrA Roswell Sartwell

1098.description:
U.S. Marine Corps EA-6B Prowlers assigned to Marine Tactical Electronic Warfare Squadron (VMAQ-3), conduct pre-flight inspections prior to departing Marine Corps Air Station Cherry Point, NC on March 24, 2017. VMAQ-3 deployed to engage in future joint operations with foreign military in the middle east.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Zachary W. Montgomery

1099.description:
Paratroopers from the 3rd Brigade Combat Team, 82nd Airborne Division drive and maneuver with their new equipment - the DAGOR and MRZR-D are the newest form of transportation for speed, versatility and load. Filmed at Fort Bragg on April 23, 2017.

Film Credits: SGT Anthony Hewitt

1100.description:
U.S. Marine Corps attack helicopters with Marine Light Attack Helicopter Squadron 267 execute a mission rehearsal exercise at Marine Corps Air Station Futenma, Okinawa, Japan on April 25, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps video by MCIPAC Combat Camera Lance Cpl. Garett Burns

1101.description:
U.S. Air Force F-35A Joint Strike Fighters refuel en-route to RAF Lakenheath, England on April 25, 2017. The Lightning II aircraft  will be forward deployed to Estonia to work with NATO's current infrastructure and strengthen interoperability with allies. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Senior Airman Christine Groening

1102.description:
Aerial view of the aircraft carrier USS George Washington (CVN-73) in the Atlantic Ocean. George Washington, home-ported in Norfolk, is underway conducting carrier qualifications in the Atlantic Ocean prior to a mid-life Refueling and Complex Overhaul (RCOH), which began in January 2017 and is expected to take 4-5 years. Filmed December 13, 2016.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Joshua David DuFrane

1103.description:
U.S. Marine and Japan Ground Self-Defense Force scout snipers shoot a range during exercise Forest Light at Somagahara, Japan on March 10, 2017. The Marines are with Company G, 2nd Battalion, 3rd Marine Regiment, 3rd Marine Division, III Marine Expeditionary Force.  

Film Credits: Sgt Isaac Ibarra

1104.description:
A U.S. Air Force crew brings a KC-135 Stratotanker in for a landing at night at an undisclosed location. Filmed on November 28, 2013 as part of the 22nd Air Refueling Wing.  

Film Credits: SrA Joshua Crawley

1105.description:
B-2 Spirit Bomber Aircraft from Whiteman Air Force Base in MO are highlighted in this video - taxi, takeoff, and aerial refueling.

Film Credits: A1C Kristin Cerri, SrA Emili Koonce, SSgt Erin Mills

1106.description:
U.S. Air Force Special Tactics Airmen from the 123rd Special Tactics Squadron, Kentucky Air National Guard, conduct a free-fall jump from a C-130 Hercules over Louisville, KY on April 21, 2017.

Film Credits: MSgt Philip Speck

1107.description:
Cockpit view of a C-17 Globemaster III crew from Joint Base Charleston, SC as they practice touch-and-go procedures and conduct aerial refueling. Filmed on March 29, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by SSgt Laura Beckley

1108.description:
Aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN 71) conducts flight operations, April 19, 2017.

Film Credits: CPO Jennifer Roy

1109.description:
U.S. Air Force (8th Fighter Wing) aircraft on the flight line and takeoff during exercise Max Thunder-17 at Kunsan Air Base South Korea. Filmed on April 20, 2017.

Film Credits: SSgt Joshua Rosales

1110.description:
U.S. Air Force Air Traffic Controllers on the job in the Tower at Joint Base Langley-Eustis, VA on April 19, 2017.

Film Credits: SrA Megan Reed

1111.description:
U.S. Marines conduct annual table three marksmanship qualification at Hicacal Range Facility - U.S. Naval Station Guantanamo Bay, Cuba on April 10, 2017. Unit - 3rd Battalion, 2nd Marine Regiment, 2d Marine Division (2d MARDIV) - 3/2 Conus-Based Alert Force.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Jaycee Martell

1112.description:
The Seawolf-class fast-attack submarine USS Jimmy Carter (SSN 23) transits the Hood Canal as the boat returns home to Naval Base Kitsap-Bangor. Jimmy Carter is the last and most advanced of the Seawolf-class attack submarines, which are all homeported at Naval Base Kitsap. Filmed on April, 14, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Lt. Cmdr. Michael Smith - Released

1113.description:
Cockpit view of an F-15E Strike Eagle fighter jet crew training for deployment over Mountain Home Air Force Base, Idaho on November 2, 2016.

Film Credits: SrA Citiyah Burton

1114.description:
F-16 fighter jets from the 162nd Wing, Tucson, AZ participate in Sentry Aloha, an exercise with over 400 airmen and 60 aircraft. Sentry Aloha exercises are held to provide the Air National Guard, U.S. Air Force and DoD counterparts a multi-faceted, joint venue, with supporting infrastructure and personnel that incorporates current, realistic, integrated training to equip warfighters with the necessary skills to fly, fight and win. Filmed on April 11, 2017.

Film Credits: MSgt Charles Givens

1115.description:
WWII era B-25 Mitchell Bombers land at Wright-Patterson AFB in Ohio, the home of the National Museum of the U.S. Air Force. The aircraft were at the museum as part of the 75th anniversary of the Doolittle Tokyo Raid. Filmed on April 17, 2017.

Film Credits: A1C Johnathon Wines

1116.description:
Two U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptors and four Belgian Air Component F-16 Fighting Falcons receive fuel over Iraq in support of Operation Inherent Resolve on April 11, 2017. Refueling aircraft - KC-135 Stratotanker from the 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron.

Film Credits: SrA Joshua Hoskins

1117.description:
F-35A Lightning II Joint Strike Fighters from the 34th Fighter Squadron at Hill Air Force Base, Utah, land at Royal Air Force Lakenheath, England on April 15, 2017. The arrival marks the first F-35A Lightning II training deployment to the U.S. European Command area of responsibility or any overseas location as a flying training deployment.

Film Credits: SSgt Armando Aparicio, SrA Gabriela Keiser, SrA Elizabeth Taranto

1118.description:
Pre-Commissioning Unit Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78) arrives at Naval Station Norfolk after completing builder’s sea trials. The first-of-class ship and the U.S. Navy's first new aircraft carrier design in 40 years spent several days conducting builder’s sea trials, a comprehensive test of many of the ship’s key systems and technologies. Filmed on April 14, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Kristopher Ruiz

1119.description:
The U.S. Navy and Marines team up in an amphibious operation from ship to shore aboard the USS San Diego (LPD-22), including launching AAVs, LCAC transport, and ground pounding... by the U.S. Marines of course. Filmed April 7-14, 2017.

Film Credits: Cpl Timothy Valero

1120.description:
An RQ-21A Blackjack drone is launched from the flight deck of the USS San Diego (LPD-22) on April 12, 2017. The RQ-21A Blackjack is an intelligence, surveillance, reconnaissance unmanned aircraft capable of being launched and recovered from flight decks on U.S. Navy ships.

Film Credits: Cpl Timothy Valero

1121.description:
Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 161 conducts operations from the flight deck aboard the amphibious transport dock ship USS San Diego (LPD-22) in the Pacific Ocean. Filmed during PHIBRON-MEU Integration on April 9, 2017. PMINT is at-sea training giving the 15th MEU an opportunity to work closely with their Navy counterparts.

Film Credits: Cpl Timothy Valero

1122.description:
CH-47F Chinook Crew Chiefs Fire M-240H machine guns during a gunnery exercise at the Orchard Combat Training Center near Boise, Idaho on April 3, 2017. Units - Charlie Co., 1-140th Aviation Regt, and Bravo Co., 1-168th General Support Aviation Brigade, Washington Army National Guard.

Film Credits: SGT Matthew Sissel

1123.description:
Japanese Ground Self-Defense Force service members fast rope from a MV-22 Osprey and U.S. Marines fast rope off of a Japanese CH-46 Sea Knight Chinook during Forest Light, at Somagahara, Japan, March 9, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Isaac Ibarra

1124.description:
Aircraft Carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN 71) conducts flight operations on April 11, 2017. Theodore Roosevelt is underway conducting a tailored ship's training availability off the coast of Southern California to be ready.

Film Credits:  CPO Jennifer Roy

1125.description:
The U.S. Air Force today (April 13, 2017) dropped a GBU-43/B Massive Ordnance Air Blast bomb (MOAB), also called the the Mother Of All Bombs, on a tunnel system used by ISIS and the Taliban in eastern Afghanistan. This footage is of a test in 2003, but the devastation can be called the same on the ground at the site it was dropped in AF. The blast radius is about a mile wide... very close to a small nuclear device.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Courtesy Video

1126.description:
U.S. Marines conduct cold weather training at Sekiyama, Japan, during exercise Forest Light, March 13-15, 2017. Forest Light is a bi-lateral training event conducted by the Japan Ground Self-Defense Force and deployed U.S. Marines.  Unit - Company G, 2nd Battalion, 3rd Marine Regiment, 3rd Marine Division, III Marine Expeditionary Force.

Film Credits: Sgt Isaac Ibarra

1127.description:
U.S. Marine Corps CH-53E Super Stallion is the largest helicopter in the U.S. Military, capable of carrying 37 troops or lifting 18 tons. Footage shows CH-53Es conducting battle drills and tactics during Weapons and Tactics Instructor course (WTI) 2-17 near Yuma, AZ on April 7-8, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. AaronJames B. Vinculado, Cpl. Justin M. Smith, Lance Cpl. Benjamin B. Drake

1128.description:
U.S. Marine Corps Super Huey helicopter gunships (a.k.a. UH-1Y Venom) fire rockets and machine guns down on a mock village (Yodaville) near Yuma, AZ during a close air support (CAS) training exercise. Day and night footage filmed during Weapons and Tactics Instructor Course (WTI) 2-17 on April 7, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Vdeo by Sgt. Daniel D. Kujanpaa, Cpl. Justin M. Smith

1129.description:
U.S. Marines call for AH-1W SuperCobra and AH-1Z Viper helicopters  in urban close air support (UCAS) exercises during Weapons and Tactics Instructor course (WTI) 2-17 at Yodaville, AZ on April 5-6, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Justin M. Smith, Cpl. AaronJames B. Vinculado

1130.description:
Royal Dutch Marines conduct a live-fire exercise in Fast Raiding Interception Special Forces Craft (FRISC) from Camp Lejeune, NC on March 9, 2017. The Royal Dutch Marines with 1st Troop, 32nd Raiding Squadron worked together with U.S. Marines as part of annual bilateral training to strengthen relations and increase interoperability.

Film Credits: U.S. Marines Video by Lance Cpl. David Luckey

1131.description:
Helicopter view of the newest U.S. aircraft carrier, PCU Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78)  as it gets underway on it's own power for the first time and heads out for initial sea trials. Filmed on April 8, 2017. The Ford is currently designated pre-commissioning unit (PCU), and is expected to be commissioned sometime in 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Ridge Leoni - Released

1132.description:
America's Newest Supercarrier, PCU Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78) departs Huntington Ingalls Industries Newport News Shipbuilding for builder’s sea trials on April 8, 2017. The Ford is currently designated a pre-commissioning unit (PCU), expected to be commissioned in 2017.

Film Credits: PO2 Ryan Litzenberger

1133.description:
The U.S. and ROK Marines conduct a joint live-fire exercise with Abrams Tanks and Assault Amphibious Vehicles near Pohang, South Korea on April 7, 2017.

Film Credits: SSgt Braden Anderson

1134.description:
U.S. Marines shoot on an aerial gun range aboard UH-1Y Venom helicopter gunships during Weapons and Tactics Instructor (WTI) course 2-17 at Chocolate Mountain, Gunnery Range. The Gunships land and rearm and refuel before going back into the fight. Filmed on April 5, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Benjamin B. Drake, Cpl. AaronJames B. VInculado

1135.description:
View from the conning tower of a U.S. Navy fast-attack submarine, the nuclear powered USS Texas (SSN-775) underway in the Pacific Ocean on March 15, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Austin Rooney, Jimmy Shea, Jonathan Snyder - Released

1136.description:
A fire drill aboard the fast-attack nuclear submarine USS Texas (SSN-775) while underway in the Pacific Ocean on March 15, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Austin Rooney, Jimmy Shea, Jonathan Snyder - Released

1137.description:
Take a rare look inside the Auxiliary Machinery Room of a U.S. Navy fast-attack nuclear submarine, USS Texas (SSN-775), as crew members perform routine maintenance while underway in the Pacific Ocean. Filmed on March 15, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Austin Rooney, Jimmy Shea, Jonathan Snyder - Released

1138.description:
The U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcon Makos go to Greece and participate in INIOHOS-17, a Hellenic air force-led exercise with Air Forces from Greece, Israel, and Italy at Andravida AB, Greece from March 27 - April 6, 2017. Unit - 93rd Fighter Squadron, 482nd Fighter Wing.

Film Credits: TSgt Jeremy Roman

1139.description:
Flight line footage of Italian Air Force AMX Fighter-Bomber aircraft and air-crews at Hellenic (Greece) air exercise INIOHOS-17, Andravida Air Base, Greece from March 27 - April 6, 2017. Air Forces from Greece, Israel, Italy, and the U.S. are participating in this exercise. Unit - 51st Wing, Istrana Air Base, Italy. 

Film Credits: TSgt Jeremy Roman

1140.description:
U.S. Marines refuel AH-1Z Viper helicopters in a forward arming refueling point (FARP) exercise during Weapons and Tactics Instructor (WTI) course 2-17 at Yuma, AZ on April 3, 2017. The FARP exercise is aimed at refueling and rearming aircraft quickly so the attack helicopters can get back in the fight ASAP. Unit - Marine Wing Support Squadron (MWSS).   

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by LCpl. Benjamin B. Drake

1141.description:
HH-60 Pave Hawk loaded into a C-17 Globemaster III transport jet at Nellis Air Force Base on March 27, 2017.  

Film Credits: A1C Christina Ensley and A1C Mychal Fox

1142.description:
U.S. Air Force KC-10 Extender refuels U.S. Marine Corps AV-8B Harriers, French Air Force Dassault Rafales, and Royal Australian Air Force F/A-18 Hornets over Iraq on Mar 22, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by SrA Joshua A. Hoskins

1143.description:
U.S. Army advisors from 45th Infantry Brigade Combat Team monitor the firing of a Ukrainian BM-21 Grad, 122 mm, multiple rocket launcher during a combined-arms battalion live-fire exercise held at the Yavoriv Combat Training Center in Ukraine on March 29, 2017. The U.S. advisors are deployed in support of Joint Multinational Training Group-Ukraine, a mission geared towards training and professionalizing the Ukrainian army and developing Ukrainian combat training center staff. 

Film Credits: 1LT Kayla Christopher

1144.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a frag assault course, a multipurpose small arms range, weapons familiarization range, and a multipurpose rocket range - 40mm high-explosive grenade launcher range, during Talon Exercise (TALONEX) 2-17 at U.S. Army Yuma Proving Grounds, Yuma, AZ from March 21-24, 2017 - day & night. The purpose of TALONEX is for ground combat units to conduct integrated training in support of the Weapons and Tactics Instructor Course (WTI) 2-17 hosted by Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1).

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Dani A. Zunun

1145.description:
U.S. Air Force Instructor Pilots from the 560th Flying Training Squadron at Joint Base San Antonio-Randolph join two Vietnam era prisoner of war survivors for a Freedom Flight aboard T-38 Talons for the 44th Freedom Flyer Reunion over JBSA-Randolph, Texas, March 30, 2017. The Freedom Flyer Reunion is an annual celebration recognizing the service of Air Force Prisoners of War during the Vietnam War, their honorable return, and their connection with the 12th Flying Training Wing during Operation Homecoming. Operation Homecoming was the return of 591 American prisoners of war (POWs) held by North Vietnam following the Paris Peace Accords that ended U.S. involvement in the Vietnam War.

Film Credits: US Air Force Video by SrA Daniel Fernandez

1146.description:
U.S. Army AH-64D Apache Longbow Helicopters assigned to the 12th Combat Aviation Brigade (12th CAB) conduct a gunnery exercise at 7th Army Training Command - Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany on March 29, 2017. The 12th CAB prepares for full-spectrum combat aviation operations in support of the United States Army, the United States Army-Europe and other designated combined joint task force commands. 

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Visual Information Specialist Gertrud Zach

1147.description:
F-16C Fighting Falcons from the 93rd Fighter Squadron, 482nd Fighter Wing participated in Exercise INIOHOS-17 at Andravida Air Base, Greece from March 27 - April 6, 2017. 

Film Credits: TSgt Jeremy Roman

1148.description:
Two Afghan A-29 Super Tucanos fly over Afghanistan during a training mission on March 22, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by TSgt Jose A. Rodriguez Jr

1149.description:
Mortarmen from the 45th Infantry Brigade Combat Team, Oklahoma Army National Guard supervise Ukrainian mortarmen from 1st Battalion, 28th Mechanized Infantry Brigade during a combined-arms battalion live-fire exercise held at the Yavoriv Combat Training Center, Ukraine on March 29, 2017. The Oklahoma Guardsmen are deployed in support of Joint Multinational Training Group-Ukraine, a mission geared towards training and professionalizing the Ukrainian army.

Film Credits: 1LT Kayla Christopher

1150.description:
U.S. Marines of Marine Rotational Force Europe 17.1 (MRF-E) participated in Exercise Joint Viking, in the Arctic Circle of Norway, March 9-14, 2017. The Marines were joined by their British, Norwegian and Dutch allies. 

Film Credits: Sgt Patricia Claypool-Morris

1151.description:
U.S. Marines with Marine Aircraft Group 29 conducts an integrated air mission commander check aboard CH-53E Super Stallions and MV-22B Ospreys at Marine Corps Air Station New River, NC on March 23, 2017. An air mission commander check is designed to increase squadron’s proficiency with its aircraft and check crew proficiency. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Daphne D. Rodriguez, MCIEAST Combat Camera - Released

1152.description:
A U.S. Air Force KC-10 Extender from the 908th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron delivers fuel to U.S. Marine Corps EA-6B Prowlers, French Air Force Dassault Rafales, a U.S. Air Force B-52 Stratofortress and F-15E Strike Eagles in support of Operation Inherent Resolve over Iraq on March 20, 2017.  

Film Credits: SrA Joshua Hoskins

1153.description:
U.S. Marines with Bravo Battery, 1st Battalion, 12th Marine Regiment set-up and shoot M-777 Howitzers on a fire missions at Pohakuloa Training Area in Hawaii. Filmed on March 23, 2017 during Exercise Spartan Fury.  

Film Credits: LCpl Brendan Custer

1154.description:
Compiled footage of U.S. Marine Corps F/A-18C and F/A-18D Hornet fighter jets on the flight line, in-flight refueling, and in-flight cockpit camera views. 

Film Credits: LCpl Jake McClung, Sgt Isaac Lamberth, Lance Cpl. Donato Maffin, Sgt Anthony Rayis, Major Erik Sprague, Sgt Anthony Rayis, Sgt Anthony Rayis

1155.description:
Pilots, Support Staff and F-16 Fighting Falcons of the 149th Fighter Wing (Lone Star Gunfighters), conduct daily flight operations at Joint Base San Antonio-Lackland, TX. Filmed on March 10, 2017.

Film Credits: Sean Schroeder

1156.description:
Royal Dutch Marines, the Netherlands Korps Mariniers, conduct fast rope insertion training from a U.S. Marine Corps CH-53 helicopter at Camp Lejeune, NC on March 09, 2017. The Royal Dutch Marines worked together with U.S. Marines as part of an annual bilateral training exercise to strengthen relations and increase interoperability.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl Jaycee M. Martell

1157.description:
The U.S. Navy Railgun is being developed at Naval Surface Warfare Center Dahlgren Division, VA and is moving forward towards deployment aboard Zumwalt-Class destroyers. The Railgun uses electro-magnetic pulses, instead of gunpowder, to fire a projectile at incredible speeds. The speed at which these rounds reach make it unnecessary to have high-explosive warheads. The kinetic energy of the round is enough to make them deadly on impact. 

Film Credits: Naval Surface Warfare Center Dahlgren Division - Released

1158.description:
U.S. Marines and Republic of Korea Marines conduct amphibious actions at Pohang during Korea Marine Exercise Program 17-6 (KMEP) on March 16, 2017.

Film Credits: U. S. Marine Corps Video by MCIPAC Combat Camera Cpl. Jordan Walker

1159.description:
U.S. Marines with Special Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force - Southern Command (SPMAGTF-SC) conduct marksmanship training at Marine Corps Base Camp Lejeune, NC on March 16, 2017. The shooting range is part of pre-deployment training for an upcoming deployment to Central America and will prepare the Marines to train alongside partner nations. The M4 Carbine is the standard issue rifle for the U.S. Marine Corps. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Ian Leones

1160.description:
Although the U.S. Navy retired it's EA-6B Prowlers in the past, the Marine Corps is still flying this capable electronic warfare jet, as of 2017. The EA-6B has the ability to neutralize enemy air defenses that rely on early warning radar. It locks-on to radar and illuminates electronic footprints. The EA-6B detects, sorts, classifies, jams and destroys air defenses, leaving the enemy with two options - leave the radar on, or turn it off. Either way, enemy air defenses are reduced and made useless.

Film Credits:  Marine Corps Air Station Miramar, CWO2 Izzel Sanchez, SSgt Aaron Richardson, SrA Joshua Hoskins

1161.description:
Special Operations Forces jump from C-130 over N'Djamena, Chad on March 4, 2017.

Film Credits: A1C Johnathon Wines, SSgt Ashley Corkins

1162.description:
Royal Dutch Marines (Korps Mariniers) with 1st Troop, 32nd Raiding Squadron, conduct urban quick response training at Camp Davis, NC on March 14,2017. The Royal Dutch Marines worked together with U.S. Marines as part of an annual bilateral training exercise to strengthen relations and increase interoperability. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Melissa M. Lettieri

1163.description:
U.S. Marines with 2nd Assault Amphibian Battalion, 2nd Marine Division, conduct a live-fire exercise consisting of buddy-rush drills and 60mm mortars during Deployment for Training (DFT) at Fort Stewart, GA on March 11, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Williams Quinteros

1164.description:
U.S. Marines with 2nd Assault Amphibian Battalion, 2nd Marine Division conduct a live-fire grenade range during Deployment for Training (DFT) at Fort Stewart, GA on March 10, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Williams Quinteros

1165.description:
U.S. Marines Assault Amphibious Vehicles (AAVs) with 2nd Assault Amphibian Battalion, 2nd Marine Division conduct a river-crossing exercise as part of Deployment for Training (DFT) at Fort Stewart, GA on March 16, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Williams Quinteros

1166.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 169th Fighter Wing, South Carolina Air National Guard takeoff and land at Tyndall Air Force Base, Florida on March 16, 2017 as part of the Weapon Systems Evaluation Program (WSEP). The WSEP’s purpose is to evaluate a unit’s ability to effectively deliver munitions through all stages, from ammo build to weapons loading to the actual launching or dropping of the weapons from the aircraft.

Film Credits: U.S. Air National Guard Video by Master Sgt. Carl Clegg

1167.description:
U.S. Abrams M1A2 and Polish Leopard 2 tank crews train together in maneuvering and tactics at Karliki, Poland to improve interoperability and communications. Filmed on March 15, 2017. Units - U.S. 3rd Armored Brigade Combat Team, 4th Infantry Division. Polish 1st Tank Battalion, 10th Armored Cavalry Brigade.

Film Credits: Sgt. Austin Majors

1168.description:
The aircraft carrier USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN-69) conducts flight operations in the Atlantic Ocean with Greyhound logistics aircraft assigned to the Rawhides of Fleet Logistics Support Squadron (VRC-40) and F/A-18 Hornet strike fighters assigned to the Gladiators of Strike Fighter Squadron (VFA-106). Filmed on February 5, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Nathan T. Beard - Released

1169.description:
Weapons qualifications aboard the USS America (LHA-6). The Mark 38, Mod 2 30mm machine gun hits remote-controlled small boat targets on February 2, 2017. The test is called combat systems ship qualifications trials (CSSQT) and included upload/download, dud/misfire and watch-team training on both the Mark 38, Mod 2 30mm gun and the close-in weapon system (CIWS).
