Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Joshua Samoluk - Released

1170.description:
USAF Airmen from the 169th Fighter Wing, South Carolina Air National Guard load munitions on F-16 fighter jets during the Weapons Systems Evaluation Program (WSEP) at Tyndall Air Force Base, Florida on March 11, 2017. The WSEP’s purpose is to evaluate a unit’s ability to effectively deliver munitions through all stages, from ammo build to weapons loading to the actual launching or dropping of the weapons from the aircraft.

Film Credits: (U.S. Air National Guard Video by Master Sgt. Carl Clegg

1171.description:
Hill Air Force Base in Utah is going forward with the development and training of pilots and crew members for the F-35A Lightning II Joint Strike Fighter, even though many can't get past the fact that the USAF is proceeding with this aircraft. Filmed on January 14, 2017.

Film Credits: Joshua Carter

1172.description:
Live-Fire range in Estonia... U.S. Army M1A2 Tanks and Estonia Defense League Soldiers with Milan 2 anti-tank rockets work together. U.S. Soldiers from C Company, 1st Battalion, 68th Armor Regiment, 3rd Brigade Combat Team, 4th Infantry Division partnered with the Estonian Defense League to conduct a coordinated anti-tank range. Interview with First Lieutenant Zachary Lim, 2nd Platoon Leader, C Company, 1st Battalion, 68th Armor Regiment, 3rd Brigade Combat Team, 4th Infantry Division. Filmed on March 14, 2017.

Film Credits: SGT Joshua Joyner

1173.description:
NATO countries military. Filmed 2017.

Film Credits: NATO Channel, A1C Ericha Guyote

1174.description:
U.S. Army Paratroopers load onto C-130 Hercules and conduct day and night jumps over Wright-Patterson Air Force Base, to maintain proficiency, March 11, 2017.

Film Credits: A1C Johnathon Wines

1175.description:
U.S. Army Paladin M109A6 Howitzer crews are wrapping up 12 days of training in the desert on Dona Ana Range near Fort Bliss, Texas on March 12, 2017. The main task is to build and increase the speed and accuracy of the six firing platoons. The battalion is running 24 hours a day and "jumping" locations every day. In this exercise, the command posts were broken down into smaller nodes, creating smaller "footprints" that are lighter, faster and more agile, increasing survivability. Unit - 4th Battalion, 27th Field Artillery Regiment, 1st Armored Division.

Film Credits: Abigail Meyer

1176.description:
U.S. Marines with recon, ordnance, aviation, and infantry units conduct Realistic Urban Training (RUT) at Twentynine Palms, CA.  Units - 15th Marine Expeditionary Unit Maritime Raid Force, 15th Marine Expeditionary Unit Aviation Ordnance Division, 1st Battalion, 5th Marine Regiment, and Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 161 (Reinforced). Filmed March 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Timothy Valero, LCpl Jacob Pruitt, Sgt Paris Capers, LCpl Nathan McAllister

1177.description:
Footage of F/A-18F Super Hornets with Strike Fighter Squadron 213 (VFA-213) Fighting Blacklions while deployed aboard the aircraft carrier George H.W. Bush (CVN 77). VFA-213 is an aviation unit of the U.S. Navy attached to Carrier Wing Eight (CW-8) based at Naval Air Station Oceana, Virginia.

Film Credits: Lt. Micheal Reilly, Seaman Apprentice David Lee, PO3 Travis Litke, PO3 Preston Paglinawan, Seaman Connor A McDermott, PO3 Daniel Gaither, PO3 David Lee, U.S. Navy Video Released

1178.description:
"Maximum 10 minutes and we’re ready to fire, fully combat-capable." Romania sends 100 men from its 205th Air Defense Battalion to Poland in support of NATO troops on the Alliance’s eastern flank. Filmed on March 10, 2017.

Film Credits: NATO Channel

1179.description:
A-10 Warthogs from the 124th Fighter Wing practice targeting humvees at the Saylor Creek Training Range in Idaho on February 10, 2017. 

Film Credits: SrA Connor Marth

1180.description:
The Maui Space Surveillance Complex, which belongs to Air Force Space Command, is home to several telescopes that track objects orbiting the Earth, such as satellites and space debris. The complex is located 10,000 feet above sea level on top of Haleakala, a dormant volcano on the island of Maui, Hawaii. This location is considered to be one of the best places on Earth to view space from. The time lapse sequence was captured over a three-day period by a team from Airman magazine, the U.S. Air Force's official publication.
Time lapse photography by: Andrew Arthur Breese, Tech Sgt. Bennie J. Davis III
Production Assistance by: Tech Sgt. Matthew Bates
Music by: Effacé L'autre Endroit (Creative Commons)

1181.description:
Red Flag 17-2 aerial combat exercise at Nellis Air Force Base, NV is underway from February 27 to March 10, 2017. Filmed on March 3, 2017, Red Flag is the U.S Air Force's premier air-to-air combat training exercise held four times per year. Participants often include both United States and allied nations' combat air forces.

Film Credits: TSgt Jeffery Foster

1182.description:
A U-2 Dragon Lady completes a flight over Southwest Asia to gather reconnaissance information on enemy positions. Filmed on March 9, 2017. Unit - 99th Expeditionary Reconnaissance Squadron.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by SrA Joshua Hoskins

1183.description:
The U.S. Air Force KC-10 Extender was first introduced in 1981.  KC-10 air tankers from Travis Air Force Base capture the precision of aerial refueling on March 3, 2017. Unit - 60th Air Mobility Wing.

Film Credits: SSgt Scott Taylor

1184.description:
A U.S. Navy P-8A Poseidon aircraft from Patrol Squadron 10 (VP-10) conducts a surveillance mission during exercise Cobra Gold 2017 in Thailand on February 17, 2017. The P-8A Poseidon is the Navy's newest maritime, patrol and reconnaissance aircraft. It is a multi-mission capable replacement aircraft for the legacy P-3C Orion. 
Specifications
Primary Function:  Anti-Submarine Warfare (ASW) and Anti-surface Warfare (ASuW), Intelligence, Surveillance and Reconnaissance (ISR)
Contractor:  Boeing Defense, Space and Security
Propulsion:  2 CFM 56-7B engines with 27,300 lbs. thrust each
Length:  129.5 feet (39.47 meters)
Height: 42.1 feet (12.83 meters)
Wingspan:  123.6 feet (37.64 meters)
Maximum Gross Takeoff:  189,200 pounds (85,820 kilograms)
Airspeed:  490 knots (564 mph) true air speed
Ceiling:  41,000 feet (12,496 meters)
Range:  1,200 nautical miles radius with four hours on station
Crew:  Nine
Armament:  Torpedoes, cruise missiles 
More Info: http://www.navair.navy.mil/index.cfm?fuseaction=home.display&key=cfd01141-cd4e-4db8-a6b2-7e8fbfb31b86 

Film Credits: SSgt Jason Fudge

1185.description:
German PzH 2000, 155mm self-propelled howitzers assigned to the 131st Artillery Battalion, conduct fire missions during Exercise Dynamic Front II at Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany on March 7, 2017. Dynamic Front is an artillery operability exercise and focuses on developing solutions within theater level fire systems by executing multi-echelon fires and testing interoperability at the tactical level. It includes nearly 1,400 participants from nine NATO nations.

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Visual Information Specialist Gertrud Zach

1186.description:
Spanish Air Force Eurofighter Typhoon jets participate in Exercise Red Flag 17-2 at Nellis Air Force Base on March 1, 2017. Red Flag 17-2 runs from February 27 to March 10, 2017. Red Flag is the U.S. Air Force's premiere aerial combat training exercise held four times per year. Participants include U.S. aircraft as well as allied country aircraft.

Film Credits: A1C Julian Kemper

1187.description:
The United States deployed the Terminal High Altitude Area Defense (THAAD) anti-missile system in the Republic of Korea (South Korea) on March 6, 2017. This video includes 2015 test flight footage from the U.S. Missile Defense Agency.

Film Credits: Ben Listerman

1188.description:
Special Tactics Airmen from the 24th Special Operations Wing call in close air support at Eglin Air Force Base, FL during operation Emerald Warrior on March 3, 2017.   

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by A1C Maygan Straight

1189.description:
The M270 Multiple Launch Rocket System (MLRS) is an armored, self-propelled, multiple rocket launcher. The weapon is capable of firing Tactical Missile System (ATACMS) rounds and hitting targets 300 km (190 mi) away. With the warhead reaching an altitude of about 50 km (164,000 ft), the M270 can be used in shoot-and-scoot tactics, firing its rockets rapidly, then moving away to avoid counter-battery fire.  

Film Credits: SGT Stephen Wright

1190.description:
The USAF Air Combat Command F-16 Viper Demonstration Team from Shaw AFB, SC performs in a Heritage Flight at Davis-Monthan AFB on February 13, 2017. The demonstration is a commemoration of the U.S. Air Force's past and present aircraft.

Film Credits: A1C Sean Sweeney

1191.description:
Live fire exercise of Multiple Launch Rocket System (MLRS) at the Ft. Chaffee Joint Maneuver Training Center, Barling, Arkansas, on March 4, 2017. Unit - 1st Battalion, 142nd Field Artillery Brigade, Arkansas National Guard.

Film Credits: Lt. Col. Keith Moore

1192.description:
This is compiled footage of U.S. Marine Corps School Of Infantry, Infantry Training Battalion (ITB)-east. After boot camp Marines go to the School of Infantry (SOI). Some go to ITB and some go to non-infantry MCT. The ITB mission is to train and qualify Marines in entry level infantry military occupational specialties in order to provide the Operating Forces with Marines capable of conducting expeditionary combat operations. ITB is a 59-day training course that develops new Marines into infantrymen who can fight, survive, and win in combat situations. All footage filmed at Marine Corps Base Camp Lejeune - January 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Tanner Casares, Cpl Andrew Kuppers, Cpl Manuel Serrano

1193.description:
An F-16 Fighting Falcon engine is tested in full afterburner at the Engine Test Cell Facility, commonly referred to as the "Hush House". The General Electric F110-GE-100 turbofan produces close to 29,000 pounds of static thrust in afterburner, which can propel the Fighting Falcon to approximately twice the speed of sound. The test was conducted at the Atlantic City Air National Guard Base in Egg Harbor Township, N.J. on January 31, 2017.

Film Credits: MSgt Andrew Moseley

1194.description:
President Trump visited Pre-Commissioning Unit Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78) aboard Marine One on March 2, 2017 to meet with Sailors and shipbuilders of the Navy's first-in-class aircraft carrier during an all-hands call inside the ship's hangar bay. Footage is of Trump's arrival and departure aboard Ford. 

Film Credits: PO2 Kristopher Ruiz

1195.description:
Navy Corpsmen selected to serve with Marine Corps Operating Forces conduct a “trauma trail” as part of their Field Medical Service Technician course aboard Camp Pendleton, California on March 2, 2017. The course is designed to train Sailors in combat trauma, field medical service skills, combat survival skills, and physical endurance to meet the requirements for the worldwide mission of the Marine Corps Operating Forces. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sergeant Hector de Jesus

1196.description:
U.S. Air Force C-130 airdrops a MRZR ultra-light tactical vehicle used by special forces at Moody Air Force Base on March 1, 2017. 

Film Credits: Amn Giancarlo Carter

1197.description:
U.S. Army CH-47F helicopters from the 82nd Combat Aviation Brigade (CAB), practice low level flight maneuvers and landings in mountainous terrain in Djibouti, Africa on December 24, 2016. Plus, a CH-47F from the 82nd CAB conducts deck landing qualifications aboard the USS Whidbey Island (LSD-41) in the Gulf of Aden on November 11, 2016.  

Film Credits: SrA Natalie Plas

1198.description:
U.S. Paratroopers with the 173rd Airborne Brigade conduct a training jump out of a CH-47F Chinook helicopter during an airborne operation over the Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany on February 15, 2017. Units - 1st Squadron, 91st Cavalry Regiment and 1st Battalion, 214th Aviation Regiment, 12th Combat Aviation Brigade. 

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Visual Information Specialist Christoph Koppers

1199.description:
C-130 Hercules from the 36th Airlift Squadron, Yakota Air Base, Japan practice flight maneuvers including low level flight, tactical takeoffs, landings, and airdrop during Exercise Cope North 17 at Andersen Air Force Base, Guam. Filmed on February 22, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. Aaron Richardson

1200.description:
The B-52 Bomber from years ago has been used in many roles. The B-52H Stratofortress is now being used by the U.S. Air Force in a new role, as a close air support aircraft. Filmed February 2017. 

Film Credits: SrA Jordan Castelan, TSgt Jose Rodriguez, SrA Gabriel Stuart

1201.description:
Flight Operations aboard the U.S. Navy aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) in the Mediterranean Sea. Filmed February 2017. Plus, newly released clips by Lt. Zachary Huff from the “Raging Bulls” Strike Fighter Squadron (VFA-37) showing other aircraft air refueling from the cockpit of his jet, and a night F/A-18 recovery aboard the USS Bush in 2014. 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class David Lee, Oscar Sosa, Lt. Zachary Huff, PO2 Travis Litke - Released

1202.description:
U.S. Marines maneuver AAV-P7/A1 Assault Amphibious Vehicles from shore to sea at Onslow Beach, Camp Lejeune, NC on February 22, 2017. Unit - 2nd Platoon, Alpha Company, 2nd Assault Amphibian Battalion, 2nd Marine Division. Filmed on February 22, 2017.   

Film Credits: LCpl Williams Quinteros

1203.description:
Operation Spartan Pegasus 2017 shows joint interoperability between the U.S. Army and Air Force to conduct air operations and ground mobility in extreme cold conditions. Army, 4th Brigade, 25th Infantry jumps over Deadhorse, Alaska, inside the Arctic Circle on February 22, 2017. 

Film Credits: SrA Joshua DeGuzman, SSG Daniel Love

1204.description:
Aerial refueling footage of a B-1B Lancer (BONE) and an E-3 Sentry (AWACS) flying over the South Pacific. Also, footage of an EA-6B Prowler and F/A -18 Super Hornets flying over Iraq. Refueled by the 909th Air Refueling Squadron and the 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron respectively. Filmed February 2017. 

Film Credits: US Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. Aaron Richardson and SrA Joshua A. Hoskins

1205.description:
U.S. Army Paratroopers from 4th Brigade, 25th Infantry jump near Deadhorse, Alaska in operation Spartan Pegasus. Deadhorse is about 250 miles north of the Arctic Circle. Spartan Pegasus demonstrates the Army's ability to rapidly deploy forces in an extreme cold weather environment and move on an objective. Filmed on February 22, 2017. 

Film Credits: Video by Staff Sgt. Daniel Love

1206.description:
U.S. Marines with Marine All-Weather Fighter Attack Squadron 224 (VMFA(AW)-224) conduct Exercise Jaded Thunder 17 at Salina, Kansas. Jaded Thunder is a joint services exercise to complete training requirements and prepare for future deployments. Filmed February 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Luisa F. Torres

1207.description:
A U.S. Air Force KC-10 Extender completes a refueling sortie over Iraq on Feb. 22, 2017. The KC-10 Extender offloaded 126,000 pounds of fuel to coalition aircraft - AV-8B Harrier, German GR4 Tornado, F-15E Strike Eagle, and B-52H Stratofortress.

Film Credits: SrA Tyler Woodward

1208.description:
U.S. Navy Independent Duty Corpsman (IDC) students go through hyper-realistic training, including combat scenarios, shipboard emergency scenarios, and prolonged care scenarios, at Strategic Operations (STRATOPS) in San Diego, as part of their IDC training at Surface Warfare Medical Institute (SWMI). IDCs are specialized hospital corpsmen and serve at diverse duty stations in the Navy from Surface Ships, Sea Bees, Special Warfare units such as the SEALs or Expeditionary Warfare and also billets with the Fleet Marine Force. These Sailors serve on land or sea alongside Navy and Marine Corps warfighters, and at isolated duty stations where no medical officer is assigned (such as submarines). More info: 
(1) http://www.med.navy.mil/sites/nmotc/swmi/Pages/IndependentDutyCorpsman.aspx
(2) http://www.militarynews.com/norfolk-navy-flagship/news/top_stories/independent-duty-corpsman-a-specialized-lifesaver/article_2f8a5631-949b-559f-8bc5-c46adfbfa525.html

Film Credits: Austin Rooney

1209.description:
Apache helicopters arrive at Ramstein Air Base in Germany and are offloaded from a C-5M Super Galaxy transport plane.

Film Credits: SSgt John Archiquette

1210.description:
F/A-18 Super Hornets takeoff from the U.S. aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) during a deployment in the 6th Fleet Area of Operations on February 13, 2017.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class David Lee - Released

1211.description:
Aerial refueling U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptors over Iraq in support of Combined Joint Task Force - Operation Inherent Resolve on February 12, 2017. U.S. Airmen from the 908th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron delivered the fuel from a KC-10 Extender.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by SrA Joshua A. Hoskins

1212.description:
Amphibious Assault Ship USS Bataan (LHD-5) executes a live-fire test of the Close In Weapon System (CIWS) in preparation for an upcoming deployment. Filmed on February 20, 2017.

Film Credits: PO3 Caleb Strong

1213.description:
Service members from Thailand, the Republic of Korea and the U.S. participate in an amphibious capabilities demonstration at Hat Yao, in Rayong Province, Thailand, during exercise Cobra Gold on February 17, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Chad Butler

1214.description:
KC-135 Stratotanker from 909th Air Refueling Squadron, Kadena Air Base, Japan refuels F-16 Fighting Falcons, F-15 Strike Eagles, and B-1B Lancers during Exercise Cope North 17 with pilot/boom operator communications. Filmed on February 15, 2017. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. Aaron Richardson

1215.description:
Without question, the M142 High Mobility Artillery Rocket System (HIMARS) is the most deadly ground based rocket artillery in use by any army nowadays. Used by the U.S. Army and Marines, this weapon is responsible for accurately targeting and selectively destroying more enemy combative than any other rocket system on Earth.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Daphne D. Rodriguez, CWO3 James A. Burks, SGT Christopher Tobey, SrA Elizabeth Taranto

1216.description:
Footage of the F-35A Lightning II (Joint Stike Fighter) aircraft from the 388th Fighter Wing at Hill AFB, UT, as participation in exercise Red Flag 17-1 at Nellis AFB. The F-35A racked up 145 kills, 7 losses, which is 20:1 ratio, in this installment of Red Flag 17-1, from January 23 to February 10, 2017. Sourced: http://breakingdefense.com/2017/02/f-35a-at-red-flag-90-mission-capable-key-systems-up-every-flight/  - Soundbite from Captain Tim Six, F-35A Pilot. And thanks to YT channel - https://www.youtube.com/user/xero993

The QF-16 replaced the QF-4 "Phantom" Aerial Target, which flew its last unmanned mission August 17, 2016. This flight on February 10, 2017 represents the official start of the QF-16 program at Holloman Air Force Base, NM.

U.S. Unit - 3rd Battalion, 29th Field Artillery Regiment, 3rd Armored Brigade Combat Team, 4th Infantry Division.

The ammunition on-load is the final requirement for the ship to deploy later this summer. America is capable of supporting a wide spectrum of military operations and missions, including putting Marines ashore for combat operations, launching air strikes, keeping sea lanes free and open for movement of global commerce and delivering humanitarian aid following a natural disaster.

Flight operations at Volk Field Air National Guard Base in Wisconsin. F-16 Fighting Falcons prep, takeoff, and fly in formation with F-35A Lightning II fighter jets on temporary duty (TDY) from Eglin AFB.

U.S. Army Paladin artillery crews fire 155 mm rounds downrange at the training site in Drawsko Pomorskie, Poland. U.S. B-1B Lancer bombers have been deployed to Andersen Air Force Base in Guam as a "Continuous Bomber Presence". For more information visit https://www.mda.mil

1237.description:
The worlds first nuclear aircraft carrier, USS Enterprise (CVN-65) was decommissioned on February 3, 2017, after 55 years in service to the United States Navy.

1239.description:
U.S. Army Artillery crews test fire new gun tubes on the M109A6 Paladin, 155mm Howitzer, at McCrady Training Center in South Carolina on January 27, 2017. The crewmembers loaded the breech, exited the vehicle, and fired the rounds with a 50 foot lanyard for safety... just in case there is a malfunction of the new tube. All 12 guns fired successfully. Filmed on January 27, 2017. Unit - 178th Field Artillery Battalion, 678th Air Defense Artillery Brigade, South Carolina Army National Guard.

Film Credits: MSgt Carl Clegg

1240.description:
The U.S. Navy's new E-2D Advanced Hawkeye "battle management" aircraft has been sent to Marine Corps Air Station Iwakuni, Japan on February 2, 2017. The Advanced Hawkeye is assigned aboard aircraft carriers and provides airborne early warning and command and control to the carrier air wing. The E-2D can act as a sensor to guide the fleet's weapons onto targets that other aircraft and ships can not locate. Also it warns of incoming anti-ship missile attacks. This aircraft can also coordinate missions such as air warfare, strike warfare, surface warfare and search and rescue operations. It distributes tactical information from onboard sensors to command centers and other assets. The Advanced Hawkeye can operate in all weather conditions. More info: http://www.military-today.com/aircraft/e2d_advanced_hawkeye.htm  

Film Credits: LCpl Sara Abrego, LCpl Emma Norris

1241.description:
Footage of Exercise Red Flag 17-1 at Nellis Air Force Base, NV. Red Flag is an international aerial combat training exercise which is hosted at Nellis 4 times per year. Red Flag 17-1 runs from January 23 to February 10, 2017.

1242.description:
U.S. Air Force fighter aircraft takeoff at Nellis AFB, NV as part of Red Flag 17-1. Exercise Red Flag is an advanced aerial combat training exercise hosted at Nellis Air Force Base, Nevada - four times per year. Filmed on January 30, 2017.

U.S. Marines conduct a battalion live-fire exercise with the Expeditionary Fire Support System (EFSS). EFSS is a 120mm mobile mortar system which can be transport by MV-22 Osprey. U.S. Army engineers from the 82nd Airborne Division drive a forward resupply convoy near Tactical Assembly Area Filfayl, Iraq on January 23, 2017. Unit - Company B, 37th Brigade Engineer Battalion, 2nd Brigade Combat Team, "Falcon Brigade".

1250.description:
U-2 pilots are probably the most highly trained pilots in the world - very top secret. And even though some may say the U-2 is outdated and obsolete, the U-2 has been updated with the most advanced sensors and optics in existence, making it a tremendous asset to the U.S. Air Force to this day. During high-altitude missions, U-2 pilots often see a natural occurrence called the "terminator line" - the line which separates day and night. Here in this video a U-2 pilot expains what the terminator line is, and you get to see it.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Andrew Arthur Breese - 9 RW Public Affairs Beale AFB, CA

The A-29 is a multi-role, fixed wing aircraft that has been provided to the Afghan Air Force for air-to-ground support and aerial reconnaissance in counterinsurgency operations. Afghan pilots and maintainers began training on the aircraft at Moody Air Force Base, GA in February 2015. This footage was filmed at Moody Air Force Base, GA on January 27, 2017.

The Boneyard is the largest aircraft storage facility in the world with about 5,000 retired military aircraft covering 2,600 acres. Maintained by the 309th Aerospace Maintenance and Regeneration Group, crews at the Boneyard preserve aircraft for possible future use, pull aircraft parts to supply to the field, and perform depot-level maintenance and aircraft regeneration in support of U.S. Air Force operations.

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Andrew Arthur Breese

1259.description:
Almost 6,000 Sailors attached to the George H.W. Bush Carrier Strike Group departed Norfolk and Mayport, Florida on January 21, 2017 for a scheduled deployment. Led by Commander, Carrier Strike Group 2, Rear Adm. Kenneth R. Whitesell, the strike group is comprised of the staff of CSG-2; USS George H.W. Bush (CVN 77); the nine squadrons and staff of Carrier Air Wing (CVW) 8; Destroyer Squadron (DESRON) 22 staff and guided-missile destroyers USS Laboon (DDG 58) and USS Truxtun (DDG 103); and Mayport-based guided missile cruisers USS Philippine Sea (CG 58) and USS Hue City (CG 66).

The squadrons of CVW-8 will depart bases including Naval Air Station (NAS) Oceana, NAS Whidbey Island, NAS Jacksonville, NAS Lemoore and Naval Station Norfolk. CVW-8 includes Strike Fighter Squadron (VFA) 213 "Fighting Black Lions"; VFA-31 "Tomcatters"; VFA-87 "Golden Warriors"; VFA-37 "Ragin Bulls"; Electronic Attack Squadron (VAQ) 131 "Lancers"; Early Warning Squadron (VAW) 124 "Bear Aces"; Helicopter Mine Countermeasure Squadron (HSM) 70 "Spartans"; Helicopter Sea Combat Squadron (HSC) 9 "Tridents"; and a detachment from Fleet Logistics Support Squadron (VRC) 40 "Rawhides".

Film Credits: PO2 Nicolas Lopez, Robert Gensic

1260.description:
On Inauguration Day 2017, the Presidential Salute Battery (The Old Guard) conducts a 21 Gun Salute in honor of newly sworn-in President Trump. The Presidential Salute Battery is a U.S. Army artillery battery that is part of the 3rd United States Infantry Regiment, the President of the United States' escort regiment. The battery renders gun salutes according to a customary order of arms which is 21 volleys for heads of state (including the President of the United States and former presidents); 19 for the Vice-President of the United States, foreign chiefs of government, and members of the cabinet of the United States; and 17, 15, 13, and 11 for flag officers of the rank of O-10, O-9, O-8, and O-7, respectively. The unit is equipped with eight 3-inch anti-tank guns of World War II vintage, mounted on 105mm Howitzer chassis. Each gun weighs 5,775 pounds and fires 75mm blank shells with 1.5 pounds of powder.

Film Credits: SSG Jedhel Somera

1261.description:

Historically, the Military District of Washington commander leads service members of all branches of the armed forces in formation down Pennsylvania Avenue during the first pass-in-review by the new president and renders the first salute to the newly sworn in commander-in-chief.

Film Credits: This work, Trump Participates in First Pass in Review as Commander in Chief, is free of known copyright restrictions under U.S. copyright law. - https://www.dvidshub.net/video/506003/trump-participates-first-pass-review-commander-chief

The EC-130 is a U.S. Air Force Electronic Warfare plane, heavily modified C-130 Hercules, used to disrupt enemy command and control communications, perform offensive counterinformation operations, and suppress enemy air defenses. The movement included M109A6 Paladin Howitzers and support carriers, Bradley Fighting Vehicles, and M1A2 Abrams Tanks. Film Credits: CPT Scott Kuhn, SSG Timothy Hughes, SSG Thanh Pham

1278.description:
The test was conducted in October 2016 and consisted of 103 Perdix micro-drones launched from three U.S. Navy F/A-18 Super Hornet fighter jets. It demonstrated advanced swarm behaviors such as collective decision-making, adaptive formation flying, and self-healing. “Due to the complex nature of combat, Perdix are not pre-programmed synchronized individuals, they are a collective organism, sharing one distributed brain for decision-making and adapting to each other like swarms in nature,” said Strategic Capabilities Office (SCO) Director William Roper. “Because every Perdix communicates and collaborates with every other Perdix, the swarm has no leader and can gracefully adapt to drones entering or exiting the team.” The demonstration is one of the first examples of the Department of Defense using teams of small, inexpensive, autonomous systems to perform missions once achieved only by large, expensive ones. Originally designed by Massachusetts Institute of Technology engineering students, the Perdix drone was modified for military use by the scientists and engineers of MIT Lincoln Laboratory starting in 2013. Perdix is an expendable UAV designed to fly low to capture video and transmit it back to controllers. It could have numerous applications, though the SCO has only mentioned Perdix’s ability to fly a low-altitude intelligence, surveillance and reconnaissance missions.
 
Film Credits: This work, Perdix Swarm Demo Oct. 2016, is free of known copyright restrictions under U.S. copyright law. Produced by the U.S. DOD.

1281.description:
The Battle of Iwo Jima was one of the bloodiest battles between America and Japan during WWII. The strategic island of Iwo Jima was occupied by 22,000 Japanese soldiers when U.S. Marines invaded and took the island after a 36 day battle which left about 20,000 Japanese soldiers killed and 7,000 Marines killed --- February 19 to March 26, 1945.
 
Film Credits: National Archives and Records Administration, SSgt Edmund Hatch, Cpl Isaac Ibarra

1282.description:
Red Flag Alaska is an air combat exercise held four times a year out of Eielson Air Force Base and Elmendorf Air Force Base. It is a multi-national training event involving several aircraft units whose military missions may differ significantly from that of other participating units. In other words, Army units and Air Force units, and Marine Corps Special Forces may be training simultaneously. 

Film Credits: Staff Sgt. Matthew K. Pardini, SSgt Michael Cowley, TSgt Matt Hecht, Sgt Megan Scullin, SrA Carly Kavish, SSgt Peter Reft, TSgt Jose Rodriguez, SrA Joshua DeGuzman, A1C Jared Bunn

1283.description:
Wednesday December 21, 2016 the QF-4 Phantom II retired from active duty. Over the last 53 years the Phantom became one of the most beloved airframes in the U.S. Military. Over the years it connected to thousands of people on an emotional level as it served as a symbol of hope and freedom during one of the most difficult times our country has faced. Lt. Col. Ronald King, 82nd Aerial Target Squadron Detachment 2 Commander and the last active duty Airman to pilot the QF-4, describes his experience serving with the Phantom.

1286.description:

1290.description:
The Grumman C-2 Greyhound is a twin-engine, high-wing cargo aircraft, designed to carry supplies, mail, and passengers to aircraft carriers in the U.S. Navy. It was designated as Carrier Onboard Delivery (COD) and made its first flights back in the 1960's. Here are various clips of C-2 Greyhounds launching and landing aboard aircraft carriers. The C-2 is slated to be replaced by the MV-22 Osprey by year 2022.

Film Credits: Petty Officer 3rd Class Jared King, LCpl Cody Woods, PO3 Devin Kates

1291.description:
Precision airstrikes by the United States begin with high altitude intelligence surveillance and reconnaissance (ISR) planning and vetting of targets before they are struck. The RQ-4 Global Hawk and U-2 Dragon Lady from the 99th Expeditionary Reconnaissance Squadron are highlighted in this video.

Film Credits: TSgt Jeremy Roman

1292.description:
The A-10 Thunderbolt II, nicknamed "Warthog" for its unusual appearance, has been flying for the U.S. Air Force since the 1970's and was specifically designed as a ground attack aircraft to destroy Soviet tanks. Over the years, the Warthog has become a legendary Close Air Support jet because of its huge 30mm gatling cannon (GAU-8) which fires depleted Uranium rounds capable of penetrating heavy armor, its long loiter time over targets, its high maneuverability, and its Titanium armor which contributes to survivability. In addition to having the deadly GAU-8, the Warthog can be armed with a variety of bombs and missiles adding to its lethality. If you check any list of "best close air support aircraft", you will find the A-10 Thunderbolt II Warthog is at the top of the list, or near the top of most every list you will find. This video is a compilation of A-10 clips including live-fire munitions, aerial refueling over Afghanistan, takeoff and landing, and cockpit video.

Film Credits: William Lewis, SrA Rachel Maxwell, SrA Aaron Hauser, SGT Meghan Berry, SSgt Daniel Negrete, SSgt Michelle Revoir, SSgt John Raven, MSgt Pedro Jimenez, A1C Jean-Paul Arnaud-Marquez, SSgt Samuel O'Brien, SrA Austin Willhoit

1293.description:
U.S. Marines with 2nd Battalion, 6th Marine Regiment conduct a battalion field exercise at Camp Lejeune, December 2016 to sustain combat proficiency. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Cpl. Adam Edwards, LCpl Samuel Taylor, LCpl Preston Shay

1294.description:
U.S. Marine Corps recruits conduct water survival training at Parris Island Boot Camp, South Carolina on December 13, 2016. 

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Debra S. Rookus and Lance Cpl. Daniel Lobo  - Released

1295.description:
A USAF C-130 Hercules cargo plane from the 737th Expeditionary Airlift Squadron transfers 44,000 lbs of ammunition to Iraq on December 15, 2016 to be used in the fight against ISIS. 

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by TSgt Jose A. Rodriguez Jr

1296.description:
F-15E Strike Eagle flight crews are briefed and then proceed to their aircraft for pre-flight inpections prior to taxis and takeoff during Exercise Razor Talon at Seymour Johnson Air Force Base on December 15, 2016. Units - 336th Fighter Squadron, U.S. Air Force.

Film Credits: Airman Shawna Keyes

1297.description:
Operation Christmas Drop is a tradition that serves as a training mission for the United States Air Force. It started in 1952 and has become the longest running humanitarian airlift in the world. USAF C-130 Hercules cargo planes from Yokota Air Base, Japan airdrop needed supplies over the Micronesian Islands, December 2016.

Film Credits: TSgt Michael Davis, A1C Nathan Eckert

1298.description:
A combat search and rescue exercise (CSAR) with mutiple branches of the Military in Arizona. Members of the 355th Fighter Squadron, 79th Rescue Squadron and 48th Rescue Squadron from Davis Monthan - the 71st Rescue Squadron from Moody AFB and United States Marines practice a air crash casualty, search and rescue drill in preparation for deployment.  

Film Credits: SSgt Samuel O'Brien

1299.description:
The M2 Browning Machine Gun has been used in warfare since WWI, but upgraded with the .50 BMG round, it is much more lethal... "Ma Deuce". The M2 has been produced longer than any other machine gun. The Browning .50 caliber machine gun has been used extensively by the United States. It is also a machine gun used by many NATO countries.

Film Credits: SSgt Brandon Owen, SSgt Tanner Iskra, PO1 Paul Seeber, LT Desiree Frame, SGT Arthur Haring, SGT Arthur Haring

1300.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a platoon assault live-fire exercise during Korea Marine Exchange Program 17-1 on November 25, 2016 at Suseong-ri range, South Korea. Before big scale assaults Marines initially rehearse with their fire teams and work their way up to performing them with the platoon. The U.S. Marines are assigned to 3rd Battalion, 2nd Marine Regiment which is forward deployed from Camp Lejeune, North Carolina, to 3rd Marine Division, based in Okinawa, Japan.

Film Credits: Sgt Isaac Ibarra

1301.description:
A Royal Air Force (RAF) A400 Atlas aircrew gives an incentive flight to U.S. Air Force Airmen at Scott Air Force Base, Illinois on December 12, 2016. The Airbus A400M Atlas is a four-engine turboprop military transport aircraft, mid-sized between a C-130 and a C-17. The A400M is a relatively new aircraft, making its maiden flight in 2009. The first operational units were delivered to the French Air Force in 2013, Turkish Air Force and the RAF in 2014.

Film Credits: SrA Timothy Kirchner

1302.description:
One of the oldest rivalries in college football history, Army vs Navy, ended with an Army win on December 10, 2016. The Army team broke a 14 game losing streak to Navy dating back to 2001, when it pulled off a 21-17 upset win against a top 25 ranked Navy team. Congrats Army!

Film Credits: SGT Jose Torres Jr.

1303.description:
U.S. Marines conduct an Urban Assault Course as part of a Deployment for Training (DFT), on Fort Pickett, VA, December 2, 2016. Unit - Weapons Company, 3rd Battalion, 8th Marine Regiment, 2d Marine Division.

Film Credits: Cpl Dani Zunun

1304.description:
Live-fire training with U.S. Marine Corps UH-1Y Venom and AH-1Z Viper attack helicopters for the first time in Okinawa, Japan on December 2, 2016. The live-fire shoot took place off the coast of Okinawa on remote range W-174. The Marines are with HMLA-267, assigned to Marine Aircraft Group 36, 1st Marine Aircraft Wing, III Marine Expeditionary Force.

Film Credits: LCpl Nelson Duenas, Cpl Steven Tran

1305.description:
A U.S. Air Force production describing the role of B-52 Bombers from Barksdale Air Force Base now deployed in Southwest Asia. Produced in November, 2016. 

Film Credits: SrA Gabriel Stuart

1306.description:
Footage of Exercise Steel Knight-17: U.S. Marines of the 1st Marine Division conduct multiple training exercises during Steel Knight-17. Steel Knight is an annual exercise lead by the 1st Marine Division that covers much of the western United States and California coast. Focusing on live-fire maneuvers, warfare tactics, and command and control capabilities, Steel Knight tests Marines and Sailors across a range of environments to ensure that the 1st Marine Division is the Marine Corps' largest, most capable, and most lethal combat force ready to be deployed for battle.   

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Preston J. Hightower, LCpl Branden Bourque, LCpl Frank Cordoba, MSgt Daniel Kauppila, LCpl Skyler Treverrow, Pfc. Mike Hernandez - Released

1307.description:
Slow Motion footage of U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptors, F-35A Lightning II Joint Strike Fighters, and F-15E Strike Eagles during Day 5 of Exercise Checkered Flag 17-1 at Tyndall Air Force Base. Filmed on December 9, 2016. More info about Checkered Flag 17-1 here: http://www.nellis.af.mil/News/tabid/6431/Article/1020026/tyndall-to-host-checkered-flag-17-1-and-combat-archer-17-3.aspx   

Film Credits: A1C Tybee Hurst

1308.description:
Day 4 operations at Exercise Checkered Flag 17-1, featuring U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptors, F-35A Lighting II Joint Strike Fighters, F-16 Fighting Falcons, and F-15E Strike Eagles. Checkered Flag 17-1 at Tyndall Air Force Base, Florida runs December 5-16, 2016. Aircrews will be evaluated on their ability to mobilize, integrate, deploy and employ combat air power on a large scale. Air power assets from six Air Combat Command installations are participating: Tyndall AFB, Florida; Shaw AFB, South Carolina; Mountain Home AFB, Idaho; Moody AFB, Georgia; Eglin AFB, Florida; and Tinker AFB, Oklahoma. The Florida Air National Guard and Louisiana Air National Guard will also provide air assets during the exercise. More info about Checkered Flag 17-1 here: http://www.nellis.af.mil/News/tabid/6431/Article/1020026/tyndall-to-host-checkered-flag-17-1-and-combat-archer-17-3.aspx   

Film Credits: A1C Tybee Hurst

1309.description:
U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptors, F-35A Lighting II Joint Strike Fighters, F-16 Fighting Falcons, and F-15E Strike Eagles join forces in tactical integration training during Exercise Checkered Flag 17-1 at Tyndall Air Force Base, December 5-16, 2016. Aircrews will be evaluated on their ability to mobilize, integrate, deploy and employ combat air power on a large scale. Air power assets from six Air Combat Command installations are participating: Tyndall AFB, Florida; Shaw AFB, South Carolina; Mountain Home AFB, Idaho; Moody AFB, Georgia; Eglin AFB, Florida; and Tinker AFB, Oklahoma. The Florida Air National Guard and Louisiana Air National Guard will also provide air assets during the exercise. More info about Checkered Flag 17-1 here: http://www.nellis.af.mil/News/tabid/6431/Article/1020026/tyndall-to-host-checkered-flag-17-1-and-combat-archer-17-3.aspx   

Film Credits: A1C Roswell Sartwell, A1C Tybee Hurst, SSgt William Jackson

1310.description:
U.S. Army paratroopers conduct Exercise Mountain Shock on December 2, 2016. Exercise Mountain Shock is a bilateral training exercise with the Slovenian Armed Forces to build teamwork and readiness between allied NATO countries.     

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Specialist Davide Dalla Massara and Paolo Bovo - Released

1311.description:
U.S. Marines make an amphibious landing at Red Beach, Camp Pendleton, California on December 4, 2016 as part of exercise Steel Knight 2017.       

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Master Sgt Daniel F. Kauppila and LCpl Skyler Treverrow - Released

1312.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers conduct a preliminary armament calibration test fire of a Counter Rocket, Artillery, and Mortar, (C-RAM) system at Al Asad Air Base, Iraq on November 14, 2016. The C-Ram is a land-based Phalanx weapon system comparable to the U.S. Navy's shipboard version of CIWS. It is designed to defeat incoming artillery, rockets and mortar rounds in the air before they can hit their ground targets. Unit - 5th Battalion, 5th Air Defense Artillery Regiment.       

Film Credits: U.S. Army Video by Sgt. Neil Stanfield

1313.description:
U.S. Marines conduct Integrated Training Exercise 1-17, including urban warfare training, at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center, Twentynine Palms, CA. This training is a pre-deployment exercise designed to prepare Marines to take over as the Ground Combat Element for the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit.       

Film Credits:  Sgt Patricia Claypool-Morris, LCpl Daniel Betancourt

1314.description:
The U.S. Aircraft Carrier USS John C. Stennis enters Pearl Harbor in advance of National Pearl Harbor Remembrance Day 2016. President Franklin D. Roosevelt delivered this speech to Congress one day after the devious attack by Japan on Pearl Harbor on December 7, 1941 --- 

"Yesterday, December 7, 1941 - a date which will live in infamy - the United States of America was suddenly and deliberately attacked by naval and air forces of the Empire of Japan. The United States was at peace with that nation and, at the solicitation of Japan, was still in conversation with its Government and its Emperor looking toward the maintenance of peace in the Pacific.

The attack yesterday on the Hawaiian Islands has caused severe damage to American naval and military forces. Very many American lives have been lost. In addition American ships have been reported torpedoed on the high seas between San Francisco and Honolulu.

Yesterday the Japanese Government also launched an attack against Malaya. Last night Japanese forces attacked Hong Kong. Last night Japanese forces attacked Guam. Last night Japanese forces attacked the Philippine Islands. Last night the Japanese attacked Wake Island. This morning the Japanese attacked Midway Island.

As Commander-in-Chief of the Army and Navy, I have directed that all measures be taken for our defense.

Always will we remember the character of the onslaught against us. No matter how long it may take us to overcome this premeditated invasion, the American people in their righteous might will win through to absolute victory.

I ask that the Congress declare that since the unprovoked and dastardly attack by Japan on Sunday, December seventh, 1941, a state of war has existed between the United States and the Japanese Empire."     

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Petty Officer 2nd Class Laurie Dexter, PO2 Jerome Johnson - Released

1315.description:
Two U.S. Air Force F-15E Strike Eagles conduct an aerial refueling operation with a KC-135 Stratotanker, at twilight, somewhere over Iraq, on December 1, 2016.   

Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by TSgt Jose A. Rodriguez Jr

1316.description:
U.S. Marines tested the Lethal Miniature Aerial Missile System (LMAMS) during a pre-deployment training exercise at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center, Twentynine Palms, CA. The LMAMS is a small, man-portable missile, Umanned Aerial Vehicle (drone) that carries a high-explosive warhead intended to be used against targets like snipers and enemy combatants planting IEDs. LMAMS is a single-use weapon that can be carried in a soldier's backpack. Filmed on October 28, 2016. USMC Unit - 3rd Battalion, 5th Marine Regiment, India Company.

Film Credits: United States Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl Daniel Betancourt Jr

1317.description:
First entering service in the mid 1980's, the B-1B was designed to penetrate Soviet airspace and deliver nuclear weapons. Over the years when the Soviet Union collapsed, the B-1B was designated "Lancer" and nicknamed "Bone" from B-One. It has since been used as a conventional bomber in conflicts and wars. Today the Bone is still a slim, sleek and beautiful aircraft, with it's deadly nuclear capabilities very much intact.

U.S. Air Force Footage - Released and Documented

1318.description:
Ukrainian Soldiers assigned to 1st Battalion, 80th Airmobile Brigade conduct an air assault and situational training exercise, led by U.S. Soldiers from the 3rd Infantry Division on November 28, 2016 at the International Peacekeeping and Security Center, Yavoriv, Ukraine.

Film Credits: SGT Jacob Holmes

1319.description:
U.S. Marines conduct fire-team attack and maneuvers at range TC-11, Arta, Djibouti.  Marines with Special Purpose Marine Air Ground Task Force-Crisis Response-Africa Ground Combat Element (SPMAGTF-CR-AF GCE) completed fire-team range drills to sustain core infantry skills and increase readiness to support contingency operations on November 12, 2016.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Staff Sgt. David L. Proffitt

1320.description:
New Marine Corps recruits meet the drill instructors responsible for transforming them into Marines at Marine Corps Recruit Depot Parris Island. Filmed on November 5, 2016.

Film Credits: LCpl Maximiliano Bavastro

1321.description:
U.S. Marines shoot with Lithuanian and Romanian Soldiers, and get to shoot AK-47 and HK G36 assault rifles on a live-fire range at the Rukla Training Area, Lithuania. Filmed during Exercise Iron Sword 16 with U.S. Marines from Black Sea Rotational Force 16.2.

Film Credits: Cpl Clarence Wimberly

1322.description:
Although older than most people alive nowadays, the B-52 has been upgraded and modernized. It's not really used as a bomber anymore. It's used more as a deterrent - a nuclear cruise missile delivery platform. Think about a nuclear missile submarine flying in the sky. For example, a Trident Nuclear Submarine can deliver 24 atomic missiles. And on the other hand, one B-52H Statofortress can launch 26 Nuclear Cruise Missiles (from up to 600 miles away from the target). That's a lot of firepower for just one airplane.

Credits: U.S. Air Force, Department of Defense

1323.description:
The Marine Corps version of the F-35 Joint Strike Fighter (F-35B) conducts the first integrated operations with other assigned aircraft aboard the USS America (LHA-6) on November 19, 2016. Twelve F-35B Lightning II fighter jets embarked on USS America (LHA-6) to demonstrate shipboard integration alongside other Marine Corps Air Combat Element assets. 

Credit: LCpl Dana Beesley, Cpl Thor Larson

1324.description:
Aircraft carrier USS Nimitz (CVN-68) transits the Suez Canal - time lapse video. The Suez Canal is approximately 120 miles long. The canal is an artificial sea-level waterway in Egypt, connecting the Mediterranean Sea and the Red Sea. It opened in November 1869 after 10 years of construction. Under international treaty, the Suez Canal may be used in time of war as in time of peace, by every vessel of commerce or of war, without distinction of flag. Filmed November 2013.

Credit: Courtesy United States Navy Video - Released -- Music: https://www.audioblocks.com/stock-audio/summer-daze-full.html

1325.description:
F-4 Phantom II fighter jet makes its final appearance at the Aviation Nation Air Show - Nellis Air Force Base in Nevada. Filmed on November 12, 2016.
 
Film Credits: A1C Christina Ensley

1326.description:
U.S. Marine Corps Recruits practice close order drills at Marine Corps Recruit Depot Parris Island - and then are evaluated on Final Drill at the Peatross Parade Deck. This drilling teaches recruits discipline, uniformity, to move to action and to obey orders.
 
Film Credits: LCpl Aaron Bolser, LCpl Debra Rookus

1327.description:
Eurofighter Typhoons are highlighted from the United Kingdom, Germany, and Italy. But other NATO fighter jets are also featured... German Tornadoes, F-16 Fighting Falcons from Norway, Czech and Swedish Gripens, French Rafale and Mirage 2000D jets, plus Canadian CF-188 Hornets.
 
Film Credits: NATO TV, MSgt Shane Cronin, William Lewis, A1C Rachel Webster, TSgt Tristan McIntire, SSgt Robert Kingery, SSgt John McRell

1328.description:
M-1 Tanks fire in Norway - U.S. Marines from the Black Sea Rotational Force conduct a live-fire exercise at Setermoen, Norway, November 17, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: Sgt Michelle Reif

1329.description:
U.S. Marines shoot M240B Machine Guns during live-fire Exercise Platinum Lynx at Babadag Military Training area in Romania on September 27, 2016. Unit - Black Sea Rotational Force, Fleet Anti-Terrorism Security Team Europe, USMC. 
 
Film Credits: Sgt Kirstin Merrimarahajara, LCpl Timothy Lutz

1330.description:
U.S. Coast Guardsmen fast rope from MH-60S Night Hawk helicopters to demonstrate what a Visit, Board, Search and Seizure (VBSS) operation might look like in real-world conditions. Coast Guardsmen assigned to the San Diego-based Coast Guard Maritime Safety and Security Team (MSST-91109) particitpated with helicopters from Helicopter Sea Combat Squadron (HSC-21) to VBSS aboard the littoral combat ship USS Fort Worth (LCS-3) as part of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) Defense Informal. Filmed at Pearl Harbor, HI on September 30, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: PO2 Laurie Dexter, PO2 Katarzyna Kobiljak, PO2 Gabrielle Joyner, PO2 Jeff Troutman, SSgt Chris Hubenthal, PO2 Jerome Johnson

1331.description:
The U.S. Navy amphibious transport dock ship USS John P. Murtha (LPD-26) pulls in to Naval Base San Diego for the first time to be homeported. The Murtha became officially commissioned October 8, 2016 before transiting from Pascagoula, MS in order to serve its first duty station in San Diego. Filmed on November 18, 2016.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by PO1 Marcus Stanley and PO3 Christopher A. Veloicaza - Released

1332.description:
U.S. Marine Scout Snipers conduct aerial sniper training aboard an MH-60S Seahawk helicopter on October 22, 2016. Unit - Weapons Company, Battalion Landing Team, 2nd Battalion, 4th Marine Regiment, 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit aboard the USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6).
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl David A. Diggs - Released

1333.description:
U.S. Marine Corps AV-8B Harriers takeoff, land, and refuel aboard USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6) in the Pacific Ocean on  August 27, 2016. The Harriers are part of the the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit, the only continuously forward deployed MEU in the Marine Corps. 
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl David A. Diggs - Released

1334.description:
Marines with Company E, Battalion Landing Team, 2nd Battalion, 4th Marine Regiment, are inserted by MV-22 Osprey on Ie Shima Island, Okinawa, Japan during a training exercise on August 29, 2016. Company E is the helicopter assault element of the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit, and specializes in sea and land-based vertical assault by helicopter and tiltrotor aircraft.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl David A. Diggs - Released

1335.description:
The U.S. Air Force 914th Aeromedical Evacuation Squadron trains and equips combat-ready aeromedical evacuation crews to provide lifesaving in-flight patient care worldwide in response to contingencies and humanitarian emergencies. Filmed at the Gulfport Combat Readiness Training Center, MS during exercise Southern Strike 17 on October 25, 2016.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video by Staff Sgt. John Raven

1336.description:
U.S. Marine Corps recruits conduct pugil stick bouts at Marine Corps Recruit Depot Parris Island, SC on November 15, 2016. Pugil stick fights are used to simulate close quarters combat and build proficiency in rifle bayonet techniques.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Daniel A. Lobo - Released

1337.description:
U.S. Air Force Explosive Ordnance Disposal personnel conduct a munitions burn at an undisclosed location in Southwest Asia on November 9, 2016. The 386th Expeditionary Civil Engineer Squadron conducted the burn to dispose of unserviceable ammunition totaling 18,974 pieces of ammunition, including 20mm cartridges and 5.56 NATO cartridges, among other ordnance. Since the ammunition is from unknown origins, the EOD team can’t verify if and for how long it has been exposed to the elements. The burn was conducted to dispose of ammunition determined to be unsafe.
 
Film Credits: TSgt Lance Daigle

1338.description:
German Soldiers shoot an assortment of firearms into ballistics gelatin to study the effects of bullet wounds on the human body. Ballistic gelatin is comparable in density to human muscle tissue. This testing was done during a NATO Special Operations Combat Medical Course to help medical teams better understand the damage caused by various ammunition. Filmed at the International Special Training Centre in Pfullendorf, Germany on October 27, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: Martin Greeson

1339.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a TRAP exercise (Tactical Recovery Of Aircraft & Personnel). Marines with Fox Company, 2nd Battalion, 7th Marine Regiment, provide TRAP capability to the Special Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force - Crisis Response - Central Command (SPMAGTF-CR-CC). SPMAGTF-CR-CC is a crisis response unit that has the ability to project combat power over long distances using aviation, logistical, and ground combat assets. Filmed on November 11, 2016.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Sgt. Donald Holbert and Cpl. Chelsey Courtney

1340.description:
Polish Army Soldiers and U.S. Army Paratroopers exchange anti-tank weapons to keep NATO commitments current and stable. Filmed in Poland on October 29, 2016.
 
Film Credits: SSG Thanh Pham

1341.description: A U.S. Air Force C-5M Super Galaxy and C-17 Globemaster III transport planes land at Incirlik Air Base In Turkey. Filmed in July 2016. Footage courtesy of SSgt Greg Cerny, USAF.

1342.description:
U.S. Marines jump into icy water as part of extreme cold weather training conducted by Soldiers of the Norwegian Army. Marines with Black Sea Rotational Force, filmed in Blåtind, Norway on November 4, 2016.
 
Film Credits: LCpl Timothy Lutz

1343.description:
U.S. Marines practice cold weather driving in the M1 Assault Breacher Vehicle, M88A2 Armored Recovery Vehicle, and M1A1 Abrams Main Battle Tanks in Setermoen, Norway on November 7-9, 2016. Marines from Black Sea Rotational Force conduct extreme cold weather driver training.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Lance Cpl. Timothy J. Lutz

1344.description:
Elements of the 10th Mountain Division, U.S. Army, conduct a live-fire exercise on Range 44 at Fort Drum, NY.  Filmed on November 8, 2016.
 
Film Credits: SFC James Tapin

1345.description:
Flight Deck footage of F/A-18 Super Hornets being recovered aboard the aircraft carrier USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76) during exercise Keen Sword 17 in the Philippine Sea on November 2, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: PO2 Adrienne Powers

1346.description:
Video sequences of U.S. Air Force Aircraft: A-10 Thunderbolt II, C-17 Globemaster III, F-4 Phantom, F-15E Strike Eagle, F-35 Lightning II Joint Strike Fighter, F-22 Raptor.
 
Film Credits: A1C Julian Kemper

1347.description:
U.S. Navy divers conduct new towing techniques and safety procedures with an Orion Space Capsule test vehicle, called the Boilerplate-Testing Article (BTA), in the Pacific Ocean on October 28, 2016. NASA is testing the BTA with the USS San Diego (LPD-22) to reduce personnel required and increase safety. U.S. Navy Units - Explosive Ordnance Disposal Mobile Unit 3 and Mobile Dive and Salvage Company 3-1.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Navy Combat Camera By Petty Officer 3rd Class Alfred A. Coffield

1348.description:
Two Air Force master sergeants became the first enlisted Airmen in six decades to complete solo flights during Initial Flight Training (IFT) at the 1st Flying Training Squadron in Pueblo, Colorado on November 3, 2016. Both soloed in a DA-20 Katana at Pueblo Memorial Airport as part of the Air Force’s IFT program, which is mandatory for all manned aircraft pilots, combat systems officers and remotely piloted aircraft pilots. The Air Force announced on Dec. 17, 2015, the initiative to train enlisted RPA pilots for RQ-4 Global Hawk flying operations. As a result, the Enlisted Pilot Initial Class began Oct. 12 with four students training alongside 20 recently commissioned officers. - http://www.af.mil/News/ArticleDisplay/tabid/223/Article/996754/first-two-enlisted-pilots-complete-solo-flights.aspx
 
Film Credits: SrA Kelly OConnor, A1C Moshe Paul

1349.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a live-fire training event with never before used (in the Marine Corps) Rifle Suppressors on Range 400 at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center (MCAGCC). This Integrated Training Exercise (ITX) 1-17 prepares Marines for future deployments.
 
Film Credits: Sgt Patricia Claypool-Morris

1350.description:
U.S. Marine Corps F/A-18D Hornets and Indonesian Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcons began exercise Cope West 17 at Sam Ratulangi International Airport, Indonesia on November 1, 2016. This fighter-focused, bilateral exercise between the U.S. Marines and Indonesian Air Force is focused on interoperability. Both the U.S. F/A-18D Hornets and Indonesian F-16 Falcons bring unique capabilities. This footage filmed on November 3, 2016. Marine Corps Unit - Marine All-Weather Fighter Attack Squadron 225.
 
Film Credits: Cpl Aaron Henson

1351.description:
M109 Paladin Howitzer fires rounds at Al Asad Air Base in Iraq. Filmed October 2016.

Film Credits: SGT Neil Stanfield

1352.description:
B-52H Bombers get rolling during a MITO (Minimum Interval Takeoff) at Minot Air Force Base in North Dakota. B-52H Stratofortress Bombers provide an effective and ready deterrent force by flying global strike and nuclear deterrence missions. The B-52H is capable of flying thousands of miles, with aerial refueling, and launching up to 26 nuclear tipped cruise missiles on targets from hundreds of miles away. Units - 5th Bomb Wing, 2nd Bomb Wing. Filmed on October 31, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: SSgt Kristine MacDonald

1353.description:
U.S. Combat Camera Marines with Marine Corps Installations-East conduct underwater helicopter egress training at Camp Lejeune, North Carolina on October 25, 2016.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Video by Staff Sgt. Albert J. Carls, MCIEAST Combat Camera/Released

1354.description:
The Marine Corps version of the F-35, the F-35B Lightning II, is undergoing phase 3 developmental testing aboard the amphibious assault ship USS America (LHA-6). Filmed on October 31, 2016.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Petty Officer 1st Class Demetrius Kennon/Released

1355.description:
Canadian CF-188 Hornet fighter jets are highlighted in this NORAD exercise Vigilant Shield 2017 at Thule Air Base, Greenland. Thule is the northernmost base of the U.S. Air Force and is home to the 21st Space Wing's global network of sensors providing missile warning, space surveillance and space control to North American Aerospace Defense Command (NORAD). Exercise Vigilant Shield is an annual exercise sponsored by The North American Aerospace Defense Command and led by Alaskan NORAD Region, in conjunction with Canadian NORAD Region and Continental NORAD Region, who undertake field training exercises aimed at improving operational capability in a bi-national environment. This exercise provides crucial training opportunities for numerous military personnel with a variety of aircraft and assets from Canada and the United States to improve interoperability and to demonstrate NORAD’s ability to defend North America. Filmed in October 2016.
 
Film Credits: SrA Shellby Matullo, SrA Jacob Albers

1356.description:
Airmen from the 816th Expeditionary Airlift Squadron and 332nd Expeditionary Logistics Squadron perform a munitions run in a C-17 Globemaster III to support Operation Inherent Resolve on October 28, 2016. The ordnance was delivered to an undisclosed location in Southwest Asia. Operation Inherent Resolve is the coalition intervention against ISIS. The 816th and the 322nd squadrons are actively engaged in tactical airlift operations supporting the Mosel offensive in Iraq.
 
Film Credits: A1C Joshua Hoskins

1357.description:
An  HC-130 Hercules air tanker from the 102nd Rescue Squadron, New York Air National Guard, conducts aerial refueling training with HH-60G Pave Hawk helicopters during exercise Southern Strike 17 on October 26, 2016. Southern Strike 17 is a total force, multi-service training exercise hosted by the Mississippi Air National Guard’s Combat Readiness Training Center in Gulfport, Mississippi from October 24 through November 4. Filmed on October 26, 2016.
 
Film Credits: SSgt Laura Beckley

1358.description:

1362.description:
Staff Sergeant Reckless was a decorated war horse who held official rank in the United States Marine Corps. She was purchased in October 1952 for $250 In Seoul, Korea and trained to be a pack horse for the Recoilless Rifle Platoon, Anti-Tank Company, 5th Marine Regiment, 1st Marine Division. She served in numerous combat actions during the Korean War, carrying supplies and ammunition, and was also used to evacuate wounded. The highlight of her nine-month military career came in late March 1953 during the Battle for Outpost Vegas when, in a single day, she made 51 solo trips to resupply multiple front line units. She was wounded in combat twice, given the battlefield rank of corporal in 1953, and then a battlefield promotion to sergeant in 1954, then again to Staff Sergeant in 1959. She also became the first horse in the Marine Corps known to have participated in an amphibious landing, and following the war was awarded two Purple Hearts, a Marine Corps Good Conduct Medal, and was included in her unit's Presidential Unit Citations. More info on Staff Sergeant Reckless: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sergeant_Reckless 
 
Film Credits: Cpl Asia Sorenson, This work, Sgt. Reckless: A Horse of a Different Breed, is free of known copyright restrictions under U.S. copyright law. - https://www.dvidshub.net/video/296891/sgt-reckless-horse-different-breed

The four-day competition will include approximately 30 events such as land navigation, advanced marksmanship, medical simulations and more. The Ospreys with the MEUEX launched from Marine Corps Air Station Yuma, AZ -- the Super Stallions with the Long Range Raid Exercise launched from Hubbard Airfield, Ft. Huachuca, AZ. Both exercises were part of Weapons and Tactics Instructor course (WTI) 1-17. WTI is a seven week training event hosted by Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1) cadre which emphasizes operational integration of the six functions of Marine Corps aviation in support of a Marine Air Ground Task Force. MAWTS-1 provides standardized advanced tactical training and certification of unit instructor qualifications to support Marine aviation Training and Readiness and assists in developing and employing aviation weapons and tactics. Evacuated aircraft and designated personnel will return when the storm danger has passed. The A-10s are from the 23rd Fighter Group which includes the 74th, 75th and 76th Fighter Squadrons.

The United Kingdom, Estonia, Poland and Spain, along with 10 other nations are preparing to take over NATO's Very High Readiness Joint Task Force (VJTF) in 2017. The VJTF is NATO’s spearhead force designed to react to a crisis situation at short notice. Filmed on September 15, 2016.

U.S. Navy ship USS Green Bay (LPD-20) launches a RIM-116 Rolling Airframe Missile (RAM) during a live-fire exercise on September 18, 2016. The RIM-116 RAM is primarily intended to defend against anti-ship cruise missiles. It is named "Rolling Airframe Missile" because it rolls around its longitudinal axis to stabilize its flight path, much like a bullet fired from a rifled barrel.

1427.description:
The future USS Zumwalt (DDG-1000) gets underway in Bath, Maine. The Zumwalt will be the world's most technologically advanced warship to date, using an integrated power system (IPS) to provide electric power for propulsion and ship services. The IPS generates approximately 78 megawatts of power, nearly what a nuclear-powered aircraft carrier generates. It will be able to meet the total ship electric power requirements and provide extra capacity to accommodate future weapons and computing systems. In addition to its advanced propulsion systems, Zumwalt is much larger than today's destroyers. At 610 feet long and 80.7 feet wide, Zumwalt is 100 feet longer, with a flight deck that is 93 percent larger than an Arleigh Burke-class destroyer. The U.S. Navy's newest guided-missile destroyer is still designated PCU Zumwalt (pre-commissioned unit) until it is commissioned in Baltimore, Maryland on Oct. 15, 2016.  Filmed on September 7, 2016. More information on the technology of USS Zumwalt here: http://nationalinterest.org/blog/the-buzz/inside-americas-lethal-new-stealth-destroyer-16306
                           
Film Credits: United States Navy Video/Released

1433.description:
Clips showing 120mm mortar systems in action. 

Filme Credits: Sgt Michelle Reif, MSgt Bryce Piper, Sgt Paul Robbins, Sgt Joseph Scanlan, SGT Toby Wall, SGT Alan Brutus

1434.description:
Training footage of the U.S. Army's 4th Brigade Combat Team (Airborne), 25th Infantry Division (Spartan Brigade) - the only U.S. airborne infantry brigade in the Pacific Theater. Their motto is "Sparta Lives". Filmed on August 22, 2016.
 
Film Credits: SSG Daniel Love

1435.description:
U.S. Air Force aircrews prepare aircraft to retaliate after a simulated attack by North Korea during Exercise Beverly Herd 16-2 at Osan Air Base in South Korea. This was a week long exercise held at the end of August 2016. Units - 25th Fighter Squadron, 51st Munitions Squadron, 51st Civil Engineer Squadron, 51st Fighter Wing. 
 
Film Credits: SrA Daniel Robles, SSgt Ashley Manz

1436.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers conduct live fire exercises using UH-60 Black Hawk Helicopters, M2A2 Bradley Fighting Vehicles, and M1A2 Abrams Tanks. Filmed at Pabrade, Lithuania on August 30, 2016. Units - 3rd Battalion, 69th Armor Regiment (3–69 AR) and 3rd Battalion, 501st Aviation Regiment, 10th Combat Aviation Brigade.
 
Film Credits: PFC James Dutkavich

1437.description:
US Army 82nd Airborne Paratroopers execute a mass parachute jump from C-17 Globemaster III transport aircraft with the 8th Airlift Squadron - over Fort Bragg, NC on July 12, 2016. 

Film Credits: TSgt Jose Rodriguez

1438.description:
Documentary farewell to the B-52 Stratofortress bomber aircraft at Andersen Air Force Base in Guam. 
 
Film Credits: SrA Ameka Mmoh

1439.description:
U.S. Air Force aircrew flying MC-130H Combat Talon II from the 15th Special Operations Squadron conduct low-level flight training and mass container drop system (CDS) training during Task Force Exercise Olympus Archer at Wright Patterson Air Force Base, OH on August 21, 2016.  
 
Film Credits: A1C James Merriman

1440.description:
Paratroopers from the 82nd Airborne Division fire the M3 Multi-role Anti-armor Anti-tank Weapon System (MAAWS) during a qualification range on Fort Bragg, NC on August, 30 2016. The M3 MAAWS, also known as the Carl Gustaf Recoilless Rifle, is an 84mm man-portable, multi-role, parachute jumpable, recoil-less rifle that can be reloaded and fired multiple times. 
 
Film Credits: SGT Jonathan Cobert

1441.description:
U.S. Soldiers (Airborne) assigned to Special Operations Command Europe (SOCEUR) execute parachute free-fall training over a drop-zone at Malmsheim, Germany on August 17, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: U.S. Army video by Visual Information Specialist Jason Johnston and U.S. Airman Senior Master Sergeant Dean L. Unger/Released

1442.description:
GoPro view of a U.S. Marine Corps UH-1Y Super Huey helicopter firing Hydra 70 Rockets during Exercise Koolendong 16 at Bradshaw Field Training Area, Northern Territory, Australia on August 29, 2016. Unit - Marine Light Attack Helicopter Squadron 367 (HMLA-367).  
 
Film Credits: MCIPAC Combat Camera Cpl. Jordan Walker

1443.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcons assigned to the 455th Air Expeditionary Wing takeoff from Bagram Airfield in Afghanistan - day and night footage. Filmed on August 25, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: SrA Robert Dantzler

1444.description:
Ordnance crewmembers from the USAF 18th Aircraft Maintenance Squadron load live munitions on F-15 Eagle aircraft at Kadena Air Base on Okinawa Japan - August 22, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: A1C James Merriman

1445.description:
U.S. Air Force Combat Control Teams (CCT) with the 21st Special Tactics Squadron conduct military free fall jumps from CV-22 Ospreys with the 8th Special Operations Squadron. The training jumps were part of Task Force Exercise Olympus Archer at Wright Patterson Air Force Base in Ohio. The focus of Olympus Archer is to maximize training opportunities for more than 230 Air Commandos with the the 1st Special Operations Wing. Filmed on August 18, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: A1C James Merriman

1446.description:
U.S. Army Paratroopers from the 82nd Airborne Division load onto C-17 Globemaster III and C-130 J Super Hercules Aircraft at Pope Army Air Field, NC and Fort Polk, LA on July 13-16, 2016 as part of an Emergency Deployment Readiness Exercise called Operation Devil Strike. Operation Devil Strike was an exercise to ensure the ability to deploy Global Response Force infantry assault troops on short notice. 
 
Film Credits: SrA Nicholas Priest

1447.description:
U.S. Air Force advisers with Train, Advise, Assist Command-Air (TAAC-Air) fly Afghan air force MD-530F Cayuse Warrior helicopters to a range near Kabul, Afghanistan, for live-fire training on Aug. 11, 2016. TAAC-Air is part of the 438th Air Expeditionary Wing. 
 
Film Credits: SSgt Aaron Richardson

1448.description:
Maintainers use dummy rounds to test the weapons systems on an AH-64D Apache Helicopter from D. Co. 1st of the 151st ARB, SCARNG. An ammunition handling check is done periodically to check the onboard weapons systems to include the 30mm M230 E1 Automatic Gun, the AGM-114 Hellfire Missile and the Hydra 70 Rocket. 

Film Credits: MSgt Carl Clegg

1449.description:
U.S. Service members from the Train, Advise, Assist, Command-Air (TAAC-Air) fly Afghan Air Force A-29 Super Tucanos to a range in Afghanistan to demonstrate the aircraft's close air support ability August 14, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: SSgt Aaron Richardson

1450.description:
U.S. Army BGM-71 TOW anti-tank missiles fired from mounted Humvees and Bradley Fighting Vehicles. All footage filmed in 2015 and 2016. TOW stands for - Tube-launched, Optically tracked, Wire-guided. 

Film Credits: Gerhard Seuffert, Matthias Fruth, SSG Scott Shoemaker, Matthew Oldham

1451.description:
Air Force F-35A Joint Strike Fighters and Navy EA-18G Growler electronic warfare aircraft takeoff and land at Volk Field Air National Guard Base on August 22, 2016. Members of the 58th Fighter Squadron and F-35A's from Eglin AFB, Florida deployed to Volk Field to integrate with 4th generation aircraft from the Air Force and Navy in aerial combat exercise Northern Lighting. It is the largest F-35 Lightning II deployment to date.  

Film Credits: SSgt Tarelle Walker

1452.description:
B-52H Stratofortress Bombers taxi, takeoff and land during Red flag 16-3 air combat exercise on July 9, 2016. Red Flag is a realistic combat training exercise involving the air, space, and cyber forces of the USA and allies. It takes place at Nellis Air Force Base north of Las Vegas, and on the Nevada Test and Training Range which has more than 15,000 square miles of airspace and 2.9 million acres of land. 

Film Credits: A1C Christina Ensley, William Lewis, 99th Air Base Wing Public Affairs

1453.description:
U.S. Army M1A2 Abrams Tank Crews with 3rd Battalion, 69th Armor Regiment conduct bounding maneuvers during a live-fire exercise at Adazi, Latvia on August 22, 2016. 

Film Credits: SSG Anthony King

1454.description:
U.S. Marines conduct comprehensive live-fire training at Bradshaw Field Training Area, Northern Territory, Australia during Exercise Koolendong 2016. The Marines with 1st Battalion, 1st Marine Regiment are part of Marine Rotational Force - Darwin, and  Exercise Koolendong is a tri-lateral training exercise between U.S. Marines, Australian Defense Forces, and French Armed Forces New Caledonia. All footage filmed in August, 2016.  

Film Credits: MCIPAC Combat Camera Cpl. Jordan Walker

1455.description:
Navy SEAL and Marine Corps Forces Special Operations Command (MARSOC) members conduct free fall training jumps from Black Hawk helicopters over Stuttgart, Germany on August 19, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: SSG Kerry Collier

1456.description:
U.S. Army Special Forces soldiers drop in by Black Hawk helicopters on the Fast Rope Insertion Extraction System (FRIES) in Stuttgart, Germany on August 19, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: SSG Kerry Collier

1457.description:
U.S. Marines and Soldiers with the French Armed Forces New Caledonia (FANC) swap small arms on a live-fire target range during Exercise Koolendong 2016 at Bradshaw Field Training Area, Northern Territory in Australia on August 17, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: MCIPAC Combat Camera Cpl. Jordan D. Walker

1458.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a movement to contact drill at Bradshaw Field Training Area, Northern Territory, in Australia on August 10, 2016. Marines with 1st Battalion, 1st Marine Regiment, Marine Rotational Force - Darwin are taking part in Exercise Koolendong , a tri-lateral training exercise between U.S. Marines, Australian Defense Forces and French Armed Forces New Caledonia.
 
Film Credits: MCIPAC Combat Camera Cpl. Jordan D. Walker

1459.description:
The amphibious transport dock ship USS Green Bay (LPD-20) fires MK-46 30mm gun during a live-fire exercise on August 17, 2016.  
 
Film Credits: PO3 Patrick Dionne

1460.description:
Scenes from Red Flag Aerial Combat Exercise...  various multinational warplanes taxis, takeoff, and land at Nellis Air Force Base in Nevada.  
 
Film Credits: A1C Christina Ensley, A1C Mychal Fox, William Lewis, TSgt Scott Olguin, SrA Aaron Hauser, SrA Rachel Maxwell, TSgt Colleen Urban, A1C Rachel Webster, Lea Greene, SSgt Cody Griffith, SSgt Annemarie Stella

1461.description:
U.S. Marines with Delta Company, 1st Tank Battalion, 1st Marine Division conduct Large Scale Exercise (LSE) at Marine Air Ground Command Center Twentynine Palms, California on August 18, 2016.
 
Film Credits: LCpl Shellie Hall

1462.description:
F-35C Carrier Variants of the Lightning II Joint Strike Fighter conduct flight operations aboard the aircraft carrier USS George Washington (CVN-73) on August 14, 2016. The F-35C is going through its third and final developmental test phase (DT-III) and starting carrier qualifications. The F-35C is expected to be Fleet operational in 2018. Units - Salty Dogs of Air Test and Evaluation Squadron (VX-23) and Grim Reapers of Strike Fighter Squadron (VFA-101).
 
Film Credits: Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Anna Van Nuys, Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Jonathan Price, Mass Communication Specialist Seaman Brian Sipe

1463.description:
Three main bomber aircraft in the U.S. Air Force arsenal, the B-1 Lancer, B-2 Spirit, and B-52 Stratofortress, have been moved to Andersen Air Force Base in Guam to conduct integrated aerial exercises for the first time in history. Filmed on August 16-17, 2016.
 
Film Credits: A1C Nathan Eckert

1464.description:
Multiple clips of E-2C Hawkeyes during land based refueling, and launch/landing aboard U.S. Navy aircraft carriers. The Northrop Grumman E-2C Hawkeye is a twin-turboprop plane designed to be an airborne early warning and control platform. It has advanced radar and surveillance capabilities which allow it to detect enemy aircraft and missile activity, and communicate these threats to friendly aircraft and land forces. More info about the E-2C Hawkeye here: http://www.navair.navy.mil/index.cfm?fuseaction=home.displayPlatform&key=FAD3E30B-AD5C-441A-8925-624BD0BA45F1 

Film Credits: Cpl Waiyan Tin, MC3 Ryan Seelbach, MC3 Jon Price, Gregory Wilhelmi, PO3 Joshua Haiar

1465.description:
Members of the 305th Rescue Squadron prepare for helicopter flight training. The 305th Rescue Squadron is part of the 943rd Rescue Group, a reserve component of the U.S. Air Force which is stationed at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base, Arizona. When mobilized, the 943rd is tasked to support combat rescue operations under control of the Air Combat Command. Filmed on May 18, 2016.

Film Credits: A1C Jean-Paul Arnaud-Marquez

1466.description:
Marine Corps UH-1Y Venom door gunners (crew chiefs) fire the GAU-21 .50 Caliber machine gun and the GAU-17 minigun during a training mission at Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range in California on April 12, 2016.

Film Credits: A1C Tybee Hurst

1467.description:
F-22 Raptors from the 43rd Fighter Squadron and T-38 Talons from the 2nd Fighter Training Squadron are shown during day two flight line operations from exercise Sentry Savannah 16-3 at The Air Dominance Center in Georgia. Filmed on August 2, 2016. 

Film Credits: A1C Tybee Hurst

1468.description:
U.S. Marines with the 25th Marine Regiment practice a beach landing in amphibious assault vehicles at Grayling Aerial Gunnery Range in Michigan on August 11, 2016.

Film Credits: TSgt Timothy Diephouse

1469.description:
U.S. Air Force maintenance crews at Al Udeid Air Base, QA perform post flight checks and rearming of a B-52 Bomber after it returns from a mission on June 2, 2016. Unit - 379th Air Expeditionary Wing.

Film Credits: SSgt Tory Patterson

1470.description:
Cockpit video from a U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcon fighter jet.

Film Credits: SSgt Erin Mills

1471.description:
The AH-64 Apache Helicopter is the most effective attack helicopter in the world.

Film Credits: Christoph Koppers, SFC Eric Pahon, SSG Mark Shrewsbury, PO1 Michael Sandberg, and SSG Justin Puetz

1472.description:
HMAS Canberra (L02) arrives at Pearl Harbor, departs Pearl Harbor, plus flight deck operations with helicopters landing and taking-off. Canberra is classified as a Landing Helicopter Dock ship, also sometime called a light aircraft carrier. All footage filmed during Exercise RIMPAC in July 2016.

Film Credits: PO2 Johans Chavarro, PO2 Laurie Dexter, Royal Australian Navy Video by Leading Seaman Tom Gibson

1473.description:
