Bravo Company, 3rd Combined Arms Battalion, 69th Armor Regiment, U.S. Army, conduct a Joint Company Live Fire Exercise with Lithuanian and Polish Troops during Operation Atlantic Resolve in Rukla, Lithuania on August 11, 2016.

Film Credits: SSG Anthony King

1474.description:
Pilots assigned to the Screwtops of Airborne Early Warning (VAW-123) are awarded the Armed Forces’ Air Medal aboard the aircraft carrier USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN 69). They saved their E-2C Hawkeye from crashing into the sea after an arresting cable snapped while landing.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Michael R. Gendron/Released

1475.description:
M109A3 "Paladin" Self-Propelled Howitzers from 1st Battalion, 41st Field Artillery Regiment fire rounds down range during Exercise Flaming Thunder at Pabrade Training Area in Lithuania on August 9, 2016.

Film Credits: SSG Anthony King

1476.description:
54th Fighter Group F-16s taxiing and taking off from Holloman Air Force Base, New Mexico. The 54th Fighter Group is a tenant unit from Luke Air Force Base, Ariz. The 54th Fighter Group is responsible for two F-16 pilot training squadrons, the 311th and 314th Fighter Squadrons. Tail flashes include LF for Luke Air Force Base, and HO for Holloman Air Force Base. Filmed on August 5, 2016.

Film Credits: SrA BreeAnn Sachs

1477.description:
F-22 Raptors from Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson takeoff at night with full afterburners. Filmed on June 6, 2016.

Film Credits: A1C Jared Bunn

1478.description:
U.S. Military Hand Grenade Training Footage.

Film Credits: Sgt Robert Bush, SSG Sean Everette, SSgt Erik Cardenas, LCpl Jenna Loofe, Martin Greeson

1479.description:
U.S. Army Air Cavalry units conduct live-fire air assault at Rodriguez Live Fire Range in South Korea on August 6, 2016. Units - 2nd Battalion, 12th Regiment and 1st Squadron, 17th Regiment. Filmed on August 6, 2016.

Film Credits: SGT Fred Brown, SGT Christopher Dennis

1480.description:
U-2 reconnaissance planes, nicknamed the "Dragon Lady", take off from Beale Air Force Base, CA and land at RAF Fairford, UK - with wide field of views and chase car views. Unit - 9th Reconnaissance Wing. Filmed June 6, 2016.

Film Credits: SrA Benjamin Bugenig

1481.description:
Footage of six different U.S. Military Aircraft operating at undisclosed locations in Southwest Asia - including takeoffs, landings, inflight refueling, and flight line checks. In order of appearance: KC-10 Extender, E-3 Sentry, U-2 Dragon Lady, RQ-4 Global Hawk, EA-6B Prowler, F-15 Strike Eagle. All footage filmed in July, 2016.

Film Credits: SSgt Aaron Richardson

1482.description:
AC-130J Ghostrider Gunship landing and taxi to the flight line at Hurlburt Field, FL on July 18, 2016.

Film Credits: TSgt Eric Craft, A1C James Merriman

1483.description:
Flight line operations featuring F-22 Raptors during day one of Exercise Sentry Savannah 16-3 at The Air Dominance Center in Savannah, GA. Filmed on August 8, 2016. Unit - 43rd Fighter Squadron.

Film Credits: A1C Tybee Hurst

1484.description:
U.S. Marines tested a variety of new technology, including Robots at Twentynine Palms, CA during Marine Air Ground Task Force (MAGTF) Integrated Experiment (MIX-16). MIX-16 tests 21st century concepts in a realistic environment likely to be seen in the future. Filmed on July 25 - August 5, 2016.

Film Credits: LCpl Molly Hampton

1485.description:
U.S. F-22 Raptor fighter jet aircrews conduct preflight checks before launch at an undisclosed location overseas. Plus aerial refueling and closeup views of the aircraft in-flight. Filmed on July 11 and July 13, 2016.

Film Credits: SSgt Aaron Richardson

1486.description:
U.S. B-1 Lancer bombers, nicknamed The Bone, arrive at Andersen Air Force Base in Guam on August 8, 2016.

Film Credits: A1C Nathan Eckert

1487.description:
A U.S. Air Force pilot preps and flies a U-2 Dragon Lady reconnaissance plane (including cockpit video) on a mission from an undisclosed location overseas on July 14, 2016. Unit - 99th Expeditionary Reconnaissance Squadron.

Film Credit: SSgt Aaron Richardson

1488.description:
Overhead drone footage of combined arms live fire exercise with U.S. Army M1A2 tanks from the 3rd Battalion, 116th Cavalry Brigade Combat Team, Oregon and Idaho National Guard. Filmed on August 6, 2016 during Exercise Saber Guardian 16 at Cincu Training Center, Romania.

Film Credit: CPT John Farmer, SPC Mackenzie Layne

1489.description:
U.S. Army 82nd Airborne Division Paratroopers execute training jumps from C-17 Globemaster III planes over Fort Bragg, NC. All footage is from a mass-tactical jump conducted on July 12-13, 2016 as part of Battalion Mass-Tactical Week 16-07. The purpose of Battalion Mass-Tactical Week 16-07 is to increase Air Force and Army efficiency in executing a Joint Forcible Entry Operation. USAF Unit - 8th Airlift Squadron.

Film Credit: TSgt Jose Rodriguez

1490.description:
U.S. Soldiers construct an improved ribbon bridge over the Olt River in Romania then execute a tactical crossing over the floating bridge with U.S. and Romanian armored vehicles under simulated attack. Filmed August 1-4, 2016. Units - 125th Multi-Role Bridge Company (MRBC) and 1st Battalion, 64th Armor Regiment, 1st Armored Brigade Combat Team, 3rd Infantry Division plus Romanian Land Forces.

Film Credit: 1SG Kevin Hartman, CPT John Farmer, SPC Devone Collins

1491.description:
Marine Corps M1A1 Tank Crews with 2nd Tank Battalion and 4th Tank Battalion integrated in a week-long exercise at Camp Lejeune, NC to train for future deployment. Filmed July 18-21, 2016. 

Film Credit: Sgt Matthew Callahan

1492.description:
Royal Australian Regiment (RAR) infantry soldiers conduct live-fire operations during RIMPAC 2016 at Pōhakuloa Training Area, HI. The 2nd Battalion RAR conducted live-fire training over a ten day period during Rim of the Pacific (RIMPAC) 2016. RIMPAC is the world's largest maritime exercise including 26 nations from June 29 to August 4. 

Film Credit: POIS Paul Berry/Royal Australian Navy

1493.description:
U.S. Navy Seal Team 1 jump from an MC-130J﻿ Super Hercules into water with no helmet. Filmed on July 26, 2016. 

Film Credit: Sgt William Holdaway

1494.description:
The Littoral Combat Ship USS Coronado (LCS-4) enters Pearl Harbor. The Coronado has a high-speed trimaran hull and is designed to defeat all coastal threats. Filmed on August 1, 2016.

Film Credit: PO2 Johans Chavarro

1495.description:
Polar Roar is a U.S. Air Force exercise to send a message to Russia with B-52 bombers launched from Alaska and navigating over the North Pole towards the Baltic Sea region. Filmed on August 1, 2016.

Film Credit: A1C Jayson Burns

1496.description:
U.S. Marines transported by CH-53E helicopters conduct a fast insertion air raid with the EFSS 120MM - M327 Mortar system at Camp Hansen, Okinawa, Japan on June 30th, 2016.

Film Credit: LCpl David Diggs

1497.description:
Multinational warships conduct replenishment at sea (RAS) with fast combat support ship USNS Rainier (T-AOE 7) during RIMPAC 2016. The ships in order of appearance: HMCS Calgary (FFH 335) • JS Chokai (DDG 176) • USS Mobile Bay (CG 53) • USS William P. Lawrence (DDG 110) • USS John C. Stennis (CVN 74). RIMPAC (Rim of the Pacific) is the world's largest maritime exercise including 26 nations, more than 40 ships and submarines, more than 200 aircraft, and 25,000 personnel. RIMPAC 2016 goes from June 30 to August 4, in and around the Hawaiian Islands and Southern California. Filmed on July 26, 2016.

Film Credit: PO2 Antonio Turretto Ramos, PO3 Christopher Veloicaza, PO3 Neil Grim

1498.description:
Slow Motion footage of various aircraft demonstrations during the Arctic Thunder Open House 2016 Airshow at Joint Base Elmendorf–Richardson, AK on July 30, 2016.

Film Credit: A1C Joshua DeGuzman

1499.description:
U.S. Army M-1 Abrams tanks conduct a gunnery exercise at Trzebien Training Area in Poland on July 28, 2016. Unit - D-Co, 3rd Battalion, 69th Armor Regiment.

Film Credit: SSG Thanh Pham

1500.description:
U.S. Navy P-3 Orion from Patrol Squadron One (VP-1) conducts an anti-submarine and maritime surveillance sortie during Exercise RIMPAC 2016 on July 29, 2016.

Film Credit: PO2 Katarzyna Kobiljak

1501.description:
U.S. Air force A-10 Thunderbolts and KC-135 Stratotankers deployed at Ämari Air Base in Estonia on July 28, 2016. Units - 442nd Fighter Wing and 185th Air Refueling Wing

Film Credit: SSgt David Asbra

1502.description:
An ISIS vehicle is destroyed near Manbij, Syria by a guided bomb and drives into a tree on July 27, 2016.

Film Credit: https://www.dvidshub.net/video/476488/jul-3-coalition-aircraft-destroys-daesh-vehicle-near-manbij-syria

1503.description:
Helicopter view of mass warship formation including 40 ships and submarines sailing in formation during RIMPAC 2016. Rim of the Pacific (RIMPAC) is the world's largest maritime exercise including 26 nations, more than 40 ships and submarines, more than 200 aircraft, and 25,000 personnel. Filmed on July 28, 2016.

Film Credit: PO1 Paul Seeber

1504.description:
Forty ships and submarines from 13 nations sail in close formation during Rim of the Pacific (RIMPAC) 2016 on July 28, 2016. RIMPAC is the world's largest international maritime exercise including 26 nations, more than 40 ships and submarines, more than 200 aircraft, and 25,000 personnel from June 30 to August 4.

 Film Credits: U.S. Navy Combat Camera by Chief Mass Communication Specialist Paul Seeber - Released

1505.description:
The F-35B Joint Strike Fighter introduced itself to Exercise Red Flag at Nellis AFB for the first time in July 2016. Plus, Four F-35A Lightning II fighter jets fly in formation above Hill AFB in Utah on July 25, 2016.

 Film Credits: A1C Megan Qualls, SSgt Danny Rangel

1506.description:
Eight Humvees are air dropped from a C-17 cargo plane over Fort Bragg, NC during exercise Crescent Reach 16. Crescent Reach is an annual exercise designed to test and evaluate Joint Base Charleston’s ability to mobilize and launch a large-scale aircraft formation in addition to train, process and deploy Airmen and cargo in response to a simulated crisis abroad. Filmed on May 26, 2016.

Film Credits: TSgt Jose Rodriguez

1507.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 120th Fighter Squadron participate in Operation Panther Strike at Pápa Air Base in Hungary. Panther Strike is part of Operation Atlantic Resolve, a show of solidarity by the U.S. to NATO allies. Filmed July 19-22, 2016.

 Film Credits: MSgt Wolfram M. Stumpf

1508.description:
USS Arleigh Burke (DDG-51) launches three SM-2 Standard Missiles from the aft Vertical launching System as part of their Combat System Ship Qualification Trials (CSSQT). The Spanish navy ship Cristobol Colon (F-105) and Arleigh Burke are conducting cooperative air defense test exercises including Tactical Data Link interoperability and live missile firing events. These events are the first interoperability test of the latest AEGIS Baseline 9.C1 with a foreign ship, as well as the first combined Combat Systems Ship Qualification Trial with the Spanish navy since 2007. Filmed on July 21, 2016.

 Film Credits: PO1 Gary Prill, Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Shelby Tucker

1509.description:
Ground Crew at Mountain Home Air Force Base prepares the F-35A fighter jet to takeoff. Filmed on June 1, 2016.

 Film Credits: SSgt Sarah Trachte

1510.description:
WWII Era P-38 Lightning flies with an F-35A Lightning II and F-16 Fighting Falcon over the skies of Utah on October 14, 2015.

 Film Credits: SSgt Benjamin Landon

1511.description:
MK-38 25 mm machine gun system fires from the amphibious assault ship USS Boxer (LHD 4) during an integrated live fire exercise on July 27, 2016. Plus instructors teach from past naval exercises.

 Film Credits: PO3 Michael Eckelbecker, PO2 Patrick Kelley, PO3 David Flewellyn, PO3 Patrick Dionn

1512.description:
U.S. Navy F-18 Hornets and Canadian CF-18 Hornets refueled by KC-135R Stratotanker during RIMPAC 2016. The world's largest international maritime exercise, RIMPAC includes 26 nations, more than 40 ships and submarines, more than 200 aircraft, and 25,000 personnel. RIMPAC 2016 is the 25th exercise in the series that began in 1971. Filmed on July 23, 2016.

 Film Credits: TSgt Lauren Gleason

1513.description:
At Langley Air Force Base, the U.S. Air Force celebrates the 95th anniversary of William "Billy" Mitchell, the U.S. Army General who is regarded as the father of the United States Air Force. Aircraft in the video are: B-1 Bomber, B-52 Bomber, F-15 Eagle, F-22 Raptor, and T-38 Talon. Plus cockpit video from a T-38 during the flyover. Filmed on July 22, 2016.

 Film Credits: A1C Nicolas Myers

1514.description:
U.S. Air Force A-10 Thunderbolt II Warthogs from the 122nd Fighter Wing, Indiana Air National Guard during a training event in Sliac, Slovakia on July 26, 2016.

 Film Credits: A1C Ericha Guyote

1515.description:
Additional Footage of three F-35B Lightning II fighters jets (2 USMC and 1 RAF) making a transatlantic flight from MacDill Air Force Base to RAF Fairford, with an escort of two KC-10 Extender air tankers. This flight marked the first time the F-35B traveled across the Atlantic. Filmed on June 29, 2016.

 Film Credits: SrA Scott Taylor

1516.description:
Flight Deck Crew Members of the USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN-69) launch and recover planes while on patrol in the Arabian Sea on July 22, 2016. For more USN aircraft carrier videos look at this playlist - https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLnOwvB9zfF0xhPw_Mi5nMwu5MzpkoteOr

 Film Credits: Jonathan Snyder

1517.description:
The U.S. F-35A Joint Strike Fighter is being perfected and the software bugs are being eliminated on it's way to Initial Operating Capability (IOC).  Film released on July 25, 2016.

 Film Credits: A1C Chelsie Taddonio

1518.description:
Cockpit and aerial video of U.S. Army UH-72A Lakota Helicopters flying above Volk Field Air National Guard Base, WI. Filmed on July 15, 2016. Unit -  Indiana National Guard, Company C, Detachment 1, 1st Battalion, 376th Aviation Regiment.

 Film Credits: SSgt Nikoletta Kanakis

1519.description:
U.S. Marines with Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 262, practice ditching techniques inside of the helo dunker, underwater egress trainer at Camp Hansen, Okinawa in Japan on July 18, 2016.

 Film Credits: LCpl David Diggs

1520.description:
Closeup views of U.S. Marine Corps F/A-18 Hornet fighter jets refueling inflight during RIMPAC 2016. Unit - Marine Fighter Attack Squadron 115

 Film Credits: Sgt William Holdaway

1521.description:
The HMCS Vancouver (FFH 331) conducts a replenishment-at-sea in the Pacific Ocean during Rim of the Pacific 2016 (RIMPAC). Twenty-six nations, more than 40 ships and submarines, more than 200 aircraft and 25,000 personnel are participating in RIMPAC from June 30 to Aug. 4, in and around the Hawaiian Islands and Southern California. The world's largest international maritime exercise, RIMPAC provides a unique training opportunity that helps participants to foster and sustain the cooperative relationships that are critical to ensuring the safety of sea lanes and security on the world's oceans. RIMPAC 2016 is the 25th exercise in the series that began in 1971

 Film Credits: Canadian Forces Combat Camera video by MCpl Mathieu Gaudreault

1522.description:
F-35A Lightning II aircraft execute aerial refuelings with a KC-10 Extender July 13, 2016 on the flight from England to the United States. The fighters were returning to Luke Air Force Base in Arizona after participating in the world's largest air show, the Royal International Air Tattoo at RAF Fairford.

 Film Credits: U.S. Air Force Video By SSgt. Madelyn Brown

1523.description:
U.S. Marine Corps F-35B Aircraft participate in exercise Red Flag 16-3 at Nellis Air Force Base just 15 miles north of Las Vegas NV. This marks the first time Marines have participated in Red Flag with the F-35B. Filmed On July 19, 2016. Unit - 3rd Marine Aircraft Wing, Marine Fighter Attack Squadron 121

 Film Credits: A1C Christina Ensley

1524.description:
U.S. Army paratroopers from the 82nd Airborne Division go through French Jungle Warfare School in Gabon, Africa - filmed June 2016. 

 Film Credits: Pfc. Deven Waller, SFC Brien Vorhees, SGT Henrique de Holleben

1525.description:
Joint Multinational Training Group-Ukraine special forces from America, Canada, and Ukraine train with various sniper rifles. Filmed in Yavoriv, UA on July 19, 2016.

 Film Credits: SGT Jacob Holmes

1526.description:
RIMPAC 2016 action on the aircraft carrier USS John C. Stennis (CVN-74) during flight deck operations. RIMPAC (Rim of the Pacific) is the world's largest multinational naval exercise, held every 2 years. For more info on RIMPAC: http://www.public.navy.mil/surfor/Pages/RIMPAC-2016.aspx#.V43nDuIrKM8

 Film Credits: PO3 Neil Grim

1527.description:
U.S. Marines rifle marksmanship qualification on tables 1 and 2 at Marine Corps Air Station Yuma, AZ. For more info on the tables read this: https://www.quora.com/What-do-you-have-to-do-to-get-an-Expert-score-in-the-US-Marine-Corps-rifle-and-pistol-qualification-tests - Or this: http://www.marines.mil/Portals/59/MCO%203574.2K.pdf - Filmed July 2016.

Film Credits: Cpl Conner Robbins

1528.description:
Aircraft Carrier USS John C. Stennis (CVN-74) conducts a live-fire operation of the Close-In Weapons System (CIWS) during RIMPC 2016 on July 17, 2016.

Film Credits: MCSA William Ford

1529.description:
Warships depart Pearl Harbor Naval Base for RIMPAC (Rim of the Pacific) 2016. RIMPAC is the world's largest international maritime exercise. Twenty-six nations, more than 40 ships and submarines, more than 200 aircraft and 25,000 personnel are participating from June 30 to August 4, in and around the Hawaiian Islands and Southern California. Time Lapse footage filmed in July 2016 and music added by Gung Ho Vids.

Film Credits: PO1 Benjamin Lewis
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

1530.description:
United States Marine Corps pilots and crew members conduct pre-flight checks on their F/A-18C Hornet fighter jets before taxiing to the runway for takeoff at Tyndall Air Force Base during a deployment for training (DFT). Filmed in 2013. Unit - Marine Fighter Attack Squadron 232 (VMFA-232).

Film Credits: Cpl. Jesse Witten, 3rd MAW Combat Camera

1531.description:
Members of the U.S. Air Force, 83rd Expeditionary Rescue Squadron (Bagram Airfield, AF), describe the job they do. They are ready 24/7 to drop whatever they’re doing, start up a helo and get to a comrade that needs help. Their goal is to “make your bad day not your last day.” Filmed on July 13, 2016.

Film Credits: SrA Robert Dantzler

1532.description:
U.S. Marines alongside Australian and Indonesian service members conduct an amphibious raid training scenario at Kahuku Training Area, HI during Rim of the Pacific (RIMPAC) 2016. RIMPAC is held every 2 years and is the world’s largest international maritime exercise - including Twenty-six nations, 49 ships, six submarines, about 200 aircraft, and 25,000 personnel. Filmed on July 13, 2016. 

Film Credits: LCpl Rene Lucerobonilla

1533.description:
Aerial view of the decommissioned USS Thach (FFG-43) being hit by missiles and torpedoes during a live-fire sinking exercise (SINKEX) as part of RIMPAC 2016 near Hawaii. Units from Australia, the Republic of Korea, and the U.S. participated in the SINKEX to gain proficiency in tactics and targeting against a surface combatant. The USS Thach was an Oliver Hazard Perry-class frigate of the U.S. Navy and was decommissioned and struck in November 2013. RIMPAC (Rim of the Pacific) is the world's largest international maritime exercise, including twenty-six nations, more than 40 ships and submarines, more than 200 aircraft, and 25,000 personnel - held every 2 years. Filmed on July 14, 2016. More info on the USS Thach SINKEX and environmental impact here: https://www.dvidshub.net/news/204149/rimpac-units-participate-sinking-exercise

Film Credits: PO1 Dominique Canales

1534.description:
Flying in Sikorsky MH-60S Seahawks, members of Helicopter Sea Combat Squadron Six (HSC-6) conduct training evolutions during RIMPAC 2016 at Marine Corps Training Area Bellows, HI. HSC-6 is based at Naval Air Station North Island, is part of Carrier Air Wing 11, and deploys aboard the aircraft carrier USS Nimitz (CVN-68). Filmed on July 14, 2016.

Film Credits: PO1 Benjamin Lewis

1535.description:
F-16 fighter jet pilots and crew members from the South Carolina Air National Guard (SCANG) prep and launch, headed to Osan Air Base, South Korea for a U.S. Pacific Command Theater Security Package (TSP) deployment. The 169th Fighter Wing jets launched from McEntire Joint National Guard Base on July 11, 2016.  Approximately 300 Airmen and 12 F-16 Fighting Falcons will form the 157th Expeditionary Fighter Squadron while deployed.

Film Credits: SMSgt Edward Snyder

1536.description:
U.S. Marines and a member of U.S. Army-Task Force Atlas train Iraqi Army explosive ordinance disposal (EOD) technicians on the anti-personnel obstacle breaching system (APOBS) at Al Asad Air Base in Iraq on July 2, 2016. APOBS is an explosive line charge system that allows breaching through antipersonnel obstacles. It is used in Iraq particularly to defeat improvised explosive devices (IEDs). Task Force Atlas is the counter-improvise explosive device (CIED) task force for the Combined Joint Task Force - Operation Inherent Resolve.

Film Credits: SGT Kalie Jones

1537.description:
Royal Australian Navy Ship HMAS Canberra (L02) conducts a ship-to-shore transfer of troops and equipment via amphibious landing craft near Pohakuloa Training Area, HI - as part of exercise RIMPAC 2016. Filmed on July 12, 2016. Unit - 2nd Battalion, Royal Australian Regiment

Film Credits: Cpl Natalie Dillon

1538.description:
U.S. Marines and Canadian Soldiers enter the Infantry Immersion Trainer (IIT) at Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton, CA. The IIT is  a training facility for “hands on” practical application of tactical skills and decision making in an immersive, realistic scenario training environment. Formerly a tomato packing plant, the IIT has been turned into an embattled Middle Eastern town through the use of sets, actors, and special effects such as projections, pyrotechnics, sounds, and smells. The combination of live and virtual training is what makes this an example of immersive training.

Film Credits: Cpl Rachael Zilliox, SSgt Kevin Maynard

1539.description:
F-35B demonstrates some aerial capabilities during the 2016 Farnborough International Airshow in Great Britain. The F-35B is the U.S. Marine Corps version of the Lightning II Joint Strike Fighter.

Film Credits: SrA Rebecca Long

1540.description:
Prep and launch of BQM-167A aerial targets, a sub-scale aerial target system designed and manufactured by Composite Engineering for the U.S. Air Force. The system can be deployed to provide target drones for the test and evaluation of new air-to-air weapons systems of the USAF and the US Department of Defense. BQM-167A targets are operated and maintained by the 82nd Aerial Targets Squadron at Tyndall Air Force Base in Florida. Filmed on July 13, 2016.

Film Credits: MSgt Burt Traynor

1541.description:
A C-17 transport plane lands and unloads a Patriot Missile Battery and Royal Netherlands Army Soldiers on White Sands Missile Range, NM. Dutch and US Soldiers set up the Patriot system as part of an emergency rapid deployment exercise on June 19, 2016.  

Film Credits:  John Hamilton

1542.description:
Strykers and armored fighting vehicles in action during tranining exercises. Filmed 2016.

Film Credits: SGT Kyle Burns, SGT Alan Brutus,  SGT Nikayla Shodeen, SFC Ben Houtkooper, SPC James Garvin

1543.description:
F-16 fighter jets are refueled in "hot pit" operations at Shaw Air Force Base on June 22, 2016. Airmen from the 20th Petroleum Oil and Lubricant Shop quickly refueled the jets on the flight line. Hot pit means the aircraft is refueled as engines are still running to decrease turn around time. 

Film Credits: A1C Justin Warren

1544.description:
U.S Soldiers fire M142 high mobility rocket system and M777 howitzers from Kara Soar Base, Iraq during an operation to support the Iraqi Army. Filmed on June 13, 2016. Unit - 1st Battalion, 320th Field Artillery Battalion, 2nd Brigade Combat Team, 101st Airborne Division (Air Assault) and 1st Battalion, 182nd Field Artillery Regiment.  

Film Credits:  1LT Daniel Johnson

1545.description:
U.S. Air Force Combat Control Team instructors and Special Operations Weather Team instructors from the 334th and 335th Training Squadrons conduct a training jump at Keesler Air Force Base, MS on July 8, 2016.

Film Credits: Matthew Hames

1546.description:
The C-5 Galaxy is the largest aircraft in the United States Air Force.

Film Credits: A1C Chandler Baker, Douglas Lay
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

1547.description:
USS America (LHA-6) arrives at Pearl Harbor Naval Base for multinational maritime exercise RIMPAC 2016. Time lapse filmed on July 6, 2016.

Film Credits: MC1 Demetrius Kennon
AudioBlocks Music: https://www.audioblocks.com/stock-audio/summer-daze-full.html
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

1548.description:
An air assault exercise during Rapid Trident, which is a regional command post and field training exercise that involves about 2,000 Soldiers from 13 different nations, held at the International Peacekeeping and Security Center in Yavoriv, Ukraine June 27 - July 8, 2016.

Film Credits: SGT Jacob Holmes

1549.description:
Polish Air Force F-16 fighter jets perform takeoffs, landings, and the Polish Pilots show some skills with air maneuvers. Filmed on June 6, 2016.

Film Credits: Nato Channel

1550.description:
French Army soldiers and U.S. Marines execute an offensive attack during a combined mechanized vehicle integration training exercise at French Army Center for Urban Combat Training at Camp Sissonne, France on June 21, 2016. SPMAGTF-CR-AF Marines trained alongside a company of French Army soldiers, integrating their skills and resources including weaponry and military vehicles to form an effective battle plan, similar to what they may face in the event of a future crisis.

Film Credits: Sgt Kassie McDole

1551.description:
Aerial view of ships moored at Pearl Harbor Naval Base during Rim of the Pacific (RIMPAC) 2016 on July 1, 2016. The Arizona Memorial cannot be missed in this PHOTOEX by U.S Army helicopters from 3rd Battalion, 25th Aviation Regiment (3-25 AVN) Alpha Company Stingrays.

Film Credits: PO1 Benjamin Lewis

1552.description:
Belgian B-Hunter UAV (unmanned aerial vehicle) filmed at Koksijde Air Base on June 28, 2016.
 
Film Credits: NATO Channel

1553.description:
U.S. Marines with 3rd Assault Amphibian Battalion conduct amphibious combat sustainment training at Camp Pendleton, CA. An Assault Amphibian Battalion is responsible for forcible entry and ship-to-shore transportation of ground combat forces. Filmed on June 28-30, 2016.
 
Film Credits: Sgt Jacob Osborne, Cpl Jonathan Boynes, Cpl Garrett White

1554.description:
Cockpit video of A-10 Thunderbolt II "Warthogs" during Hawgsmoke 2016, a competition of A-10 pilots including strafing runs. Filmed at Gila Bend, AZ in June, 2016.  More here: https://hawg-smoke.com/about/
 
Film Credits: SrA Samuel O'Brien

1555.description:
Alex Keyes, a  rallycross driver with Dreyer & Reinbold Racing gives U.S. Marines Corporal Shannon West a ride-along view of the Red Bull Global Rallycross race track at Marine Corps Air Station New River, NC on June 30, 2016. The world's best rallycross drivers will compete at MCAS New River for the second season in a row for a doubleheader on July 2-3, 2016, featuring an all-new course layout, bringing the track even closer to the fans. To learn more, please visit www.mccslejeune-newriver.com/rallycross/.
 
Film Credits: Cpl. Shannon West - Marine Corps Installations East Combat Camera

1556.description:
Five multinational warships dock at Pearl Harbor Naval Base before the start of exercise Rim of the Pacific (RIMPAC) 2016. In order of appearance: HMCS Calgary (FFH-335), HMNZS Te Kaha (F77), HMAS Ballarat (FFH 155), USS Howard (DDG-83), and USS Mobile Bay (CG-53). RIMPAC is the world's largest international maritime exercise including 26 nations, more than 40 ships and submarines, more than 200 aircraft and 25,000 personnel. RIMPAC 2016 takes place from June 30 to August 4, in and around the Hawaiian Islands and Southern California. Filmed on June 28-29, 2016.
 
Film Credits: PO1 Jason Swink

1557.description:
Eleven ships from multinational navies arrive at Pearl Harbor (Joint Base Pearl Harbor–Hickam) for the start of RIMPAC 2016. Rim of the Pacific (RIMPAC) is the world's largest international maritime exercise with 26 nations, 200 plus aircraft, more than 40 ships and submarines, and 25,000 personnel participating. RIMPAC 2016 is the 25th exercise in the series and will take place from June 30 to August 4. Filmed on June 28-29, 2016.
 
Film Credits: PO2 Laurie Dexter, PO1 Phillip Pavlovich, PO1 Meranda Keller

1558.description:
Extended footage and closeup inflight views of three F-35B Lightning II fighter jets making their first transatlantic flight. The F-35s flew from Marine Corps Air Station Beaufort in South Carolina and landed at RAF Fairford in Gloucestershire, England. They were refueled 15 times over the Atlantic by two USAF KC-10 air tankers. 
 
Film Credits: Cpl. Brian Burdett

1559.description:
Three U.S. Marine Corps F-35B Lightning II Joint Strike Fighter jets make their first transatlantic flight from MacDill AFB in Tampa, FL to Gloucestershire, England. They were refueled 15 times over the Atlantic by two USAF KC-10 Extender air tankers. Filmed on June 29, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: Cpl. Brian Burdett

1560.description:
F-35B Lightning II Joint Strike Fighter pilots and support crews practice for summer airshows at Marine Corps Air Station Beaufort, SC. The F-35B crewmembers will be flying the fighter aircraft in the Royal International Air Tattoo and the Farnborough International Airshow in the summer of 2016. Filmed on June 17, 2016. Units - Marine Fighter Attack Training Squadron 501 (VMFAT-501) and U.K. Royal Air Force.
 
Film Credits: Cpl Jonah Lovy

1561.description:
F-35B Lightning II fighter jets takeoff at night from Marine Corps Air Station Beaufort en-route to the United Kingdom where they will participate in the Royal International Air Tattoo and the Farnborough International Airshow. Personnel with Marine Fighter Attack Training Squadron 501 (VMFAT-501) and the U.K. Royal Air Force will work together to display some capabilities of the F-35B. Filmed on June 29, 2016.
 
Film Credits: Cpl Jonah Lovy

1562.description:
Royal Norwegian Air Force (RNoAF) F-16 fighter jets takeoff and land at Orland Air Base, Norway, plus aerial views during a NATO Joint Intelligence, Surveillance and Reconnaissance exercise on June 28, 2016.
 
Film Credits: NATO Channel

1563.description:
Royal Australian Navy ships HMAS Canberra (L02) and HMAS Ballarat (FFH 155) arrive at Pearl Harbor, HI for the start of RIMPAC 2016. Rim of the Pacific (RIMPAC) is the world's largest international maritime exercise with 26 nations, 200 plus aircraft, more than 40 ships and submarines, and 25,000 personnel participating. RIMPAC 2016 is the 25th exercise in the series and will take place from June 30 to August 4. Filmed on June 28, 2016.
 
Film Credits: PO1 Meranda Keller

1564.description:
U.S. Air Force KC-135 Stratotankers refuel French Mirage 2000 fighter jets in-flight over Iraq. Filmed on June 15 and April 8, 2016. USAF Unit - 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron.
 
Film Credits: SSgt John McRell, SSgt Michelle Di Ciolli

1565.description:
Footage of the USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN-69), informally known as "IKE". The USS Eisenhower is the second of ten Nimitz-class nuclear powered aircraft carriers currently in service with the U.S. Navy and was commissioned in 1977. The Mighty IKE is still in active service and on patrol at the time of this writing. All footage filmed in 2016.
 
Film Credits: SN Adam Austin, Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Michael R. Gendron, Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Robert J. Baldock, PO3 Alex Delgado

1566.description:
USS San Antonio (LPD-17) departs Naval Station Norfolk as part of the Wasp Amphibious Ready Group (WSP ARG) deployment to the U.S. 5th and 6th Fleet areas of responsibility. Filmed on June 25, 2016.
 
Film Credits: PO2 Sonja Wickard

1567.description:
U.S. Paratroopers with the 173rd Airborne Brigade team-up with soldiers from Poland, Canada, and the United Kingdom to conduct an assault demonstration on urban terrain during NATO Exercise Anakonda 2016 at Wedzryn, Poland on June 14, 2016.   

Film Credits:  SSG Anthony Johnson, SFC Whitney Hughes

1568.description:
U.S. Marines undergo the standard 11-day Marine Corps Combat Readiness Evaluation (MCCRE) at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms, CA on June, 13, 2016. This MCCRE helped prepare Marines of 3rd Battalion, 7th Marine Regiment for deployment with Special Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force - Crisis Response - Central Command, based at an undisclosed location in Southwest Asia.
 
Film Credits: LCpl Timothy Valero

1569.description:
U.S. Army Field Artillery Squadron - 1st person point-of-view firing M-777 during Saber Strike 16 Combined Live Fire Exercise at Tapa, Estonia on June 20, 2016. Saber Strike 2016 is a cooperative training exercise designed to improve joint interoperability between America and Europe. Filmed on June 20, 2016. Unit - Archer Battery, Field Artillery Squadron, 2nd Cavalry Regiment - 1-181st Field Artillery
 
Film Credits: SSG Ricardo Hernandez-Arocho

1570.description:
A U.S. Marine Corps KC130J air tanker executes an aerial refueling mission with F-35B Lighting II fighter jets over Marine Corps Air Station Yuma, AZ on June 21, 2016. Units - Marine Aerial Refueler Transport Squadron 352, Marine Air Group 11, 3d MAW - Marine Fighter Attack Squadron 121, Marine Aircraft Group 13, 3d Marine Aircraft Wing(MAW).
 
Film Credits: LCpl Jessica Lucio

1571.description:
Royal Marines Commandos and NATO forces conduct an amphibious assault from the flagship HMS Ocean in the Baltic Sea off the coastline of Poland during Exercise Baltops 2016. 15 NATO nations plus Finland and Sweden have participation in Baltops 2016. Filmed on June 16, 2016.
 
Film Credits: https://www.dvidshub.net/video/470704/amphibious-assault-baltops-2016-b-roll

1572.description:
Two nuclear powered Nimitz-class aircraft carriers: USS John C. Stennis (CVN-74) and USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76) conduct strike group operations in the U.S. 7th Fleet area of operations (Philippine Sea/South China Sea) on June 18, 2016.
 
Film Credits:  U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 1st Class Elijah G. Leinaar - Released

1573.description:
Members of the U.S. Army conduct a gunnery exercise at Rodriguez Live Fire Range in South Korea on June 14, 2016. Unit - 1st Cavalry Division, 1st Brigade Combat Team, 2nd Battalion, 8th Cavalry Regiment, "Mustangs"    

Film Credits:  SGT Fred Brown

1574.description:
FGM-148 Javelin fire-and-forget anti-tank missile in action during exercise Saber Strike 16 at Estonian Defense Forces central training area near Tapa, Estonia on June 19, 2016.
 
Film Credits:  SFC Ben Houtkooper

1575.description:
The FGM-148 Javelin is a man-portable fire-and-forget anti-tank missile. Javelin has a stated effective range of 2500 meters, However, at The Battle of Debecka Pass in Iraq, Javelins were observed to hit targeted vehicles at ranges up to 4200 meters: http://www.defensemedianetwork.com/stories/roughnecks-at-war-the-battle-of-debecka-pass/ Unit - 2d Cavalry Regiment, U.S. Army
 
Film Credits:  SGT Kyle Burns

1576.description:
U.S. Navy aircraft carrier USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76) flight deck and bridge operations underway in the 7th Fleet area of responsibility. Filmed 2016.
 
Film Credits: PO3 Devin Kates

1577.description:
Two U.S. Navy aircraft carriers have been deployed to the Philippine Sea: USS John C. Stennis (CVN-74) and USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76). They are conducting dual strike group operations in the U.S. 7th Fleet area of operations in support of security and stability in the Indo-Asia-Pacific, and possibly to respond to China's military expansion in this area. Filmed on June 18, 2016.
 
Film Credits: MC3 Nick A. Grim, MC3 Jake Greenberg

1578.description:
American aircraft carrier USS John C. Stennis (CVN-74) leads ships from the Indian Navy, and the Japanese Maritime Self-Defense Force as a strike group in exercise Malabar 2016, a tri-lateral naval exercise to strengthen relationships between multi-national navies. Filmed in the Western Pacific on June 17, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: PO3 Neil Grim

1579.description:
Scenes of  Exercise Anakonda 16 with multiple NATO nations conducting a combined live-fire assault in this Polish-led multinational operation. Filmed on June 15, 2016.
 
Film Credits: NATO Channel

1580.description:
USMC AV-8B Harrier vertical landing and takeoff aboard USS Wasp (LHD-1) on May 8, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: PO2 Nathan Wilkes

1581.description:
Members of the U.S. Army - 3rd Battalion, 69th Armored Regiment conduct a Combined Arms Live Fire Exercise (CALFEX) in Drawsko Pomorskie, Poland as part of Anakonda 2016. Anakonda 2016 is a Polish-led multinational exercise, taking place in Poland from June 7-17. It involves more than 31,000 participants from more than 20 nations. Filmed on June 16, 2016.
 
Film Credits: SPC James Garvin

1582.description:
USNS Big Horn (T-AO-198), a fleet replenishment oiler, conducts a double underway replenishment for fuel of USS Whidbey Island (LSD-41) and USS WASP (LHD-1) as part of an alongside connected replenishment (CONREP) on April 14, 2016.
 
Film Credits: GySgt Neill Sevelius

1583.description:
Canadian and Turkish armed forces conduct Military Operations on Urban Terrain (MOUT) training in Wedrzyn, Poland during 
Exercise Anakonda 2016. Anakonda 2016 is a Polish-led training exercise involving more than 30,000 troops from 24 NATO countries, the largest military exercise in Eastern Europe since the Cold War ended. Filmed on June 15, 2016.
 
Film Credits: SGT Rodney Roldan

1584.description:
The U.S. Navy aircraft carrier USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN-69) transits the Strait of Gibraltar into the Mediterranean Sea for forward deployment duties on June 13, 2016.
 
Film Credits: PO3 Michael Gendron

1585.description:
Infantry Troops from Norway and Lithuania conduct a combined ground assault operation during Exercise Saber Strike 16. Saber Strike is a Europe-led cooperative training exercise designed to improve joint interoperability through a range of missions that prepare the 13 participating NATO nations from the Baltic Region to support multinational contingency operations and act as one army. Filmed at Adazu Military Base, Rix, Latvia on June 16, 2016.
 
Film Credits: Cpl Stephanie Cervantes

1586.description:
U.S. Marines with 1st Battalion, 1st Marine Regiment, conduct platoon-level live-fire and maneuver during exercise Southern Jackaroo in Shoalwater Bay, Queensland, Australia on May 22, 2016.
 
Film Credits: Cpl Jordan Walker

1587.description:
Highlights from Saber Strike 16 features British Infantry Troops conducting a live-fire ground assault with U.S. close-air, artillery, and tank support. The exercise includes 13 participating nations and takes place May 27-June 22. Filmed at Adazu Military Base, Rix, Latvia on June 12-14, 2016.
 
Film Credits: Cpl Immanuel Johnson, Cpl Kelly Street, Cpl Stephanie Cervantes

1588.description:
U.S. Navy Sailors from Explosive Ordnance Disposal Mobile Unit Five (EODMU5) conduct a helicopter, visit, board, search and seizure (HVBSS) training operation (with GoPro footage) aboard the Arleigh Burke-class guided-missile destroyer, USS Curtis Wilbur (DDG-54) from an MH-60S Sea Hawk Helicopter, assigned to the "Island Knights" of Helicopter Combat Squadron (HSC-25). EODMU5 is embarked aboard the aircraft carrier USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76). Filmed on June 10, 2016. 
 
Film Credits: PO1 Elijah Leinaar

1589.description:
Fourteen aircraft from four nations fly in formation below a USAF KC-135 during BALTOPS 16. Plus a USAF B-52 takes on fuel in-flight. BALTOPS is an annual NATO maritime exercise held in the Baltic Sea region. Aircraft from Germany, Poland, Sweden, and USA filmed on June 6, 2016. KC-135 is from 434th Air Refueling Wing.
 
Film Credits: SrA Erin Babis

1590.description:
Members of the 82nd Airborne Division conduct convoy live-fire training during a battalion field exercise at Fort Bragg, NC. The training prepares an Aviation Support Battalion (ASB) for the critical task of convoy security while deployed. Filmed on June 10, 2016. Unit - 122nd Aviation Support Battalion, 82nd Combat Aviation Brigade, 82nd Airborne Division, U.S. Army
 
Film Credits: SSG Christopher Freeman

1591.description:
The Diver Augmented Vision Display (DAVD) is a heads-up display prototype created at the Naval Surface Warfare Center Panama City Division. The prototype fits into a Kirby Morgan dive helmet - the same helmet presently used by military and commercial divers, and was created with a 3D printer. DAVD offers situational awareness, or "sector sonar," that enables topside divers to provide visual communications to divers below the surface. The real-time operational data enables divers to be more effective and safe in their missions -- providing expanded situational awareness and increased accuracy in navigating to a target such as a ship, downed aircraft, or other objects of interest.
 
Film Credits: Jacqui Barker, U.S. Navy imagery by Richard Manley/Released

1592.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers from the 173rd Airborne Brigade (Sky Soldiers) conduct an Air Assault Raid by helicopter in Poland as part of Exercise Anakonda 2016 on June 6, 2016.  Anakonda is a Polish-led, multinational exercise involving over 31,000 Soldiers from over 20 nations.
 
Film Credits: SFC Whitney Hughes

1593.description:
U.S. Army Tankers maneuver the M1A2 System Enhancement Package (SEP) V2 Abrams main battle tank during Operation Anakonda in the Drawsko Pomorskie Training Area (DPTA) near Olezno, Poland on June 9, 2016. Unit - 2nd Battalion, 7th Infantry Division, 1st Armored Brigade Combat Team
 
Film Credits: SGT Ashley Marble,  PFC Jacquelynn Gaines

1594.description:
Japan Air Self-Defense Force and USAF C-130 Hercules, E-3 Sentry, and F-22 Raptors takeoff at Exercise Red Flag-Alaska 16-2. Filmed on June 8, 2016.
 
Film Credits:  Senior Airman Carly Kavish and Airman Richard Hayes

1595.description:
Polish Armed Forces launch SA-6 surface-to-air missiles (SAM) during Exercise Anakonda 2016 on June 9, 2016. Anakonda 2016 takes place between June 7-17, 2016 in Poland and international air and sea spaces of the Baltic Sea. It will involve approximately 31,000 troops, 3,000 vehicles, 120 aircraft and 12 ships from 19 Allied countries.
 
Film Credits:  NATO Channel

1596.description:
Scenes from Trojan Footprint 16, a large-scale special operations readiness exercise which brought together special operations forces from 10 different nations to train together as one military team to test the NATO Response Force alert and deployment sequence.  
 
Film Credits:  This work, Trojan Footprint 16 B-roll, is free of known copyright restrictions under U.S. copyright law. https://www.dvidshub.net/video/465423/trojan-footprint-16-b-roll#.V1l44uIrKM8

1597.description:
Cockpit video from a Marine Corps KC-130J Air Tanker as it takes off from Iwakuni, Japan and lands at Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson, Alaska for Exercise Kodiak Mace. Filmed on June 6, 2016. Unit - Marine Aerial Refueler Transport Squadron-152 (VMGR-152) 
 
Film Credits:  Cpl Cory Schubert

1598.description:
U.S. Navy submarine tender USS Frank Cable (AS-40) deploys from Guam for the first time in 14 years, and dolphins jump (a sign of good luck for mariners). The USS Cable has over 500 Sailors and civilian personnel aboard and is underway for the Indo-Asia-Pacific region. Filmed on June 6, 2016. 
 
Film Credits:  SCPO Paul Cage

1599.description:
The Combat Arms Section at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base is an indoor shooting range used to train active duty Air Force, Office of Special Investigations, 445th Airlift Wing, Navy, Army, and Marine members. Instructors there train as many as 3,500 students each year who fire an average of 30,000 rounds each month from 21 shooting stations. The 13 types of weapons used include government-issued pistols, rifles, shotguns, machine guns and other weapons. The instructors administer 17 different courses for these weapons. They also inspect and maintain all the weapons stored in the facility's armory. This means that the instructors also double as gunsmiths. Filmed on June 6, 2016.
 
Film Credits:  Ryan Law

1600.description:
The USS Houston (SSN-713), a Los Angeles-class fast attack submarine of the U.S. Navy, departs Pearl Harbor for the last time before it is decommissioned. The Houston is en route to Puget Sound Naval Shipyard to commence its inactivation process after 33 years of service. Filmed on June 6, 2016.
 
Film Credits:  PO1 Jason Swink

1601.description:
Members of the Australian Army with Battle Group Waratah, 8th Brigade, perform synchronized combat arms training during exercise Southern Jackaroo at Shoalwater Bay, Queensland, Australia on May 23, 2016.
 
Film Credits:  Cpl Jordan Walker

1602.description:
Aerial views and twilight flight operations aboard the USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN-69). The USS Eisenhower is a nuclear-powered aircraft carrier of the United States Navy. Filmed May 3-4, 2016.
 
Film Credits:  Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Michael R. Gendron, Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class J. Alexander Delgado

1603.description:
U.S. Army Rangers show their training at Fort Benning, Georgia. Ranger School is the Army’s premier small unit tactics and leadership school. The 62-day course pushes Ranger students to their mental and physical limits by forcing them to operate on minimal food and sleep. 77,000 Soldiers have earned the Ranger Tab since the school opened in 1952. In 2014, 4057 students attempted the course; 1609 earned the Ranger Tab. All men and women who attend Ranger School have met the exact same standards.
 
Film Credits:  A1C Joshua Hoskins, SSgt Thomas Smith

1604.description:
Aerial and flight deck views of the USS Harry S. Truman (CVN-75) the eighth Nimitz-class aircraft carrier of the United States Navy, named after the 33rd President of the United States. The USS Truman is currently deployed to the eastern Mediterranean Sea. Aerial underway footage filmed on May 5, 2016. Replenishment footage filmed on February 24, 2016. Flight deck footage filmed on June 3, 2016.
 
Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video/Released, Mass Communications Specialist 2nd Class J. Marzullo, Mass Communications Specialist 3rd Class Galen Hogan-Barden, SN Bobby Siens

1605.description:
The only U.S. foward-deployed aircraft carrier USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76) departs Yokosuka, Japan to conduct a scheduled patrol. Filmed on June 4, 2016.
 
Film Credits: PO3 David Flewellyn

1606.description:
A-10 Thunderbolt II teams compete in Hawgsmoke 2016 at Gila Bend, AZ included bombing, long range, and short range strafing runs. Filmed on June 2, 2016.

Film Credits: SrA Samuel O'Brien

1607.description:
U.S. Air Force B-52 Bombers land at Royal Air Force Fairford in Gloucestershire, England to take part in NATO exercise BALTOPS 16. BALTOPS is the largest multinational maritime exercise in the Baltic Sea region. Approximately 6,100 maritime, ground, and air force troops from participating nations will participate in a joint environment to ensure regional security. BALTOPS is an annually recurring event designed to enhance flexibility and interoperability, as well as to demonstrate resolve of allied and partner forces to defend the Baltic region. Participating nations in BALTOPS 2016 include Belgium, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Italy, Latvia, Lithuania, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Spain, Sweden, United Kingdom, and the United States.

Film Credits: SrA Gabriel Stuart

1608.description:
U.S. Marine Corps Staff Sgt. Jason May, senior drill instructor with Company M, Recruit Training Regiment, gives a speech to new recruits on pick-up day at Marine Corps Recruit Depot San Diego, CA on May 20, 2016. He spoke to the recruits about the responsibilities of the drill instructors and what is expected of the recruits during the 13 weeks of recruit training.

Film Credits: Sgt John Lamb

1609.description:
U.S. Soldiers and Marines enrolled in the Lightning Academy practice shipboard insert and extract techniques aboard a U.S. Army Logistics Support Vessel (LSV-2). The Lightning Academy is a training institution within the 25th Infantry Division which includes the Lightning Leaders Course, Pre-Ranger Course, Combatives levels one and two, Adaptive Leaders Program, Tactical Rifle Course, and Air Assault. Filmed on January 12, 2016.

Film Credits: SSG John C Garver

1610.description:
U.S. Army Long Range Surveillance (LRS) pronounced "Lurse" are small, long-range scout teams that infiltrate deep into enemy territory, construct and hide in surveillance sites, and provide continuous reconnaissance. Filmed on March 17, 2016.

Film Credits: SFC Jason Kriess

1611.description:
U.S. Air Force aircraft and paratroopers with the U.S. 173rd Airborne Brigade, the Italian Folgore Brigade, and British 16th Air Assault Brigade conduct large scale airborne operations during Exercise Saber Junction 16 - near Hohenfels, Germany. Filmed in April, 2016.

Film Credits: SGT Jacob Sawyer, A1C Lance Valencia, A1C Chandler Baker, SGT Jacob Sawyer, SPC Nathanael Mercado

1612.description:
M1A2 Abrams and Leopard 2 conduct live fire and maneuvers during the Nordic Tank Challenge 2016 competition at Holstebro, Denmark. The competition included two tanks crews each from Sweden, Norway, Canada, Germany, Poland, Denmark and the U.S. to claim the title of best tank crew. The winner was the Royal Danish Army's 2nd Tank Squadron, 1st Armor Brigade. Filmed on May 26, 2016.

Film Credits: SFC Daniel Shapiro

1613.description:
Members of the U.S. Army 82nd Airborne Division conduct a mass airdrop of equipment and troops from C-17 aircraft during exercise Crescent Reach 16. The airdrop was made over Pope Air Field, NC to simulate a large aircraft  formation launch with troops in response to a world crises situation. Filmed on May 26, 2016.

Film Credits: SSgt Chelsi Urban

1614.description:
U.S. Marines shoot the M142 High Mobility Artillery Rocket System (HIMARS) during a live-fire exercise in the Philippines on April 4, 2016. Unit - 2nd Platoon, Fox Battery, 14th Marine Regiment

Film Credits: SSgt Jason Fudge, Cpl Jonathan LopezCruet

1615.description:
Memorial Day Tribute To The U.S. Armed Forces 2016. Memorial Day is a day of remembering the men and women who gave their lives while serving in the U.S. Armed Forces. God Bless them.

Film Credits: U.S. Armed Forces
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids
Music by AudioBlocks: https://www.audioblocks.com/stock-audio/epic-cinematic-movie-trailer-music.html

1616.description:
American Aggressor Squadrons are trained to act as an opposing force in air exercises, and those fighter jets are painted in a camouflage scheme which resemble Russian aircraft. The U.S. first used aggressor aircraft for training in 1968 at the Navy Fighter Weapons School, "Top Gun" - Miramar, CA.

Film Credits: SSgt Cody Griffith, SrA Taylor West, SrA Ariel Tumlinson, TSgt Miguel Lara, SrA Andrew Walck, SSgt Jose Rodriguez, SSgt Greg Cerny

1617.description:
U.S. Navy USS Hopper (DDG-70) successfully executed a test of the Standard Missile-3 (SM-3) Block IB Threat Upgrade guided missile on May 25, 2016 off the west coast of Hawaii. This flight test is designated Controlled Test Vehicle-01a and demonstrated the successful performance of design modifications to the SM-3 third-stage rocket motor nozzle.

Film Credits: Leah Garton

1618.description:
American aircraft carrier USS John C. Stennis (CVN-74) conducts routine flight operations and a show of force demonstration in the South China Sea. Filmed in April and May of 2016.

Film Credits: PO3 Neil Grim, PO3 Luke Moyer

1619.description:
U.S. Army M109A6 Paladin Self-Propelled Howitzer crew compartment view during a call for fire mission in Joint Exercise Eager Lion 2016 at Training Area 1, Jordan on May 24, 2016. Unit - B Battery, 1st Battalion, 7th Field Artillery Regiment, 1st Infantry Division

Film Credits: SGT Neil Stanfield

1620.description:
Special Operations Forces (SOF) conduct a rehearsal for International Special Operations Forces Week 2016 at the Tampa harbor near downtown Tampa, FL on May 24, 2016. The main event is 1330-1400 May 25, 2016.

Film Credits: SSgt Jayson Price

1621.description:
Shots of the Ohio Class submarine USS Kentucky (SSBN-737). United States Navy Ohio-class submarines carry 24 Trident thermonuclear ballistic missiles per boat. There are currently 14 Trident Submarines in USN service, making up about 50% of the American active nuclear inventory.

Film Credits: PO2 Amanda Gray

1622.description:
A-10 Thunderbolt II and F-16 Fighting Falcon fighter jets do the Elephant Walk during Exercise Beverly Herd 16-01 at Osan AB, South Korea on May 9, 2016. The aviation term "Elephant Walk" dates back to World War II when large fleets of allied bombers would conduct attack missions with up to 1000 aircraft. Those who observed this said the large numbers of aircraft on the runway in nose-to-tail formations looked like elephants walking to a watering hole. Over time, it was incorporated into the terminology of the U.S. Air Force to identify a "maximum surge sortie".

Film Credits: SSgt Ashley Manz

1623.description:
The Air Force Ranger Assessment Course is a 15 day event designed to find Air Force candidates qualified to attend U.S. Army Ranger School. On average, only 35-50 percent of participating Airmen complete this course, and since 1950 barely 300 Airmen have been Ranger qualified. Filmed at Fort Bliss, TX in April/May 2016.  

Film Credits: SGT Jacob Holmes

1624.description:
Special Operations Forces conduct a free fall jump over MacDill Air Force Base in Florida on May 23, 2016.

Film Credits: SSG Jerimiah Richardson

1625.description:
GoPro view of U.S. Army M1 Assault Breacher Vehicles firing off a Mine Clearing Line Charge (MICLIC) at a Gunnery Exercise in Grafenwoehr, Germany on May 19, 2016. Unit - 10th Engineer Battalion

Film Credits:  MAJ Randy Ready

1626.description:
Fuel is delivered to a U.S. F/A-18 Jolly Rogers CAG and other F/A-18 Super Hornets armed (hot load) over Iraq. Plus, U.S. F-16s and F-15s get gas in the sky during a refueling mission over Iraq, including boom operator communications with pilots on all. Filmed on April 29 and May 5, 2016. Air Refueling Unit - 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron

Film Credits:  SSgt Aaron Richardson

1627.description:
U.S. Marine Corps drill instructors conduct an inspection of Company I recruits at Marine Corps Recruit Depot San Diego, CA on May 13, 2016. The drill instructors inspected recruits on the proper wear of uniforms, the cleanliness of rifles, and knowledge of Marine Corps history and traditions. DI Unit - Company I, 3rd Recruit Training Battalion, Recruit Training Regiment

Film Credits: Sgt John Lamb

1628.description:
A KC-130J Air Tanker from Marine Aerial Refueler Transport Squadron 152 (VMGR-152) refuels two F/A-18D Hornets from Marine All- Weather Fighter Attack Squadron 242 (VMFA-242) in the skies over Marine Corps Air Station Iwakuni, Japan. Filmed on April 26, 2016.

Film Credits: LCpl Donato Maffin

1629.description:
Cockpit video of the MD-530F Cayuse Warrior Helicopter being flown by U.S. Air Advisers from TAAC AIR/438th AEW. U.S. and Afghanistan Air Forces jointly fly the MD-530F in Afghanistan. Filmed on May 8, 2016.

Film Credits: SSgt John McRell

1630.description:
U.S. Marines conduct range 400 on Twentynine Palms, CA on May 9, 2016. Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center (MCAGCC) Range 400 is used to train rifle companies in the techniques and procedures for attacking fortified areas, and is one of the most dynamic live-fire ranges in the Marine Corps. Unit In Video - 2nd Battalion, 8th Marine Regiment

Film Credits: LCpl Clarence Wimberly

1631.description:
U.S. Enlisted Airmen from the 4th Special Operations Support Squadron preflight for launch an AC-130U Spooky Gunship at Hurlburt Field, FL on May 6, 2016 during Exercise Emerald Warrior. Emerald Warrior is a U.S. Special Operations Command mission designed to train special operations forces to respond to real and emerging worldwide threats.

Film Credits: SrA Sean Walker

1632.description:
Abrams Tank crews fire their main guns (interior, exterior, and GoPro views) during the 2016 Sullivan Cup Competition at Fort Benning, GA. The competition was held from May 2-6, 2016, and included tank crews from the U.S. Army, U.S. Marines, and Canada. The winner of the 2016 Sullivan Cup Competition - 1-252 AR, 30th ABCT - NCARNG - "Old Hickory!"

Film Credits: SFC Adam Fischman

1633.description:
U.S. Marines with 2nd Battalion, 8th Marine Regiment, conduct a precision fires range at Twentynine Palms, CA on May 4, 2016. The Range was conducted to further improve the Marines proficiency with precision fires for future operations during Integrated Training Exercise 3-16.

Film Credits: LCpl Clarence Wimberly

1634.description:
Marines with 11th Marine Expeditionary Unit, Maritime Raid Force - conduct an insert raid via CH-53E Super Stallion during Marine Expeditionary Unit exercise (MEUEX) at Camp Pendleton, CA on May 12, 2016. MEUEX is a stepping stone to the five training evolutions a MEU must go through to be ready for its final Certification Exercise, which will send the MEU on its upcoming deployment.

Film Credits:  GySgt Robert Brown

1635.description:
U.S. Air Force Airmen with the 24th Special Operations Wing free fall jump from U.S. Army CH-47 Chinook 5th battalion, 159th Aviation Regiment, near Hurlburt Field, FL. Filmed as part of Exercise Emerald Warrior on May 7, 2016.

Film Credits:  A1C Jacob Albers, A1C Jourdan Barrons, A1C Joshua Hoskins

1636.description:
U.S. Air Force Airmen from the 24th Special Operations Wing conduct call for fire and close air support proficiency training with U.S. Army AH-64D Apache helicopters and a U.S. Air Force AC-130U Spooky gunship as part of Exercise Emerald Warrior 2016. Filmed near Hurlburt Field, Florida on May 10, 2016.

Film Credits:  A1C Joshua Hoskins

1637.description:
U.S. Air Force AC-130U Spooky Gunship on a close air support training mission over Eglin Range, FL during Exercise Emerald Warrior 2016. Filmed on May 10, 2016. Unit -  4th Special Operations Squadron 

Film Credits:  A1C Natalie Plas

1638.description:
The first two F-35B fighter jets land at Marine Corps Air Station in Yuma, AZ. Plus, F-35 Joint Strike Fighters fly over Hill Air Force Base in Utah. Film released on April 10-11, 2016.

Film Credits:  SSgt Staci Miller, Sgt Travis Gershaneck, PFC George Melendez

1639.description:
Competitors in the Strong Europe Tank Challenge meet to get a look at each other's tanks. Seven platoons from 6 NATO nations (Denmark, Germany, Italy, Poland, Slovenia and the United States) are participating in the Strong Europe Tank Challenge at Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany May 10-13, 2016. The competition is designed to foster military partnership, build esprit de corps and promote interoperability with NATO nations. This is footage from the first day of the event. Denmark and Poland have the Leopard 2A5, Germany the Leopard 2A6, Italy the Ariete, Slovenia the M-84 and U.S. M1A2 Abrams.

Film Credits:  Matthew Oldham, Christian Marquardt, Sarah Tate

1640.description:
U.S. Air Force Special Operations Airmen parachute jump over water in the night sky. Filmed on April 5, 2016.

Film Credits:  A1C Natalie Plas

1641.description:
USAF  Aircrews from the 4th and 5th Special Operations Squadron conduct live-fire training in AC-130U Spooky special operations aircraft from Hurlburt Field in Florida during Exercise Emerald Warrior 16. Emerald Warrior is an annual exercise held by U.S. Special Operations Command to train special operations forces for deployment and real-world scenarios. Filmed on May 4-6, 2016. Additional Units - 1st Special Operations Aircraft Maintenance Squadron

Film Credits:  SSgt Steven Witt, SrA Thomas Smith, A1C James Merriman

1642.description:
USAF Airmen with the 16th Special Operations Squadron conduct live-fire training and aerial refueling in an AC-130W Stinger II special operations aircraft over Eglin Range, FL on May 4, 2016. 

Film Credits:  A1C Jacob Albers

1643.description:
Takeoff of an AC-130W Stinger II special operations aircraft at Hurlburt Field, Florida during Exercise Emerald Warrior 16 on May 3, 2016. Exercise Emerald Warrior is an annual event held by Air Force Special Operations Command which provides pre-deployment readiness training for special operations forces. Unit - 16th Special Operations Squadron based at Cannon Air Force Base, NM. 

Film Credits:  A1C Natalie Plas

1644.description:
1st clip - Two Kaman K-MAX helicopters arrive at Marine Corps Air Station, Yuma  on April 7, 2016. 2nd clip - An unmanned Kaman K-MAX lands and takes off on Camp Bastion, AF on Dec. 1, 2012. The Kaman K-MAX is a cargo helicopter which can be flown either by a pilot - or unmanned by remote control as the Cargo Resupply Unmanned Aircraft System (CRUAS).  

Film Credits: Sgt Travis Gershaneck, Sgt Gregory Moore

1645.description:
Cockpit video of U.S. Air Force instructor pilots flying new A-29 Super Tucano aircraft that were recently delivered to the Afghan Air Force. Filmed on April 28, 2016. USAF pilots are from TAAC Air/438th AEW.

Film Credits: SSgt John McRell

1646.description:
The M3 Carl Gustav is an 84 mm man-portable reusable anti-tank recoilless rifle. The U.S. Army has a large number of these weapons in their inventory, also called Multi-Role Anti-Armor Anti-Personnel Weapon System (‪‎MAAWS‬). Filmed at Fort Bragg on April 4, 2016. Unit - 2nd Brigade Combat Team, 82nd Airborne Division

Film Credits: SSG Dillon Heyliger

1647.description:
The HC-130P and HC-130J aircraft are used for personnel recovery and in Search and Rescue. Pararescuemen (PJ) based at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base conduct operations from these airframes in training and in real-world situations. Filmed in 2012.

Film Credits: SrA Brandi Hansen, TSgt Amanda Helton, 1st Combat Camera Squadron

1648.description:
USAF and South Korean aircraft takeoff and land at Kunsan Air Base during patrol of South Korean airspace and the Korean Demilitarized Zone (DMZ). Exercise Max Thunder filmed April 2016.

Film Credits: SSgt Joseph Park

1649.description:
Opening remarks by Senator John McCain at a Senate Armed Services Committee hearing on the F-35 Joint Strike Fighter (JSF) Program - April 26, 2016. This video will be boring to most, but many others might find interesting to hear some facts, that a lot of people don't know. To see the entire hearing (1hr and 48mins) go to: https://www.dvidshub.net/video/460847/defense-leaders-testify-f-35-joint-strike-fighter-program-with-graphics#.VydUeeIrKM8

Film Credits: DOD News

1650.description:
U.S. Marines and Republic of Korea (ROK) Marines train together in clearing various obstacles on a simulated battlefield at Camp Rodriguez, South Korea. The training is part of the Korean Marine Exchange Program (KMEP) and is designed to enhance the combat readiness of U.S and South Korean troops. The ROK Marines are with 1st ROK Marine Division. The U.S. Marines are with 9th Engineer Support Battalion, 3rd Marine Logistics Group, III Marine Expeditionary Force. Filmed on April 6, 2016. 

Film Credits: Cpl Ryan Mains

1651.description:
U.S. Marines train using the AT-4, LAW, and SMAW shoulder fired rocket launchers at Babadag Training Area in Romania as part of Exercise Platinum Lynx 16-3 on March 23, 2016. Unit - 1st Battalion, 8th Marines, Black Sea Rotational Force

Film Credits: LCpl Kyle Kauffman

1652.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcon operations at Bagram Airfield in Afghanistan. The 457th Expeditionary Fighter Squadron arrived at Bagram on April 27, 2016 to begin their rotational duty. The 457th "Texas Falcons" are home-based at NAS Fort Worth JRB.

Film Credits: SrA Robert Dantzler

1653.description:
MQ-9 Reaper drone operations at Kandahar Airfield in Afghanistan. Filmed on March 9, 2016. Submitted by 455th Air Expeditionary Wing Public Affairs.

Film Credits: Senior Airman Timothy Kirchner

1654.description:
Two U.S. F-22 Raptors refuel inflight as they fly from RAF Mildenhall to Lithuania. This marks the first time the F-22 Raptor has been deployed to Lithuania. Filmed on April 27, 2016.

Film Credits: SSgt Nathan Tucker

1655.description:
U.S. F-15 Strike Eagle fighter jets participate in air exercise INIOHOS at Andravida Air Base in Greece on April 5, 2015. This was just a temporary deployment to exchange interoperability between countries. Unit - 48th Fighter Wing, RAF Lakenheath, UK.

Film Credits: SSgt Armando Aparicio

1656.description:
The HH-3E helicopter was a search and rescue helicopter used by the U.S. to recover downed pilots - historically it was nicknamed the "Jolly Green Giant".

Film Credits: TSgt Aaron Drobnack

1657.description:
South Korean F-15K Slam Eagle fighter jets take off from Kunsan Air Base in South Korea. Filmed on April 20, 2016.    

Film Credits: SSgt Joseph Park

1658.description:
U.S. Army members assemble a floating bridge (called Improved Ribbon Bridge) across the Imjin River in South Korea, and then send Bradley Fighting Vehicles and M-1 Abrams tanks across it. Filmed On April 6, 2016. Units - 74th Multi Role Bridging Company and Chinooks from the 6th Squadron, 6th Cavalry Regiment, building the bridge. Plus 2nd Battalion, 8th Cavalry Regiment, 1st Brigade Combat Team, 1st Cavalry Division, crossing.

Film Credits: SGT Fred Brown

1659.description:
The U.S. has sent an Air Contingent of A-10C Thunderbolt II planes and HH-60G Pave Hawk helicopters, along with support personnel, to Clark Air Base in the Philippines. It is not yet clear how long the aircraft and airmen will remain at Clark, but future rotations are planned. The Warthogs, Pave Hawks, and airmen will remain at Clark “as long as both the Philippines and the United States deem necessary,” said Lt. Col. Damien Pickart, a Pacific Air Force spokesman. The Air Force detachment will be joining Navy P-8 Poseidon aircraft already at Clark, a major U.S. Military air base until it was closed in 1991. Clark was reopened to U.S. Forces in June 2012. The move could be interpreted as a counter to China's construction of military bases in the Spratly Islands, an area roughly 230 miles off the Philippine coast. Filmed on April 20-21, 2016.

Film Credits: TSgt James Stewart

1660.description:
Cockpit video of a U.S. Marine Corps MV-22 Osprey as it transports earthquake relief supplies from the Japanese Ship Hyuga (DDH-181). The humanitarian relief was bound for victims of the Kumamoto Earthquake which struck on April 16, 2016. This video filmed on April 23, 2016. Unit - Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 265 (Reinforced) 

Film Credits: Cpl Cory Schubert

1661.description:
A mass formation of thirty-two OH-54D Kiowa Warrior helicopters flies over Fort Bragg, NC for the last time. This flyover set a Guinness world record for the largest formation flight of helicopters (the previous record was 30). The Kiowa is being retired and it's role is being replaced by the U.S. Army Apache helicopter. Filmed on April 15, 2016. Unit - 1st Squadron, 17th Cavalry Regiment, 82nd Combat Aviation Brigade, U.S. Army

Film Credits: SSG David Birchfield

1662.description:
A simultaneous synchronized launch of fourteen AH-64D Apache Attack Helicopters from the South Carolina Army National Guard at McEntire Joint National Guard Base headed to Fort Stewart, Georgia for annual training. Filmed on April 23, 2016.

Film Credits: SGT Brad Mincey, SGT David Erskine

1663.description:
Tactical Air Control Party (TACP) members from the Texas Air National Guard (TANG) and Czech Republic Military conduct a training scenario with the 357th Fighter Squadron of A-10 Thunderbolt II aircraft from Davis-Monthan Air Force Base on the Barry M. Goldwater Range in Arizona on April 12, 2016.

Film Credits: A1C Jean-Paul Arnaud-Marquez

1664.description:
U.S. Air Force C-130 Hercules cargo/transport planes takeoff from Aviano Air Base in Italy during Exercise Saber Junction 16. And cockpit camera of C-130 Hercules takeoff and fly-over and landing at Fort McCoy, WI during Exercise Global Medic 2013. 

Film Credits: TSgt Andrew Jackson, SrA Joshua Roberts

1665.description:
U.S. Air Force Pararescuemen (PJs) free-fall jump from a C-17 Globemaster III transport plane over the Philippines during exercise Balikatan 2016. Filmed on April 18, 2016.

Film Credits: TSgt Andrew Jackson

1666.description:
The USNS Charles Drew (T-AKE-10) of Military Sealift Command conducts a trilateral Replenishment At Sea (RAS), providing fuel and cargo to the guided missile destroyer USS Stockdale (DDG-106), vertical lift of cargo (VERTREP) to the Australian frigate HMAS Anzac (FF-150), and fuel to the Japanese helicopter destroyer JS Ise (DDH-182). Filmed on April 19, 2016.

Film Credits: Grady T. Fontana

1667.description:
The U.S. Air Force set a new world speed record for magnetically levitated sled systems (MagLev) sending a rocket propelled sled down a 2100 ft track reaching 633 mph (1018.71 Km/h) at Holloman AFB on March 4, 2016. The current speed record for a MagLev train is 366 mph, set by the Japanese. The current world land speed record stands at 763.035 mph, set in October 1997 by British Royal Air Force pilot Andy Green driving the jet-powered Thrust SSC. Unit - 846th Test Squadron

Film Credits:  SrA BreeAnn Sachs

1668.description:
Japan Maritime Self Defense Forces and American Military Forces work together to load U.S. MV-22 Ospreys with humanitarian supplies bound for Kumamoto earthquake victims aboard the Japanese ship JS Hyuga (DDH-181). Filmed on April 19, 2016.

Film Credits:  SN Michael Sanchez

1669.description:
Soldiers from the 82nd Airborne Division conduct static line jumps from a C-17 Globemaster III during exercise Red Devil Mass Tac at Fort Bragg, NC on April 13 2016. Exercise Red Devil Mass Tac is a joint readiness exercise conducted by the 82nd ABN Division and the 437th Airlift Wing to help prepare both units for future real-world scenarios. 

Film Credits:  A1C Jacob Albers

1670.description:
Forward Looking Infrared (FLIR) guntape from AH-64 Apache helicopters as they engage targets, only to illustrate the effectiveness of FLIR systems integrated with the AH-64 helicopter in combat situations.

Film Credits:  Derivative Works Gung Ho Vids

1671.description:
The Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center at Twentynine Palms, CA (29 Stumps) is the largest Marine Corps Base in the world. Marine Air-Ground Task Force (MAGTF) training is highlighted in this video. 29 Stumps is the premier training facility in the world for USMC operations and draws military personnel from across the globe for live-fire Combined Arms Exercises. It is called 29 Stumps because it's in the middle of the desert and there is not a palm tree to be found.

Film Credits: Cpl Connor Hancock

1672.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcons drop GBU-39 Small Diameter Bombs over South Korea. This was the first time this weapon has been dropped from a U.S. fighter in South Korea. This was a test drop and the footage from this drop is being used to help with safety assessments of weapons separation and bomb flight profiles - UNCLASSIFIED. The GBU-39 Small Diameter Bomb (SBD) is a 250 lb precision-guided glide bomb that is intended to provide aircraft with the ability to carry a higher number of more accurate bombs. Most US Air Force aircraft will be able to carry a pack of four SDBs in place of a single 2,000 lb bomb. Filmed from the cockpit on May 21, 2015. Unit - 36th Fighter Squadron part of the US Air Force's 51st Operations Group at Osan Air Base

Film Credits:  SSgt Erin Mills

1673.description:
U.S. Army Apache AH-64D helicopter crew members conduct a team movement exercise with German Tiger helicopter crews at Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany on March 30, 2016. U.S. Unit - 1st Battalion, 3rd Aviation Regiment, 12th Combat Aviation Brigade. German Unit - Kampthubschrauber Regiment 35

Film Credits:  Pfc. Javon Spence

1674.description:
U.S. Marines conduct an air assault via MV-22B Ospreys, flying into a simulated combat zone and executing an infantry bounding maneuver. Then they are extracted on the Ospreys back to base as part of Weapons and Tactics Instructor (WTI) course 2-16 at East Tac Airfield in Arizona on April 8, 2016.  WTI is a seven week training event hosted by Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1) which emphasizes operational integration of the six functions of Marine Corps aviation in support of a Marine Air Ground Task Force. MAWTS-1 provides standardized advanced tactical training and certification of unit instructor qualifications to support Marine Aviation Training and Readiness. Marine Corps Unit -  India Company, 3rd Battalion, 6th Marine Regiment, 2nd Marine Division, II Marine Expeditionary Force

Film Credits: Sgt Daniel Kujanpaa

1675.description:
U.S. Navy destroyer Donald Cook was buzzed in the Baltic Sea by Russian SU-24 planes on April 12, 2016 - marking the second time in less than a year that Russians have overflown U.S. warships in the region.    

Film Credits: U.S. NAVY 6TH FLEET VIDEO/RELEASED - DSC 0002 - DSC 0012 - DSC 0015

1676.description:
Multinational Fighter Jets take part in exercise Frisian Flag 2016 at Leeuwarden, Netherlands. Frisian Flag is a NATO air exercise. Participating in the exercise: U.S. F-15 Eagles, Dutch F-16 Fighting Falcons, Finnish F/A-18 Hornets, German Eurofighters, Polish F-16 Fighting Falcons, Belgian F-16 Fighting Falcons, Danish F-16 Fighting Falcons, French Mirage 2000. Filmed on April 11, 2016.

Film Credits: SSgt John Archiquette

1677.description:
F-22 Raptors and air crews from the 95th Fighter Squadron, Tyndall Air Force Base, Florida, have been deployed to Royal Air Force Lakenheath, England, to conduct air training with other European based aircraft. The aircraft will also forward deploy from the U.K. to NATO bases to maximize training opportunities, affirm commitments to NATO allies and deter any actions that destabilize regional security. Filmed on April 11, 2016.

Film Credits: A1C Roswell Sartwell

1678.description:
U.S Marines conduct machine gun and rocket training at Camp Schwab, Okinawa, Japan. The Marines executed a live-fire exercise in preparation for deployment. Filmed on January 26, 2016. Unit - Charlie Company, Battalion Landing Team 1st Battalion, 5th Marines, 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps motion imagery by Lcpl. Servando A. Morales/Released

1679.description:
Iceland, a country which has no military, depends on its NATO partners to surveil and police its airspace. And so the United States has committed it's aircraft, and aircrews (Men and Women) to defend Iceland against aggressor nations. Filmed on April 9, 2016.  Unit - 104th Fighter Wing, Massachusetts Air National Guard, USAF

For more Icelandic Air Policing info go here: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Icelandic_Air_Policing

Film Credits: MSgt Kevin Nichols

1680.description:
U. S. Marine Corps infantry units call in helicopters to attack simulated enemy positions during an offensive air support exercise at Mt. Barrow Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range In California. UH-1Y Venom, AH-1W Super Cobra, and A/MH-6X Mission Enhanced Little Bird helicopters were used in the training exercise. Filmed on April 5, 2016. Units - 3rd Battalion, 6th Marine Regiment, 2nd Marine Division, II Marine Expeditionary Force and Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One

Film Credits: Sgt Daniel Kujanpaa

1681.description:
Royal Dutch Marines, officially know as Korps Mariniers, conduct boat raid exercises with Fast Raiding, Interception and Special Forces Craft (FRISC) at Camp Lejeune, NC during a bilateral training event with U. S. Marines.  The Korps Mariniers is the marine corps and amphibious infantry component of the Royal Netherlands Navy. The marines are trained to operate anywhere in the world in all environments, under any condition and circumstance, as a rapid reaction force. Filmed on March 15, 2016.

Film Credits: LCpl Clarence Wimberly, 2D MARDIV, Combat Camera/Released

1682.description:
Romanian Air Force MiG 21 LanceRs take to the sky with Canadian CF-188 Hornets during Exercise Resilient Resolve over Constanta, Romania. GoPro cockpit video from one of the MiG-21s filmed on March 31, 2016. 

Film Credits: NATO TV

1683.description:
Two U.S. Air Force B-52 Stratofortress Bombers landed at Al Udeid Air Base in Qatar on April 9, 2016. The B-52's are from Barksdale AFB in Louisiana and will be supporting Operation Inherent Resolve. This marks the first time B-52 Bombers have been based in the Middle East since the Gulf War in 1990.

Film Credits: SSgt Aaron Richardson, SSgt Michelle Di Ciolli

1684.description:
HIMARS shots. The M142 High Mobility Artillery Rocket System (HIMARS) is a multiple rocket launcher used by the U.S. Army and Marines. The HIMARS can fire a variety of rockets with variable ranges and multiple munitions. Units - 27th Special Operations Wing + Tango Battery 5-11th, Camp Bastion

Film Credits: CWO3 James A. Burks, SGT Christopher Tobey, SrA Elizabeth Taranto

1685.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcons and an E-3 Sentry airborne warning and control system (AWACS) plane refuel over Iraq in support of Operation Inherent Resolve. Aerial refueling was conducted by a USAF KC-135 Stratotanker from the 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron. Filmed on April 5, 2016. 

Film Credits: SSgt Michelle Di Ciolli

1686.description:
German Combat Aviation Regiment 36 trains with Tiger helicopters at the 7th Army Joint Multinational Training Command, Grafenwoehr Training Area on March 30, 2016. Film Credits: Christoph Koppers


Tiger Specs:
General characteristics

Crew: Two: pilot and weapon systems officer
Length: 14.08 m fuselage (46 ft 2 in)
Rotor diameter: 13.00 m (42 ft 8 in)
Height: 3.83 m (12 ft 7 in)
Disc area: 133 m² (1,430 ft²)
Empty weight: 3,060 kg (6,750 lb)
Loaded weight: 5,090 kg (11,311 lb)
Max. takeoff weight: 6,000 kg (13,000 lb))
Powerplant: 2 × MTU Turbomeca Rolls-Royce MTR390 turboshafts, 958 kW (1.303 shp) each
Internal fuel capacity: 1,080 kg (2,380 lb)
Performance

Maximum speed: 290 km/h with mast, 315 km/h without mast (157 knots, 181 mph with mast, 170 knots or 196 mph without mast)
Range: 800 km (430 nm, 500 mi) combat (with external tanks in the inboard stations: 1,300km)
Service ceiling: 4,000 m (13,000 ft)
Rate of climb: 10.7 m/s (2,105 ft/min)
Power/mass: 0.23 hp/lb (0.38 kW/kg)
Armament

Guns:
1× 30 mm (1.18 in) GIAT 30 cannon in chin turret, with up to 450 rounds.
On each of its two inner hardpoints and two outer hardpoints the Eurocopter Tiger can carry a combination of the following weapons:

Inner hardpoints:
1x 20 mm (0.787 in) autocannon pods, or
