22x 68 mm (2.68 in) SNEB unguided rockets in a pod, or
19x 70 mm (2.75 in) Hydra 70 unguided rockets in a pod or
4x AGM-114 Hellfire missiles (Australia/France) or
4x Spike-ER missiles (Spain) or
4x PARS 3 LR missiles (Germany) or
4x HOT3 missiles (Germany)
Outer hardpoints:
2x Mistral air-to-air missiles, or
2x FIM-92 Stinger air-to-air missiles (Germany), or
12x 68 mm (2.68 in) SNEB unguided rockets in a pod or
7x 70 mm (2.75 in) Hydra 70 unguided rockets in a pod

1687.description:
Marine Corps UH-1Y Venom helicopter crews fire down on the mock village of Yodaville near Yuma, Arizona during an Urban Close Air Support live-fire exercise. The UH-1Y is equipped with two door-gunner machine guns and forward-firing rockets. Filmed on April 1, 2016. Unit - Lima Company, 3rd Battalion, 6th Marine Regiment and Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1)

Film Credits: LCpl Christopher Thompson, LCpl Marcus Campbell

1688.description:
Close In Weapon System radar guided gatling gun locks onto an AV-8B Harrier and tracks it inflight during an operational test aboard the USS Germantown (LSD-42). Filmed on February 15, 2016. 

Film Credits: PO3 James Vazquez

1689.description:
Six B-1 Lancer bombers takeoff with afterburners glowing at Dyess Air Force Base in Texas. The B-1 has the nickname "Bone", derived from B-One. Filmed on February 19, 2016.

Film Credits: A1C Shawn White

1690.description:
A U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptor and a WWII era P-51 Mustang perform during the "Thunder and Lightning Over Arizona" air show at Davis-Monthan AFB in Arizona on March 17, 2016.

Film Credits: A1C Jean-Paul Arnaud-Marquez

1691.description:
Two clips of C-17 Globemaster III conducting aerial refueling. Clip 1) Filmed from the cockpit, with pilot audio, a C-17 from the 317th Airlift Squadron, 437th Air Mobility Wing is refueled over Joint Base Charleston, SC on March 20, 2016. Clip 2) A C-17 receives fuel from a KC-135 Stratotanker with the 151st Air Refueling Wing over Idaho on December 17, 2014.

Film Credits: A1C Jacob Albers, SrA Danny Rangel

1692.description:
Two U.S. Air Force F-35A Lightning II fighter jets conduct training operations with F-16 Fighting Falcons at McEntire Joint National Guard Base in South Carolina. This marked the first time McEntire has hosted the F-35. Filmed on March 21-22, 2016. F-35s are from the 33rd Fighter Wing, and F-16s are from the South Carolina Air National Guard. 

Film Credits: TSgt Caycee Watson

1693.description:
A U.S. Air Force F-15 Eagle fighter jet takes off and does various in-flight maneuvers, flimed from the back seat cockpit. Filmed on April 1, 2016 by the 144th Fighter Wing, California Air National Guard.

Film Credits: MSgt David Loeffler

1694.description:
U.S. Marine Corps drill instructors get in-the-face of new recruits on pick-up day, at Marine Corps Recruit Depot in San Diego, CA on March 18, 2016.

Film Credits: Sgt John Lamb

1695.description:
A USAF KC-135 Stratotanker refuels French Mirage fighter jets and U.S. F/A-18 Super Hornets over Iraq in support of Operation Inherent Resolve on March 30, 2016. KC-135 aircrew from the 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron.

Film Credits: SSgt Aaron Richardson

1696.description:
U.S. Marine Corps UH-1Y Venom helicopter aircrews get some trigger time training over the Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range during a live-fire exercise at Weapons and Tactics Instructor (WTI) course 2-16 on March 30, 2016. 

Film Credits: Sgt Daniel Kujanpaa

1697.description:
Members of the U.S. Army 3rd Brigade Combat Team (Mechanized), 3rd Infantry Division conduct a large-scale live-fire exercise (Operation Hammer Strike) at Camp Buehring in Kuwait. The combined arms training included Assault Breacher Vehicles, HIMARS, M1A2 Tanks, Bradley Vehicles, Apache Helicopters, F-15 Close Air Support, Medical Evac Personnel and treatment, and Infantry Troops engaging close quarters. Filmed on November 7, 2012.

Film Credits: SPC Derrick Ramey, SPC Eddrenia Scott

1698.description:
Members of the Royal Netherlands Marine Corps (Korps Mariniers) shoot machine guns from Fast Riding Interceptor Special Craft (FRISC) during a live-fire bilateral training exercise at Camp Lejeune, NC on March 18, 2016.

Film Credits: Lance Cpl. Preston A. Shay

1699.description:
Subscribe to my channel for more military videos. This video was compiled from footage uploaded on my channel: https://www.youtube.com/GungHoVids -  I have over 2300 vids uploaded as of this writing, and more to come.

Credits: Footage courtesy of the U.S. DOD. 
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

1700.description:
U.S. Army AH-64 Apache helicopters land on the USS Ponce (AFSB(I)-15) in the Persian Gulf to rearm and refuel for a service-integrated training exercise. Filmed on March 17, 2016. Apache Unit - 3rd Squadron, 6th Cavalry Regiment, 40th Combat Aviation Brigade

Film Credits: SSG Ian Kummer

1701.description:
Scenes from the American aircraft carrier USS John C. Stennis (CVN-74) while on a regularly scheduled 7th Fleet deployment. The Stennis is number seven of ten nuclear powered Nimitz-Class supercarriers operated by the United States Navy. Filmed in March 2016.  

Film Credits: Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Eric Melone, Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Luke Moyer, Mass Communication Specialist Seaman Zachary C. Wolfe - U.S. Navy Video/Released

1702.description:
GoPro footage of 412th Civil Affairs Battalion Airborne Day Jump Drop Operations conducted on Wright-Patterson Air Force Base. Filmed on March 19, 2016. 

Film Credits: SrA Franchesca Pancham

1703.description:
U.S. Marines and members of the Australian Army team up in a live-fire assault exercise in support of the Korean Marine Exchange Program at Suseong Ri firing range near Pohang, South Korea on March 21, 2016. The Korean Marine Exchange Program is a combined exercise conducted by forward-deployed U.S. forces with the Republic of Korea Marine Corps and Australian Army in order to strengthen interoperability and working relationships across a wide range of military operations. Units - U.S. Marines from Company A, 1st Battalion, 3rd Marine Regiment and Company B, 6th Royal Australian Regiment, Australian Army and Republic of Korea Marine Corps 

Film Credits: LCpl Daniel Auvert

1704.description:
Video includes: U.S. Navy Sailors ride an LCAC from beachhead to ship, plus a combined force of U.S. Marines, Royal New Zealand soldiers, Republic of Korea Marines, and Australian Marines conduct an amphibious landing drill on the beaches near Pohang, South Korea. Units - 5th and 6th Air Naval Gunfire Liaison Companies, 3D Marine Expeditionary Brigade and Royal New Zealand Soldiers, 161st Artillery Battalion, 16th Field Regiment and Republic of Korea Marines and Assault Craft Unit (ACU) 5, USS Boxer (LHD-4). Filmed in March, 2016.

Film Credits: Jesse Monford, PO2 Debra Daco, SSgt Brandon Owen

1705.description:
Flight Deck Operations aboard the USS Ronald Reagan, as planes launch and land on March 23, 2016. The video shows an EA-18G Growler launching, F/A-18 Super Hornets being launched and recovered, a Grumman C-2 Greyhound being recovered, and what appears to be a wave-off of Super Hornet as it makes a landing approach.

Film Credits:  PO3 Devin Kates

1706.description:
U.S. Marines fire the M2 .50 caliber heavy machine gun during live fire training at Suseongri Live Fire Range, Pohang, Republic of Korea on March 3, 2016. Unit - 5th Air Naval Gunfire Liaison Company, 3rd Marine Expeditionary Brigade

Film Credits:  SSgt Brandon Owen

1707.description:
Kent Pietsch pilots the Jelly Bean plane, landing it on a moving truck at the Thunder And Lightning Over Arizona air show at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base on March 17, 2016.

Film Credits:  A1C Jean-Paul Arnaud-Marquez

1708.description:
A U.S. Air Force KC-135 Stratotanker from the 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron refuel a British E-3D Sentry over Iraq in support of Operation Inherent Resolve. Filmed on March 22, 2016.

Film Credits:  SSgt Michelle Di Ciolli

1709.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcon aircrews from the 177th Fighter Squadron conduct night flight operations at Atlantic City Air National Guard Base, NJ on March 12, 2016 during exercise Dastardly Devil 16-1. This exercise is designed to test the  operational readiness of the New Jersey Air National Guard (NJANG) in a deployed environment.

Film Credits:  MSgt Andrew Moseley

1710.description:
AV-8B Harriers with U.S. Marines Corps Attack Squadron 214 conduct flight operations aboard the USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6) on February 25, 2016.

Film Credits:  LCpl Servando Morales

1711.description:
A U.S. Air Force C-17 Globemaster III executes an air drop of supplies and men onto the U.S. Navy's Ice Camp Sargo in the Arctic Ocean during Ice Exercise (ICEX) 2016. Two squadrons worked together to airdrop ten PJs and two Alaska National Guard Soldiers. ICEX is a joint-force exercise which allows multiple military branches to assess readiness and operational capabilities of U.S. Navy submarines in the arctic. Units - 212th Rescue Squadron, 249th Airlift Squadron

Film Credits:  SrA Carly Kavish

1712.description:
The U.S. Navy aircraft carrier USS John C. Stennis (CVN-74) patrols the South China Sea, refueling at sea with USNS Tippecanoe (T-AO 199), and conducting flight operations of aircraft takeoffs and landings, plus cockpit footage of fighter jets - in response to China's recent attempt to take over sea lanes with a militay buildup on the Spratly Islands. Filmed In March 2016.

Film Credits:  PO3 Luke Moyer, PO3 Eric Melone, MC3 Kenneth Rodriguez Santiago

1713.description:
Examples of how American Air Superiority can shape the battlespace on the ground against an enemy. The MC-12 Liberty Intelligence, Surveillance and Reconnaissance (ISR) aircraft, plus the AC-130 Gunship are featured.

Film Credits:  SrA Andrew Buchanan, Staff Sgt. Cory Boatwright, Staff Sgt. Jeffrey Curtin, Staff Sgt. Robert Kingery, SrA James Bell, SrA Brandi Hansen

1714.description:
F-15 Fighter Jet air crews conduct a sortie scramble exercise at Kadena Air Base, Okinawa, Japan during routine training on March 18, 2016. Unit -  44th Fighter Squadron and the 44th Air Maintenance Unit

Film Credits:  SSgt Shawn Bryant

1715.description:
U.S. Army Paratroopers engage targets on a live-fire exercise during Exercise Rock Sokol at Pocek Range in Postonja, Slovenia. Unit -  2nd Battalion, 503rd Infantry Regiment, 173rd Airborne Brigade

Film Credits: Davide Dalla Massara

1716.description:
KC- 135 crewmembers from the 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron (USAF), execute aerial refueling of F-15 Strike Eagles over Iraq in support of Operation Inherent Resolve. Filmed on March 17, 2016.

Film Credits: SSgt Michelle Di Ciolli

1717.description:
U.S. and Republic of Korea (ROK) Marines send rounds downrange at Sanseori Range, South Korea during an artillery barrage live-fire exercise. The U.S. artillery battery fired the M-777A2 Howitzer while the South Koreans employed the KH-179 Howitzer. The live-fire event was part of Exercise Ssang Yong 16, filmed on March 15, 2016. Units - U.S. Marines with Golf Battery, 1st Battalion, 11th Marines, 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit and ROK Marines, Bravo Battery

Film Credits: SGT Mark Brejcha

1718.description:
U.S. Air Force B-52 Stratofortress Bombers from Barksdale AFB land at Moron Air Base in Spain for NATO exercises Cold Response 16 and SERPENTEX. Filmed on March 3, 2016. Unit - 2d Bomb Wing (2 BW),  Air Force Global Strike Command, Eighth Air Force.

Film Credits: A1C Jayson Burns

1719.description:
The U.S. Navy nuclear submarine USS Hartford (SSN-768) breaks through arctic ice as it surfaces near Ice Camp Sargo during Ice Exercise 2016 (ICEX 2016). Filmed on March 16, 2016.

Film Credits: PO2 Tyler Thompson

1720.description:
Amazing cockpit compilation footage from inside U.S. Fighter Jets as they takeoff, roll, and pull some gravity.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video/Released

1721.description:
SM-2 Missiles (Standard Missile-2) are fired by U.S. Navy ships during a live-fire Missile Exercise (MISSLEX) as the USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN-69) strike group completes the final certification exercise prior to deployment, Composite Training Unit Exercise (COMPTUEX). As part of the Aegis Weapons System, the SM-2 variants are lethal against subsonic, supersonic, low-altitude and high-altitude, high-maneuvering, diving, sea-skimming, anti-ship cruise missiles fighters, bombers and helicopters in an advanced electronic countermeasures environment. SM-2 missiles have successfully intercepted targets over its flight test history with more than 2,650 tests from United States and Allied ships.  Filmed on March 15, 2016. Ships - Arleigh Burke-class guided-missile destroyers USS Roosevelt (DDG-80), USS Nitze (DDG-94), USS Stout (DDG-55), USS Mason (DDG-87), Ticonderoga-class guided-missile cruisers USS San Jacinto (CG-56) and USS Monterey (CG-61) 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video/Released

1722.description:
U.S. Army Paratroopers fire an M119A3, 105mm Howitzer during the Exercise Rock Sokol at Pocek Range in Postonja, Slovenia on March 8, 2016. Unit - Battery B, 4th Battalion, 319th Airborne Field Artillery Regiment, 173rd Airborne Brigade

Film Credits: Paolo Bovo

1723.description:
Two F-35A Lightning II joint strike fighter jets with the 62 Fighter Squadron successfully deployed 4 laser-guided bombs in a test over the Barry M. Goldwater Range, AZ. The test was flown out of Luke Air Force Base in Arizona, and it brings the F-35A one step closer to Initial Operating Capability (IOC). Filmed on March 15, 2016.

Film Credits: Released by the USAF/Luke AFB

1724.description:
Two clips showing 155mm self propelled howitzers. Clip One shows the German 131st Artillery Battalion - Panzerhaubitze 2000 firing rounds at Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany on March 15, 2016. Clip Two shows the American 1st Battalion, 82nd Field Artillery Regiment - M109A6 Paladin firing rounds at Rodriguez Range in South Korea on March 10, 2016.

Film Credits: Gertrud Zach, SGT Fred Brown

1725.description:
U.S. Navy and Coast Guard divers execute a dive under an ice flow in the Arctic Ocean during Ice Exercise (ICEX) 2016 at Ice Camp Sargo on March 10, 2016. Units - Mobile Diving and Salvage Unit 2, Regional Dive Locker West and Regional Dive Locker Pacific 

Film Credits: MC2 Tyler Thompson

1726.description:
Movie actor Gerard Butler receives flight surgeon briefing, pilot briefing, and safety training prior to climbing into the back seat of an F-16 Fighting Falcon to fly with the U.S. Air Force Thunderbirds aerial demonstration team. Afterwards he describes his experience. Filmed at Nellis Air Force Base, NV on March 5, 2016. 

Film Credits: SrA Rachel Maxwell

1727.description:
Air and Marine Operations of the U.S. Customs and Border Protection conduct a demonstration at the 2016 Tucson Air Show. Filmed on March 13, 2016.

Film Credits: Daniel Barrios

1728.description:
F-35A Lighting II takeoff from Eglin Air Force Base, reaching 10,000 flying hours on it's way to Initial Operating Capability (IOC). Filmed on March 10, 2016.

Film Credits: SSgt Tarelle Walker

1729.description:
A Marines Corps KC-130J Super Hercules conducts aerial refueling with an MV-22b Osprey and an F-35 Lightening II during a training flight over Southern California on March 8, 2016. Units - Marine Aerial Refueled and Transport Squadron (VMGR) 352, Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron (VMM) 165, Marine Fighter Attack Squadron (VMFA) 121

Film Credits: LCpl Harley Robinson

1730.description:
Various ships of the U.S. Navy and Republic of Korea assemble off the coast of the ROK for exercise Ssang Yong 16 on March 8, 2016. Ssang Yong 16 is a biennial combined amphibious exercise conducted by forward-deployed U.S. forces with the Republic of Korea Navy and Marine Corps, Australian Army, and the New Zealand Army in order to strengthen interchangeability and working relationships across a wide range of military operations. Filmed on March 9. 2016.

Film Credits: Released by the U.S. Navy

1731.description:
A-10 Thunderbolt II air crews with the 455th Air Expeditionary Wing fly strike sorties over Afghanistan. The A-10 is nicknamed The Warthog. Filmed in March 2014.

Film Credits: SrA Anthony Hetlage
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

1732.description:
U.S soldiers from 1st Battalion, 503rd Infantry Regiment, 173rd Infantry Brigade Combat Team (Airborne) conduct Exercise Sky Soldier 16 in cooperation with Spanish Armed Forces Airborne Brigade (BRIPAC) . The exercise took place at Chinchilla training area, Spain on March 8, 2016. 

Film Credits: Vincenzo Vitiello

1733.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcons with the 36th Fighter Squadron takeoff at Osan Air Base, South Korea as part of Exercise Beverley Midnight 16-01. The exercise is designed to test the warfighting capabilities of units under the 51st Fighter Wing focusing on readiness, defending the base, and executing flying operations. Filmed on March 7, 2016.

Film Credits: SSgt D.J. Ayres

1734.description:
A C-17 Globemaster III transport plane conducts a series of touch-and-go landings at Bryant Army Airfield in Alaska on March 7, 2016. This marked the first time a C-17 has used the runway since it was built in 1958. Unit - 517th Airlift Squadron, U.S. Air Force

Film Credits: SrA Carly Kavish

1735.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a live-fire squad assault course on Camp Red Devil at Fort Carson, CO. Filmed on February 27, 2016. Units - 1st Platoon, 2nd Platoon, Alpha Battery, 3d Low Altitude Air Defense Battalion 

Film Credits: Cpl Danial Ghaffari, Cpl Xzavior McNeal

1736.description:
Three B-52 Bomber air crews takeoff from Barksdale AFB in support of U.S. Strategic Command's Bomber Assurance and Deterrence Mission for Exercise Cold Response 16 in Norway. Filmed on February 29, 2016.

Film Credits: A1C Shellby Matullo

1737.description:
U.S. Marine Corps drill instructors send their recruits through the obstacle course aboard Marine Corps Recruit Depot San Diego, CA on February 25, 2016. Recruits are sent through the obstacle course multiple times to test their endurance and strength during boot camp. Unit -  Company K, 3rd Recruit Training Battalion, Recruit Training Regiment

Film Credits: Sgt John Lamb

1738.description:
Various U.S. Fighter Aircraft taxis and takeoff during night operations at Exercise Red Flag 2016 (Nellis AFB) with Las Vegas night lights as a backdrop. Filmed January and February 2016.

Film Credits: A1C Christina Ensley, A1C Mychal Fox, William Lewis, TSgt Scott Olguin, SSgt William Jackson

1739.description:
Several Squadrons of U.S. Marine Corps EA-6B Prowler Electronic Warfare Jets conduct a formation flight above Marine Corps Air Station Cherry Point, NC on March 1, 2016. The Prowler is a twin engine, four seat aircraft used for jamming enemy radar systems, and in gathering radio intelligence on enemy air defense systems. Squadrons - VMAQT-1, VMAQ-2, VMAQ-3, and VMAQ-4

Film Credits: CWO2 Izzel Sanchez

1740.description:
U.S. Marines fire Stinger missiles at Vaagan Range in Orland, Norway on Feb 25, 2016. The FIM-92C Stinger is a Man-portable air-defense system (MANPADS) surface-to-air missile (SAM). Unit - Bravo Battery, 2nd Low Altitude Air Defense (LAAD) Battalion

Film Credits: Sgt Kathryn Bynum

1741.description:
U.S. Marines conduct mounted patrols on Camp Red Devil at Fort Carson, CO - firing .50 Caliber Machine Guns from High Mobility Multipurpose Wheeled Vehicles (HMMWVs). This training event was filmed on February 19, 2016. 

Film Credits: Cpl Danial Ghaffari

1742.description:
U.S. Air Force Fighter Jets (F-15 Strike Eagles, F-16 Fighting Falcons, A-10 Thunderbolt IIs) conduct Close Air Support training at Aerial Gunnery Range Grand Bay, Moody AFB, Georgia on February 18, 2016.  

Film Credits: SrA Braden Anderson

1743.description:
U.S. F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 13th Fighter Squadron conduct weapons training during exercise Cope North 16 out of Andersen Air Force Base, Guam on February 25, 2016. 

Film Credits: Senior Airman Andrew Walck

1744.description:
Explosive Ordnance Disposal (EOD) Marines with 2nd Explosive, Battalion 252 conduct a Demolition Range in preparation for Exercise Cold Response 16 on February 22, 2016 in Norway.

Film Credits: Sgt Kirstin Merrimarahajara

1745.description:
Focus on the F-35A Lightning II fighter jet  at Hill Air Force Base in Utah, and why the U.S. Air Force is going forward full speed ahead with the project and going to make it  successful... in spite of the haters. 

Film Credits: This work, Team Hill F-35 Video, is free of known copyright restrictions under U.S. copyright law.
https://www.dvidshub.net/video/451204/team-hill-f-35-video#.Vs0kTLerSM8

1746.description:
U.S. Marines conduct multiple live-fire training evolutions during Exercise Fuji Viper 16-3 in Japan. Marines from 1st Battalion, 3rd Marine Regiment were filmed over a 2 week period of Fuji Viper - a training exercise for Marines and Sailors to maintain proficiency in the U.S. Pacific Command area of operations. Filmed in February 2016. 

Film Credits: LCpl Cody Shepard

1747.description:
Amphibious assault ship USS Boxer (LHD-4) takes on food and supplies during a replenishment-at-sea (RAS) with fleet replenishment oiler USNS Henry J. Kaiser (T-AO-187). Filmed in time lapse on February 21. 2016. 

Film Credits: PO2 Debra Daco, Mass Communications Specialist 3rd Class Jesse Monford

1748.description:
The U.S. Air Force Thunderbirds Demo team is escorted by a KC-135 Stratotanker for aerial refueling on a trip from Nellis AFB to Florida. Filmed on February 19, 2016. KC-135 from McDill AFB.  

Film Credits:  A1C Bradley Tipton, Communications audio courtesy of Ryan Raiche ABC Action News

1749.description:
Service members from the Royal Thai, Republic of Korea, and U.S. Armed Forces participate in a combined arms live fire exercise (CALFEX) at Bam Cham Khrem in Thailand - Exercise Cobra Gold 2016. Filmed on February 18, 2016. 

Film Credits:  LCpl Brooke Deiters

1750.description:
U.S. Marines with 1st Battalion, 3rd Marine Regiment conduct live-fire training on 60mm mortars, .50 caliber machine guns from humvees, and hand grenades at Camp Fuji in Japan. Filmed in February, 2016.

Film Credits:  LCpl Cody Shepard

1751.description:
Air Force Pararescue is the only U.S. Department of Defense combat force specifically organized and equipped to conduct full spectrum personnel recovery. "These Things We Do, That Others May Live", is the statement they train by, live by, and die to achieve.

Film Credits:  TSgt Amanda Helton

1752.description:
Norwegian soldiers from the Telemark Battalion demonstrate the effects of icy water on U.S. Marines from the Combined Arms Company in Rena, Norway on February 16, 2016.

Film Credits:  Sgt Tatum Vayavananda

1753.description:
B-1 Pilots and Crew Members gear up, perform pre-flight checks with various footage of the cockpit and instrument panels - then they taxi and takeoff at Dyess Air Force Base in Texas. The official designation of this long-range supersonic bomber is B-1 Lancer, but it has a nickname... "The Bone" which is a derivative name coming from B-One. Filmed on February 2, 2016.

Film Credits: A1C Shawn White

1754.description:
Hugh Jackman the actor who plays "Wolverine" in the X-Men Movies prepares for a back seat flight aboard a USAF F-16 Fighting Falcon and then follows through... here is the footage. Hugh was in town at Fort Worth Air Force Reserve Base In Texas to promote his upcoming film "Eddie The Eagle" and show his support for the U.S. Military. Filmed on February 19, 2016.

Film Credits: SrA Benedick Calantas, PO2 Jason Howard

1755.description:
Flight Deck Operations from two U.S. Navy Wasp Class amphibious assault ships... USS Boxer (LHD-4) and USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6). Filmed over December 2015 and February 2016.

Film Credits: Mass Communications Specialist 3rd Class Jesse Monford, Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Debra Daco, LCpl Servando Morales

1756.description:
U.S. Marines point their M1A1 Main Battle Tanks at targets on a live-fire range while working with the Norwegian Telemark Battalion in Rena, Norway on February 18, 2016.

Film Credits: Sgt Tatum Vayavananda

1757.description:
Training fighter pilots during the F-16 Basic Course at Luke Air Force Base in Arizona. Luke AFB instructor pilots talk about the training and mindset that are involved in preparing a pilot to fly combat missions. Filmed on February 16, 2016. 

Film Credits: MSgt Michael Jackson

1758.description:
U.S. Marines M1A1 Tanks demonstrate their speed as they travel on a road through a Nordic forest during exercise Cold Response 16. Filmed on February 16, 2016 • Bi-lateral training with Norway and the United States held at Rena, Norway.

Film Credits: Sgt Tatum Vayavananda

1759.description:
The Norwegian Telemark Battalion instructs U.S. Marine M1A1 tankers on techniques of driving tracked vehicles in winter conditions on an ice track in Rena, Norway on February 15, 2016. This training is part of exercise Cold Response 16...  bilateral training to improve U.S. Marine Corps capability to operate in cold-weather environments. It looks like the Leopard 2 tankers won the skate match.

1760.description:

1780.description:

In this video you will see a KC-135 Stratotanker crew from the 91st Air Refueling Squadron, MacDill Air Force Base, Florida, conducting a refueling mission as part of the Tanker Task Force for Exercise Red Flag 16-1. The footage includes refueling of U.S. Navy EA-18G Growlers, F-15C Eagles from the 131st Fighter Squadron, Barnes Air National Guard Base, and F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 157th Fighter Squadron from McEntire Joint National Guard Base, South Carolina. Aerial refueling is a very intricate operation between aircraft... it could all go to hell in an instant... without expert coordination. Filmed on January 28, 2016.

1795.description:

AFGSC is a Major Command of the United States Air Force and is based at Barksdale Air Force Base in Louisiana. AFGSC provides combat-ready forces to conduct strategic nuclear deterrence and global strike operations in support of the President of the United States and combatant commanders. The command has a worldwide area of responsibility and installations assigned to AFGSC include Barksdale Air Force Base, Malmstrom Air Force Base, Minot Air Force Base, F. E. Warren Air Force Base, Dyess Air Force Base, Ellsworth Air Force Base, Kirtland Air Force Base, and Whiteman Air Force Base. The motto of AFGSC is "Deter...Assure...Strike!"

Basically the United States is saying... back off little Kim because we have nukes too. Filmed on January 10, 2016.

1812.description:

Many experts are still not convinced that North Korea set off a Hydrogen Bomb or just a boosted Atomic Bomb. Filmed on January 10, 2016.

1813.description:
The M1128 Stryker Mobile Gun System (MGS) carries a 105mm cannon, the same gun tube of the original M-1 Abrams tank. The main purpose of the MGS is to provide direct fire support for infantry troops - for example to knockout bunkers, machine gun positions, and buildings occupied by enemy troops. The MGS is autoloading, can store 18 rounds of main gun ammo in the turret, and has a rate of fire of six rounds per minute. It also mounts an M2 .50 caliber machine gun and an M240C coaxial machine gun.

Film Credits: SPC Andrew Geisler, SGT Kyle Burns, SSG Katie Gray

1814.description:
A live-fire exercise of the Patriot Missile System from a NATO Missile Firing Installation (NAMFI) in Greece. Filmed on October 1, 2015. The Patriot system is a long-range, all-altitude, all-weather air defense system to counter tactical ballistic missiles, cruise missiles, and advanced aircraft. It is in service in Egypt, Germany, Greece, Israel, Japan, Kuwait, Netherlands, Saudi Arabia and Taiwan.

Developed by Raytheon, the Patriot missile is equipped with a track-via-missile (TVM) guidance system. Midcourse correction commands are transmitted to the guidance system from a control center.

The target acquisition system in the missile acquires the target in the terminal phase of flight and transmits the data using the TVM downlink via the ground radar to the control station for final course corrections and calculations. The course correction commands are transmitted to the missile via the missile track command uplink. The high-explosive 90kg warhead is situated behind the terminal guidance section.

The range of the missile is 70km and maximum altitude is greater than 24km. The minimum flight time is less than 9 seconds, and the maximum flight time is less than 3.5 minutes.

Since 2010, Raytheon has developed the Patriot guidance enhanced missile (GEM-T). The upgrade involves a new fuse and the insertion of a new low noise oscillator, which increases the seeker sensitivity to low radar cross-section targets. The GEM-T missile provides an upgraded capability to defeat air-breathing, cruise, and ballistic missiles. More than 1000 GEM-Ts are now in service.

Film Credits:  SrA Zachary Boyer

1815.description:
U.S. Air Force KC-135 crew members from the 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron, refuel a B-1B Lancer and A-10 Thunderbolt II aircraft over Iraq in support of Operation Inherent Resolve on January 6, 2015.

Film Credits: SSgt Michelle Di Ciolli

1816.description:
The Expeditionary Fire Support System (EFSS) was developed for the U.S. Marine Corps to fill the gap between the 81mm mortar and the 155mm howitzer. With the new GPS guided precision extended range munition (PERM) developed by Ratheon, the M327 has an extended range of 10 miles with an accuracy of 6 feet, and having 2.5 - 3 times more lethality. The extra range comes from tail fins and canards for in-flight adjustments and to make the round glide as it descends, and the greater lethality is a result of this flight path - normal artillery rounds impact at a 45 degree angle, which blows the top half of the round straight up into the air, but descending at a sharp angle places more energy and fragmentation directly on a target. 

Film Credits:  MSgt Bryce Piper, Sgt Paul Robbins, Sgt Joseph Scanlan

1817.description:

Presumably this would include operations in the town of Marjah where one U.S. Serviceman was killed and several U.S. Special Operations Forces where pinned down for hours by Taliban fighters on January 5, 2015.

1818.description:
Joint Terminal Attack Controllers (JTAC) are specially qualified service members who direct combat aircraft  from a forward position while engaged in close air support and offensive air support operations. U.S. Air Force Combat Control Teams (CCT) are ground combat forces specialized in air traffic control, fire support and command, control, and communications in covert or austere environments. CCTs are often assigned individually or as a team to Army Special Forces, Army Rangers, and Navy SEALs to provide expert air support coordination and communications capabilities. Many CCTs also qualify and maintain proficiency as joint terminal attack controllers.

This video shows two clips of JTACs and CCTs calling for fire support from A-10 Thunderbolt II aircraft (Warthogs). 1st Clip: U.S. Marine Corps JTACs work with A-10 pilots during a live-fire exercise at Savannah Combat Readiness Training Center (CRTC) in Townsend, GA on May 20, 2014. 2nd Clip: A U.S. Air Force Combat Control Team call in A-10s during a live ordnance drop near Nellis AFB in Nevada on September 23, 2011.

Film Credits: Sgt Gregory Boyd, SrA Aaron Hauser

Here is footage of jet fighters from: Sweden, the United Arab Eremites, Australia, Pakistan, Colombia, and The United Kingdom as they taxis, takeoff, and land during the exercise. Red Flag is an advanced aerial combat training exercise hosted annually at Nellis Air Force Base in Nevada.

Film Credits:  SrA Aaron Hauser, William Lewis, SrA Rachel Maxwell, TSgt Colleen Urban,  A1C Rachel Webster

The 115th Fighter Wing is a unit of the Wisconsin Air National Guard, stationed at Truax Field Air National Guard Base in Madison, Wisconsin. 1833.description:
The Israel Missile Defense Organization (IMDO) and the U.S. Missile Defense Agency (MDA) successfully completed a series of tests of the David's Sling Weapon System designated DST-4. David's Sling is an Israel Defense Forces military system being jointly developed by the Israeli defense contractor Rafael Advanced Defense Systems and the American defense contractor Raytheon, designed to intercept medium to long-range rockets and cruise missiles fired at ranges from 40 km (24.85 miles) to 300 km (186.41 miles). It is designed to intercept the newest generation of tactical ballistic missiles, such as Iskander, using an on-board dual CCD/IR seekers to distinguish between decoys and the actual warhead of the missile. David's Sling is meant to bolster the second tier of Israel's theater missile defense system. The two-stage radar and electro-optic guided system has a 70-300 kilometer range, three times that of Iron Dome. The system can be deployed against aircraft and missiles, with plans to convert the system to intercept cruise missiles in the future. DST-4 was the final milestone before declaring delivery of an operational system to the Israeli Air Force in 2016. Filmed on December 21, 2015.

http://www.mda.mil/

Film Credits: Leah Garton

1834.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 455th Air Expeditionary Wing (455 AEW) still fly combat missions over Afghanistan as of December 2015. The 455 AEW is a provisional United States Air Force unit attached to U.S. Air Forces Central Command at Bagram Airfield, Afghanistan. An F-16 is prepared for a sortie. Filmed on December 14, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Timothy Kirchner

1835.description:
The F-35 Lighting II Joint Strike Fighter is said to be the most advanced military aircraft in the world. Some people agree - and many people disagree. It is certainly the most expensive military weapons system ever developed over the entire projected lifetime of the program. Although the F-35 has been the object of much criticism, the United States is going "full-tilt" ahead with the project, and three variants of the fighter jet are being built and are in various stages of testing and deployment... F-35A (conventional takeoff and landing) for the Air Force, F-35B (short take-off and vertical-landing) for the Marine Corps, and F-35C (Catapult Assisted Take-Off But Arrested Recovery) for the Navy. If Lockheed Martin can fulfill it's promises, the F-35 may well be the most effective military aircraft on Earth. But those promises are very lofty. So love it or hate it, the F-35 Lightning II is here to stay... and time will tell the full story of this aircraft. Three variants of the F-35 Joint Strike Fighter are shown in this video.

Film Credits: A1C Roswell Sartwell, MC3 Lisa Reese, MC3 Theodore Quintana, PFC Remington Hall, Sgt Maxwell Pennington, Cpl Travis Gershaneck

1836.description:
The 174th Attack Wing (New York Air National Guard) flying the MQ-9 Reaper drone is now conducting training flights from Hancock Field Air National Guard Base and Syracuse Hancock International Airport as of December 16, 2015. The MQ-9 Reaper is the most deadly remotely piloted aircraft (RPA) in the U.S. Air Force arsenal as of this time - having more ordnance handling capability than the MQ-1 Predator drone.

The 174th Attack Wing is the first Air Force organization in the United States to fly an RPA in class "C" airspace, the common airspace around commercial airports. 

Prior to this date all flight operations of the MQ-9 aircraft were conducted at Wheeler Sack Army Airfield at Fort Drum. The Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) granted approval for the 174th to begin launch and recovery operations with the MQ-9 Reaper drone from Hancock Field Air National Guard Base and the Syracuse International Airport this week.

The FAA approval follows a technical and operational review for the safe and effective takeoff and recovery of MQ-9 aircraft at Hancock Field, home to operator and maintenance training of MQ-9 crews. The FAA modified airspace around Hancock Field in 2013 to expand available training areas and provide transition from high altitude down to Hancock Field. 

The 174th Attack Wing was established in 1947 as the first Air National Guard flying unit in New York State. Throughout its history, it has flown F-47 Thunderbolts, F-51 Mustangs, F-84 Thunderjets, F-86 Sabres, A-37 Dragonflies, A-10 Thunderbolts and the F-16 Fighting Falcon. It currently flies the MQ-9 Reaper remotely piloted aircraft.  Filmed On December 16, 2015.

Film & Text Credits: MSgt Eric Miller, Edited by Gung Ho Vids

1837.description:
An artillery command center controls digital targeting of M119A3 Howitzers. U.S. paratroopers and Italian army soldiers set up and fire M119A3 Howitzers during Exercise Shardana at Capo Teulada in Italy. Filmed October 2015. Unit - 4th Battalion, 319th Airborne Field Artillery Regiment, 173rd Airborne Brigade and Italian Army Soldiers

Film Credits: Massimo Bovo

1838.description:
Special Operations Soldiers from Special Operations Command Europe conduct a requalification jump out of Stuttgart Army Airfield in Germany on December 10, 2015. 

Film Credits: Martin Greeson

1839.description:
Footage of F-15C Eagle fighter jets from the 120th Fighter Wing Detachment-1 on the flight line at Joint Base Pearl Harbor–Hickam in January 2012. The F-15s, which were part of the Montana Air National Guard, were performing alert missions as F-22 Raptors were being converted to full duty status in Hawaii. In March 2014 the 120th Fighter Wing was changed over to the 120th Airlift Wing (still stationed at Great Falls Air National Guard Base) and the F-15s were reassigned to other bases. Yes this footage is relatively old but it's still cool, so I posted it.

Film Credits: SrA Nikolas Asmussen

1840.description:
M109A6 Paladin Self-Propelled Howitzers send some rounds downrange at Camp Udairi Training Range in Kuwait. The howitzer crews were completing routine certification and qualification in order to ensure readiness in support of Operations Spartan Shield and Inherent Resolve. Filmed on December 13, 2015. Unit - 1st Battalion, 7th Field Artillery Regiment, U.S. Army

Film Credits: SPC Megan Lobos

1841.description:
F-35A Lightning II fighter jets taxis and takeoff at Tyndall Air Force Base during air combat exercise Checkered Flag 16-1 on December 11, 2015. Checkered Flag is a large-force exercise allowing various legacy and 5th generation fighter aircraft to train together in combat scenarios. F-35s are from the 33rd Fighter Wing.

Film Credits: A1C Roswell Sartwell

1842.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcon and F-22 Raptor fighter jets taxi and takeoff at Tyndall AFB during Air Combat Exercise Checkered Flag 16-1. Filmed on December 11, 2015. Units -  F-22s with 95th Fighter Squadron, F-16s with 77th Fighter Squadron, F-16s with the 18th Aggressor Squadron, T-38s with the 2nd Fighter Training Squadron

Film Credits: A1C Roswell Sartwell

1843.description:
The U.S. Air Force RQ-4B Global Hawk has a wingspan of 130.9 ft (39.9 m), which is longer than the wingspan of a Boeing 757 at 124.6 ft (38 m). RQ-4B is an unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) surveillance aircraft and is arguably the largest military UAV flying regular missions as of 2015. It is powered by a single Rolls-Royce F137-RR-100 turbofan engine with a cruising speed of 357 mph, maximum range of 14,154 mi, and maximum altitude of 60,000 ft. The Global Hawk performs a similar role as the Lockheed U-2 and by using high-resolution synthetic aperture radar (SAR), long-range electro-optical/infrared (EO/IR) sensors, as well as long loiter times over target areas - it can survey as much as 40,000 square miles of terrain a day. Full specs of the RQ-4 Block 40 Global Hawk from Northrop Grumman:
 
Specifications
Wingspan ........................................................ 130.9 ft (39.9 m)
Length ................................................................... 47.6 ft (14.5m)
Height ....................................................................... 15.4 ft (4.7m)
Gross Takeoff Weight ..................... 32,250 lbs (14,628 kg)
Maximum Altitude ................................... 60,000 ft (18.3 km)
Payload ...................................................... 3,000 lbs (1,360 kg)
Ferry Range ....................................... 12,300 nm (22,780 km)
Loiter Velocity .................... 310 knots TAS (True Air Speed)
On-Station Endurance at 1,200 nm ............................ 24 hrs
Maximum Endurance .................................................... 32+ hrs

http://www.northropgrumman.com/Capabilities/GlobalHawk/Documents/Datasheet_GH_Block_40.pdf

Film Credits: SrA Andrew Buchanan, SSgt Priscilla Christensen

1844.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcons, F-22 Raptors and F-35 Lighting II fighter jets launch at Tyndall AFB during Checkered Flag 16-1. Checkered Flag is a USAF large-force exercise which gives a variety of legacy and fifth-generation aircraft the chance to practice and train together in combat scenarios. Filmed on December 11, 2015.

Film Credits: SSgt William Jackson

1845.description:
An F-35B Lightning II Joint Strike Fighter from Marine Fighter Attack Squadron 121 (VMFA-121) conducts a vertical landing and short takeoff at a Forward Arming and Refueling Point (FARP) at Marine Corps Base, Camp Pendleton in California on December 10, 2015. This marked an important milestone in the evolution of the aircraft as it conducted the first Close Air Support missions in support of ground combat elements during exercise Steel Knight 16.

Film Credits: LCpl Jessica Lucio

1846.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 18th Aggressor Squadron and F-22 Raptors from the 325th Fighter Wing takeoff on the first day of Exercise Checkered Flag 16-1 at Tyndall AFB in Florida. Checkered Flag is a large-force exercise which gives a variety of legacy and fifth-generation aircraft the chance to practice and train combat scenarios together.  Filmed on December 10, 2015.

Film Credits: SSgt William Jackson

1847.description:
An F-35B Lightning II from Marine Fighter Attack Squadron 121 (VMFA-121) participates in a simulated forward refueling exercise at Red Beach on Camp Pendleton, CA. Filmed on December 12, 2015.

Film Credits: Sgt Brian Marion, Cpl Alissa Schuning

1848.description:
U.S. Air Force aircrews of the 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron practice dry contact aerial training between a KC-135 Stratotanker and a KC-10 Extender in the skies over Southwest Asia on December 9, 2015. 

Film Credits: SSgt Robert Kingery

1849.description:
Scenes of U.S. Army Soldiers training at Fort Irwin National Training Center (NTC) in the Mojave Desert, California.

Film Credits: Courtesy U.S. Army

1850.description:
U.S. Air Force Thunderbirds receive mid-air refueling from the 22nd Air Refueling Wing out of McConnell Air Force Base on August 13, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Rachel Maxwell

1851.description:
Video explains the intricacies of aerial refueling and how the U.S. Air Force uses this capability and aircraft like the KC-135 Stratotanker to maintain air supremacy across the globe. Unit - 191st Air Refueling Squadron, Selfridge Air National Guard Base, MI

Film Credits: TSgt Rachel Barton

1852.description:
Reconnaissance Marines land on the beach and send back vital information to commanders off the coast to paint a picture of the landing zone and enemy activity. Working off of real-time intelligence sent by the Recon Marines, commanders then organize a larger beach landing that is used to support a Marine Air Ground Task Force operation in a forward-deployed combat environment. Units - 2nd Reconnaissance Battalion and 2nd Assault Amphibian Battalion, 2nd Marine Division, II Marine Expeditionary Force

Film Credits: Sgt Paul Peterson

1853.description:
U.S. Soldiers conduct weapons familiarization training with German soldiers at Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany on December 9, 2015. Unit - Combined Arms Training Center, 7th Army Joint Multinational Training Command (JMTC)

Film Credits: Markus Rauchenberger

1854.description:
Two episodes of "Welcome To The MEU" - a video series following the 31st MEU (Marine Expeditionary Unit).
Recon Corpsman - In this episode, take a behind-the-scenes look at the highly trained corpsmen who serve in the Marine Force Recon community - the Special Amphibious Reconnaissance Corpsman (SARC).
Force Recon - In this episode, lock and load as you tag along with one the most demanding and specialized units in the Marines Corps.

Welcome To The MEU Playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLnOwvB9zfF0zAw5ol1zIN-z-r8xP0nOB5

Film Credits:  Cpl August Light

1855.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers fly in on UH-60 Black Hawk helicopters during an air assault exercise at Schofield Barracks Army Base in Hawaii on December 2, 2015. Unit - 2nd Battalion, 35th Infantry Regiment, 3rd Brigade Combat Team, 25th Infantry Division

Film Credits: SGT Lawren Massey

1856.description:
A U.S. Air Force F-15 Pilot with the 173rd Fighter Wing GoPro cockpit video with music audio - routine training mission. Filmed in 2014.

Film Credits: United States DOD Produced Footage 
Music Copyright Protected by AudioBlocks and Gung Ho Vids

1857.description:
A U.S. Air Force KC-135 Stratotanker from the 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron refuels Canadian CF-18 Hornets over Southwest Asia on December 4, 2015 - in support of Operation Inherent Resolve. 

Film Credits: SSgt Robert Kingery

1858.description:
M1A2 Tanks, M109A6 Paladin Howitzers, and Bradley Fighting Vehicles send rounds down range in a combined arms joint live-fire exercise at Fort Hood, TX. The 2nd Brigade Combat Team (Black Jack Brigade) and the 3rd Brigade Combat Team (Grey Wolf) are featured in this video - both elements are part of the 1st Cavalry Division, U.S. Army.

Film Credits: SGT Gonzales, 11th PAD and SGT Elliot Valdez

1859.description:
A U.S. Air Force E-8 Joint Surveillance Target Attack Radar System (Joint STARS) aircraft is readied for mission launch at Al Udeid Air Base in Qatar on November 24, 2015. The E-8 Joint STARS is a ground surveillance, battle management, and command and control aircraft. It tracks ground vehicles and some aircraft, collects imagery, and relays tactical pictures to ground and air theater commanders. Unit - 7th Expeditionary Airborne Command and Control Squadron (7 EACCS)

Film Credits: TSgt Charles McNamara

1860.description:
The Arleigh Burke-class guided-missile destroyer USS Lassen (DDG 82) test fires the close-in weapon system (CIWS) on September 16, 2015.

Film Credits: PO2 Corey Todd Jones

1861.description:
U.S Marines and Australian Army Soldiers conduct an integrated artillery and air assault during Exercise Talisman Sabre 15 at Bradshaw Training Area, Northern Territory in Australia. Filmed in July, 2015. 

Film Credits: SGT Kyle Burns

1862.description:
U.S. Soldiers from 2nd Squadron, 2nd Cavalry Regiment shoot the FGM-148 Javelin Missile system at a live-fire exercise on the Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany on November 24, 2015.

Film Credits: SGT Kyle Burns

1863.description:
U.S. Marines from the 31st MEU conduct combat marksmanship drills while forward deployed on the USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6). The Marines shot M9 Beretta pistols, M4 Carbine and M16A4 Service Rifles at targets set up on the elevator deck of the Wasp class amphibious assault ship to maintain proficiency. The 31st MEU is the only continuously forward deployed MEU (Marine Expeditionary Unit) in the Marine Corps.

Film Credits: LCpl Cody Woods, Cpl August Light,  Cpl Abbey Perria

1864.description:
Cockpit Video from an AS350 A-Star helicopter of the U.S. Customs & Border Protection (CBP) as it conducts a tour over Tucson, AZ and surrounding mountains. Filmed on November 19, 2015.

Film Credits: Daniel Barrios

1865.description:
USMC tank crews participate in Tiger Competition XII on Camp Lejeune, NC. The competition is used to pick the top tanker crew in the Marine Corps through fire and maneuver missions. Filmed on June 2, 2015. Unit - 2nd Tanks, 2D Marine Division

Film Credits: LCpl Adam Edwards

1866.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15E Strike Eagles taxi and takeoff during Exercise Razor Talon at Seymour Johnson Air Force Base, NC on November 20, 2015. During the exercise, aircrews trained to suppress and destroy enemy air defenses, as well as refine airborne refueling operations. Unit - 4th Fighter Wing

Film Credits: SrA Candace Harris

1867.description:
U.S. Air Force C-130 Hercules takeoff and aerial view as it navigates over scenic California coastline and through red night skies - music audio.

Film Credits: Douglas Lay
