Creative Consultant: https://www.youtube.com/user/mejszjek

1868.description:
U.S. Navy Landing Craft Air Cushion (LCAC) launches and embarks aboard the amphibious assault ship USS Boxer (LHD 4 ). Filmed on September 5, 2015.

Film Credits: LT Russell Wolfkiel, CPO Steven Zurell

1869.description:
U.S. Army sniper candidates go through basic long-range target shooting in Djibouti, Africa. Filmed on October 14, 2015. 

Film Credits: A1C Ashley Mikaio

1870.description:
B-roll footage of a C-17 Globemaster III from Wright-Patterson Air Force Base. Various panning and zooming shots of the transport plane, plus taxis, takeoff and touch-and-go landing. Public Domain footage filmed on August 20, 2015 - available for download here: https://www.dvidshub.net/video/437875/c-17-broll#.VlQiELerSM_

Film Credits: James Truitt

1871.description:
The AC-130 Gunship is the aircraft that the Taliban feared most in Afghanistan. Video shows AC-130s from Air Force Special Operations Command (AFSOC) in live-fire action.

Film Credits: Staff Sgt. Cory Boatwright, Staff Sgt. Jeffrey Curtin, Staff Sgt. Robert Kingery

1872.description:
The aircraft carrier USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76) sails with ships from the Japanese Navy in the waters south of Japan during a photo exercise on November 23, 2015.

Film Credits: PO2 Adrienne Powers

1873.description:
Cockpit video of an A-10 Thunderbolt II as it flies in formation over the Fresno State vs United States Air Force Academy football game on October 24th, 2015 - filmed in fast and slow motion. A-10s from Davis-Monthan Air Force Base.

Film Credits: A1C Jean-Paul Arnaud-Marquez

1874.description:
Footage of U.S. Soldiers training with the M1117 ASV. The M1117 Guardian Armored Security Vehicle, or ASV, is an internal security vehicle manufactured by Textron Marine & Land Systems for use by the U.S. Army's Military Police Corps. The design was inspired by the French VAB. Its armament consists of an Mk 19 grenade launcher and M2HB Browning machine gun, mounted in the turret and a M240H Medium Machine Gun mounted outside the gunner's hatch. Unit - 203rd Military Police Battalion

Film Credits: SGT Brenda Smith

1875.description:
A-10 Thunderbolt II Warthogs pre-flight checks and takeoffs at Biggs Air Field on Fort Bliss, TX in preparation for Operation Hustler Trough II - a joint fires exercise with participants from more than 10 different Army and Air Force elements from across the United States. Filmed on November 2, 2015.

Film Credits: SGT Thanh Pham

1876.description:
B-52 aircrews perform a minimum interval takeoff (MITO) at Barksdale Air Force Base. A MITO is designed by the United States Air Force to get its bomber fleet in the air within fifteen minutes of an alert of incoming missiles, that being the time in which the bases would be obliterated. Filmed on September 3, 2014.

Film Credits: A1C Shellby Matullo, A1C Lauren OConnor

1877.description:
U.S. Marines alongside partner nation military members shoot targets with M-16 and M-4 rifles on the range in Ilha do Governador, Brazil during UNITAS Amphibious 2015. Filmed on November 17, 2015. Unit - Golf Company, 2nd Battalion, 23rd Marine Regiment, Marine Forces Reserve

Film Credits: Cpl Bethany Barnoski

1878.description:
Combat Camera members have been on the front lines of all military events from WWII to any change of command ceremony. The footage these professional videographers bring to us is often stunning in the reality it shows. It gives us a inside look at our military in action. The lens does not lie, and it is brought to you through the eyes of professional U.S. Armed Forces camera men and women who put their lives on the line to bring you excellent footage.

Film Credits: SGT Luther Washington

1879.description:
Soldiers conduct a gunnery exercise on the Fort Riley U.S. Army installation in Kansas. Filmed on September 24, 2013. Unit - 1st Squadron, 4th Cavalry Regiment 4th Infantry Brigade Combat Team, 1st Infantry Division

Film Credits: SGT Luther Washington

1880.description:
U.S. aircraft takeoff and land at  Andersen Air Base, Guam during Exercise Valiant Shield 2014. Valiant Shield is a biennial exercise focusing on the joint training of Air Force, Navy, Army, and Marine Corps to counter Chinese claims over international waters also claimed by neighboring countries in the East and South China Sea. Filmed on September 14, 2014.

Film Credits: Sgt Lena Wakayama

1881.description:
A KC-135 Stratotanker refuels a B-1 Bomber during a combat air sortie over SW Asia. KC-135 unit -  340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron  

Film Credits: TSgt Justin Suddeth

1882.description:
The USS Ohio (SSGN-726) makes port at Kota Kinabalu, Malaysia on November 14, 2015. SSGN stands for - SS means submarine, G means guided missile, and N means nuclear-powered. The Ohio was originally commissioned in 1981 as a Fleet Ballistic Missile Submarine (SSBN) carrying 24 Trident missiles tipped with thermonuclear warheads, but was later converted to an SSGN carrying a maximum of 154 cruise missiles. 

Film Credits: PO1 Brandon Shelander

1883.description:
Cockpit video of an F-15 pilot during a memorial flyover for the funeral of Brigadier General Robinson Risner at the Pentagon. Filmed on January 23, 2014.   

Film Credits: SrA Emma Duff

1884.description:
An Air National Guard C-130H Hercules aircrew performs a heavy load airdrop near Mansfield Lahm Air National Guard Base, OH with GoPro camera mounted on the cargo. Filmed on October 19, 2015. Unit - 164th Airlift Squadron 

Film Credits: TSgt Joseph Harwood

1885.description:
U.S. Marines conduct fast rope training from a CH-53 E Super Stallion helicopter during Weapons and Tactics Instructor Course (WTI) 1-16 at Auxiliary Airfield 2 in Yuma, AZ on October 2, 2015. Unit - 2nd Battalion, 7th Marine Regiment, 1st Marine Division  

Film Credits: Sgt Daniel Kujanpaa

1886.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcon fighter jets from Hill Air Force Base in Utah fly in formation - cockpit video with pilot communications.  

Film Credits: Video released by Air Force Public Affairs Agency

1887.description:
A U-2 "Dragon Lady" spy plane prepares for flight - with takeoff, landing and chase car footage. Units - 380th Expeditionary Aircraft Maintenance Squadron - 99th Expeditionary Reconnaissance Squadron - 380th Air Expeditionary Wing

Film Credits: TSgt Matthew Pardini, Maj. Jefferson Heiland

1888.description:
Footage of various aircraft refueling inflight during Exercise Gunfighter Flag, a joint Advanced Combat Operations Training (ACOT) event held November 2-6, 2015. The ACOT included Airmen from Travis Air Force Base alongside Airmen from various other bases, the US Army and Navy, as well as the Singapore Air Force.  The training exercise touched on all combat situations. This video is footage of the refueling exercise near Mountain Home AFB, Idaho. 

Film Credits: SrA Scott Taylor

1889.description:
The longest flight in MV-22 history was conducted by U.S. Marines on November 14, 2015. The flight was from Miramar, CA to Rio de Janeiro, Brazil - 6165 miles. This movement was in support of UNITAS Amphibious Operations 2015. Units - Marine Aerial Refueler Transport Squadron 452 and Fixed Wing Transport Squadron 234, Marine Air Group 41, 4th Marine Aircraft Wing

Film Credits: Cpl Bethany Barnoski

1890.description:
Four clips (HD/60fps) of military aircraft aerial refueling - B-52 Stratofortress, C-17 Globemaster III, B-2 Spirit, and F-22 Raptor.

Film Credits: SrA Danny Rangel, TSgt Rachel Barton, George Kale

1891.description:
F/A-18 Super Hornets from Strike Fighter Squadron 213 (VFA-213) "Fighting Black Lions" launch and land aboard the aircraft carrier George H.W. Bush (CVN-77). Filmed March 2014.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video/Released

1892.description:
The Grumman C-2 Greyhound is a twin-engine, high-wing cargo aircraft, designed to carry supplies, mail, and passengers to and from aircraft carriers of the United States Navy - designated Carrier Onboard Delivery (COD). A C-2 Greyhound launches and lands aboard the aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77).

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video/Released

1893.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15C Eagles and F-15E Strike Eagles are now based at Incirlik Air Base in Turkey to patrol Turkish airspace. Filmed on November 13, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Daniel Asselta

1894.description:
Twelve U.S. Air Force F-15 jet fighters arrive at Incirlik Air Base in Turkey. Six F-15Cs will conduct combat air patrols in Turkish air space to help secure sovereign Turkish airspace and six F-15 Strike Eagles will join A-10s and other aircraft already conducting missions as part of Combined Joint Task Force - Operation Inherent Resolve. Filmed on November 13, 2015. The F-15s are all based at RAF Lakenheath, UK.

Film Credits: SrA Daniel Asselta

1895.description:
U.S. Marines with 3rd Marine Aircraft Wing conduct deck landing qualifications in AH-1Z Viper and CH-53 Super Stallion helicopters aboard the USS Pearl Harbor dock landing ship. Filmed on November 12, 2013. 

Film Credits: Sgt Megan Scullin

1896.description:
F-22 Raptors with the 325th Fighter Wing takeoff at Tyndall Air Force Base during Exercise Crown Royal on November 12, 2015. Crown Royal is designed to improve the ability to deploy combat power worldwide.

Film Credits: SSgt William Jackson

1897.description:
The Boeing KC-46A Pegasus is slated to begin replacing the aging KC-135 Stratotanker. The U.S. Air Force has ordered 179 KC-46As from Boeing, with 18 to be delivered by 2017. The Pegasus made its first flight on September 25, 2015 - meeting the latest deadline for the new air tanker.

Film Credits: David Fitzroy, SrA Jarrod Vickers

1898.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15E Eagle pilots and aircrews from the 48th Fighter Wing (48 FW) conduct flight operations in support of Operation Inherent Resolve at RAF Lakenheath in England. Filmed on November 12, 2015.

Film Credits: A1C Gabriela Calderon

1899.description:
U.S. Marines conduct demolition training at Range 108 - Camp Pendleton. The  Marines learned about the destructive capabilities of various explosives including dynamite, TNT, shape charges and C4. The charges are used by engineers to destroy heavily armored vehicles, defensive obstacles and bridges. Filmed on June 29, 2013. Unit - Bravo Company, 1st Combat Engineer Battalion, 1st Marine Division

Film Credits: Sgt Christopher J. Moore

1900.description:
Two Norwegian F-35 Lightning II fighter jets flew in from the Lockheed Martin production plant at Fort Worth, TX and the first Royal Norwegian Air Force (RNoAF) Student Pilot conducted his initial flight of the aircraft at Luke Air Force Base, AZ on November 10, 2015. Norway will have seven F-35s stationed at Luke AFB. In addition to the United States and Norway, Australia also has F-35s at Luke. Other countries that will participate in F-35 training at Luke include Turkey, Italy, the Netherlands, Japan, Korea and Israel.

Film Credits: SrA Jenna Bigham, TSgt Michael Jackson

1901.description:
The U.S. Navy's EA-6B Prowler entered operation in 1971 and after serving in every major aerial conflict since the Vietnam War was finally retired in June 2015. The four-seat electronic warfare aircraft was the Navy's main aerial platform for jamming enemy radar and communications for nearly 45 years. The Prowler will be replaced by the EA-18G Growler which is based on the F/A-18F Super Hornet airframe.

Film Credits: Damon Moritz, A1C Eric Mann, Lea Greene, SSgt Cody Griffith, William Lewis, SrA Rachel Maxwell
Image Credit: Lance Cheung

1902.description:
U.S. Marines with the 1st Marine Division work alongside members of the British Army's  29 Commando Regiment Royal Artillery during a live fire exercise at Twentynine Palms, CA on September 27, 2015. Units - Battery I, 3rd Battalion, 11th Marine Regiment, 1st Marine Division and 8 (Alma) Commando Battery,  29 Commando Regiment Royal Artillery

Film Credits: Cpl Hannah Carlson

1903.description:
U.S. Marines with the 3rd Assault Amphibian Battalion conduct combat marksmanship qualifications at the Yuma Proving Grounds, AZ in order to enhance combat readiness. The battalion's primary weapon system is the Amphibious Assault Vehicle or AAV. The AAV is a 29-ton armored vehicle that carries up to 21 combat-loaded Marines and is armed with the UGWS (UpGunned Weapons Station), which mounts a .50 cal (12.7 mm) M2HB machine gun and a Mk-19 40 mm grenade launcher. The AAV is the only armored vehicle in the U.S. inventory that is fully capable of operations both on land and in the ocean. Filmed on  November 6, 2015.

Film Credits: Cpl Conner Robbins

1904.description:
Members of the U.S. Army's 82nd Airborne Division jump from C-17 Globemaster III transport planes near Zaragoza, Spain during NATO Exercise Trident Juncture - Ultimate Reach 16. Filmed on November 4, 2015. Units - 82nd Airborne Division, 2nd Brigade Combat Team and 18th Air Force, Air Mobility Command, USAF  

Film Credits: A1C Eric Mann, SSG Dillon Heyliger

1905.description:
Compilation video showing Military Footage from the Gung Ho Vids Channel on YouTube. All clips are taken from videos uploaded on Gung Ho Vids channel.

Film Credits: Footage Courtesy Of The United States Department Of Defense
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids
Creative Consultations: https://www.youtube.com/user/mejszjek

1906.description:
U.S. Marines join forces with Spanish and Portuguese Marines during a trilateral exercise to strenthen NATO interoperability on November 3, 2015 at Pinheiro da Cruz, Portugal.

Film Credits: SSgt Vitaliy Rusavskiy

1907.description:
U.S. Marines enter the Infantry Immersion Trainer (IIT) at Camp Pendleton. The IIT provides realistic hands-on training in an immersive, scenario-based environment. It is designed to improve tactical skills and decision making in real-world combat situations. Of course all Marines killed in the IIT are designated KIA for the purposes of training... they are not really dead. Filmed on November 5, 2015.

Film Credits: Sgt Kevin Maynard

1908.description:
The first two Italian Air Force pilots complete their initial flights in F-35 Lightning II fighter jets at Luke Air Force Base in Arizona. One of the jets flown was an Australian F-35, to emphasize the partner nation relationship of the F-35 program. Filmed on November 5, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Jenna Bigham, TSgt Michael Jackson

1909.description:
Music video shows the U.S. Military in action. Subscribe to Gung Ho Vids.

Film Credits: Footage Courtesy Of The United States Department Of Defense.
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

1910.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15C Eagle fighter jets from the 493rd Fighter Squadron takeoff from RAF Lakenheath to patrol the Turkish air border. Earlier in October a Russian jet violated Turkish air space which alarmed NATO partners. Filmed on November 6, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Amanda Sampson

1911.description:
Four USAF F-22 Raptors conduct an aerial refueling mission over the United Kingdom before flying in formation behind the KC-135 air tanker. Filmed on September 12, 2015. 

Film Credits: SSgt Nathan Tucker

1912.description:
A-10 Thunderbolt IIs from the 25th Fighter Squadron taxi during night operations at Osan Air Base, South Korea. Plus an F-16 Fighting Falcon takeoff at night. Maintenance crews from the 25th Aircraft Maintenance Unit recover and service aircraft during readiness exercise Vigilant Ace 16. F-16 filmed on October 26, 2015 and A-10s filmed on November 2, 2015.

Film Credits: SSgt D.J. Ayres

1913.description:
Elephant Walk is a USAF term for taxiing of military aircraft right before takeoff, when they are in close formation. The term dates back to World War II when large fleets of allied bombers would conduct attacks in missions containing up to 1,000 aircraft. KC-135 Stratotankers perform an Elephant Walk prior to takeoff at McConnell Air Force Base, KS. Filmed on January 1, 2014.

Film Credits: TSgt Alexander Farver

1914.description:
Weapons load crew members from the 25th Aircraft Maintenance Unit load munitions onto A-10 Thunderbolt II attack planes on November 1, 2015 during Exercise Vigilant Ace 16 at Osan Air Base, South Korea.

Film Credits: SrA Kelly Greenwell

1915.description:
Airmen prepare F-15C Eagle jet fighters on the flight line prior to aircraft launching during Exercise Southern Strike 16 at New Orleans Naval Air Station. These highly trained and technologically advanced maintenance crew members keep USAF aircraft in the air everyday 24/7/365 round the clock. Filmed on October 28, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Nicholas Priest

1916.description:
U.S. Marines with Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron (VMM-163) fly over Lake Tahoe during Mountain Training Exercise MTNEX 6-15 out of Mountain West Aviation, Lake Tahoe Airport, California on October 29, 2015.

Film Credits: Cpl Rachael Zilliox

1917.description:
Footage of Exercise Southern Strike 16 with F-22 Raptors, F-15 Eagles, and T-38 Talon Training jets. Plus interviews with some of the participating pilots. Exercise Southern Strike is an annual event conducted by the Louisiana Air National Guard involving various joint aircraft platforms from regional Bases. Filmed October 30, 2015.

Film Credits: TSgt Burt Traynor

1918.description:
USAF T-38 Talon jets with the 2nd Fighter Training Squadron takeoff and land at New Orleans Naval Air Station. Cockpit video of Exercise Southern Strike-16 on October 27, 2015.

Film Credits: TSgt Burt Traynor

1919.description:
Soldiers from the 4th Infantry Brigade Airborne jump over Deadhorse, Alaska drop zone during a training exercise north of the Arctic Circle.   

Film Credits: SGT Eric-James Estrada

1920.description:
Footage of the 4th Infantry Brigade Combat Team, U.S. Airborne, during Operation Spartan Fusion out of Joint Base Elmendorf–Richardson. Army paratroopers rig and jump out of a C-17 Globemaster troop carrier jet. Filmed on October 21, 2015.

Film Credits: SSG Daniel Love

1921.description:
The 55th Rescue Squadron (55 RQS) "Night Hawks" is a unit of the U.S.  Air Force flying HH-60G Pavehawk helicopters. This unit is trained to deploy rapidly for combat search and rescue missions all over the world. Their primary mission is to rescue any military personnel in hostile conditions... and their motto is, "These Things We Do That Others May Live". Unit home is Davis-Monthan AFB.

Film Credits: A1C Taylor Harrison

1922.description:
First flight of the RQ-7B Shadow Version 2 unmanned aerial system (UAS), as it takes off from Yakima Training Center, WA. The new UAS will someday allow Apache Attack Helicopter Pilots to control the unmanned aircraft while inflight and see what the Shadow v2 sees. The U.S. Army's 4th Attack Reconnaissance Squadron, 6th Cavalry is testing the latest model of the intelligence-gathering UAS. 

Film Credits: SSG Vanessa Atchley
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

1923.description:
U.S. Marines with the 4th Light Armored Reconnaissance Battalion (4th LAR) conduct a move and shoot exercise on the range at Base Alvarez de Sotomayor in Spain on October 27, 2015. 

Film Credits: Sgt Sara Graham, Sgt Tatum Vayavananda

1924.description:
U.S. Marines with Marine Corps Europe (MARFOREUR) practice long-range shooting with the M110 Semi-Automatic Sniper System (M110 SASS) during NATO Exercise Trident Juncture 15 at Almería, Spain. Filmed on October 27, 2015.

Film Credits: SGT Ian Morales

1925.description:
U.S. Marines launch a night attack aboard UH-1Y Super Huey and AH-1Z Cobra helicopter gunships during Final Exercise 2 (FINEX 2) at Weapons and Tactics Instructor course (WTI) 1-16 on the Chocolate Mountains Aerial Gunnery Range in California. Filmed on October 22, 2015.

Film Credits: Lance Cpl. Jeremy L. Laboy

1926.description:
Watch a USAF E-3 Sentry (AWACS) takeoff in darkness with cockpit view, daylight aerial refueling with KC-135 and cockpit view, plus command control officers performing console duties. Filmed on October 20, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Greg Cern

1927.description:
U.S. and Hungarian Soldiers conduct a live-fire exercise to send a message to Russia... Brave Warrior is a NATO exercise. The events in Ukraine will not be duplicated. Filmed on October 21, 2015. 

Film Credits: SGT Kyle Burns

1928.description:
U.S. and Canadian Forces conduct bi-lateral training out of Canadian Forces Base Goose Bay. Exercise Vigilant Shield 16 is an annual event designed to increase effective NORAD interoperability between the U.S. and Canada to bolster air space defense of the North America continent. Filmed October 2015.

Film Credits: SSgt Laura Beckley, SSgt George Solis, MSgt David Loeffler, SrA Greg Cerny 
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

1929.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15 fighter jets from the 144th Fighter Wing takeoff from 5 Wing Goose Bay military installation in Canada during Exercise Vigilant Shield 16. Vigilant Shield is an annual joint exercise conducted between the U.S. and Canadian Forces to strengthen NORAD. Filmed on October 22, 2015.

Film Credits: SSgt George Solis

1930.description:
U.S. Air Force aircrews perform postflight checks and maintenance on F-15 Eagle fighter jets after they return from flying tactical engagement scenarios during Exercise Vigilant Shield 16 at 5 Wing Goose Bay in Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada. Filmed on October 21, 2015. Unit - 144th Fighter Wing out of Fresno, California

Film Credits: SSgt Laura Beckley

1931.description:
Top Aces (Discovery Air Defence) Alpha Jets takeoff from 5 Wing Goose Bay in Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada during Exercise Vigilant Shield 16 on October 10, 2015. Discovery Air Defence is a military contractor based out of Montreal, Quebec that provides airborne training services to the U.S. and Canadian Armed Forces.

Film Credits: SSgt Laura Beckley

1932.description:
A C-5 Galaxy, the USAF's largest plane, does a touch and go landing at Westover Air Reserve Base in Massachusetts on October 16, 2015.

Film Credits: MSgt W.C. Pope

1933.description:
U.S. Marines fresh out of boot camp go to their second stage of training, Marine Corps School of Infantry. The School of Infantry's training mission is to make sure, "Every Marine is, first and foremost, a Rifleman". This video shows Marines with Golf Company, Marine Combat Training Battalion, School of Infantry West, being trained in basic rifle marksmanship at Camp Pendleton. Filmed on October 22, 2015.

Film Credits: CPL Shaltiel Dominguez

1934.description:
U.S. Marines with 2nd Reconnaissance Battalion conduct fast rope training from a CH-53E helicopter at Camp Lejeune, NC on October 20, 2015. Super Stallion unit - Marine Heavy Helicopter Squadron 366 (HMH-366)

Film Credits: LCpl Koby Saunders

1935.description:
A Royal Norwegian Air Force F-35 student pilot gets fitted for his Gen III Helmet Mounted Display System during training  at Luke AFB. The pilot is one of the first Norwegian F-35 pilots in training at Luke. Filmed on October 16, 2015.

Film Credits: A1C Joshua Altice, TSgt Michael Jackson

1936.description:
Footage of KC-135 air tankers executing aerial refueling missions with F-15 Eagles during Exercise Vigilant Shield 16 - plus pilot and boom operator communications/audio. Filmed on October 19, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Greg Cerny

1937.description:
U.S. Paratroopers with the 173rd Airborne Brigade train with various weapons during Exercise Rock Proof V at Postonja, Slovenia. Weapons systems included... M240 machine gun, M320 grenade launcher, M2 machine gun, M4 carbine, and the M777A2 howitzer. Filmed on October 15-16, 2015.

Film Credits: Davide Dalla Massara, Paolo Bovo

1938.description:
U.S. Airmen from the 144th Fighter Wing, based out of Fresno, California prepare for a morning launch of F-15 Eagles during Exercise Vigilant Shield 16 at 5 Wing Goose Bay, Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada. Filmed on October 20, 2015.

Film Credits: MSgt David Loeffler, SSgt George Solis

1939.description:
U.S. Air Force A-10 Thunderbolt II aircraft land at Incirlik Air Base in Turkey for close air support duty during Operation Inherent Resolve. Filmed on October 16, 2015. 

Film Credits: SrA Daniel Asselta, SrA Megan Mallory

1940.description:
Ohio National Guard members flying a UH-60 Black Hawk helicopter conduct water rescue training near Columbus, OH. 

Film Credits: SSG George Davis

1941.description:
I compiled footage of the NASA Project Morpheus vertical takeoff and vertical landing (VTVL) test vehicle and created this video of day and night test flights. All the footage is from Public Domain clips available for download here - https://morpheuslander.jsc.nasa.gov/videos/

Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

1942.description:
The United States launched a Top Secret spy satellite on August 28, 2013. A United Launch Alliance (ULA) Delta 4 Heavy rocket carried a payload for the National Reconnaissance Office (NRO) and lifted off from Space Launch Complex-6 at Vandenberg Air Force Base. The mission was designated USA-245.

Film Credits: Michael Stonecypher

1943.description:
MICLIC explosions from training exercises and footage from the  War in Afghanistan. The M58 Mine Clearing Line Charge (MICLIC) is a rocket propelled explosive line charge. It is used to clear a path through minefields and other obstacles. The clearing line contains 1750 lbs of C4 explosive and is approximately 350 feet long.

Film Credits: SGT Aaron Ricca, SGT Aaron Ricca, Sgt Bryan Nygaard, LCpl Justin Davis
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

1944.description:
U.S. Soldiers from the 173rd Airborne Brigade train alongside members of the Lithuanian Land Forces during Operation Eagle Shock in Pabrade, Lithuania. Filmed on October 14, 2015. 

Film Credits: SFC Daniel Shapiro

1945.description:
U.S. Air Force KC-135 Stratotanker conducts aerial refueling with a B-1 Lancer from the 37th Bomb Squadron and A-10 Thunderbolts from the 163rd Expeditionary Fighter Squadron over Southwest Asia on October 13, 2015. 

Film Credits: SSgt John Raven

1946.description:
Compilation video of the huge USAF C-17 Globemaster III in action. Video includes footage of takeoffs and landings (with cockpit view), loading and unloading an M1 Abrams tank, cargo drop, paratrooper jump, and firing flares. 

Film Credits: William Lewis, TSgt Justin Suddeth, TSgt Anthony Kuhn, SrA Aaron Hauser, SSgt Erin Mills, SrA Brandi Hansen, Douglas Lay
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

1947.description:
U.S. Marine Corps CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters sling load M-777 Howitzers to a firebase and Marines set up the artillery pieces for live-fire target practice. USMC CH-53E Super Stallions assigned to Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1) executed the externally lift of M777 howitzers in support of Assault Support Tactics 1, and Marines with C Battery, 1st Battalion, 11th Marine Regiment, 1st Marine Division set up and fired the 155mm howitzers during Weapons and Tactics Instructor Course (WTI) 1-16 at Firebase Burt, Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range in California. Filmed on October 12, 2015.

Film Credits: Sgt. Juanenrique Owings, Sgt Daniel Kujanpaa

1948.description:
An F-35C Lightning II Carrier Variant Joint Strike Fighter is launched at night from the deck of the aircraft carrier USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN-69) during sea-trial testing of the jet. Filmed on October 8, 2015. 

Film Credits: Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Alexander Delgado

1949.description:
A U.S. Marine Corps KC-130J Super Hercules air tanker executes an aerial refueling mission with two AV-8B Harriers (Designated VA-2 Matador II by the Spanish Navy). The KC-130J took off from Morón Air Base in Spain and the Harriers departed Naval Station Rota, Spain. Filmed on May 15, 2015. (Marine Unit) - Special-Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force Crisis Response-Africa (Spanish Unit) - 9th Aircraft Squadron 

Film Credits: Sgt Paul Peterson

1950.description:
The U.S. Navy's Special Warfare Combatant-Craft Crewmen (SWCC, pronounced "Swick") is a Special Operations Force that operates and maintains an inventory of small craft used to support special operations missions, mostly missions with Navy SEALs. This is a U.S. Navy recruiting video, cleared for public use.

This video is Public Domain. If you would like to download a copy of this video go here: https://www.dvidshub.net/video/410047/swcc-hd#.VhxKdCFViko

1951.description:
U.S. Marines and British Royal Marine Commandos train together in various close quarter battle techniques during Exercise Tartan Eagle in Newcastle Upon Tyne, England. Filmed from September 21-25, 2015.  

Film Credits: MSgt Chad McMeen

1952.description:
Flight Deck Control room aboard the aircraft carrier USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN-69) during sea-trial testing of F-35C Joint Strike Fighters. Flight Deck Control is where the Aircraft Handling Officer (ACHO - also called the handler or mangler) oversees the movement and positioning of every aircraft on the carrier flight deck. The ACHO uses a tracking tool nicknamed "The Ouija Board" - a scale model replica of the carrier’s flight deck. Miniature planes are moved around on the Ouija Board to reflect the location and status of the aircraft on the carrier's flight deck. When an aircraft moves on deck or it's status changes, it also moves on The Ouija Board and it's status is updated. Filmed on October 2, 2015.   

Film Credits: PO3 Michael Gendron, MC3 Theodore Quintana

1953.description:
U.S. Marines fire 60mm mortars, .50 caliber machine guns, and call in AH-1Z Viper attack helicopters to culminate an offensive close air support exercise at night. The integrated live-fire attack was conducted on the Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range in California on October 6, 2015. Units - Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1) - Weapons Company, 2nd Battalion, 7th Marine Regiment, 1st Marine Division

Film Credits: Sgt Daniel Kujanpaa

1954.description:
U.S. Marine Corps AH-1Z Viper attack helicopters fire Hydra 70 Rockets and M197 20mm Cannons at ground targets during a close air support exercise (CASEX) at Mt. Barrow, Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range in California. Filmed on October 6-8, 2015.

Film Credits: Sgt Daniel Kujanpaa, Sgt Juanenrique Owings

1955.description:
U.S. Marine Corps AV-8B Harriers refuel and rearm at a Forward Arming and Refueling Point (FARP) at Yuma Proving Grounds, AZ as part of ongoing Weapons and Tactics Instructor training (WTI.1-16). The Harriers were refueled with engines running, also known as Hot Pit Refueling. Filmed on October 6, 2015.

Film Credits: Cpl Waiyan Tin

1956.description:
U.S. Army conducts a Combined Arms Live Fire Exercise (CALFEX) with M1A2 Main Battle Tanks and Bradley Fighting Vehicles at Fort Bliss, TX. Soldiers with the 325th Airborne Infantry Regiment and the 1st Armored Division participated in the CALFEX on October 2, 2015.

Film Credits: SSG Dillon Heyliger

1957.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a beach raid exercise using amphibious assault vehicles (AAV) in the Philippines during Amphibious Landing Exercise 2015 (PHIBLEX 15). Filmed on October 5, 2015. Unit - Company G, 2nd Battalion, 3rd Marines Regiment

Film Credits: Sgt Harold Johnson

1958.description:
U.S. Army M109A6 Paladin Self-Propelled Howitzers fire rounds on the range at Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany during Exercise Combined Resolve V. Filmed on October 7, 2015. Unit - 1st Battalion, 41st Field Artillery Regiment, 1st Brigade Combat Team, 3rd Infantry Division

Film Credits: Markus Rauchenberger

1959.description:
U.S. Marine Corps UH-1Y Venom gunships fire rockets and machine guns on the simulated village of Yodaville during a helicopter close air support (CAS) training exercise near Yuma, AZ. The Marines conducted the live-fire exercise as part of Weapons and Tactics Instructor (WTI) Course 1-16, hosted by Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1). MAWTS-1 is stationed at Marine Corps Air Station Yuma. Filmed on October 2, 2015.

Film Credits: Cpl Waiyan Tin

1960.description:
An F-35C Lightning II Carrier Variant Joint Strike Fighter is launched from the aircraft carrier USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN-69) as part of sea-trial testing - video filmed from the Integrated Catapult Control Station (ICCS), nicknamed "The Bubble."  Filmed on October 4, 2015.

Film Credits: MC3 Theodore Quintana, U.S. Navy Video/Released

1961.description:
F-35C Lightning II Carrier Variant Joint Strike Fighters assigned to Air Test and Evaluation Squadron (VX) 23 "Salty Dogs" launch and land aboard the aircraft carrier USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN-69) as part of sea-trial testing.  Filmed October 3-4, 2015.

Film Credits: MC3 Theodore Quintana, MC3 Lisa Reese, U.S. Navy Video/Released

1962.description:
U.S. Marines with 1st Force Reconnaissance Company, 1st Marine Expeditionary Force conduct a helocast out of a UH-1Y Venom helicopter over Lake Ferguson in Yuma, Arizona on Oct. 3, 2015. 

Film Credits: Sgt Daniel Kujanpaa

1963.description:
U.S. Marine UH-1Y Huey helicopter gunship crews conduct an urban close air support exercise, shooting targets in a simulated city during day and night operations at Yodaville near Yuma, AZ. These operations are part of a larger training exercise called Weapons and Tactics Instructor (WTI) Course, which train Marine Corps instructor personnel in war tactics to be handed down to the fleet after they graduate. Day footage filmed on October 2, 2015... night footage filmed on April 4, 2015.

Film Credits: Lance Cpl. Jeremy L. Laboy, Sgt Daniel Kujanpaa

1964.description:
A French Air Force Dassault Rafale Aircraft goes through pre-flight checks prior to takeoff at Biggs Army Airfield/Fort Bliss, TX during Exercise Bold Quest 15-2 on October 1, 2015. The goal of Bold Quest is to improve compatibility of communication between allied air forces during operational situations.

Film Credits: SSgt Warren Spearman

1965.description:
U.S. Marines at Weapons and Tactics Instructor (WTI) Course 1-16, conduct an aerial gunnery exercise in UH-1Y Venom helicopters near Yuma, Arizona on September 30, 2015. WTI is a seven week course held by Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1). MAWTS-1 provides standardized tactical training and certification of unit instructors to support Marine aviation training and readiness and assists in developing and using aviation weapons and tactics.

Film Credits: Cpl Waiyan Tin

1966.description:
A short clip of various civilian and military groups performing at the 2015 Miramar Air Show aboard Marine Corps Air Station (MCAS) Miramar, San Diego, Calififornia on October 2, 2015.

Film Credits: Cpl Alexander Pool

1967.description:
(Clip 1) --- F-15s at Seymour Johnson Air Force Base in North Carolina move out in advance of Hurricane Joaquin. Filmed on October 1, 2015. (Clip 2) --- F-15E Strike Eagles assigned to the 366th Fighter Wing arrive at Gowen Field in Boise, Idaho. Filmed on August 2, 2015.

Film Credits: A1C Nathaniel Stout, TSgt John Winn

1968.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a long range raid live-fire exercise on September 12, 2015 in Southwest Asia - undisclosed location - CENTCOM AOR. Unit - Special Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task force – Crisis Response – Central Command, 15th Marine Expeditionary Unit, 5th Marine Expeditionary Brigade

Film Credits: Cpl Jacob Smith

1969.description:
U.S. Army Paratroopers from the 2nd Brigade Combat Team, 82nd Airborne Division jump over White Sands Missile Range in New Mexico during Network Integration Evaluation 16.1 (NIE 16.1). NIE 16.1 runs from September - October 2015, and is designed to test various aspects of the Army’s battlefield network with focus on experimentation, testing manned and unmanned teaming, as well as overall force readiness. Filmed on September 27, 2015.

Film Credits: SSG Dillon Heyliger, John Hamilton

1970.description:
U.S. F-22 Raptors deploy from Hawaii headed to the CENTCOM Area of Responsibility, which includes Syria, Iraq, Afghanistan, and all of the Middle East. Filmed On September 30, 2015. Unit - U.S. Air Force, 199th Fighter Squadron, 19th Fighter Squadron, 154th Wing, 15th Wing

Film Credits: SrA Orlando Corpuz

1971.description:
U.S. Marines from Fifth Battalion Eleventh Marines fire the M31 Guided Multiple Launch Rocket System (GMLRS) at Emerson Lake, Marine Air Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms in California on September 20, 2015.

Film Credits: Cpl Hannah Carlson

1972.description:
Security force Marines with Special Purpose Marine Air Ground Task Force - Crisis Response - Central Command, conduct a Combat Marksmanship Range - table 5 shoot on September 29, 2015 at an undisclosed location within the Central Command Area of Operations. 

Film Credits: Cpl John Baker

1973.description:
Pre-flight operations on F/A-18 Super Hornets during exercise Bold Quest 15-2 at Holloman Air Force Base in New Mexico. Filmed on September 29, 2015,  

Film Credits: SrA BreeAnn Sachs

1974.description:
Scenes from U.S. Army and Japan Self-Defense Forces troops training together during Operation Rising Thunder 2015 at the Yakima Training Center, WA. Filmed in September 2015. 

Film Credits: SSG Elwyn Lovelace

1975.description:
Six U.S. Air Force F-15C Eagles from the 123rd Expeditionary Fighter Squadron depart Campia Turzii, Romania marking the end of their Theater Security Package (TSP) deployment. Filmed on September 25, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Emma Duff

1976.description:
U.S. Air Force A-10 Thunderbolt II aircraft are filmed on the flight line as air crews load missiles at Amari Air Base in Estonia. The A-10s are part of a Theater Security Package (TSP) which the United States is rotating throughout allied countries to strengthen the NATO commitment. Filmed on September 24, 2015. Unit - 74th Expeditionary Fighter Squadron

Film Credits: TSgt Fernando X. Burgos-Ortiz

1977.description:
American and Danish tank crews work side by side during exercise Saber Strike 2015 in Drawsko Pomorskie, Poland. Filmed June 11, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Steven Adkins

1978.description:
U.S. Marines conduct an insertion and extraction training exercise from a UH-1Y Huey helicopter at Camp Lejeune in North Carolina on September 23, 2015. Units - Marine Raider Regiment and Marine Light Attack Helicopter Squadron 167 at Stone Bay 

Film Credits: Sgt Kathryn Bynum

1979.description:
Footage of the Modern Army Combatives Program (MACP) Tournament at Joint Base Lewis-McChord, WA. Round One was Level 1 MACP. Round Two through the Finals was Level 2 MACP, and the Finals featured a tactical enclosure (cage) with open strikes. The Modern Army Combatives Program was started by the U.S. Army in 1995 at Fort Benning, GA. The mission of MACP is to train Soldiers in close quarters Combatives in order to prepare them to close with and defeat the enemy in hand to hand combat. Filmed on September 11, 2015. 

Film Credits: SGT Thomas Christensen

1980.description:
Twelve A-10C Thunderbolt II close air support aircraft from the 74th Fighter Squadron "Flying Tigers" land at Amari Air Base, Estonia as part of ongoing theater security packages being rotated through allied countries in Europe. The 74th Fighter Squadron is home-based at Moody Air Force Base, Georgia. Filmed on September 20, 2015. 

Film Credits: TSgt Fernando X. Burgos-Ortiz

1981.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers shoot the M249 Light Machine Gun on a marksmanship range as part of the US Army Forces Command weapons marksmanship competition at Fort Bragg, NC. Filmed on September 21, 2015. 

Film Credits: SSG David Meyer

1982.description:
U.S. Marines insert via the fast rope insertion/extraction system (FRIES) from an MV-22 Osprey tiltrotar aircraft. Fast roping allows Marines to insert ground forces quickly from the air without the need for a controlled landing zone. Filmed on September 16, 2015. Unit - India Company, 3rd Battalion, 7th Marine Regiment, Special Purpose Marine Air Ground Task Force—Crisis Response—Central Command 

Film Credits: Cpl Jacob Smith

1983.description:
A U.S. Air Force EC-130H Compass Call conducts aerial refueling with a KC-135R Stratotanker over Utah. The EC-130H Compass Call is a USAF airborne tactical weapon system using a uniquely modified version of the C-130 Hercules airframe designed to disrupt enemy command and control communications.

Film Credits: SSgt Robert Harnden

1984.description:
The U.S. Navy destroyer USS Gridley (DDG-101) conducts a test firing of a Tomahawk Cruise Missile... multiple views with split screen and slow motion. Filmed September 1, 2015. 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video/Released

1985.description:
U.S. Soldiers train with units of the Slovak Republic Armed Forces at Kuchnya Training Area in Slovak Republic during Operation Slovak Shield. Slovak Shield is part of Exercise Dragoon Ride that increases interoperability and freedom of movement between NATO allies. Filmed on September 16, 2015. Unit - 4th Squadron, 2D Cavalry Regiment

Film Credits: Christoph Koppers

1986.description:
Two U.S. Air Force MC-12W intelligence, surveillance and reconnaissance (ISR) aircraft take off and land at Beale AFB, marking the final flight of the MC-12 Liberty for the USAF. Filmed on September 16, 2015.  
    
Film Credits: TSgt Anthony Plyler

1987.description:
Aircraft launch and land aboard the aircraft carrier USS John C. Stennis (CVN-74) as deck crew members perform their duties. The Stennis is the seventh Nimitz-class nuclear-powered supercarrier in the United States Navy.  
    
Film Credits: MC2 Lauren Howes

1988.description:
Soldiers from the U.S. and Slovak Republic conduct training on each other's weapons systems during Exercise Dragoon Crossing followed by a combined arms live fire range with U.S Strykers and the Slovakian BMPs. Filmed on September 16, 2015. Unit - 4th Squadron, 2D Cavalry Regiment, U.S. Army

Film Credits: SGT Alan Brutus

1989.description:
A U.S. Marine Corps MV-22B Osprey conducts deck landing qualifications aboard the Spanish amphibious assault ship Juan Carlos I (L61) off the coast of Spain on September 9, 2015. Marines with Special-Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force Crisis Response-Africa (SPMAGTF-AF) conducted the landing qualifications to test landing and takoffs from different parts of the ship. 
    
Film Credits: SSgt Vitaliy Rusavskiy

1990.description:
Footage of various aspects of Canada's contribution to the Combined Joint Task Force (CJTF) - Operation Inherent Resolve.  
    
Film Credits: SSG Frank Brown

1991.description:
Four U.S. Air Force F-22 Raptors takeoff from Spangdahelm Air Base, Germany headed for Tyndall Air Force Base, Florida. This marks the end of the first European training deployment of the F-22. Filmed on September 11, 2015.  
    
Film Credits: SSgt Robbie Arp

1992.description:
Exercise Swift Response... U.S. Army Paratroopers with the 82nd Airbororne Division make a jump out of a C-130J Super Hercules plane. Filmed August 26, 2015.    
    
Film Credits: SSgt Nicholas Filip

1993.description:
U.S. Army and Japanese Ground Defense Force (JGDF) Snipers sharpen their skills on the range, shooting at targets more than 800 meters away during Exercise Rising Thunder 2015 at Yakima Training Center in Yakima, WA. Filmed on September 10, 2015. Units - U.S. Army 4th Battalion, 23rd Infantry - JGDF 33rd Infantry Regiment, 10th Division 

Film Credits: SGT Vanessa Atchley

1994.description:
U.S. Air Force Nuclear Weapons Specialists from the 2nd Munitions Squadron nuclear build team at Barkdale Air Force Base prepare a Common Strategic Rotary Launcher (CSRL) for loading on a B-52 bomber. The CSRL is loaded internally on a B-52 and is capable of deploying 8 nuclear tipped cruise missiles. Filmed August 26, 2015.
   
Film Credits: A1C Jayson Burns

1995.description:
The old but still capable B-52 Stratofortress in action... takeoff, landing with chute, takeoff/cockpit view, dropping bombs, and aerial refueling. Barksdale Air Force Base in Louisiana is home to the B-52 long-range bomber and the 2d Bomb Wing of the U.S. Air Force.     
    
Film Credits: A1C Jayson Burns, A1C Shellby Matullo, A1C Lauren OConnor, SSgt Tyler Prince, A1C Gabriel Stuart

1996.description:
A USAF C-130J Super Hercules aircrew from the 772 Expeditionary Airlift Squadron conducts an airlift mission in Afghanistan, delivering needed supplies to a remote area by parachute drop.  
    
Film Credits: SSgt Nick Brooks

1997.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a live-fire close air support exercise with AH-1 Cobra helicopters firing missiles and machine guns at targets on the Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range in California. 
    
Film Credits: LCpl Jacob Krummel, Aaron Shortt

1998.description:
Fighter Pilots in training fly T-38 Talon jets out of Sheppard Air Force Base in Texas - cockpit camera view. The T-38 Talon is a twin-engine, high-altitude, supersonic jet trainer. The T-38C incorporates a "glass cockpit" with integrated avionics displays, head-up display and an electronic "no drop bomb" scoring system. The instructor and student sit in tandem on rocket-powered ejection seats in a pressurized, air-conditioned cockpit. Shepard AFB is home to the 80th Flying Training Wing.
    
Film Credits: Chip Denton

1999.description:

Elements of the 15th MEU are ashore in Kuwait for sustainment training to maintain skills developed during their pre-deployment training period. This marks the first time F-22 fighter aircraft have been deployed to Europe and is intended to bolster the security of U.S. NATO Allies and partners nations in the European theater. 2061.description:
Footage of multiple test firing of CIWS aboard various U.S. Navy ships. The Phalanx CIWS (pronounced sea-whiz) is primarily a close-in weapon system for defense against anti-ship missiles. It consists of a radar-guided 20 mm Gatling gun mounted on a swiveling base and is used by the U.S. Navy on every class of surface combat ship. The CIWS is designed to be the last line of defense against anti-ship missiles, with an effective range Of 1-5 nautical miles and 4,500 rounds per minute rate-of-fire.

The CIWS has two antennas that work together to engage targets. The first antenna is for searching. The search antenna provides bearing, range, velocity, heading, and altitude information to the computer. This information is analyzed to determine whether the object should be engaged. Once the computer identifies a target, the CIWS pivots to face the target and then hands the target over to the tracking antenna. The tracking antenna observes the target until the computer determines that the probability of a successful hit is maximized and then the system will either fire automatically or will recommend fire to the operator. While firing, the system tracks outgoing rounds and "walks" them onto the target.

Film Credits: PO1 Henry Dunphy, PO3 Samuel Souvannason, PO3 David Flewellyn, PO3 Patrick Dionne, PO3 David Flewellyn

Film Credits: SSgt Cody Griffith

2090.description:
U.S. Marines from Marine Fighter Attack Squadron 232 "Red Devils" prepare F/A-18 Hornets for airstrikes over South West Asia - night and day footage. Filmed on July 15-16, 2015.

Film Credits: Cpl Cansin Hardyegritag

2091.description:
Footage of U.S. Navy LCAC (Landing Craft Air Cushion) leaving ship, beach landing, and returning to ship with pilot point-of-view.

Film Credits: Sgt Juanenrique Owings, PO2 Eric Crosby, PO2 Eric Crosby

2092.description:
After a seven month deployment, the USS New York (LPD-21) and her crew makes homecoming port at Naval Station Mayport in Jacksonville, Florida on July 19, 2015.

Film Credits: PO1 John Smolinski

2093.description:
U.S. Marines Launch the High Mobility Rocket System (HIMARS) at Bradshaw Field Training Area in Australia during exercise Talisman Sabre 2015 on July 12, 2015.

Film Credits: TSgt James Stewart, SSgt Mike Lahrman

2094.description:
The aircraft carrier USS George Washington (CVN-73) conducts flight operations in the South China Sea on May 19, 2015. F/A-18 Super Hornet, E-2C Hawkeye, and C-2 Greyhound aircraft from Carrier Air Wing 5 (CVW-5) are shown taking-off and landing.

Film Credits: MC3 Jon Price

2095.description:
A U.S. KC-10 Extender air tanker refuels F/A-18 Super Hornet strike fighters over Australia during exercise Talisman Sabre 2015. Filmed on July 15, 2015.    

Film Credits: TSgt James Stewart

2096.description:
Multiple F-35 Lightning II aircraft takeoff and land at Eglin Air Force Base in Florida. Plus preflight prep with air crews and taxis to and from runway.   

Film Credits: SSgt Tarelle Walker

2097.description:
Royal Air Force F-35 pilots from the United Kingdom work with the U.S. Marine Corps during STOVL (short takeoff vertical landing) flight operations at Eglin Air Force Base in Florida. Filmed on July 14, 2015.   

Film Credits: Senior Airman Stephen Ellis, SSgt Tarelle Walker

2098.description:
USAF A-10 Thunderbolts on the flight line, taxis, and takeoff from Lask Air Base in Poland on July 9-10, 2015.   

Film Credits: A1C Sieana Mackiewicz

2099.description:
The CH-53 Super Stallion is the biggest helicopter in the U.S. Military. Footage of Marine Corps Super Stallion helos during exercises Talisman Sabre 2015, Talon Reach 5, and the last flight of the "Ugly Angels" (HMH-362). Courtesy of the United States Marine Corps.   

Film Credits: LCpl Mandaline Hatch, Sgt Daniel Kujanpaa, Sgt James Mercure

2100.description:
U.S. Marines and Australian Soldiers conduct a tactical aerial insertion with MV-22 Ospreys during exercise Talisman Sabre 2015 at Fog Bay, Australia on July 11, 2015.  

Film Credits: TSgt James Stewart

2101.description:
U.S. Marines with the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit (31st MEU) conduct an amphibious landing on Dundee Beach in Australia during exercise Talisman Sabre on July 8, 2015. Quadcopter footage included.  

Film Credits: Cpl Rebecca Whitworth, CWO3 Clint Runyon, Sgt Harold Johnson

2102.description:
USARAK Soldiers rig and jump into Shoalwater Bay Training Area, Australia during exercise Talisman Sabre 2015. Filmed on July 8, 2015. Unit - The 4th Brigade Combat Team (Airborne), 25th Infantry Division is an airborne infantry brigade combat team of the United States Army, home-stationed at Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson. It is the only airborne brigade combat team in the Pacific Theater.  

Film Credits: SrA Carly Kavish

2103.description:
U.S. F-15 Strike Eagle jet fighters from Mountain Home Air Force Base (428th Buccaneers) arrive at Davis-Monthan AFB to train on Arizona's military training ranges. Filmed on July 7, 2015. 

Film Credits: SrA Austin Willhoit

2104.description:
U.S. Navy aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) launches strike aircraft in the Persian Gulf on July 7, 2015. The ship is deployed to the U.S. 5th Fleet area of operations conducting maritime security operations. 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video/Released

2105.description:
The USS Ohio (SSGN-726) is a U.S. Navy nuclear powered guided missile submarine. Originally commissioned as an SSBN (fleet ballistic missile submarine), the Ohio was converted and reclassified to SSGN. SS stands for submarine, G stands for guided missile, and N stands for nuclear powered. The Ohio is capable of launching both conventional and nuclear-tipped cruise missiles from 22 tubes, each equipped with 7 Tomahawk cruise missiles.  

Film Credits: PO1 Kenneth Takada, LT Edward Early

2106.description:
The aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) conducts night flight deck operations in the U.S. Navy 5th Fleet area of responsibility on July 7, 2015.  

Film Credits: U.S. Navy video by Mass Communication Specialist Seaman Alex Millar/Released

2107.description:
Footage of U.S. Marines with Marine Heavy Helicopter Squadron 461 and members of Regimental Combat Team 7 conducting a combat raid and interdiction operation against the Taliban in Nawzad, Helmand Province in Afghanistan. Filmed July 22, 2013.
       
Film Credits: Sgt Gabriela Garcia

2108.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighter Jet Pilots are caught chit-chatting with boom operators while refueling inflight. 

Film Credits: MSgt Jason Wilkerson

2109.description:
U.S. Air Force KC-135 crewmembers from the 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron refuels F-16s from the 35th Fighter Wing, Misawa Japan and A-10 Warthogs from the 127th Wing from Selfridge Air Base, MI over Southwest Asia on June 30, 2015. 

Film Credits: SSgt John Raven

2110.description:
An F-15 Eagle Jet Fighter with painted tails fins (otherwise known as livery) takes-off from Mountain Home Air Force Base in Idaho. Filmed on June 19, 2015. 

Film Credits: A1C Justin Carnahan

2111.description:
U.S. Army National Guard Special Operations Forces (SOF) - Green Beret Combat Divers are highlighted, with attention to different military assets that work with them during training missions. 

Film Credits: Army SSgt Adam Fishman, Travis Sauls

2112.description:
U.S. Marines conduct rappelling and fast-rope training from an MV-22 Osprey at Marine Corps Air Station New River, NC on June 23, 2015. Units - Marine Special Operations Command (MARSOC), Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron VMM-263

Film Credits: Sgt Orlando Perez

2113.description:
Cockpit video from an F-15D Eagle (two seat trainer) while flying in formation with other F-15 Eagles from the 122nd Fighter Squadron, and F-35 Lightning II Joint Strike Fighters. The video includes a flyover of the city of New Orleans, LA. Filmed in November of 2014.

Film Credits: SrA Robert Kingery

2114.description:
Previous test launches of the Minuteman III ICBM nuclear missile from Vandenberg AFB in California between September 2013 to June 2015.

Film Credits: Michael Stonecypher

2115.description:
MQ-1B Predator pilot and sensor operator from the 6th Reconnaissance Squadron (6th RS) fly a training mission from a ground control station at Holloman AFB in New Mexico. The MQ-1B Predator is an armed, multi-mission, medium altitude, long-endurance remotely piloted aircraft. The MQ-1 can perform the following missions and tasks: intelligence, surveillance, reconnaissance, close air support, combat search and rescue, precision strike, buddy-lase, convoy & raid over watch, route clearance, target development, and terminal air guidance. Filmed June 15, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA BreeAnn Sachs

2116.description:
Different kinds of U.S. Military aircraft takeoff at Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson in Alaska during exercise Northern Edge 2015 on June 18, 2015 -- C-130 Hercules, P-8 Poseidon, P-3 Orion, E-3 Sentry (AWACS), C-17 Globemaster III, F-15 Eagle, F-22 Raptor.    

Film Credits: SrA Carly Kavish

2117.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Aggressors take off at Eielson Air Force Base in Alaska during exercise Northern Edge 2015 on June 15, 2015. F-16 Aggressor aircraft act as an opposing force in military wargames and have a camouflage scheme to emulate Russian planes.       

Film Credits: SSgt Estrella Martinez

2118.description:
U.S. Air Force KC-10 Extenders (air tankers) take off at Eielson Air Force Base in Alaska during exercise Northern Edge 2015 on June 15, 2015. 

Film Credits: SSgt Estrella Martinez

2119.description:
U.S. Air Force C-130 crew conducts a medical evacuation training exercise at Fort McCoy in Wisconsin with British and Canadian counterparts as part of exercise Patriot Warrior 2015. Filmed on June 20, 2015. 

Film Credits: A1C Natalie Powell, A1C Eric Mann

2120.description:
An M1A2 Abrams Tank is transported via C-17 Globemaster III from Ramstien Air Base in Germany to  Bulgaria as part of Operation Speed and Power, the first time for an M1A2 to fire live rounds in Bulgaria. Filmed on June 20, 2015. Cockpit video and landing scene added for effect. 

Film Credits: SGT Alan Brutus, SGT Jesiah Dixon, TSgt Amanda Helton, SMSgt Edward Snyder

2121.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15 Strike Eagles arrive at Aviano Air Base in Italy for a joint training exercise. F-15 fighter jets from the 492nd Fighter Squadron based at RAF Lakenheath in England fly-over and land at Aviano Air Base for a DACT mission. Filmed on June 9, 2015.

Film Credits: A1C Chandler Baker

2122.description:
Load testing of the The Electromagnetic Aircraft Launch System (EMALS) aboard the future aircraft carrier PCU Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78). The EMALS will replace traditional steam catapult launching systems on the Ford (still under consruction) and all future U.S. Navy aircraft carriers. This new technology uses stored kinetic energy and solid-state electrical power conversion which permits a high degree of computer control, monitoring, and automation. The system will be capable of launching all current and future carrier air wing aircraft. EMALS delivers: • Higher launch energy capacity • Substantial improvements in system weight, volume, and maintenance • Increased reliability and efficiency • More accurate end-speed control. Filmed on June 15-16, 2015.

Film Credits: PO3 Ryan Litzenberger

2123.description:
U.S. Marines with the 31st MEU (Marine Expeditionary Unit) shoot a combat marksmanship range aboard the USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6) on June 13, 2015.

Film Credits: Cpl Abbey Perria

2124.description:
U.S. and Polish F-16 fighter jets takeoff from Lask Air Base in Poland during Operation Atlantic Resolve and Exercise Eagle Talon. The bilateral training is being conducted during the month of June with aircraft and aircrews from the USAF 169th Fighter Wing, the USAF 52nd Fighter Wing, and the 32nd Tactical Air Wing from Poland. Footage from June 5 and June 17, 2015.

Film Credits: SMSgt Edward Snyder

2125.description:
U.S. Air Force 5th AMXS Weapons Load Team - loading Navy Mark-62 QUICKSTRIKE mines to a B-52 Stratofortress in support of an ALTOPS-15 mission. The MK-62 QUICKSTRIKE is a recoverable, inert-loaded mine identical in size and weight to its armed-service mine counterpart. It is designed solely for training aviation personnel flying B-52H, F/A-18A/D, B-1B, B-2A, or P-3C aircraft in the techniques of carrying mines and planting minefields by an aircraft during anti-submarine warfare. 

Film Credits: A1C Lauren OConnor

2126.description:
U.S. Abrams M1A2 and Danish Leopard-2 Tanks conduct live-fire maneuvers during exercise Saber Strike-15 at Drawsko Pomorskie Training Area in Poland on June 16, 2015.   

Film Credits: SrA Steven Adkins

2127.description:
A Pennsylvania Air National Guard (ANG) crew flying a Michigan ANG KC-135 Stratotanker refuels Maryland ANG A-10 Thunderbolts in-flight. Filmed on June 9, 2015.

Film Credits: SSgt Marvin Wigfall

2128.description:
U.S. F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 169th Fighter Wing go through pre-flight checks on the flightline prior to launch at Lask Air Base in Poland During Operation Atlantic Resolve 2015. Filmed on June 5, 2015.

Film Credits: SMSgt Edward Snyder

2129.description:
U.S. M1A2 Tanks and Bradley Fighting Vehicles conduct live-fire and maneuver exercises at Central Training Area near Tapa, Estonia on June 13 and 14, 2015. Unit - 2nd Battalion, 7th Infantry Regiment, 1st Armored Brigade Combat Team, 3rd Infantry Division

Film Credits: SSG Cody Harding

2130.description:
Cockpit video from a Vanguard Squadron Van's Aircraft RV-3 performing aerobatics during the Wings Over Whiteman Air Show 2015 at Whiteman Air Force Base. The Vanguard Squadron is a US based ethanol powered aerobatic team that flies 6-10 airshow events each year and currently has five Van's RV-3 aircraft. 

Film Credits: A1C Emili Koonce

2131.description: An introductory look at the U.S. Air Force Test Pilot School (USAF TPS) located at Edwards AFB. Follow  the class of 15-ALPHA during the first few weeks of USAF TPS and get a glimpse of Test Pilot training. Did you know not all USAF TPS students are pilots? In addition to student pilots, there are students who are also engineers and combat systems operators.

2132.description:
Two U2 "Dragon Lady" Spy Planes from the U.S. Air Force 9th Reconnaissance Wing land at Royal Air Force (RAF) station in Gloucestershire, England. Filmed on June 9, 2015.

Film Credits: TSgt Joseph Vigil

2133.description:
The 82nd Aerial Target Squadron at Holloman AFB is the only unit in any military branch still flying the F-4 Phantom. All of the F-4's at Holloman will be turned into target drones. Once piloted solo as a drone, the QF-4 is never manned again. This is part of phasing out of the F-4 Phantom. The QF-4 drones are then flown over White Sands Missile Range where military and private sectors use them as targets to test aerial and ground weapons systems. Filmed on June 2, 2105.  

Film Credits: A1C JaoTorey Johnson

2134.description:
U.S. M1A2 tanks from 1st Armored Combat Brigade, 3rd Infantry Division practice battlefield maneuvers at Tapa Military Base in Tapa, Estonia. Filmed April - June 2015.  

Film Credits: SSG Cody Harding, SSG J Byers

2135.description:
AV-8B Harrier jet pilots practice short takeoffs and vertical landings (STOVL) aboard the USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6) on June 9, 2015. Unit - Marine Attack Squadron 311, 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit  

Film Credits: Cpl Abbey Perria

2136.description:
U.S. Marine landing support specialist and U.S. Army Soldiers attach a 1,000-pound cargo load to an MV-22 Osprey with a single-point hook during External Cargo Lift Training. Filmed on June 6, 2015.   

Film Credits: Cpl Jacob Smith

2137.description:
F-35 fighter jets from the 56th Fighter Wing at Luke AFB conduct an aerial refueling mission with two KC-135 air-tankers over Arizona on June 5, 2015.  

Film Credits: SrA Jenna Bigham

2138.description:
Austrian Pilatus PC-7 aircraft fly close air support strafing runs over a U.S. 173rd Airborne Brigade JTAC Team and Slovenian M-84 tanks during exercise Adriatic Strike 2015. The NATO exercise includes troops from Austria, Belgium, Canada, Croatia, the Czech Republic, France, Hungary, Italy, Lithuania, Latvia, Montenegro, the Netherlands, Romania, Slovenia, and the United States. Filmed on June 2-4, 2015.  

Film Credits: A1C Lauren

2139.description:
U.S. Marine Corps pilots fly a UH1-Y Super Huey during a Utility Basics Exercise in Yuma, Arizona. JML refers to a girl I used to know and still love. Give a thumbs up if you have ever been in love. This is my tribute the her. Thanks - GHV.      

Film Credits: Sgt Robert Brown

2140.description:
B-52s from Minot Air Force Base, North Dakota during operations at Royal Air Force Fairford, England, in support of U.S. European Command Exercises BALTOPS 15 and Saber Strike 15. Bomber missions such as these ensure bomber crews and supporting deployed troops maintain a high state of readiness and proficiency, demonstrating their ability to provide a flexible and always-ready global strike capability. 

Film Credits: A1C Lauren

2141.description:
F-16 fighter jets from the USAF and ROKAF taxi and takeoff during Exercise Buddy Wing 15-4 at Kunsan Air Base in South Korea. Kunsan Air Base is home to the U.S. Air Force 8th Fighter Wing, known as the "Wolf Pack", plus the Republic of Korea Air Force 38th Fighter Group. Buddy Wing exercises are conducted at various ROKAF and U.S. Air Force bases multiple times throughout the year in South Korea. The combined fighter exchange program provides pilots an opportunity to exchange ideas and practice combined tactics in order to fight and fly as one Allied force. Filmed on June 3-4, 2015.

Film Credits: SSgt Andrew Helmkamp

2142.description:
B-2 Spirit Bomber operations at Royal Air Force Fairford, England include taxi, takeoff, landing, hot-pit refueling, and engine-running crew change. Filmed on June 7, 2015.

Film Credits: A1C Lauren OConnor

2143.description:
The U.S. Air Force Wings Of Blue parachute team perform tandem jumps, recording with GoPro cameras. The primary mission of the Wings of Blue is to run the Air Force Academy's Basic Freefall Parachuting course, Airmanship 490 (AM-490). Members of the team serve primarily as jumpmasters and instructors for the course, teaching students about parachuting and training them to make unassisted freefall skydives. AM-490 is the only first-jump program in the world where students can make their first freefall jump without assistance. Each year, more than 700 cadets are given the opportunity to take AM-490 and earn their jump wings. Filmed on June 4, 2015.

Film Credits: Kevin Conroy

2144.description:
Soldiers and Airman experience the grueling "zero" day of two week Air Assault training at Camp Rilea, Oregon. Candidates are required to overcome 9 obstacles, some of which are mandatory in order to continue with the rest of training. Filmed on June 2, 2015.

Soldiers are not considered “Air Assault Students” until after successful completion of Zero, the first day of the course, which requires students to complete an obstacle course and two-mile run.

Prior to the obstacle course, students will conduct a two-mile run. Students must complete the run in under 18:00 minutes.

The obstacle course is designed to assess a student’s upper body strength, agility, endurance, confidence, and ability to perform at heights without displaying fear or distress. This test is critical in determining if a student will be able to complete Air Assault School without becoming a safety risk to themselves, instructors, or other students during the tough and demanding training events conducted throughout the course. 

There are nine total obstacles. There are two obstacles that are considered mandatory, and failing one of the two will result in being dropped from the course. The other seven are minor obstacles, and the Air Assault prospect is allowed to fail one of the seven and still continue. This means that failing two of the minor obstacles will result in being dropped from the course.

Film Credits: SGT Aaron Ricca

2145.description:
A-10C Warthog cockpit video during a Combat Search & Rescue (CSAR) training mission over Arizona. Filmed on January 20, 2015. Unit - 354th Fighter Wing

Film Credits: SrA Austin Willhoit

2146.description:
GoPro helmet-cam footage of U.S. Marines with the 15th MEU - USS Rushmore (LSD-47) practice amphibious assault platoon transport with AAV-7 Amphibious Assault Vehicles at Marine Corps Base Hawaii on May 18-19, 2015.

Film Credits: Sgt Emmanuel Ramos

2147.description:
U.S. Marines with 3rd Battalion, 11th Marines conduct a movement to firing positions and a Battalion Fire Exercise with M-777 Howitzers at Lavic Lake - Twentynine Palms, California. Filmed May 28-30, 2015.

Film Credits: LCpl Hannah Carlson

2148.description:
The F-35B Lightning II Joint Strike Fighter is undergoing operational testing (OT-1) at sea aboard the USS Wasp (LHD-1). The OT-1 phase is set to evaluate and assess the integration of the F-35B into Marine Corps aviation while operating across different flight, maintenance, and logistical operations that are common in the Marine Corps. Filmed on June 1, 2015.

Film Credits: Lance Cpl. Remington Hall

2149.description:
The U.S. Navy guided-missile destroyer USS Ross (DDG-71) operating in the Black Sea observes a fly-over by a Russian Sukhoi Su-24 (Fencer) on June 1, 2015. The Russian aircraft was not armed (wings clean) and the U.S. Arleigh Burke-class warship did not deviate from it's course. The USS Ross (DDG-71) carries an armament of ninety RIM-156 SM-2 surface-to-air missiles, or BGM-109 Tomahawk cruise missiles, or RUM-139 VL-ASROC anti-submarine missiles... or a combination of all three up to ninety in all.  

Film Credits: Pubic Domain - This work, USS Ross (DDG 71) Observes the Overflight by a Russian SU 24 Aircraft, is free of known copyright restrictions under U.S. copyright law.

2150.description:
A U.S. Coast Guard crew from San Diego conducts rescue swimmer training off the coast of Newport Beach, California with a GoPro camera. The training gives pilots, rescue swimmers, and flight mechanics the opportunity to practice rescue techniques to simulate real distress situations. Filmed on May 4, 2015. Unit - U.S. Coast Guard (PADET) San Diego

Film Credits: PO2 Robert Simpson

2151.description:
An RQ-7 Shadow unmanned aerial spy vehicle is launched during Operation Fearless Guardian, the U.S. training and equipping of the Ukrainian National Guard. The RQ-7 Shadow is a surveillance UAV used for battlefield recon. Filmed on May 31, 2015. Unit - Unmanned Aircraft Systems Platoon, 173rd Airborne Brigade  

Film Credits: CPT Steven Modugno

2152.description:
U.S. Soldiers with the 173rd Airborne Brigade train with members of the Estonian Defense Force on anti-tank rockets and missiles. The AT4 is a portable shoulder fired anti-tank rocket. The FGM-148 Javelin and the BGM-71 TOW are guided anti-tank missiles.

Film Credits: SFC Joshua Brandenburg, Cpl Ryan Young

2153.description:
The U.S. Navy littoral combat ship USS Fort Worth (LCS-3), on routine patrol in international waters in the South China Sea near the Spratly Islands, is shadowed by the Chinese Navy guided-missile frigate Yancheng (FFG-546). Filmed on May 12, 2015.   

Film Credits: PO2 Conor Minto

2154.description:
U.S. Marine MV-22B Ospreys take part in a multilateral training exercise with Bulgarian and Romanian Armed Forces at the Babadag Training Area in Romania. This is the first time Marine Corps Ospreys have been used in a training exercise inside Romania. Marines from the Black Sea Rotational Force and Special-Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force Crisis Response-Africa participated in Exercise Platinum Eagle 15 on May 26, 2015.  

Film Credits: Sgt Paul Peterson

2155.description:
U.S. Marine Corps MV-22B Ospreys depart Morón Air Base in Spain headed for Mihail Kogălniceanu Air Base in Romania. The Ospreys and two KC-130J Hercules are part of an integration exercise designed to test the unit’s ability to integrate its air assets in Spain with forces already stationed in Romania. The event also marked the first time Ospreys have landed in Romania. Filmed on May 23-24, 2015. Unit - Special-Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force Crisis Response-Africa (SPMAGTF-CR-AF)

Film Credits: Sgt Paul Peterson, Cpl Ashton Buckingham

2156.description:
U.S. Fighting Falcons from the 169th Fighter Wing are deployed to Lask Air Base in Poland as part of Operation Atlantic Resolve. The Aviation Detachment pairs U.S. F-16 pilots and maintenance crews with their Polish Air Force counterparts to strengthen partnership between NATO allies. Filmed on May 28, 2015.

Film Credits: TSgt Jorge Intriago

2157.description:
The United States Air Force Thunderbirds practice maneuvers over Falcon Stadium in Colorado Springs, Colorado for the Air Force Class of 2015 Graduation Ceremony. Filmed on May 26, 2015.

Film Credits: Kevin Conroy

2158.description:
U.S. Marines and Sailors from the 15th Marine Expeditionary Unit demonstrate amphibious landing capabilities on Marine Corps Training Area Bellows, Hawaii. The Marines launched assault amphibious vehicles (AAVs) and landing craft air cushioned (LCACs) from the USS Rushmore (LSD-47) as part of exercise Culebra Koa 15. Filmed on May 19, 2015. U.S. Navy Units -  USS Essex (LHD 2), USS Rushmore (LSD 47), USS Anchorage (LPD 23), USS Port Royal (CG 73), USNS Montford Point (T-MLP 1), USNS Millinocket (JHSV 3), USNS Dahl (T-AKR 312).

Film Credits: Sgt William Holdaway, LCpl Rene Lucerobonilla

2159.description:
Four U.S. Air Force A-10 Thunderbolt II "Warthogs" taxi, takeoff and land on their first day as part of the Theater Security Package (TSP) deployed to Sliac Air Base, Slovakia. A TSP is a USAF deployment of aircraft and personnel to Eastern Europe in support of Operation Atlantic Resolve to demonstrate U.S. commitment to security and stability in the region. Filmed May 14, 2015. Unit - 354th Expeditionary Fighter Squadron 

Film Credits: SSgt Ashley Corkins

2160.description:
A U.S. P-8A Poseidon maritime patrol aircraft conducting surveillance operations over the South China Sea is warned multiple times to "go away quickly" by the Chinese Navy. Video includes audio of radio communications as the confrontation takes place. The U.S. P-8A is from Patrol Squadron 45 (VP-45) and was observing the Peoples Republic of China (PRC) Navy building an installation in the South China Sea. Filmed on May 20, 2015.  

Film and Audio Credits: PO2 Joshua Scott

2161.description:
A multi-ship formation of C-17 Globemaster III and C-130 Hercules aircraft drop over 1700 paratroopers and equipment from the 82nd Airborne Division in a simulated mobilization and deployment of the U.S. Global Response Force during Exercise Crescent Reach 2015. Members of the 437th Airlift Wing launched eleven C-17s and flew to Pope AFB, North Carolina where they were joined by four more C-17s, six C-130s, E-8 JSTARS, and F-16 Falcons. The exercise was in response to a simulated crises abroad. Filmed on May 21, 2015.  

Film Credits: A1C Eric Mann, SrA Aaron Richardson, SrA John McRell, SSgt John Raven, SSgt Steven Witt, A1C Ryan Green
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2162.description:
Fleet Week New York 2015 runs from May 20-26, appropriately covering the Memorial Day Holiday. Marines of Special-Purpose Marine Air Ground Task Force-New York put on a spectacle for schoolkids and visitors of Orange Avenue School, flying in on an MV-22 Osprey as part of the Fleet Week New York 2015 festivities.  

Film Credits: Michael Lieberknecht, Sgt Marco Mancha

2163.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a live-fire Integrated Training Exercise (ITX 3-15) to increase operational force readiness. The large-scale combined arms exercise included infantry troops, armored vehicles including M1A2 tanks, and rotary aircraft. The training event included elements of the 3rd Battalion, 8th Marines and was held at Twentynine Palms Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center (MCAGCC) on May 19, 2015. 

Film Credits: SrA Garrett Wake

2164.description:
The last C-5 Galaxy aircraft assigned to 167th Airlift Wing takes-off from Shepherd Field Air National Guard Base in West Virginia, headed to the Davis-Monthan Boneyard where it will be retired. The 167th Airlift Wing is converting over to the C-17 Globemaster III. Filmed on May 20, 2015.

Film Credits: MSgt Emily Beightol-Deyerle

2165.description:
GoPro footage of Bradley Fighting Vehicles with the 3rd Infantry Division, U.S. Army firing rounds downrange at the Vaziani Training Area, Republic of Georgia during Exercise Noble Partner. Filmed on May 21, 2015.  

Film Credits: SGT Ryan Barwick

2166.description:
The Boeing C-17 Globemaster III is a large military transport aircraft used by the U.S. Air Force (and other countries around the world). The C-17 performs strategic airlift missions, transporting troops and cargo throughout the world. In addition, it performs tactical airlift, medical evacuation, and airdrop duties. In 2013 Boeing delivered the last of 223 C-17s to the USAF. Since 1991, the C-17 Globemaster III has been the world's only strategic airlifter with tactical capabilities that allow it to fly between continents, land on short, austere runways, and airdrop supplies precisely where they are needed.

Film Credits: TSgt Matthew Pardini, TSgt Justin Suddeth, SSgt Robert Harnden, SMSgt Edward Snyder

2167.description:
The Galveston Island Beach Patrol rescued two men by boat before a Coast Guard MH-65 Dolphin helicopter crew hoisted the third man, who was injured, to safety. Filmed on May 19, 2015.  

Film Credits: Lt. Joshua Scritchfield - Air Station Houston

2168.description:
Raw footage of F-22 Raptor aircraft taxi and Inflight - produced by Lockheed Martin. 

Public Domain released on May 19, 2015 here: https://www.dvidshub.net/video/405018/raw-footage-f-22-taxing-flying-and-static#.VVviCCFVikp

2169.description:
A U.S. Air Force C-5M Super Galaxy from Travis AFB set 46 new records making the C-5 the aircraft with the most world records held in aviation history. Simulator flights, maintenance, aerial porters, load masters and operations personnel all contributed to the record setting effort. The C-5M now holds 89 World Records, the most records held by any aircraft. 

Film Credits & Image Credits: SSgt John Ayre, Roland Balik

2170.description:
The USNS Spearhead Joint High Speed Vessel (JHSV-1) returns to Naval Amphibious Base Little Creek, Virginia after a four month deployment. The Spearhead is the first ship in the Spearhead-class Joint High Speed Vessel, and is essentially a big twin-hull catamaran with four huge diesel engines. It is 338 feet long and 93 feet wide. The Spearhead has a crew of 41, can transport 312 passengers, has a capacity of 600 short tons, and can travel 43 knots (49 mph). Filmed May 16, 2015. 

Film Credits: Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Jesse A. Hyatt

2171.description:
USS George Washington (CVN-73) makes its final departure from Yokosuka, Japan on May 18, 2015 after being home-ported there as the U.S. Navy's forward-deployed aircraft carrier for seven years. George Washington will participate in the Australia-based Talisman Saber exercise in July before heading to San Diego, where about 2,000 sailors will switch over to the USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76). The Ronald Reagan will then replace the George Washington in Japan as the Navy's forward-deployed aircraft carrier, and the George Washington will sail to Norfolk, Virginia to complete a multi-year nuclear refueling and overhaul.  


Film Credits: This work, USS George Washington Leaves Japan Broll, is free of known copyright restrictions under U.S. copyright law. https://www.dvidshub.net/video/404757/uss-george-washington-leaves-japan-broll#.VVoCdSFVikp

2172.description:
Bradley Fighting Vehicles and M1A2 Tanks send rounds downrange at Fort Hood, TX. The armored vehicles are with the 2nd Armored Brigade Combat Team (Black Jack Brigade), 1st Cavalry Division, U.S. Army. Filmed May 13, 2015. 

Film Credits: SGT Elliot Valdez

2173.description:
In late summer 2016 the U.S. Navy plans to deploy a prototype electromagnetic railgun aboard the Spearhead-class joint high speed vessel USNS Trenton (JHSV-5) for at-sea testing. Tests will begin off the coast of Florida to assess the gun's ability to perform naval surface fire support against static floating targets 25–50 nmi (29–58 miles) away using GPS-guided hyper velocity projectiles (HVPs). Although the railgun will not ultimately be deployed on JHSV ships, the Navy has yet to decide which ship classes will receive fully operational railguns.

Film & Image Credits: U.S. Navy Video Released, USNS Trenton Rolls Out-U.S. Navy Photo/Released

2174.description:
Lockheed P-3 Orion Maritime Patrol Aircraft flown by US Customs and Border Protection (CBP), track smugglers in the act of transporting illegal drugs.   

Film Credits: Michael Pope

2175.description:
U.S. Soldiers from 2nd Battalion, 7th Infantry Regiment, 173rd Airborne Brigade run a Latvian military obstacle course. The soldiers went through the course to maintain their strength and agility, as they continue to support Operation Atlantic Resolve, an ongoing multinational partnership focused on joint training and security cooperation between the U.S. and other NATO allies. Filmed on May 15, 2015.   

Film Credits: SGT Summer Woode

2176.description:
U.S. Air Force Aircrews from the 144th Fighter Wing provide maintenance for F-15 Eagle fighter jets on the flight line and prepare them for takeoff. Plus footage of aerial refueling of F-15s by a KC-135 Stratotanker during exercise Sentry Savannah (15-2) out of the Air Dominance Center, Garden City, GA. Filmed on May 5 and May 13, 2015.    

Film Credits: SSgt George Solis

2177.description:
F-22 Raptors from the 525th Fighter Squadron, Joint Base Elmendorf–Richardson refuel inflight from a KC-10 Extender air tanker from the 76th Air Refueling Squadron, Joint Base McGuire-Dix-Lakehurst, N.J. Filmed on May 7, 2015.      

Film Credits: SSgt Sheila deVera

2178.description:
