Scenes of U.S. Army training at Fort Irwin, National Training Center in California include constructing an assault landing strip for C-17 aircraft, M1A2 Tank live fire exercise, M-777 Howitzer live fire exercise, and Urban Warfare training.      

Film Credits: SSG Jason Proseus, Jason Miller, MSgt Amy Cartas, Kenneth Drylie

2179.description:
The amphibious assault ship USS Essex (LHD-2) departs Naval Base San Diego on deployment - filmed on May 11, 2015.

Film Credits: Nicholas Groesch

2180.description:
USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70), Carrier Strike Group One, and ships from the Malaysian Royal Navy cruise in formation together in the South China Sea. Carl Vinson Strike group is deployed to the 7th Fleet area of operation supporting security and stability in the Indo-Asia-Pacific region. Filmed On May 10, 2015. USS Gridley (DDG-101) and KD Lekir (FSG-26) also pictured.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Samuel LeCain/Released

2181.description:
The USAF 303rd Expeditionary Rescue Squadron completes aerial refueling, combat search and rescue + personnel recovery training out of Campo Lemmonier, Djibouti in East Africa on April 14, 2015.    

Film Credits: MSgt Eric Miller

2182.description:
An MQ-9 Reaper drone flown by the 174th Attack Wing trains on touch-and-go landings at Wheeler-Sack Army Airfield in New York state on April 15, 2015.    

Film Credits: MSgt Eric Miller

2183.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a massive air assault exercise, moving an entire battalion of combat ready troops on CH-53 Super Stallion helicopters and MV-22 Ospreys. Marines with 2nd Battalion, 1st Marine Regiment (approximately 1000 Marines) took part in the large-scale air lift from Camp Pendleton to Twentynine Palms in California. The troop movement was part of exercise Dawn Blitz 2013 and included air assets from the 3rd Marine Aircraft Wing.     

Film Credits: Sgt Isaac Lamberth, Sgt Scott Reel, Cpl. Jesse Witten (3rd MAW Combat Camera)
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2184.description:
F-35B Lightning II Joint Strike Fighters perform short takeoffs and vertical landings as part of field carrier landing practice (FCLP) at Marine Corps Air Station Yuma auxiliary landing field on May 6, 2015. Unit - Marine Fighter Attack Squadron 121 (VMFA-121)     

Film Credits: Cpl Travis Gershaneck

2185.description:
The U.S. Air Force KC-Extender refuels multiple allied combat aircraft, including E-3 Sentry (AWACS), A-10 Thunderbolt II, French Mirage F-1, F/A-18 Super Hornet, keeping them on-station in the skies over enemy targets able to coordinate and strike. Unit - 908th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron      

Film Credits: TSgt Matthew Pardini, SSgt Jeffrey Curtin

2186.description:
Soldiers rappel from UH-60 Black Hawk helicopters while in U.S. Army Air Assault School (aka Sabalauski Air Assault School) at Fort Bliss, TX. Air Assault School qualifies soldiers to conduct airmobile and air assault helicopter operations, including aircraft orientation, slingload operations, proper rappelling and fast-rope techniques. The school is 10 days of rigorous, fast-paced training. Filmed on April 21, 2015.     

Film Credits: SGT Jose Ramirez

2187.description:
The High Mobility Artillery Rocket System, transported by C-130, is fired at Cannon Air Force Base in New Mexico and lights up the night sky. Filmed during exercise Emerald Warrior on April 29, 2015.    

Film Credits: A1C Elizabeth Taranto

2188.description:
Army National Guard 20th Special Forces Group (Airborne) Combat Divers perform dive re-qualification with the help of U.S. Coast Guard members from station Mayport, Florida on May 2, 2015.     

Film Credits: SSG Adam Fischman

2189.description:
U.S. Soldiers conduct an M16 rifle and M9 pistol weapons Qualification and Zero range at Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany on April 29, 2015. Unit - 7th Army Joint Multinational Training Command (JMTC)      

Film Credits: U.S. Army video by Visual Information Specialist Gerhard Seuffert/released

2190.description:
The Weapon and Tactics Instructor course (WTI) is a seven-week course of instruction hosted by Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron 1 (MAWTS-1) at Marine Corps Air Station Yuma, Arizona. It incorporates Marine Corps planning and implementation of advanced air and ground tactics through a series of escalating evolutions in order to produce certified Weapons and Tactics Intructors. WTIs serve as squadron training officers who use their skills to act as aircraft and weapons subject matter experts to provide their units with proper training and evaluation to ensure maximum combat readiness.    

Film Credits: Sgt Cody M.D. Haas

2191.description:
U.S. Coast Guardsmen from Station South Padre Island, Texas chased and apprehended Mexican nationals aboard a lancha after crews in Coast Guard aircraft spotted them fishing illegally in U.S. territorial waters May 1, 2015. One of the men has been caught and deported more than 15 times and had warrants out for his arrest.     

Film Credits: PO1 Andrew Kendrick

2192.description:
U.S. F-15 Eagles fly with Bulgarian M-29 Fulcrums and Su-25 Frogfoots at Graf Ignatievo Air Base, Bulgaria during exercise Thracian Eagle 2015. The joint exercise is designed to enhance interoperability with Bulgaria and maintain joint readiness with NATO allies. Filmed on May 2, 2015. Unit - 159th Fighter Wing, Louisiana Air National Guard     

Film Credits: MSgt Toby Valadie

2193.description:
U.S. Army M1A2 Abrams Tanks display their combat power in a demonstration for distinguished guests from the Estonian Ministry of Defense, Estonia Defense Forces, and the U.S. Ambassador in Tallinn. The demo took place at the Central Training Area in Tapa, Estonia. Filmed on April 30, 2015.     

Film Credits: SGT Dean Gannon

2194.description:
U.S. Marine Corps AH-1Z Viper Helicopters demonstrate deadly power as they fly strike runs on training targets at Mount Barrow, Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range in California. This close air support exercise supported WTI 1-15 - hosted by Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1) - Marine Corps Air Station Yuma.  

Film Credits: Cpl Jordan Walker

2195.description:
U.S. Marines from Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 262 load MV-22B Ospreys in Okinawa, Japan headed for Clark Air Base in the Philippines. The Marines pre-staged the aircraft in preparation to support humanitarian assistance and disaster relief operations following the earthquake in Nepal. Filmed on April 29, 2015.  

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps Motion Imagery by MCIPAC Combat Camera Lance Cpl. Nicholas D. Hatheway

2196.description:
Cockpit video of the U.S. Navy Blue Angels flight demonstration squadron as they takeoff and perform vertical rolls.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video Released
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2197.description:
Describes how virtual training by computer simulation is to be integrated with real world scenarios at exercise Red Flag, held annually at Nellis Air Force Base, to train allied war fighters across the globe.

Film Credits: Travis Sauls and A1C Taylor West from "In The Fight" episode 98

2198.description:
U.S. M1A2 Main Battle Tanks from the 7th Battalion, 1st Brigade, 3rd Infantry Division give a live fire demonstration for distinguished visitors and Estonian soldiers. It marks the first time that M1A2 tanks have fired shots in Estonia. Filmed on April 30, 2015.

Film Credits: SSG Cody Harding

2199.description:
The F-35 Joint Strike Fighter Flagship arrives at Luke Air Force Base, Arizona. The F-35 was flown by Brigadier General Scott Pleus, Commander of the 56th Fighter Wing, from Lockheed Martin's plant in Forth Worth, TX. Filmed on April 28, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Jenna Sarvinski

2200.description:
An all female U.S. C-17 Globemaster aircrew from the 816th Expeditionary Airlift Squadron participates in Exercise Eager Lion 2015. The exercise, involving 8,000 personnel from 19 countries, is underway as civil war rages next door in Syria. About 5,000 Americans from all services are participating in the Jordanian-led exercise, which will focus on issues such as integrated air and missile defense, and humanitarian assistance and disaster relief to address current and future conflict-security issues. 

Film Credits: SrA Andrew Walck

2201.description:
USMC Super Huey helicopters make live-fire attack runs on mock targets, with door gunners firing machine guns and miniguns during final exercise three (FINEX-3) at Marine Corps Air Station Yuma, Arizona on April 25, 2015. The UH-1Y Venom (aka Super Huey) is a twin-engine medium size helicopter gunship used by the United States Marine Corps.

Film Credits: Cpl Rachael Zilliox

2202.description:
An AC-130W Stinger II gunship and Airmen from the 73rd Special Operations Squadron fire the 30mm GAU-23/A cannon on ground targets during a close air support training exercise. The GAU-23/A is an upgraded version of the ATK Mk44 Bushmaster Automatic Cannon. Filmed on April 27, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Robert Kingery

2203.description:
Footage of various training exercises with the 3rd Armored Brigade Combat Team, 3rd Infantry Division, U.S. Army. Headquarters - Fort Benning, GA.

Film Credits: SPC Jordean Matthews

2204.description:
U.S. Soldiers with the 2-9 Infantry conduct a combined arms live-fire exercise (CALFEX) in South Korea on March 14, 2015.

Film Credits: SGT Kerry Collier

2205.description:
CH-53 Super Stallion helicopters transport U.S. Marines to assault positions during Final Exercise III as part of Weapons and Tactics Instructor Course (WTI) 2-15 near Yuma, Arizona. Filmed on April 25, 2015. 

Film Credits: LCpl Hannah Carlson

2206.description:
Confused about which drone footage you're watching? The MQ-1 Predator and the MQ-9 Reaper look very similar. Here is a fast way to tell the difference. 

Film Credits: MSgt Stanley Thompson, TSgt Michael Schocker, SrA Aaron Hauser, SrA Ariel Tumlinson

2207.description:
A-10 Thunderbolt II aircraft and aircrews from the 127th Wing "Michigan Red Devils" deploy to Southwest Asia in support of Operation Inherent Resolve. The deployment will last approximately 6 months. Filmed on April 11, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Toni Pointer

2208.description:
Members of the 4th Special Operations Squadron (4th SOS) conduct a live-fire mission in an AC-130U Spooky Gunship during exercise Emerald Warrior 2015 from Hurlburt Field, Florida. Filmed April 23,2015.

Film Credits: SSgt Ashley Manz

2209.description:
Australia's first F-35 Joint Strike Fighter pilot completes training at the Academic Training Center - Eglin Air Force Base, Florida. Filmed on April 23, 2015. 

Film Credits: SSgt Tarelle Walker

2210.description:
Members of the 7th Special Forces Group Green Berets conduct a high-altitude high-opening (HAHO) military parachute jump from a C-130H3 Hercules during training exercise Emerald Warrior 2015. Filmed on April 22, 2015. Emerald Warrior is the Department of Defense's only irregular warfare exercise, allowing joint and combined partners to train together and prepare for real world contingency operations.

Film Credits: SSgt Ashley Manz

2211.description:
U.S. Army Paladin M109A6 Howitzers conduct a fire mission to deliver effective fires in Smardan, Romania during Operation Atlantic Resolve - includes interior footage of crew loading and firing. Filmed on April 21, 2015.

Film Credits: SSG Scott Shoemaker

2212.description:
The U.S. Navy's X-47B unmanned combat air vehicle (UCAV) made aviation history by completing the first ever Autonomous Aerial Refueling (AAR) of an unmanned aircraft on April 22, 2015. While flying off the coast of Maryland and Virginia, the X-47B connected to an Omega K-707 tanker aircraft and received over 4,000 pounds of fuel using the Navy's probe-and-drogue method. This video also includes footage of launch and recovery of the X-47B aboard the aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) on August 17, 2014. - unmanned carrier-based platform (UCLASS) 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video/Released

2213.description:
A squadron of CH-46 Sea Knight helicopters with Marine Medium Helicopter Squadron 774 Fly The Barn over Norfolk, Virginia on April 21, 2015. "Fly The Barn" means to fly in mass formation. The flight was done to commemorate the last time the Sea Knights would fly before being retired, as the Marines transition over to the MV-22B Osprey tiltrotor aircraft. 

Film Credits: Cpl Jessika Acosta

2214.description:
U.S. Marines M1A2 tanks with 1st Tank Battalion maneuver live-fire attack positions to maintain combat skills on the battlefield during exercise Desert Scimitar (2014-2015) at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms, CA. 

What would happen if the U.S. sent a number of these tanks to the Ukraine?  

Film Credits: Sgt Christopher J. Moore

2215.description:
USAF Aeromedical Evacuation Squadrons provide care and movement of sick and injured soldiers using aircraft such as the C-130J Super Hercules which allow a larger patient load, long-distance transportation, and a greater ability to care for the seriously injured. Video includes footage of the 86th Expeditionary Aeromedical Evacuation Squadron out of Ramstein Air Base, Germany and the 455th Expeditionary Aeromedical Evacuation Squadron out of Bagram Airbase, Afghanistan.

Film Credits: SrA Nicholas Crisp, SrA William Branch

2216.description:
The aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) and the guided-missile cruiser USS Normandy (CG-60) sail together in the Arabian Gulf. The U.S. warships have moved closer to the coast of Yemen and are monitoring a convoy of Iranian ships carrying arms headed for Houthi rebels fighting in Yemen. Filmed April 21, 2015.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Justin R. DiNiro

2217.description:
B-2 Spirit Bombers (aka stealth bombers) from the 509th Bomb Wing at Whiteman AFB are refueled by a KC-135 Stratotanker with the Utah Air Nation Guard over Montana to maintain proficiency on aerial refueling capabilities and procedures. Filmed on February 18, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Danny Rangel, SSgt Erin Mills

2218.description:
A KC-130J Hercules air tanker conducts an inflight refueling mission with F/A 18 Hornet fighter jets during Weapons and Tactics Instructor course 2-15 out of Marine Corps Air Station Yuma, Arizona on April 16, 2015.

Film Credits: LCpl Jodson Graves, Cpl. Charles Santamaria

2219.description:
Compilation of air operations aboard the USS Green Bay (LPD-20) from March 5-30, 2015. Aircraft include AH-1 Super Cobra Attack helicopters, UH-1Y Venom "Huey" helicopters, and MV-22B Ospreys. The aircraft perform ship-to-shore missions with the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit (31st MEU) during Spring Patrol 2015 of the Asia-Pacific region.

Film Credits: LCpl Tyler Ngiraswei, Major Garron Garn

2220.description:
Cockpit video from a U.S. Army (Vermont National Guard) UH-72A Lakota helicopter as pilots take it for a flight over Northern Vermont and New York state. Filmed April 8, 2015.

Film Credits: Col. John Johnston, Warrant Office Glory O'Neil, SSG Nathan Rivard

2221.description:
U.S. Marine Corps UH-1Y Venom, AH-1 SuperCobra, and AH-1Z Viper helicopter gunships take part in an assault support tactics exercise at Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range in California. The exercise was part of Weapons and Tactics Instructor (WTI) Course 2-15, an annual training event based out of Yuma, Arizona. Filmed on April 13, 2015.

Film Credits: Cpl Waiyan Tin, LCpl Hannah Carlson

2222.description:
The Doolittle Raid, also known as the Tokyo Raid, on April 18, 1942 was the first U.S. air attack to strike the Japanese home islands during WWII. It demonstrated that Japan was vulnerable to American bombers, and was in direct retaliation for the Japanese attack on Pearl Harbor on December 7, 1941. Footage from Doolittle Tokyo Raiders Reunion at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base. Read more about the Doolittle Raid: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doolittle_Raid

Film Credits: Ken LaRock, Tech Sgt. Jeremy Zier, Matthew Clouse

2223.description:
Bradley Fighting Vehicles and crews with the U.S. Army, 1st Infantry Division conduct a live-fire exercise with Tube-launched Optically-tracked Wire-guided (TOW) anti-tank missiles. Filmed July 2014. Unit - 1st Battalion, 63rd Armor Regiment, 2nd Armored Brigade Combat Team, 1st Infantry Division   

Film Credits: SSG Tamika Dillard

2224.description:
A C-130J with the 146th Airlift Wing (146-AW) executes water drops in the Angeles Forest during annual training for the Modular Airborne Firefighting System (MAFFS) in preparation for the 2015 wildfire season. The 146-AW is a unit of the California Air National Guard stationed at Channel Islands Air National Guard Station at Oxnard, California.   

Film Credits: TSgt Ty Moore, TSgt William Moore

2225.description:
The USAF F-22 Raptor Demo Team flies at the Gulf Coast Salute Airshow 2015. The Air Combat Command F-22 Demonstration Team is based at Langley Air Force Base, Virginia. Filmed on April 11, 2015.  

Film Credits: TSgt Burt Traynor

2226.description:
CH-53E Super Stallion is the largest helicopter in the U.S. Military. It's used by the Marine Corps both as a troop and cargo transport. U.S. Marines conduct assault support tactics and day battle drills near Yuma, Arizona. Filmed April 4-13, 2015.  

Film Credits: LCpl Jodson Graves, Cpl Rachael Zilliox

2227.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a live-fire urban combat exercise at Fort Pickett, Virginia. Echo Company, Battalion Landing Team 2/6, 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit completed the training exercise in preparation for deployment to the 5th and 6th Fleet area of responsibility. Filmed April 13, 2015.

Film Credits: U.S. Marine Corps video by Cpl. Zachary W. Montgomery/Released

2228.description:
Four M1A2 Abrams Main Battle Tanks conduct a live-fire exercise at Pabrade Training Area, Lithuania. This was the first time U.S. Army tanks have been fired in Lithuania. The demonstration was part of Operation Atlantic Resolve, designed to show the U.S. military commitment to NATO allies. Filmed on April 9, 2015. Unit - Task Force 2-7 Infantry 

Film Credits: Sergeant Dean Gannon, 1st Armor Brigade Combat Team, Public Affairs NCO

2229.description:
An episodes of "Welcome To The MEU" - a video series following the 31st MEU (Marine Expeditionary Unit).
Flying The Huey - In this episode, follow Capt. Marianne Sparklin as she takes to the skies in the UH-1Y Venom "Huey" helicopter. Sparklin is with Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 262 (Reinforced), 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit

Welcome To The MEU Playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLnOwvB9zfF0zAw5ol1zIN-z-r8xP0nOB5

Film Credits: Cpl August Light

2230.description:
Two episodes of "Welcome To The MEU" - a video series following the 31st MEU (Marine Expeditionary Unit).
Splashing The AAV - In this episode, conduct a ship-to-shore operation alongside U.S. Marine Corps Cpl. Aleksandar Antic in his amphibious assault vehicle as he explains what it means to be amphibious.
Aerial Sniper - In this episode, get behind the scope with U.S. Marine Corps Sgt. Seth Utlser, chief scout sniper with Weapons Company, Battalion Landing Team 2nd Battalion, 4th Marines as he takes aim at targets from the sky.

Welcome To The MEU Playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLnOwvB9zfF0zAw5ol1zIN-z-r8xP0nOB5 

Film Credits: Cpl Abbey Perria

2231.description:
U.S. Marines and Portuguese Fuzileiros (Portuguese Marines) conduct fire and maneuver drills near Lisbon, Portugal. Marines with Special-Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force Crisis Response-Africa (SP-MAGTF-CR-AF) stationed at Moron Air Base, Spain, traveled to Portugal to train with the Fuzileiros in a week long bilateral exercise. Filmed April 7, 2015.

Film Credits: LCpl Christopher Mendoza

2232.description:
The RQ-7B Shadow unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) is used by the U.S. Army and Marine Corps for surveillance, reconnaissance, target acquisition and battle damage assessment. It is launched from a trailer-mounted pneumatic catapult, and recovered with arresting gear similar to jets on an aircraft carrier. RQ-7B Shadow carries a forward-looking Infrared camera (FLIR), a daytime TV camera with a selectable near-infrared filter, and a laser pointer. The military has been developing an upgraded version of the Shadow capable of deploying a variety of guided munitions, as well as the QuickMEDS system for delivering medical supplies to remote and stranded troops. Units: Unmanned Aerial Vehicle Squadron (VMU) 2 (U.S. Marines) - 4th Brigade Combat Team, 1st Cavalry Division (U.S. Army) 

Film Credits: Cpl Waiyan Tin, SGT Patrick Wolfe

2233.description:
U.S. Air Force and Army members conduct live-fire training with the M67 fragmentation grenade and the M18 Claymore mine. 

Film Credits: SrA Krystal Ardrey, A1C Daniel Fernandez, TSgt Scott Olguin, SrA Thomas Smith, SGT Anthony Kozleuchar, SGT Canaan Radcliffe

2234.description:
Aircraft carriers USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) and USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70) sail together in the U.S. 5th Fleet Area of Operation (AOR), as the Vinson conducts its last flight operations before leaving. The Roosevelt with take over duties supporting Operation Inherent Resolve - conducting maritime security operations, strike operations in Iraq and Syria, and theater security cooperation efforts. Filmed on April 11-13, 2015. 

Film Credits: Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Patrick Menah, Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Camilo Fernan

2235.description:
The aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70) completes final flight operations in support of Operation Inherent Resolve. USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) will relieve the Vinson in the U.S. 5th Fleet area of responsibility and continue supporting Operation Inherent Resolve, maritime security operations, strike operations in Iraq and Syria, and theater security cooperation efforts. Carrier Air Wing 17 Filmed on April 11, 2015. 

Film Credits: Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class James Bleyle

2236.description:
Twelve A-10 Thunderbolt II "Warthogs" are shown in close air support training, deployed to RoAF 71st Air Base - Campia Turzii, Romania. The A-10s from the 354th Expeditionary Fighter Squadron are part of a Theater Security Package. Also, approximately 200 Airmen and support equipment from the 355th Fighter Wing at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base, Arizona, and the 52nd Fighter Wing at Spangdahlem Air Base, Germany, will participate as a combat capable force able to respond to a wide variety of operations. Filmed April 9, 2015.  

Film Credits: SSgt Jonathan Porter

2237.description:
KC-135 Stratotankers refuel F-15C Eagles and F-15E Strike Eagles in-flight. KC-135 Stratotankers from the 909th, F-15C Eagles from the 44th and 67th Fighter squadrons, KC-135R Stratotanker from the 141st Air Refueling Squadron, F-15E Strike Eagles from the 334th Fighter Squadron

Film Credits: SSgt Maeson Elleman, A1C Matthew Hester, A1C Daniel Robles, TSgt Carl Clegg

2238.description:
Time lapse video of the Los Angeles-class fast attack submarine USS San Francisco (SSN-711) pulling into the floating dry dock Arco (ARDM 5) at Naval Base Point Loma, California. Filmed on April 2, 2015.
 
Film Credits: PO2 Kyle Carlstrom

2239.description:
The aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) conducts flight operations in the Arabian Gulf (Persian Gulf), launching aircraft in support of maritime security operations and theater security cooperation efforts in the U.S. 5th Fleet area of responsibility on October 3, 2014.  

Film Credits: Mass Communications Specialist 3rd Class Preston Paglinawan, Mass Communications Specialist 3rd Class Travis Litke, Mass Communications Specialist Seaman Apprentice David Lee

2240.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a long range combat raid exercise out of Marine Corps Air Station Yuma, Arizona on April 10, 2015. Units - 1st Battalion, 5th Marine Regiment, 1st Marine Division, 1st Marine Expeditionary Force 

Film Credits: Cpl Rachael Zilliox

2241.description:
Cockpit video of aerial refueling between a KC-130J Super Hercules air-tanker and F/A-18D Hornet fighter jets. 

Units - Marine Aerial Refueler Transport Squadron 152 (VMGR-152) "Sumos" and Marine All- Weather Fighter Attack Squadron 242 (VMFA(AW)-242) "Bats".

Film Credits: Sgt Anthony Rayis, Cockpit Video Courtesy Of VMFA(AW)-242.
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2242.description:
U.S. Marines Air Ground Support (AGS) personnel refuel and rearm AV-8B Harriers during an offensive air support exercise at Yuma Proving Grounds near Yuma, Arizona on April 7, 2015. Footage of Weapons and Tactics Instructor (WTI) Course 2-15 hosted by Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1). MAWTS-1 provides standardized tactical training and certification of unit instructor qualifications to support Marine Aviation Training and Readiness and assists in developing and employing Aviation Weapons and Tactics.

Film Credits: LCpl Hannah Carlson

2243.description:
U.S. Marines flying UH-1Y Venom Helicopters attack urban targets during a live-fire close air support exercise near Marine Corps Air Station in Yuma, Arizona. Day and night footage filmed on April 3, 2015.

Film Credits: Sgt Daniel Kujanpaa

2244.description:
The hospital ship USNS Comfort (T-AH-20) departs Naval Station Norfolk headed for the Caribbean in support of Operation Continuing Promise 2015, a periodic series of U.S. military exercises conducted under the direction of United States Southern Command to provide medical, dental, and veterinary aid to people in the Caribbean, Central and South America. Filmed April 1, 2015.

Film Credits: Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Justin Wolpert

2245.description:
U.S. Marines flying Super Huey helicopters, participate in Weapons and Tactics Instructor Course (WTI) 2-15, close air support (CAS) at Yodaville near Marine Corps Air Station Yuma, Arizona. WTI is a seven week event hosted by Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1). MAWTS-1 provides standardized tactical training and certification of unit instructor qualifications to support Marine Aviation Training and Readiness and assists in developing and employing Aviation Weapons and Tactics. Filmed on April 3, 2015.

Film Credits: Cpl Rachael Zilliox

2246.description:
Two episodes of "Welcome To The MEU" - a video series following the 31st MEU (Marine Expeditionary Unit).
The Marine Corps Fire Team: In this episode, follow a fire team of marines as they assault a simulated objective during a live fire training exercise.
Flying a Hovercraft: Mineman Chief Petty Officer Philip Phillips pilots the Landing Craft Air Cushion, or LCAC, as it transports Marines and equipment from ship to shore. The LCACs are with Naval Beach Unit 7, USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD 6).
Welcome To The MEU Playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLnOwvB9zfF0zAw5ol1zIN-z-r8xP0nOB5

Film Credits: Cpl August Light, Cpl Abbey Perria

2247.description:
Two episodes of "Welcome To The MEU" - a video series following the 31st MEU (Marine Expeditionary Unit).
The Marine Corps Fire Team: In this episode, follow a fire team of marines as they assault a simulated objective during a live fire training exercise.
Flying a Hovercraft: Mineman Chief Petty Officer Philip Phillips pilots the Landing Craft Air Cushion, or LCAC, as it transports Marines and equipment from ship to shore. The LCACs are with Naval Beach Unit 7, USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD 6).
Welcome To The MEU Playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLnOwvB9zfF0zAw5ol1zIN-z-r8xP0nOB5

Film Credits: Cpl August Light, Cpl Abbey Perria

2248.description:
Two episodes of "Welcome To The MEU" - a video series following the 31st MEU (Marine Expeditionary Unit).
Tactical Air Control Party: In this episode, see what a tactical air control party is like as Marines coordinate close air support.
At Sea: Capt. Garron Garn is on the USS Bonhomme Richard and gives viewers an update on the video series while at sea.
Welcome To The MEU Playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLnOwvB9zfF0zAw5ol1zIN-z-r8xP0nOB5

Film Credits: Cpl Abbey Perria

2249.description:
Soldiers of 3rd Battalion, 27th Field Artillery Regiment, U.S. Army, conduct a live-fire exercise with the HIMARS (High Mobility Artillery Rocket System) at National Training Center - Fort Irwin, CA. Filmed on September 15, 2014.

Film Credits: SGT Michael Grimm

2250.description:
KC-135 Stratotanker from the 191st Air Refueling Squadron executes an aerial refueling mission with an MC-130 Hercules from the 58th Special Operations Wing, USAF. Filmed on November 18, 2014. 

Film Credits: SSgt Erin Mills

2251.description:
U.S. Marines are inserted by CH-46 Sea Knight helicopters during an airfield seizure exercise at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center, Twentynine Palms.

Film Credits: MSgt Daniel Kauppila, Cpl Jesse Witten

2252.description:
Cockpit video from an F-16C Fighting Falcon with the 177th Fighter Wing as it gets fuel from a KC-135 Stratotanker in the sky over Afghanistan. Filmed out of Bagram Airfield.

Film Credits: TSgt Matt Hecht

2253.description:
F-18 fighter pilot training - Pilots from the 3rd Aircraft Wing, Marine Corps Air Station Miramar are interviewed telling what it's like being a fighter pilot and the weapons that an F-18 Hornet can deploy.  

Film Credits: Cpl Kevin Crist, Cpl Maxwell Pennington

2254.description:
Two KC-130J Hercules air tankers conduct a formation flight out of Moron Air Base in Spain on March 25, 2015. The KC-130J is largely used to transport assets and air-to-air refueling of additional aircraft. It is utilized for crisis-response missions ranging from disaster relief and humanitarian aid to embassy evacuation and security operations. Unit: Special-Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force Crisis Response-Africa (SP-MAGTF AF) 

Film Credits: 1LT Danielle Dixon

2255.description:
U.S. Marine Corps door gunners shoot GAU-31 .50 caliber machine guns and GAU-17/A miniguns from UH-1Y Venom helicopters.  

Film Credits: Sgt Jamean Berry, Cpl Alexander Pool

2256.description:
U.S. Marines with 15th Marine Expeditionary Unit execute a battalion level training exercise during Composite Training Unit Exercise (COMPTUEX) at Marine Air Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms in California on March 27, 2015. Units - Battalion Landing Team 3rd Battalion, 1st Marine Regiment   

Film Credits: Sgt Jamean Berry

2257.description:
U.S. Air Force and Romanian Joint Terminal Attack Controllers (JTAC) work together during a special forces training mission with six U.S. F-16 Fighting Falcons. The training was part of Dacian Warhawk, a joint U.S. and Romanian exercise at Campia Turzii, Romania. Filmed on April 1, 2015.   

Film Credits: A1C Austin Siegel

2258.description:
Two episodes of "Welcome To The MEU"... 
Vertical Assault - Follow Cpl. David Jorgenson as infantry Marines conduct a vertical assault into a simulated urban setting. The Marines and Sailors are with Echo Company, Battalion Landing Team 2nd Battalion, 4th Marines, 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit. 

CBRN Defense - Follow Lance Cpl. Jordan Nace while he and his teammates investigate a simulated dangerous chemical agent. These Chemical, Biological, Radiological, Nuclear Defense Specialists use scenarios like this to hone their speed, accuracy and decisiveness to defend against these types of hazards.

Welcome To The MEU Playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLnOwvB9zfF0zAw5ol1zIN-z-r8xP0nOB5

Film Credits: Cpl August Light, Cpl Abbey Perria

2259.description:
A U.S. Marine Corps Instructor from 2nd Low Altitude Air Defense Battalion (2nd LAAD) explains how to fire an FIM-92 Stinger missile. Members of the 2nd LAAD fire Stinger missiles at drone targets during training at Yuma Proving Ground in Arizona. 2nd LAAD uses Stinger surface-to-air missiles to provide close-in, low altitude air defense against enemy aircraft. The FIM-92 Stinger is an infrared homing surface-to-air missile (SAM), Man-Portable Air-Defense System (MANPADS). Filmed on March 27-28, 2015.

Film Credits: Cpl Waiyan Tin

2260.description:
U.S. Airborne elements of the 25th Infantry Division conduct a heavy-drop of paratroopers and 105mm howitzers followed by a live-fire exercise. The operation was part of Exercise Spartan Valkyrie at Malemute Drop Zone on Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson in Alaska. Filmed on March 20, 2015. Units - Spartan ‪Steel‬ Battalion, 377th Field Artillery, 4th Infantry Brigade Combat Team

Film Credits: SGT Eric-James Estrada

2261.description:
F-15C Eagle Fighter Jets from the 125th Fighter Wing are based at Jacksonville Air National Guard Base in Florida. The F-15C is a twin-engine, single seat, all-weather tactical fighter jet designed for air superiority. The F-15 Eagle is among the most successful modern fighters, having an air-to-air combat record of 104 kills to 0 losses as of February 2008.

Film Credits: MSgt Jaclyn Lyons

2262.description:
U.S. Soldiers from the 2d Cavalry Regiment (2nd Dragoons) train Latvian Soldiers on the operation and firing of M-777 Howitzers at Adazi Military Base in Latvia - part of Operation Summer Shield XII. Filmed March 24-29, 2015. 

Film Credits: SGT Toby Cook

2263.description:
1st Battalion, 503rd Infantry Regiment conducts live-fire training at Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany. The 503rd IR is part of the 173rd Airborne Brigade Combat Team based in Vicenza, Italy. Filmed March 18, 2015.

Film Credits: SSG Lisa Rodriguez Presley

2264.description:
National Museum of the U.S. Air Force footage of Bockscar, the name of the B-29 Superfortress bomber that the United States used to drop the atomic bomb, code named "Fat Man", over the Japanese city of Nagasaki on August 9, 1945. Fat Man was the second of only two nuclear weapons ever used in warfare, and it led to the unconditional surrender of Japan, ending the war in the Pacific during WWII. 

Film Credits: TSgt Nicholas Kurtz

2265.description:
U.S. Global Strike Command conducted test launches of two nuclear Minuteman III ICBMs (intercontinental ballistic missiles) as part of the missile systems testing and evaluation program on March 27, 2015. The unarmed test weapons were launched by the 30th Space Wing from Vandenberg Air Force Base in California, and traveled over 6000 miles to hit targets near the Island Of Guam in the South Pacific Ocean. GT214 and GT215 Test Launch.

Film Credits: TSgt Kurt Villavicencio, Michael Stonecypher, Captain Christopher Mesnard

2266.description:
UH-60 Black Hawk helicopter pilots from the Washington National Guard's 66th Theater Aviation Command (66th TAC) conduct deck landing qualification (DLQ) aboard the aircraft carrier USS John C. Stennis (CVN-74). DLQs are part of the 66th TAC's yearly qualifications. Pilots must complete multiple touchdown landings on the deck of a moving ship. Filmed on March 23, 2015.

Film Credits: SFC Jason Kriess

2267.description:
U.S. and Kuwaiti forces demonstrate an amphibious landing on Failaka Island in the Arabian Gulf. Highlights include Kuwaiti Rigid-Hulled Inflatable Boats, Kuwaiti AH-64D Apache Longbow and AS-332B Super Puma helicopters, U.S. Navy Landing Craft Air Cushion hovercrafts and U.S. Marine Amphibious Assault Vehicles from the USS Iwo Jima, and U.S. Navy F/A-18C Hornets from the aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson. This amphibious landing demo was filmed on March 25, 2015 as part of exercise Eagle Resolve 2015.

Film Credits: SSgt Kathryn Lozier

2268.description:
Spectacular GoPro footage of the U.S. Army Golden Knights parachute team as they free-fall though the sky. Considered by many to be the world's best parachute team, the Golden Knights have won more than 400 national championships and 60+ world championships. Stationed at Fort Bragg, North Carolina, Golden Knights members are drawn from US Army Paratroopers who have demonstrated excellence in parachuting skills. The 90 Soldiers that make up the team have all been trained in one of the Army's military occupational specialties and serve with the team for three years. 

Film Credits: http://www.goarmy.com/events/golden-knights.html

2269.description:
General Chuck Yeager, at the ripe old age of 89 years, boards an F-15 Eagle at Nellis AFB as part of an honor flight. The flight was conducted in recognition of the first manned supersonic flight, when Yeager broke the sound barrier in an experimental Bell X-1 aircraft on October 14, 1947. Filmed on October 14, 2012. 

Film Credits: SrA Cody Griffith, SrA Aaron Hauser, Todd Lane, William Lewis, SrA Rachel Maxwell, SSgt Jose Rodriguez

2270.description:
KC-130 extended-range air tankers conduct aerial refueling of F-35B Lightning II Joint Strike Fighters out of Marine Corps Air Station Beaufort, SC. Filmed on March 19, 2015. 

Film Credits: LCpl Courtney Kueker, Gunnery Sgt. Jeff Kaus

2271.description:
Daily training operations aboard the  Arleigh Burke-class guided missile destroyer USS Forrest Sherman (DDG-98) include... 5-inch gun live fire, flight deck helicopter operations, and a (VBSS) training evolution - visit, board, search and seizure. The Forrest Sherman, home-ported in Norfolk, Virginia is conducting naval operations in the U.S. 6th Fleet area of responsibility. Filmed on March 18, 2015.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy video by Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Taylor N. Stinson/Released

2272.description:
MV-22 Osprey tiltrotor aircraft with Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron (VMM-262), and AV-8B Harrier jets with Marine Attack Squadron (VMA-231), takeoff from the flight deck of the forward-deployed amphibious assault ship USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD 6). Filmed in the East China Sea on March 19, 2015.

Film Credits: MC2 Matthew Dickinson

2273.description:
United States F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 435th Air Ground Operations Wing fly over Romania with Romanian Mig-21 Lancers in exercise Dacian Warhawk. The NATO exercise was designed as a show of strength and cooperation between the two countries in light of heightened tensions with Russia. Filmed on March 18, 2015.

Film Credits: A1C Austin Siegel

2274.description:
Cockpit video of F-18 Super Hornet pilots as they conduct operations from the aircraft carrier USS Enterprise (CVN-65). Naval aviators with Strike Fighter Squadron 211 (VFA-211) "Fighting Checkmates" and Strike Fighter Squadron 11 (VFA-11) "Red Rippers" are filmed launching, landing, and flying over the Enterprise at high speed during deployments in 2011 and 2012.

Film Credits: (U.S. Navy video by Lt. Ian Schmidt) Released by Lt. j.g. Michael Hatfield, Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Jared King, U.S. Navy video/Released
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2275.description:
U.S. Army members of the 23rd Infantry Division "Tomahawks" take part in a combined arms live-fire exercise (CALFEX) at Joint Base Lewis-McChord, WA. Filmed on March 17, 2015. Units - Comanche Company, 1-23 Infantry

Film Credits: SSG Xaime Hernandez, SSG Justin Kuhl

2276.description:
U.S. Special Forces members work with Kuwaiti Special Forces during VBSS (visit, board, search and seizure) training - as part of exercise Eagle Resolve 2015 at the Kuwait Naval Station, Kuwait. A U.S. Army UH-60 aircrew from the 34th Combat Aviation Brigade helped to familiarize Kuwaiti forces with tactical loading and unloading of personnel. Filmed on March 10, 2015.

Film Credits: SSgt Kathryn Lozier

2277.description:
U.S. Marines conduct training at Marine Corps Mountain Warfare Training Center in Bridgeport, California to prepare for cold weather and extreme mountainous terrain. Filmed on January 17, 2015.  

Film Credits: Lance Cpl. Adam D. Edwards, Combat Camera, 2DMARDIV/Released

2278.description:
U.S. Air Force Special Tactics Airmen from the 24th Special Operations Wing (24 SOW) receive training on multiple heavy weapons systems on the Eglin Range in Florida. Filmed on March 13, 2015.  

Film Credits: SrA Nicholas Koetz

2279.description:
U.S. Navy hovercraft, officially designated LCAC (landing craft air cushion), conduct amphibious operations - transporting Marines and equipment between assault ships and the beachhead.  

Film Credits: Cpl Alexander Pool, WO Michael Kropiewnicki, Cpl James Skelton

2280.description:
SEAL Team 17 conducts a public demonstration of capabilities involving a helocast and an extraction by special warfare combatant-craft crewmen (SWCC). Filmed at Naval Base Coronado on March 7, 2015.   

Film Credits: Cpl Abbey Perria

2281.description: A U.S. Air Force KC-135 Stratotanker refuels Royal Canadian Air Force (RCAF) CF-188 Hornets in support of Operation Inherent Resolve. Filmed on March 4, 2015.

2282.description:
Aircraft Carriers FS Charles de Gualle (R91) and USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70) transit the Northern Arabian Gulf in support of strike operations on ISIS in Iraq and Syria. Filmed on March 8, 2015.  

Film Credits: MC2 Samuel LeCain

2283.description:
U.S. Marines with the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit (31st MEU) conduct ship-to-shore operations using Assault Amphibious Vehicles (AAV) deployed from USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6) - as part of exercise Spring Patrol 2015 at Okinawa, Japan. Filmed February 21, 2015.  

Film Credits: Cpl Abbey Perria

2284.description:
Members of the U.S. Air Force 38th Rescue Squadron (38 RQS) execute a jump from an HH-60 Pave Hawk helicopter. GoPro footage filmed on March 5, 2015 - out of Moody AFB - https://www.youtube.com/user/MoodyAFB1 

Film Credits: Maj Joseph Barnard, Maj David Depiazza, SMSgt Brendan Deligio, SrA Braden Anderson

2285.description:
A C-17 Globemaster takes-off and lands at night from Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson in Alaska. Filmed on February 2, 2015. 

Film Credits: SrA Carly Kavish, SrA Sarah Trachte

2286.description:
The littoral combat ship USS Fort Worth (LCS-3) transits the East China Sea on course for South Korea to participate in the annual U.S. - Republic of Korea Foal Eagle exercise. Filmed March 1, 2015. 

Film Credits: PO2 Conor Minto

2287.description:
C-17 Globemaster III transport planes takeoff and land at Nellis Air Force Base In Nevada. The C-17 is a large military cargo plane used by the U.S. Air Force. Capable of carrying an M1 Abrams Tank, the C-17 is large and powerful... and yet it possesses a grace and beauty which is undeniable, especially on takeoffs and landings. Check it out.

Film Credits: SrA Thomas Smith, SrA Aaron Hauser

2288.description:
U.S. Air Force aerial refueling operation: An HC-130P Combat King refuels HH-60 Pave Hawk helicopters inflight during a training mission out of Djibouti, Africa. Filmed December 8, 2014. Units - 81st ERQS and 303rd ERQS

Film Credits: SrA Thomas Smith

2289.description:
A KC-130J Hercules refuels two MV-22B Ospreys inflight during a training mission over the Atlantic Ocean. U.S. Marines with Special-Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force Crisis Response-Africa (SPMAGTF-CR-AF) completed the aerial refueling exercise with aircraft out of Morón Air Base, Spain on February 25, 2015.

Film Credits: Sgt Paul Peterson

2290.description:
A short profile of the B-1B Lancer strategic bomber, plus clips of night and day takeoffs at Al Udeid Air Base in Qatar, followed by a clip of the aircraft during aerial refueling.

Film Credits: A1C Jean-marc Betreaud, SSgt Mariko Frazee, A1C Eric Mann

2291.description:
Flight line air crews perform End Of Runway (EOR) checks on F-16 Fighting Falcons at the Combat Readiness Training Center in Savannah, GA. The EOR checkpoint is the final preflight inspection before the aircraft is cleared for takeoff. Filmed on February 11, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Justin Hodge

2292.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a qualification shooting range with the Beretta M9, a 9mm Parabellum pistol in use by the U.S. Military since 1985. Marines with Special-Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force Crisis Response-Africa (SPMAGTF-CR-AF) shoot M9 firearms at Morón Air Base in Spain on February 18, 2015. 

Film Credits: Sgt Paul Peterson

2293.description:
U.S. Air Force Para Jumpers (PJ) are elite special operations combat forces tasked with locating and recovering downed airmen in any environment. Air Force Pararescuemen undergo some of the most rigorous training of any of the special operations forces in the U.S. military, with about an 80% attrition rate in the almost two year training pipeline. During "the Pipeline", Pararescuemen must also complete a 22 week Pararescue EMT-Paramedic Training course, which gives them a National Registry of Emergency Medical Technicians-Paramedic (NREMT-P) certification.

Film Credits: MSgt Pedro Jimenez, SrA Braden Anderson, SrA John Pharr, SSgt Zach Vaughn, TSgt Amanda Helton

2294.description:
U.S. Army 25th Infantry Division soldiers conduct jungle operations, air assault and field exercises. The headquarters of the 25th ID is Schofield Barracks, Wahiawa, Hawaii. 

Film Credits: SGT Vanessa Atchley

2295.description:
U.S. Army Airborne paratroopers jump over the Deadhorse drop zone in Northern Alaska as part of exercise Spartan Pegasus 2015. Spartan Pegasus ensures the U.S. Army has the capability to operate in extreme Arctic conditions. 

Film Credits: A1C Carly Kavish, SrA Sarah Trachte

2296.description:
A KC-135 Stratotanker from the 185th Airlift Wing refuels an F-22 Raptor from Tydall Air Force Base inflight during exercise Sentry Savannah 15-1. Filmed on February 13, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Justin Hodge

2297.description:
U.S. Marines conduct an urban assault training exercise at Yodaville near Yuma, AZ. Close Air Support (CAS) was provided by AH-6 Little Bird "Killer Egg" and AH-1 SuperCobra helicopters. 

Film Credits: Cpl Brandon Ponyah, LCpl Jacob Krummel

2298.description:
F-16 Falcon fighter jets and T-38 Talon trainers takeoff during Sentry Savannah at the Georgia Air National Guard's Air Dominance Center in Savannah, GA. More than 1400 service members from the Air National Guard, Air Force and Marines participated in the two week exercise. Filmed February 2015. 

Film Credits: MSgt Jon LaDue, SrA Justin Hodge

2299.description:
Clip One - U.S. Marines conduct a combat marksmanship range at Camp Leatherneck, Helmand Province, Afghanistan, March 21, 2013. Clip Two - Marines conduct combat marksmanship drills at Morón Air Base, Spain, August 19, 2014. Clip Three -  Marines conduct a live-fire range with M1014 Shotguns at Basa Air Base, Pampanga, Philippines on October 7, 2014.

Film Credits: Cpl William Kresse, LCpl Andre Dakis, Cpl Alexander Pool

2300.description:
Day and night footage of F-22 Raptors during Red Flag 15-1. Red Flag is an advanced combat training operation held annually at Nellis Air Force Base near Las Vegas, NV. Red Flag 15-2 is scheduled for March 2 - March 13, 2015. Units - 1st Fighter Wing, 94th Fighter Squadron, 192nd Fighter Wing

Film Credits: SrA Cody Griffith, SrA Aaron Hauser, William Lewis, A1C Taylor West

2301.description:
A-10 Thunderbolt "Warthogs" fly close air support during a Combat Search and Rescue (CSAR) training exercise near Davis-Monthan Air Force Base in Arizona. CSAR operations are designed to locate and recover downed pilots in a combat zone.  Filmed February 7, 2015.

Film Credits: MSgt Sonia Pawloski

2302.description:
Aerial drone footage of Combat Camera Quick Shot 2015, a range exercise designed to sharpen small arms shooting skills of Combat Camera Service Members in a hostile environment. Filmed from February 13-17, 2015 in the Angeles National Forest, CA.

Film Credits: PO1 Daniel Gay

2303.description:
U.S. Marines with the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU) conduct a live-fire integrated assault exercise at Bradshaw Field Training Area in Australia. The Marines used a variety of weapons systems including 120mm mortars, M777A2 howitzers, LAV-25 light armored vehicles, SMAW-II rockets, M240G medium machine guns and Browning .50 caliber machine guns. MV-22 Ospreys airlifted Marines in a vertical assault from the USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6), more than 300 miles away. 

The 31st MEU played a major role in Operation Phantom Fury (2004) - the clearing of Fallujah in Iraq. Hypothetically, if the 31st MEU where combined with U.S. air power, they would probably have little trouble defeating any force ISIS could mount against them on the battlefield.

Film Credits: Sgt Jonathan Wright

2304.description:
A U.S. Army and U.S. Air Force training exercise with Army Howitzers firing while USAF Joint Terminal Attack Controllers (JTAC) call in A-10 Thunderbolts to flying close air support. Units - 2nd Battalion, 12th Field Artillery Regiment, 1st Stryker Brigade Combat Team, 4th Infantry Division and the 66th Weapons Squadron, United States Air Force Weapons School, Nellis AFB

Film Credits: SGT Meghan Berry

2305.description:
Watch day and night footage of various military aircraft during Red Flag 15-1 advanced aerial combat training at Nellis Air Force Base in Nevada. Red Flag 15-1 operations came to an end on February 13th, with Red Flag 15-2 scheduled for March 2nd to 13th. 

Film Credits: William Lewis, SSgt Annemarie Stella, A1C Taylor West

2306.description:
U.S. Navy F-18 aircraft are refueled in flight by a KC-135 Stratotanker during strike operations on ISIS targets in Syria on Sept 23, 2014. 

Film Credits: MSgt Michael Garza

2307.description:
The 2nd Infantry Division is the last remaining permanently forward-stationed division in the US Army. The 2nd ID mission is to deter aggression and maintain peace on the Korean Peninsula; and if deterrence fails, "Fight Tonight" in support of the US-Republic of Korea Alliance.

Film Credits: Songho Yun

2308.description:
Scenic aerial footage filmed aboard an MH-60S Sea Hawk helicopter from Helicopter Sea Combat Squadron Eight (HSC-8) "Eightballers" as it conducts a familiarization flight over San Diego, CA on February 10, 2015. 
         
Film Credits: PO1 Shannon Renfroe

2309.description:
Footage from the cockpit of a T-38 Talon Training Jet during Operation Sentry Savannah 15-1. Filmed February 13, 2015.
         
Film Credits: MSgt Jon LaDue

2310.description:
U.S. F-22 Raptors are refueled in flight by a KC-135 Stratotanker during a strike mission to hit a Vehicle Borne Improvised Explosive Device factory (VBIED) in Iraq on January 30, 2015.
         
Film Credits: A1C Eric Mann

2311.description:
Twelve A-10 Thunderbolts from the 355th Fighter Wing, Davis-Monthan AFB land at Lajes Field on Terceira Island in the Azores. The A-10s are enroute to Operation Atlantic Resolve in Europe. Lajes Field is used as a stop-over point for support by United States and NATO aircraft. Filmed February 11, 2015.
         
Film Credits: SrA Armando Aparicio

2312.description:
A B-52H Stratofortress from the 20th Bomb Squadron completes a training mission out of Anderson Air Force Base, Guam. Footage includes cockpit video and pilot communications during weapons drop and landing. The 20th Bomb Squadron is stationed at Barksdale AFB, LA.          

Film Credits: TSgt Jeremy Zier

2313.description:
Aircraft assigned to Carrier Air Wing 17 conduct flight operations aboard the aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70). The Carl Vinson Strike Group is deployed to the U.S. 5th fleet area of responsibility, in support of airstrikes on ISIS in Iraq and Syria. Filmed February 11, 2015.         

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video/Released

2314.description:
A squadron of F-22A Raptors from the U.S. Air Force 3rd Wing go through preflight checks before takeoff at Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson in Alaska.          

Film Credits: SrA Ross Whitley, SrA Sarah Trachte
Photo: http://www.jber.af.mil/shared/media/photodb/photos/071122-F-ZY202-005.jpg

2315.description:
AV-8B Harriers assigned to Marine Attack Squadron VMA-231 takeoff and land aboard USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD 6), which is currently deployed in the U.S. 7th Fleet area of responsibility with Marines from the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU). Filmed Janurary 28, 2015.         

Film Credits: Lance Cpl. Tyler Ngiraswei

2316.description:
AH-1W Super Cobras and CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters land and takeoff aboard the amphibious assault ship USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD 6). Bonhomme Richard is currently deployed in the U.S. 7th Fleet area of responsibility with Marines from the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU). The Super Cobra and Super Stallion helicopters are assigned to Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 262 (VMM-262). Filmed Janurary 31, 2015.         

Film Credits: Cpl. Abbey Perria

2317.description:
F-15, F-16, and F-18 fighter jets take off at night. Red Flag 15-1 advanced aerial combat training started January 26th and will continue until February 13th at Nellis Air Force Base near Las Vegas. Filmed February 3, 2015.         

Film Credits: TSgt Anthony Kuhn, William Lewis, A1C Rebecca Long, A1C Taylor West

2318.description:
U.S. Army Troopers from the 2nd Cavalry Regiment conduct a fire mission training exercise with M777 Howitzers at Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany. Filmed on January 28, 2015.         

Film Credits: Gertrud Zach

2319.description:
MH-60S Sea Hawk helicopters transfer ordnance from the USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) to the USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN-71) while underway. George H.W. Bush and Theodore Roosevelt are conducting training exercises in the Atlantic Ocean. Filmed February 5, 2015.    

Film Credits: Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Bounome Chanphouang

2320.description:
U.S. Marine Corps crew chiefs aboard UH-1Y Venom helicopters perform door gunner duties during close air support training operations at Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range in California. There is no specific Military Occupational Specialty (MOS) for "door gunner" in the Marine Corps. The MOS for UH-1 helicopter crew chief is 6174.      

Film Credits: Sgt Richard Tetreau, Sgt Robert Brown, LCpl Jacob Krummel

2321.description:
U.S. nuclear submarines arrive and depart Pearl Harbor Naval Base - USS Columbus (SSN-762), USS Santa Fe (SSN-763), and USS Cheyenne (SSN-773).      

Film Credits: PO1 Jason Swink

2322.description:
U.S. and Latvian Soldiers fire the Javelin portable anti-tank missile in a joint training exercise at Camp Adazi, Latvia. Filmed on February 6, 2015.      

Film Credits: SGT Kyle Burns

2323.description:
F-16 Block 52 Fighting Falcons taxi, takeoff, and land at McEntire Joint National Guard Base in South Carolina. The fighter jets are part of the 169th Fighter Wing, nicknamed the "Swamp Foxes".     

Film Credits: SMSgt Edward Snyder

2324.description:
Aerial footage of three airstrikes by Jordanian planes as they drop bombs on ISIS targets in Syria. Jordan's King Abdullah vowed swift revenge after it was confirmed ISIS killed a Jordanian pilot it had captured. The airstrikes came just two days after a video was released by ISIS showing the Jordanian pilot being brutally murdered. Filmed February 5, 2015.     

Film Credits: Released by U.S. DOD

2325.description:
Marines conduct mechanized assault combat training in Assault Amphibious Vehicles (AAVs), Enhanced Armament Carriers (Humvees), and M1A1 Abrams Battle Tanks. The live-fire exercises were held at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms, CA.      

Film Credits: LCpl Jonathan Boynes, Cpl Joseph Peterson      
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2326.description:
Flight deck operations aboard the aircraft carrier USS Enterprise (CVN-65), with scenes including F-18 Super Hornet and E-2C Hawkeye aircraft. Plus, pilot in-flight cockpit video. The USS Enterprise was inactivated on December 1, 2012.

Film Credits: Mass Communication Specialist Aaron Chase

2327.description:
French Marines instruct U.S. Marines on the operation and firing of the Belgium FN Minimi machine gun and the French FAMAS G2 assualt rifle at Camp Le Cocq, Ferrous, France.   

Film Credits: GySgt Cruz Sotelo

2328.description:
Four platoons of U.S. Marines complete an integrated live-fire combat exercise at Twentynine Palms, California. The training incorporated artillery support units, helicopter close air support, and anti-tank rockets. Filmed May, 2013. Units - Combat Logistics Battalion 6, 2nd Marine Logistics Group, based out of Camp Lejeune, NC.

Film Credits: Sgt Paul Peterson

2329.description:
U.S. Soldiers from the 4th Brigade Combat Team, 101st Airborne Division conduct walk and shoot training at Fort Campbell, Kentucky. The 4th BCT, nicknamed "Currahee" a Native American Cherokee word which means "stands alone", was officially disbanded and inactivated on April, 25, 2014.

Film Credits: SGT Bradley Parrish

2330.description:
An ice rescue crew from U.S. Coast Guard Station Frankfort, Michigan rescues a dog from the icy waters of Lake Michigan on February 2, 2015.

Film Credits: Video courtesy of Oliver Art Center

2331.description:
Red Flag 15-1 began on January 26th, 2015 - marking the 40th Anniversary of the air combat simulation exercise held at Nellis Air Force Base in Nevada. Footage of various military aircraft on the flight line, taxis, takeoff, and landing at Nellis AFB. Filmed January 28-29, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Cody Griffith, SSgt Annemarie Stella, William Lewis, Lea Greene

2332.description:
U.S. Marine Corps AV-8B Harrier aircraft from Marine Attack Squadron 231 (VMA-231) takeoff and land aboard the USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6), deployed in the East China Sea. Filmed on January 30, 2015. 

Film Credits: PO2 Matthew Dickinson

2333.description:
The USS Enterprise (CVN-65) transits the Suez Canal in April of 2012. The Suez Canal is approximately 120 miles long, 79 feet deep, and typically it takes a ship 12 to 16 hours to transit. Under international treaty, the Suez Canal may be used "in time of war as in time of peace, by every vessel of commerce or of war, without distinction of flag."

Film Credits: PO3 Jacob Galito

2334.description:
U.S. Marines and Canadian Forces are transported by CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters during a battle drill at the Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range near Marine Corps Air Station in Yuma, AZ. Footage includes cockpit video and POV video looking out over the back machine gun. 

Film Credits: Sgt Richard Tetreau

2335.description:
U.S. Marines with Marine Aviation Weapons and Tactics Squadron One (MAWTS-1) conduct a large scale live-fire night raid exercise on the Yuma Training Range Complex in Arizona. 

Film Credits: Aaron Shortt

2336.description:
U.S. Air Force F-15E Strike Eagles from the 4th Fighter Wing taxi and takeoff at Seymour Johnson Air Force Base in North Carolina.

Film Credits: SrA Victoria Fleck

2337.description:
Two Clips: Clip One - U.S. Marines with Battalion Landing Team, 1st Battalion, 6th Marine Regiment, 22nd Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU), conduct a shooting range from the starboard aircraft elevator aboard the USS Bataan (LHD 5) on Febuary 18, 2014. Clip Two - Marines with the Maritime Raid Force, 11th Marine Expeditionary Unit, conduct a table two and three course of fire on an air cargo elevator aboard the USS Makin Island (LHD-8) on April 10, 2014.

Film Credits: Cpl Joshua Rudy, Cpl Evan White

2338.description:
U.S. Air Force and U.S. Army personnel conduct a joint Combat Search and Rescue Training exercise (CSAR) at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base, AZ on January 20, 2015.

Film Credits: SrA Austin Willhoit

2339.description:
The C-5 Galaxy is among the largest military aircraft in the world. It provides the United States Air Force (USAF) with a heavy intercontinental strategic airlift capability, and has been operated by the USAF since 1969. The fuel load weighs 332,500 pounds, allowing the C-5 with a load of 204,904 pounds to fly 2,150 nautical miles, offload, and fly to a second base 500 nautical miles away from the original destination - all without aerial refueling. The C-5 has been used to support U.S. military operations in all major conflicts including Vietnam, Iraq, Yugoslavia and Afghanistan.

Film Credits: MSgt Emily Beightol-Deyerle, MSgt Pedro Jimenez, TSgt Kevin Coulter, TSgt Matt Hecht, SSgt Joseph Vigil

2340.description:
U.S. Coast Guard video shows a single engine Cirrus SR22 airplane running out of fuel 250 miles northeast of Maui, HI. The pilot was able to successfully deploy the aircraft's airframe parachute system and ditch the plane into the ocean. The pilot was rescued by a lifeboat from a nearby cruise ship. Filmed January 25, 2015. 

Film Credits: CPO Kurt Fredrickson, PO2 Tara Molle

2341.description:
U.S. Marines conduct an external lift training exercise with a MV-22 Osprey, attaching a 2180 lb pallet of supplies to the Osprey at Morón Air Base, Spain on January 19, 2015. Units - Special Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force Crisis Response (SP-MAGTF), Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 264 (VMM-264)  

Film Credits: Sgt Paul Peterson

2342.description:
An in-depth look at how U.S. Army Apache Block III helicopters can be teamed with unmanned aerial systems (UAS) on the battlefield. 

Film Credits: DOD Video Released/Recon: Game Changer

2343.description:
Military video news magazine featuring the F-35 Lightning II Helmet Mounted Display System and simulator. Filmed September 9, 2014.

Film Credit: Cpl Clayton Filipowicz

2344.description:
The Super Guppy is a cargo plane used to transport oversized components for NASA. Scenes include the Super Guppy landing at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base in Ohio, and cockpit footage while in flight. This flight took place on August 22, 2012 between Ellington Field, Texas and Wright-Patterson Air Force Base, Ohio - a four hour flight at 250 mph and an altitude of 12,000 feet. The Super Guppy was transporting a Crew Compartment Trainer for the Space Shuttle to the National Museum of the United States Air Force.

Film Credits: Matthew Clouse

2345.description:
KC-135 Stratotanker pilots practice touch-and-go landings (aka circuit) at Hill Air Force Base In Utah. Unit- 191st Air Refueling Squadron, Utah Air National Guard 

Film Credit: SSgt Roidan Carlson

2346.description:
U.S. Marines fire AT4 Shoulder Fired Rockets and M27 Infantry Automatic Rifles during training courses at Marine Corps Combat Center Twentynine Palms, CA on February 20, 2015. Units - Fox Company, 2nd Battalion 3rd Marine Regiment  

Film Credits: LCpl Victor Mancilla

2347.description:
OC Spray, otherwise known as oleoresin capsicum or pepper spray, is a non-lethal weapon designed to target the eyes and is used in riot control. U.S. Marines and Bulgarian Soldiers take the spray in the face to gain a first-hand account of what was apparently a very painful training day at Platinum Lion 15 in Bulgaria. Filmed January 20, 2015.   

Film Credits: LCpl Boston Berg, Sgt Russell Midori, LCpl Ryan Young

2348.description:
Welcome to the Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU): Describes the helicopter water egress simulator, and piloting the MV-22 Osprey.   

Film Credits: LCpl Tyler Ngiraswei, Cpl Abbey Perria

2349.description:
U.S. Marines Corps crew chiefs perform preflight maintenance and checks, and load CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters with equipment and personnel at Marine Corps Air Station Miramar, CA in support of Integrated Training Exercise (ITX) on January 18, 2015. ITX is a month-long exercise during which Marines conduct extensive training to ensure combat readiness for future deployment. Units - Marine Heavy Helicopter Squadron 462, Marine Aircraft Group 16, 3rd Marine Aircraft Wing

Film Credits: LCpl Jessica Lucio

2350.description:
Paratroopers from the 173rd Airborne Brigade jump from C-130 Hercules aircraft with T-11 parachutes over Juliet Drop Zone in Pordenone, Italy, January 13, 2015. The C-130 Hercules aircraft of the 86th Airlift Wing are stationed at Ramstein Air Base, Germany.   

Film Credits: Visual Information Specialist Antonio Bedin

2351.description:
The 4th Special Operations Squadron (4th SOS), nicknamed the Ghostriders, operates AC-130U Spooky II aircraft providing close air support, armed reconnaissance, interdiction missions, and special operations capabilities worldwide. The 4th SOS has been flying combat missions since the Vietnam War and is currently stationed at Hurlburt Field, Florida.  

Film Credits: SSgt Jeff Curtin

2352.description:
Footage of 1A9X1 Special Missions Aviation Airmen during preflight, ammo loading, and live fire training aboard an AC-130U Spooky Gunship at aerial gunnery range, Eglin Air Force Base, FL. The Spooky is equipped with a 105mm cannon, 40mm cannon, and a 25mm Gatling gun. Plus, it is equipped with sophisticated sensor, navigation and fire control systems to provide surgical firepower or area saturation during extended loiter periods, at night and in adverse weather. The sensor suite consists of a television sensor, infrared sensor and radar. These sensors allow the gunship to visually or electronically identify friendly ground forces and targets any place, any time. The Spooky Gunship has a crew of pilot, co-pilot, navigator, fire control officer, and electronic warfare officer (five officers) - flight engineer, TV operator, infrared detection set operator, loadmaster, and four aerial gunners (eight enlisted). 

Film Credits: SrA Stephen Ellis, SrA Brandi Hansen

2353.description:
U.S. Navy Seabee divers assigned to Underwater Construction Team One (UCT ONE) and Underwater Construction Team Two (UCT TWO) conduct surface supplied operations using Kirby Morgan 37 dive helmets during diver training aboard USAV Matamoros (LCU-2026). Diver training is a two-week, joint training evolution between UCT ONE and UCT TWO designed to reinforce standard operating procedures, qualify personnel, maintain proficiency, and evaluate dive protocol during scuba, surface supplied and recompression chamber operations. Filmed January 18, 2015.  

Film and Image Credits: PO2 Nicholas Tenorio, PO3 Tyler Thompson

2354.description:
Footage of Operation Golden Eagle, the first brigade sized Air Assault Training Operation completed at Fort Campbell, KY in more than a decade. Units included the 3rd Brigade Combat Team and 101st Combat Aviation Brigade, 101st Airborne Division. The exercise included over 1000 soldiers. Filmed April, 2014.  

Film Credits: SGT Joshua Dwyer

2355.description:
Marines with 2nd Battalion, 7th Marine Regiment sharpen their marksmanship skills with the M4 Carbine and the M16A4 rifles. The FN M16A4, using safe/semi/burst selective fire, is now the standard issue for all U.S. Marine Corps, with the M4A1 now being planned as the replacement rifle for most units in the U.S. military.  The M4A1 is used by almost all U.S special operation units including Marine Force Recon, Army Rangers, Army Special Forces, Navy SEALs, United States Air Force Pararescue and Air Force Combat Control Teams. The M4 is a shorter and lighter variant of the M16A2 assault rifle. It is a gas-operated, magazine-fed, selective fire, shoulder-fired weapon with a telescoping stock and 14.5 in barrel to better serve in close quarters combat. Just like the M16, the M4 fires a .223 caliber, or 5.56 mm NATO round. Filmed January 7, 2015.

Film Credits: Cpl William Perkins

2356.description:
Patrol Boats from Riverine Squadron 2 (RIVRON 2) provide port and harbor security at Naval Station Norfolk in Virginia, escorting the USS San Antonio (LPD-17) and the USS Oak Hill (LSD-51) as they depart for deployment. 

Film Credits: CPO Leah Stiles

2357.description:
Aerial refueling from a United States KC-135 Stratotanker to an Israeli AC-130 Hercules in U.S. airspace. Units - 186th Air Refueling Wing, Mississippi Air National Guard (USAF) - 131st Air Squadron, Israel 

Film Credits: Michelle Revoir

2358.description:
Two clips demonstrating the close air support power of A-10 Thunderbolt "Warthog" strike aircraft. 1st clip - 107th Fighter Squadron A-10s fly close air support training missions at the Grayling Air Gunnery Range in northern Michigan. 2nd clip - U.S. Marine Corps warrant officers watch a close air support demonstration by two A-10 Thunderbolt II aircraft during the Warrant Officer Basic Course at Camp Barrett, VA. Filmed April 11 and April 16, 2014.  

Film Credits: TSgt Rachel Barton, WO Michael Kropiewnicki

2359.description:
A U.S. Coast Guard MH-65 Rescue Helicopter from Air Station Los Angeles conducts rescue hoist training with Los Angeles County Fire Department Baywatch Lifeguards and Divers. The TV series "Baywatch" was loosely based on this unit.

Film Credits:  PO2 Prentice Danner, PO1 Adam Eggers

2360.description:
U.S. Army Paratroopers from the 173rd Airborne Brigade complete squad live fire training in Tapa, Estonia on June 6, 2014. Unit - Company C, 2nd Battalion, 503rd Infantry regiment  

Film Credits: SPC Jared Sollars

2361.description:
B-52 Stratofortress air crews conduct a training mission including aerial refueling and a live weapons drop. Footage includes bomb preflight and aerial refueling with the 96th Bomb Squadron at Barksdale Air Force Base in LA, aerial refueling with a Utah Air National Guard KC-135 and B-52s out of Minot Air Force Base, and battle station footage of a B-52 out of Barksdale AFB.  

Film Credits: TSgt David Clark, MSgt Jason Wilkerson, SrA Anthony Gamez
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2362.description:
Sailors fire a .50-caliber machine gun aboard the amphibious assault ship USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6) during a training exercise on January 13, 2015. The Bonhomme Richard is currently underway conducting operations in the U.S. 7th Fleet area of responsibility.

Film Credits: PO2 Matthew Dickinson

2363.description:
U.S. Marines fire the M41A4 Saber and the FGM-148 Javelin missile launchers during a live-fire training exercise at Marine Corps Base Camp Lejeune, NC on January 6, 2015. Unit - 2nd Battalion, 8th Marine Regiment, 2nd Marine Division

Film Credits: Sgt S.T. Stewart

2364.description:
Flight line operations of F-16 fighter jets and air crews at Atlantic City Air National Guard Base. The air base operates out of Atlantic City International Airport, a joint civil-military airport in Egg Harbor Township, NJ - home of the 177th Fighter Wing "Jersey Devils" of the New Jersey Air National Guard.

Film Credits: TSgt Matt Hecht, MSgt Andrew Moseley

2365.description:
U.S. Air Force KC-135 pilots execute a FAA Practical Test, commonly called a "Checkride". The checkride is a Federal Aviation Administration test that pilots must undergo to receive an aircraft pilot's certification for additional flight privileges. Utah Air National Guard members of the 191st Air Refueling Squadron practice touch and go's at Hill Air Force Base.

Film Credits: SSgt Erin Mills

2366.description:
U.S. Marines conduct live-fire training exercises at the Novo Selo Training Area in Bulgaria on January 7-8, 2015. The operations were held to increase military effectiveness for the Black Sea Rotational Force (BSRF) 14. Unit - 2nd Battalion, 2nd Marine Regiment, 2nd Marine Division

Film Credits: LCpl Boston Berg

2367.description:
U.S. Marines conduct external lift training with CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters at Marine Corps Air Station Cherry Point, NC on January 7, 2015. Units - Marine Heavy Helicopter Squadron 366 and Combat Logistics Battalion 22

Film Credits: Cpl Gregory Boyd

2368.description:
The guided-missile frigate USS Kauffman (FFG-59) departs Naval Station Norfolk for its final deployment and will operate in the U.S. 4th Fleet area of responsibility. Kauffman's final deployment also marks the last scheduled deployment by any Oliver Hazard Perry-Class frigate, and in September 2015 the ship will be the last operationally-active frigate to be decommission. A typical Navy deployment on ship could be as long as 8 months, with some being extended even longer due to world events. Filmed on January 9, 2015.

Film Credits: CPO Karen Cozza

2369.description:
The Virginia-class fast attack nuclear submarine USS Mississippi (SSN-782) departs Pearl Harbor Naval Base for a routine deployment on January 5, 2014. 

Film Credits: PO1 Jason Swink

2370.description:
A U.S. Navy MH-60R Seahawk helicopter flies over the USS Fort Worth (LCS-3) and a group of multinational naval vessels during search operations at the location of the tail section of Air Asia QZ8501. 

Film Credits: PO2 Antonio Turretto Ramos

2371.description:
The Advanced Denial System (ADS) is a focused beam of electromagnetic radiation that heats human skin painfully in order to disperse targeted individuals. The Solid State Active Denial Technology (SS-ADT) is a mobile system being developed by the U.S. Army to be deployed on vehicles.

Film Credits: Sgt Justin Boling, Cpl Clayton Filipowicz, SGT Brittany Fogel

2372.description:
M1A1 Abrams tanks firing 120mm smoothbore cannons and .50 caliber machine guns. Video includes point-of-view footage inside the tank's crew compartment as the guns are firing. Unit - Battalion Landing Team 2nd Battalion, 1st Marines, 11th Marine Expeditionary Unit

Film Credits: GySgt Rome Lazarus

2373.description:
Navy Divers from USS Fort Worth (LCS-3) assist with the search for Air Asia Flight QZ8501 by deploying a Tow Fish side scan sonar system from Fort Worth’s 11-meter rigid hull inflatable boat. Fort Worth is currently on station and supporting Indonesian-led search efforts to locate Air Asia Flight QZ8501. Filmed January 4, 2014. Diving Unit - Mobile Diving and Salvage Unit (MDSU) 1 

Film Credits: PO2 Antonio Turretto Ramos

2374.description:
Scenes from inside the M109A6 Paladin howitzer during live-fire operation. The Paladin has 4 crew members: Commander, Driver, Gunner and Loader. It can travel at a maximum speed of 40mph, and can be fired in less than 60 seconds after it comes to a stop. The Paladin self-propelled howitzer has a firing range of 24 km using unassisted rounds or 30 km using assisted rounds. But some Paladins have been upgraded to fire the Excalibur GPS/extended-range projectile, which has a range of 40 km with an accuracy of 10 m. The Excalibur round was first deployed to Afghanistan in 2008. 

Film Credits: SSG Noel Gerig, SGT Linsey Williams, SGT Lawren Massey, SSG John Higgins
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2375.description:
Airmen from the 22nd Special Tactics Squadron conduct a HALO jump (High Altitude Low Opening) above Hurlburt Field, FL.

Film Credits: SrA Michelle Di Ciolli

2376.description:
A United States Air Force KC-135 Stratotanker refuels Italian AMX attack jets in the skies over Afghanistan in August, 2012.

Film Credits: SSgt Michelle Revoir

2377.description:
U-2 pilots from the 9th Reconnaissance Wing learn bodyflight techniques in the vertical wind tunnel at Beale Air Force Base in California. Bodyflight is a skill needed for skydivers to control their bodies during free fall. Filmed October 3, 2014.

Film Credits: A1C Benjamin Bugenig

2378.description:
U.S. Navy Sailors assigned to Coastal Riverine Squadron Four (CORIVRON 4) maneuver through intracoastal waterways in their 34-foot Dauntless Sea Ark Patrol Boats during Exercise Bold Alligator 2014. Filmed October 30 - November 1, 2014.

Film Credits: CPO Larry Baruwa

2379.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a Forward Arming and Refueling Point exercise (FARP) at Marine Air Ground Task Force Training Center, Twentynine Palms, CA. Filmed in October of 2014. Units - Marine Wing Support Squadron 372 (MWSS-372), 3rd Marine Aircraft Wing (MAG-39)

Film Credits: LCpl Jordan Walker

2380.description:
The amphibious assault ship USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6) completes an underway replenishment (UNREP) in the East China Sea. Connected Replenishment (CONREP) involves rigging a cable between ships and sending supplies over a tensioned wire using a system of pulleys. Vertical Replenishment (VERTREP) is the transfer of cargo between ships using helicopters. UNREP filmed with USNS Wally Schirra (T-AKE) in April, 2014.

Film Credits: Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Christian Senyk

2381.description:
Day and night footage. Strike aircraft takeoff and land aboard the aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70) during Operation Inherent Resolve. Day footage filmed October 27, 2014. Night footage filmed December 31, 2014. 

Film Credits: Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class James Guthrie

2382.description:
Alaska Air National Guard conducts jump and hoist training near Mount Susitna on December 16, 2014. Guardian Angels from the 212th Rescue Squadron jumped from a HC-130 “King” aircraft and a HH-60 Pave Hawk helicopter. Units - 210th, 211th and 212th Rescue Squadrons  

Film Credits: SGT Balinda O'Neal

2383.description:
F-15 Eagles from 18th Wing,  Kadena Air Base, Okinawa, Japan conduct an air combat maneuver training mission near the Island of Guam. Filmed from the cockpit.  

Film Credits: SSgt Michelle Revoir

2384.description:
Aerial refueling clips in order of appearance: A-10 Thunderbolt II, B-1 Lancer, B-2 Spirit, B-52 Stratofortress, F-15 Eagle, F-16 Falcon, F-22 Raptor, and F-35 Lightning II.

Film Credits: MSgt Pedro Jimenez, MSgt Jason Wilkerson, SSgt Jose Rodriguez, SSgt Roidan Carlson, SrA Jarrod Vickers, SrA Laura Yahemiak, SrA Rachel Maxwell
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2385.description:
U.S. Coast Guard and Dominican sailors fire the Browning M2 machine gun at a weapons gunnery exercise, plus U.S. Navy crew members (USS Bonhomme Richard LHD-6) train with the .50 cal while on deployment.

Film Credits: PO1 Paul Seeber, LT Desiree Frame

2386.description:
Two clips - 1st clip shows a CV-22 Osprey being refueled in flight by a C-130 Hercules. 2nd clip shows a CV-22 landing with split screen video.

Film Credits: SrA Laura Yahemiak, Ken LaRock

2387.description:
The Crucible is the final test of a Marine recruit at boot camp, and is the culmination of all of the skills and knowledge a Marine should possess. The Crucible is a rigorous 54-hour field training exercise that includes a total of 48 miles of marching, team and individual obstacle courses, day and night assault courses, land navigation courses, individual rushes up steep hills, large-scale martial arts challenges, and countless patrols to and from each of these. It simulates typical combat situations with strenuous testing, hardship, and the deprivation of food and sleep. A recruit is given 3 MREs (meal ready-to-eat) and eight hours of sleep through the entire 54-hour event. Filmed April, 2014 at Parris Island Marine Corps Recruit Depot.

Film Credits: Cpl Nathan McKitrick, Lance Cpl. Merenzi T. Shaw

2388.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a quick reaction force exercise aboard Marine Corps Base Camp Lejeune, NC on December 17, 2014. Fox Company, 2nd Battalion, 8th Marine Regiment, 2nd Marine Division, are preparing for an upcoming deployment with the Special-Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force Crisis Response.

Film Credits: LCpl Lucas Hopkins

2389.description: The United States Army Drill Team (The Old Guard) performs during the Spirit of America 2014 tour.

2390.description:
U.S. Marines with Black Sea Rotational Force trained alongside Moldovans in anti-armor warfare. In this video, a Marine teaches a Moldovan Soldier how to fire an AT-4. Filmed December 12, 2014.

Film Credits: LCpl Ryan Young

2391.description:
C-17 Globemasters and C-130 Hercules takeoff and land at Nellis Air Force Base as part of the Joint Forcible Entry exercise (JFE-14B) on the Nevada Test and Training Range (NTTR) near Las Vegas, NV - December 6, 2014. Approximately 100 aircraft teamed up with the U.S. Army's 82nd Airborne Division to execute the U.S. Air Force Weapons School's JFE-14B exercise.

Film Credits: SrA Aaron Hauser

2392.description:
Paratroopers from the 2nd Battalion, 503rd Infantry Regiment, 173rd Airborne Brigade conduct an airfield seizure exercise at dusk on the Rivolto Italian Air Force Base - December 10, 2014. 

Film Credits: Graigg Faggionato

2393.description:
