A KC-130J aircraft with Marine Aerial Refueler Transport Squadron 252 (VMGR-252) refuels a CH-53 Super Stallion helicopter on a training flight out of Marine Corps Air Station Cherry Point, NC. Filmed on December 3, 2014.

Film Credits: Cpl Gregory Boyd

2394.description:
U.S. Marines with Company F, 2nd Battalion, 9th Marine Regiment are inserted with U.S. Army chinook helicopters to conduct a mock air raid and assault at the Rodriguez Live Fire Complex in South Korea from December 5-8, 2014.

Film Credits: Cpl Wes Lucko

2395.description:
U.S. Marines with the Force Reconnaissance Detachment, 15th Marine Expeditionary Unit and British Royal Marines shoot downrange while conducting bilateral training during realistic urban training (RUT) at Fort Hunter Liggett, California on December 11, 2014.

Film Credits: Cpl Steve Lopez

2396.description:
Aerial view of USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD 6) conducting flight operations in March of 2014. Plus, an MV-22 Osprey takes off - deck view. The Bonhomme Richard was conducting search and rescue operations as requested by the Republic of Korea Navy near the scene of the sunken ferry Sewol in the East China Sea. Filmed March 19 and March 23 of 2014. Units - Helicopter Sea Combat Squadron (HSC) 25, Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron (VMM) 265 - 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU)

Film Credits: PO3 Christian Senyk

2397.description:
U.S. Marines enter the well deck of USS Rushmore (LSD-47) in assault amphibious vehicles (AAV) during exercise Steel Knight 2015 (SK-15) on December 8, 2014. Units - Company B, 3rd Assault Amphibian Battalion, and Company A, 1st Assault Amphibian Battalion - 5th Marine Regiment

Film & Image Credits: Cpl Ricardo Hurtado, Cpl Joshua Murray

2398.description:
An A-10 Thunderbolt/Warthog goes through pre-flight checks and exits the hangar at Osan Air Base in South Korea during Exercise Beverly Bulldog 15-01. Filmed December 5, 2014.

Film Credits: SSgt Traci Keller

2399.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcons taxi to the runway and takeoff from Osan Air Base in South Korea during Exercise Beverly Bulldog 15-01. Filmed December 5-6, 2014.

Film Credits: SSgt Traci Keller

2400.description:
The Ghost Swimmer unmanned underwater vehicle (UUV) developed by the Chief of Naval Operations - Rapid Innovation Cell project Silent NEMO undergoes testing during an event at Joint Expeditionary Base Little Creek - Fort Story, Virginia. Filmed on December 12, 2014.

Ghost Swimmer is a biomimetic autonomous artificial fish that employs the actual mechanics and dynamics of live fish to create efficient swimming while conducting covert, riverine, and littoral missions.

Film Credits: Jesse Hyatt

2401.description:
U.S. Marines with Force Reconnaissance Detachment, 15th Marine Expeditionary Unit, conduct a static-line jump from an MV-22B Osprey at Fort Hunter Liggett, California on December 9, 2014.

Film Credits: Cpl Anna Albrecht

2402.description:
This is part of a video series titled Welcome to the MEU. This episode has Lance Cpl. Randy James explaining to viewers how Marines train for fast rope insertions. The Marines and Sailors are with Weapons Company, Battalion Landing Team 2nd Battalion, 4th Marines, 31st Marine Expeditionary

Film Credits: LCpl August Light

2403.description:
U.S. Navy divers from USS Anchorage (LPD 23) recover the NASA Orion space capsule after it splashed down in the Pacific Ocean on December 5, 2014. The recovery operation marked the end of Exploration Flight Test 1 (EFT-1), the first orbital test flight of the Orion spacecraft. 

The craft, without a crew, was launched on December 5, 2014, at 12:05 UTC (7:05 am EST), atop a Delta IV Heavy rocket from Space Launch Complex 37B at Cape Canaveral Air Force Station.

The mission was a four-hour, two-orbit test of the Orion crew module featuring a high apogee on the second orbit and concluding with a high-energy reentry at around 20,000 miles per hour.

Units - Expeditionary Strike Group Three, USNS Salvor (T-ARS 52), Helicopter Sea Combat Squadron Eight, Explosive Ordnance Disposal Group One, Fleet Combat Camera Pacific, and Fleet Weather Center San Diego. 

Film Credits:  PO1 Paul Seeber, PO1 Gary Keen, U.S. Navy Video Released On December 9, 2014 
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2404.description:
1st Brigade Combat Team Soldiers conduct live fire training during the multinational training exercise Combined Resolve III, in Germany. Filmed on November 28, 2014.

Film Credits: SGT Fred Brown

2405.description:
Introducing the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit new video series: Episode 1 - Welcome to the MEU. If this is something you would like to see more of, leave a comment or a thumbs up on the video and I will upload them as they are released. Thanks GHV.

Film Credits: LCpl August Light

2406.description:
Bradley Fighting Vehicles fire the Tube-launched Optically-tracked, Wire-guided Missile System (TOW) at Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany, November 20, 2014. Unit - Company B, 2nd Battalion, 12th Cavalry Regiment, 1st Brigade Combat Team, 1st Cavalry Division 

Film Credits: Matthew Oldham

2407.description:
Members of the 91st Brigade Engineer Battalion conduct a Breaching Operation at the Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany. Filmed June 6, 2014.

Film Credits: SGT Fred Brown

2408.description:
Five Kiowa Warrior helicopters flew for the final time from Bagram Airfield, followed by a demonstration of the OH-58D Kiowa Warrior, a badass little helicopter. A single engine reconnaissance helicopter that is capable of firing Hellfire missiles, Hydra 70 rockets, Stinger missiles, and 50-calibre machine guns. Soldiers of C Troop, 1st Squadron, 17th Air Cavalry Regiment, 82nd Airborne Division flew the emotional final flight because the air frame is transitioning out of use by the U.S. Army. Final flight filmed on November 22, 2014.

Film & Image Credits: SGT Chloe Barnes, SFC Eric Pahon, MAJ Enrique Vasquez
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2409.description:
An MQ-8B Fire Scout unmanned autonomous helicopter from Helicopter Maritime Strike Squadron (HSM) 35 Detachment 1 lifts off of the littoral combat ship USS Fort Worth (LCS 3) for flight operations. The MQ-8 Fire Scout is designed to provide reconnaissance, situational awareness, aerial fire support and precision targeting support for ground, air and sea forces.

The aviation detachment aboard Fort Worth consists of one MH-60R Seahawk helicopter and one MQ-8B that compliments the MH-60R by extending the range and endurance thereby enhancing maritime domain awareness. Fort Worth departed its homeport of San Diego Nov. 17 for a 16-month rotational deployment to Singapore in support of the Navy’s strategic rebalance to the Pacific. 

Film Credits: Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Antonio P. Turretto Ramos and Aviation Structural Mechanic 1st Class Gregory Kazeleski

2410.description:
Cockpit footage of U.S. Navy pilots as they takeoff and land aboard Aircraft Carriers and also a Landing Helicopter Dock (light carrier). 

Film Credits: Lt. Ian Schmidt Released by Lt. j.g. Michael Hatfield, Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Jared King, PO2 James Evans, WO Michael Kropiewnicki
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2411.description:
Sailors and Marines aboard the aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70) enjoy a traditional Thanksgiving Day dinner while underway in the Arabian Sea. Meanwhile on the flight deck, aircraft are launched and recovered in support of Operation Inherent Resolve. Filmed Thanksgiving Day, November 27, 2014. 

Film Credits: Damon Moritz

2412.description:
The Virginia-class nuclear powered submarine USS Mississippi (SSN-782) arrives at Joint Base Pearl Harbor-Hickam for a change of homeport ceremony. The Mississippi was formerly stationed at Groton, Connecticut. Filmed November 25, 2014.

Film Credits: PO1 Jason Swink

2413.description:
F-15 Eagle fighter jets from the 122nd Fighter Squadron conduct a training mission during exercise Southern Strike 15. Scenes include air-to-air refueling, flying in formation with F-35 Lightning II aircraft, and a flyover of the city of New Orleans. Filmed from the cockpit of an F-15D Eagle on November 4, 2014.

Film Credits: SrA Robert Kingery

2414.description:
The Los Angeles-class fast attack submarine USS Columbia (SSN-771) returns to Pearl Harbor, Hawaii after a six-month deployment to the Western Pacific. Filmed November 21, 2014.

Film Credits: Video Released By The U.S. Navy On November 22, 2014

2415.description:
An Air Force F-22 Raptor pilot puts his aircraft through its paces to show off some of this 5th generation fighter jet's capabilities. Filmed at Nellis AFB Red Flag 2012 and Nellis Open House Air Show on November 8, 2014.

Film Credits: SrA Aaron Hauser, SrA Rachel Maxwell, SSgt Jose Rodriguez, A1C Rachel Webster, SSgt Anthony Kuhn, William Lewis, A1C Rebecca Long and TSgt Colleen Urban
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2416.description:
U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcons and U.S. Navy F/A-18 Super Hornets taxi and takeoff for a training mission at Naval Air Station Fallon in Nevada. F-16 Swamp Fox Airmen from the 169th Fighter Wing and South Carolina Air National Guard are deployed to NAS Fallon to support Naval Carrier Air Wing One with pre-deployment fighter jet training, integrating the F-16’s suppression of enemy air defenses (SEAD) capabilities with U.S. Navy fighter pilots. Filmed November 12, 2014.

Film Credits: TSgt Caycee Watson

2417.description:
U.S. Marines practice squad level infantry tactics and fire team rushing. A Marine Corps squad is typically composed of three fireteams of four Marines and a squad leader who is usually a Sergeant or Corporal. 

Film Credits: Cpl. Andrea Olguin

2418.description:
A KC-135 Stratotanker from the 151st Air Refueling Wing - Utah Air National Guard, refuels a KC-10 Extender from the 60th Air Mobility Wing out of Travis Air Force Base, California. 

Film Credits: SSgt Robert Harnden

2419.description:
U.S. Marine Corps UH-1Y Huey helicopters conduct a close air support mission at night during exercise  Southern Strike 15 on Camp Shelby Joint Forces Training Center in Mississippi. Filmed on November 6, 2014. Unit - Marine Light Attack Squadron 773 (HMLA-773) Detachment A 

Film Credits: SrA Robert Kingery

2420.description:
The aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) returns home to Naval Station Norfolk, Virginia after a nine month deployment in the U.S. 5th and 6th Fleet areas of operation. During its deployment, USS Bush was the first U.S. aircraft carrier to support airstrikes on the terrorist group ISIS in Iraq and Syria. Filmed on November 15, 2014. 

Film Credits: Video Released By U.S. Navy

2421.description:
Airborne qualified Tactical Air Control Party (TACP) members jump from Black Hawk helicopters to increase proficiency in airborne infiltration. Filmed October 23, 2014. Unit - 3d Air Support Operations Squadron from Joint Base Elmendorf-Richardson in Anchorage, Alaska.  

Film Credits: SrA Sarah Trachte

2422.description:
The U.S. Air Force Thunderbirds perform during the 2014 Nellis Air Force Base Open House on November 8, 2014.  The Thunderbirds fly in F-16C Fighting Falcons and are assigned to the 57th Wing at Nellis AFB in Nevada.

Film Credits: SrA Aaron Hauser, SSgt Anthony Kuhn, William Lewis, A1C Rebecca Long and TSgt Colleen Urban

2423.description:
U.S. Marines with 2nd Battalion, 9th Marines practice military operations on urbanized terrain (MOUT) at the Central Training Area during exercise Blue Chromite 15 on Okinawa, Japan. Filmed November 4, 2014. 

Film Credits: LCpl Devon Tindle

2424.description:
British Tornado GR4 pilots from RAF 31 Squadron takeoff from Kandahar Air Field, Afghanistan for the last time on November 11, 2014. 31 Squadron did four tours during five years of operations in-country.

Film Credits: NATO TV

2425.description:
Staff Sergeant Katie Gray captures spectacular film of the Puna Lava Flow as it creeps nearer to the small town of Pahoa on the Big Island of Hawaii - November 8, 2014.

Film Credits: Staff Sergeant Katie Gray

2426.description:
U.S. Marines in the Marines Martial Arts Instructor Course (MAI) earn their instructor tab enabling them to train, educate, and test other Marines pursuing higher belt classes in the Marine Corps Martial Arts Program.

Film Credits: LCpl Zachary Montgomery

2427.description:
Sailors fuel and taxi F-35C Lightning II Joint Strike Fighters aboard the aircraft carrier USS Nimitz (CVN-68) off the coast of San Diego on November 4, 2014. Initial at-sea developmental testing of the F-35C began on November 3rd and is expected to last two weeks.

Film Credits: PO1 Brett Cote

2428.description:
Developmental Testing I (DT-I) for the F-35C Lightning II carrier variant Joint Strike Fighter continues as they launch and land aboard the aircraft carrier USS Nimitz (CVN 68) off the coast of San Diego. The F-35C is the carrier variant (CV) of the F-35 Lightning II Joint Strike Fighter designed for the U.S. Navy. DT-I started November 3, 2014 and is expected to last two weeks. Filmed on November 6, 2014.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video Released On November 6, 2014

2429.description:
A KC-130J Hercules and three MV-22B Ospreys conduct aerial refueling training operations in the U.S. Navy's 5th fleet area of responsibility. The Ospreys were launched and recovered by the USS Iwo Jima (LHD-7). 

Film Credits: LCpl Tucker Wolf

2430.description:
F-35C Lightning II Joint Strike Fighters are catapult launched and recovered by arresting gear aboard the aircraft carrier USS Nimitz (CVN 68) as part of continued initial at-sea Developmental Testing I (DT-I) off the coast of San Diego. The F-35C is the carrier variant (CV) of the F-35 Lightning II Joint Strike Fighter designed for the U.S. Navy. Filmed November 5, 2014. 

Film Credits:  U.S. Navy Video Released On November 5, 2014.

2431.description:
Members of the 82nd Airborne Division make a training jump over Fort Bragg, NC. One of the paratroopers jumps with a GoPro camera on his helmet.

Film Credits: SGT William Reinier

2432.description:
Assault Breacher Vehicles (ABV) clear a path for Abrams Tanks and Bradley Fighting Vehicles during operation Combined Resolve III in Germany. Filmed October 25-30, 2014.

Film Credits: SGT Fred Brown

2433.description:
CH-53E Super Stallion helicopter flight operations aboard the USS Kearsarge (LHD-3) in support of exercise Bold Alligator 14, off the eastern coast of the United States. Filmed October 31, 2014.

Film Credits: Cpl James Skelton, Sgt Anthony Ortiz

2434.description:
Marine Corps door gunners conduct a close air support mission from a UH-1Y Venom helicopter (aka Super Huey) in South Korea as part of exercise SSang Yong 2014. Unit - Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 265 (VMM-265), 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit (31st MEU)

Film Credits: Cpl Alexander Pool

2435.description:
F-35C Lightning II carrier variant Joint Strike Fighter makes aviation history by conducting its first arrested landing aboard an aircraft carrier, the USS Nimitz (CVN 68), off the coast of San Diego. The arrested landing is part of initial at-sea Developmental Testing I for the F-35C, and is expected to last two weeks. Filmed November 3, 2014. 

Film Credits:  PO1 Brett Cote, U.S. Navy Video Released On November 3, 2014

2436.description:
The USS Kearsarge (LHD-3) is a Wasp-class amphibious assault ship which carries a wide array of assets that can be deployed on short notice to carry the fight from sea to land, and inland to the enemy. Video includes shots of MH-60S Knighthawk, CH-53E Super Stallion and AH-1W Super Cobra helicopters, the AV-8b Harrier, LCAC hovercraft and MV-22 Osprey operations. 

Film Credits: Cpl James Skelton, Sgt Anthony Ortiz

2437.description:
A U.S. Navy MH-60R Sea Hawk helicopter from Helicopter Maritime Strike Squadron Seven One (HSM-71), Naval Air Station North Island, San Diego, conducts a photo exercise (PHOTOEX) flyover of the San Diego coastline on October 2, 2014.

Film Credits: PO1 Shannon Renfroe

2438.description:
Multiple clips highlighting the still very intimidating F-16 fighter jet: (Clip 1) F-16Ds from the 18th Aggressor Squadron takeoff from Eielson Air Force Base, Alaska. (Clip 2) An F-16C Fighting Falcon receives fuel from a KC-135 Stratotanker during an in-air refueling mission in Northern Afghanistan, July 22, 2014. (Clip 3) An F-16 drops a 500 lb bomb on the house of an insurgent manufacturing improvised explosive devices in Iraq. (Clip 4) F-16 Viper drops two 500 lb bombs on a building housing terrorists in Iraq. 

Film & Image Credits: SSgt Miguel Lara, SSgt Erin Mills, SSgt James L. Harper Jr. 
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2439.description:
The guided missile frigate USS Boone (FFG-28) navigates through the Strait of Magellan, the most important natural passage between the Atlantic and Pacific oceans located south of mainland South America. The strait is considered a difficult route to navigate because of the unpredictable winds, currents, and the narrowness of the passage. Filmed in 2011, the USS Boone was decommissioned in 2012.

Film Credits: PO1 Steven Smith

2440.description:
An aerial refueling mission between a KC-135 Stratotanker and a C-17 Globemaster goes smoothly with clear radio communications. Units - KC-135 Utah Air National Guard, 191st Air Refueling Squadron. C-17 446th/62d Airlift Wing McCHord Air Force Base, Washington.

Film Credits: SSgt Erin Mills

2441.description:
U.S. Navy F/A-18 pilot Lt. Ian Schmidt puts his superb flying skills on display in these video clips recorded from the cockpit of a Super Hornet fighter jet while stationed aboard the aircraft carrier USS Enterprise (CVN-65). 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video by Lt. Ian Schmidt - Released by Lt. j.g. Michael Hatfield, Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Jared King
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2442.description:
The amphibious assault ship USS Kearsarge (LHD-3) conducts routine operations off the eastern coast of the United States during exercise Bold Alligator 2014. Filmed on October 27-29, 2014.

Film Credits: Sgt Anthony Ortiz, Cpl James Skelton

2443.description:
The aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70) conducts flight operations in the Arabian Sea as part of Operation Inherent Resolve. The USS Carl Vinson has replaced USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) which is headed home to Naval Station Norfolk. Filmed on October 27, 2014.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video Released On October 30, 2014.

2444.description:
U.S. Marines attend the pre-scout sniper training course at Camp Pendleton, California on October 27, 2014. Hand selected from their units, these Marines spend countless hours during the pre-scout sniper course learning to apply their weapon systems and the skills needed to graduate and move on to the famed Marine Corps Scout Sniper Course. Unit - 1st Battalion, 7th Marine Regiment and 3rd Battalion, 1st Marine Regiment

Film Credits: Cpl Joshua Murray

2445.description:
The aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70) refuels at sea with the Indian Navy replenishment oiler INS Shakti (A57). Filmed in the Indian Ocean in 2012.

Film Credits: Zachary Bell, Damon Moritz

2446.description:
U.S. Marines fire the M2 Browning .50 caliber on a heavy machine gun range during Operation Rolling Thunder at Fort Bragg NC. Filmed October 18, 2014.

Film Credits: LCpl Zachary Montgomery

2447.description:
Scenes include a B-52 flying low over 5 Wing Goose Bay, Newfoundland and Labrador at sunset, a B-52 refueling in-flight over Utah, and cockpit video of landing.

Film Credits: SrA Ellen McCarthy, SSgt Robert Harnden

2448.description:
A fierce firefight with casualties and medivac... U.S. Marines engage the Taliban at patrol base Georgetown near Kajaki Sofla, Afghanistan on November 22, 2011. Unit: 1st Battalion, 6th Marines

Film Credits: LCpl Jacob Lagoze

2449.description:
The Sea-Based X-Band Radar-1 (SBX-1) is a fire control radar based on a seagoing semi-submersible vessel. The platform was developed by Boeing as part of the ground-based midcourse defence (GMD) component of the US Ballistic Missile Defence System (BMDS). The GMD intercepts incoming warheads. Among other things, the SBX-1 is keeping an eye on North Korea's upcoming planned space launch. Filmed on October 24, 2014.

Film Credits: Pedro Valdez

2450.description:
A look at Arlington National Cemetery, our nation's most sacred shrine to those who have honorably served our country in times of war and paid the ultimate sacrifice. We will never forget you. 

Film Credits: Mary Cochran

2451.description:
Combat footage of U.S. Marines, including interviews, as they are inserted by helicopter across the Helmand River into Kajaki Sofla, Afghanistan for Operation Western Storm. Filmed on Dec. 3, 2011. 

Film Credits: LCpl Jacob Lagoze

2452.description:
Scenic view of Alaska skyline, sunset, and mountains from the back of a C-17 transport plane out of Elmendorf Air Force Base near Anchorage, Alaska. 

Film Credits: SrA Sarah Trachte

2453.description:
U.S. Marine Corps students attending Weapons and Tactics Instructor Course (WTI) participate in Final Exercise 3 (FINEX-3) using CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters near Yuma, Arizona on October 18, 2014.

Film Credits: LCpl Jordan Walker

2454.description:
Oliver Hazard Perry-class guided-missile frigate USS Rodney M. Davis (FFG 60) performs vertical replenishment (VERTREP) and refueling with the Military Sealift Command fleet replenishment oiler USNS Pecos (T-AO-197). Filmed October 21, 2014.

Film Credit: PO3 Derek Harkins

2455.description:
The Trident ballistic missile submarine USS Pennsylvania (SSBN-735) sails through the Hood Canal/Puget Sound, returning to Naval Base Kitsap-Bangor from a strategic deterrent patrol. Filmed October 16, 2014.

Film Credits: PO1 Ahron Arendes

2456.description:
The USS Carl Vinson Carrier Strike Group (CSG-1) has moved into the 5th Fleet area of operation (Persian Gulf, Red Sea, Arabian Sea) to relieve the USS George H.W. Bush (CSG-2) during Operation Inherent Resolve . CSG-1 includes: USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70), USS Bunker Hill (CG-52), USS Gridley (DDG 101), USS Sterett (DDG 104), and USS Dewey (DDG 105).

Film Credits: Damon Moritz

2457.description:
The High Mobility Artillery Rocket System (HIMARS) carries a six-pack of rockets which can lock on a target within 16 seconds, has a range of between 40 miles and 185 miles (depending on the type of rocket being fired), and has been proven in Iraq and Afghanistan to be absolutely deadly against the enemy.

Film Credits: SGT Christopher Tobey, A1C Elizabeth Taranto

2458.description:
The aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70) relieves USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) in the Persian Gulf. Carl Vinson will take over support of maritime security operations and strike operations as part of Operation Inherent Resolve. George H.W. Bush will soon depart for its homeport at Norfolk, Virginia. Filmed October 18, 2014.

Film Credits: Damon Moritz

2459.description:
C-130 cockpit footage and helmet cam footage of a paratrooper jump during a training exercise for the Alaska Air National Guard's 211th and 212th Rescue Squadron (RQS).

Film Credits: SrA Sarah Trachte

2460.description:
Marine Corps CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters fly into the San Francisco Bay area and then fly over the Port Of San Francisco. Filmed during Fleet Week 2011.

Film Credits: Sgt Timothy Lenzo

2461.description:
The Los Angeles-class fast attack submarine USS La Jolla (SSN 701) departs Pearl Harbor Naval Base for the last time. After 34 years of commissioned service, with the last 14 years based at Pearl Harbor, La Jolla is scheduled to be decommissioned and converted to a Moored Training Ship, serving as a training platform for Nuclear Power Training at Naval Support Activity Charleston in South Carolina. 

Film Credits: PO1 Jason Swink

2462.description:
Two Clips: First clip - U.S. Soldiers with the 25th Infantry Division receive jungle survival training on snakes from Royal Thailand Army personnel. Second clip - 25th Infantry Soldiers conduct a live-fire assault exercise in Ban Dan Lan Hoi, Thailand.

Film Credits: Sgt Robert Bush
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2463.description:
U.S. Air Force Joint Terminal Attack Controllers train U.S. Army Joint Fire Observers in emergency close air support (CAS) operations by calling in Apache helicopters on practice targets, in this live fire exercise.

Film Credits: SSgt Erin Mills

2464.description:
Have a good look at the JAS-39 Gripen: Swedish Gripens taxi, takeoff and land at the Red Flag Exercise in Nevada, plus a Czech Gripen refuels in-flight via a KC-135 Stratotanker during a NATO military exercise.

Film Credits:  MSgt Shane Cronin, William Lewis, A1C Rachel Webster, SSgt Tristan McIntire 
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2465.description:
French Air Force Pilots prepare their Mirage 2000D for takeoff on a mission at Kandahar Airfield in Afghanistan.

Film Credits: SSgt Michelle Revoir

2466.description:
Soldiers with the 2d Cavalry Regiment fire the Javelin Anti-Tank Missile system at the Grafenwhor Training Area in Germany. Slow motion footage of the missile being fired is included. Filmed September 23, 2014.

Film Credits:  SGT Kyle Burns

2467.description:
U.S. Marines conduct helicopter evacuation training with the Helo Dunker at Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton, California as part of pre-deployment preparation. 

Film Credits: Cpl Christopher J. Moore, Sgt Jonathan Wright

2468.description:
U.S. Marines shoot the M27 Infantry Automatic Rifle at a live-fire range in Jordan - June 2013. 

Film & Image Credits: LCpl Juanenrique Owings, Image Released By The United States Marine Corps ID 120427-M-SR181-035

2469.description:
An A-10 Warthog pilot checks his aircraft prior to a sortie over Afghanistan. Gun camera footage shows bombing and strafing runs on targets.

Film & Image Credits: SrA Anthony Hetlage, TSgt David Kujawa 
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2470.description:
C-17 Globemaster III comes in for a perfect landing at Wheeler Army Airfield in Hawaii.

Film Credits: MSgt Ryan Kruse

2471.description:
USS Spruance (DDG-111), the 61st Arleigh Burke-class guided missile destroyer, undocks and goes to sea while showing deck crew and bridge crew performing duties. Next, various shots of the bride crew performing duties while the deck crew refuels the ship underway. Next, video of the engineering department performing duties. Next, video of the deck guns and CWIS system firing. Finally, video of helo operations while underway.

Film Credits: Videographer - MC2 (SW) Christopher Hall, Defense Media Activity Navy Production Directorate
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2472.description:
U.S. Air Force KC-135 Stratotanker refuels U.S. Navy F/A-18 Hornets and EA-6B Prowlers in support of airstrikes in Iraq and Syria. Filmed October 4, 2014.

Film Credits:  SSgt Daniel Negrete

2473.description:
CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters transport Marines to a combat operation in Helmand Province, Afghanistan on August 20, 2013. Units - Marine Heavy Helicopter Squadron 461 - Golf Company, 2nd Battalion, 8th Marines

Film Credits:  Cpl Ashley Beckett

2474.description:
U.S. Marines with 1st Reconnaissance Battalion helocast from a UH-1Y Super Huey helicopter (aka Venom or Yankee) at Senators Wash Lake near Yuma, Arizona on September 27, 2014.

Film Credits:  Cpl Brandon Ponyah

2475.description:
Flight operations on the USS Peleliu (LHA-5) at sea near the Philippines as part of exercise PHIBLEX 15. PHIBLEX 15 is an annual bilateral training exercise conducted by the Armed Forces of the Philippines, U.S. Navy and Marines in order to strengthen interoperability across a range of capabilities to include disaster relief and contingency operations. Filmed October 3, 2014.

Film Credits:  Cpl Alexander Pool

2476.description:
Pre-Commissioning Unit (PCU) America (LHA 6) returns to Ingalls Shipyard in Pascagoula, MS from Acceptance Trials on January 31, 2014. During the trials, the ship’s main propulsion, communications, steering, navigation and radar systems were tested. The USS America will be the newest amphibious assault ship of the U.S. Navy, and is scheduled to be formally commissioned during a ceremony in San Francisco, California on October 11, 2014.

Film Credits: Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Ryan Riley

2477.description:
U.S. Marines fire the M1014 Shotgun (aka Benelli M4 Super 90) at a live fire range at Basa Air Base, Pampanga, Philippines during Amphibious Landing Exercise (PHIBLEX) 15. Filmed October 7, 2014.

Film Credits:  Cpl Alexander Pool

2478.description:
U.S. Air Force Airmen conduct a search and rescue training exercise over water, jumping from a C-130 with the Rigging Alternate Method Zodiac (RAMZ). The RAMZ operation deploys an inflatable Zodiac boat which the para-rescue special operators must inflate to use in their efforts to locate... e.g. downed pilots.

Film Credits: SrA John Pharr

2479.description:
A close air support exercise with AH-1Z Viper helicopters was held by U.S. Marines at Mount Barrow, Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range in California on October 2, 2014.

Film Credits: LCpl Jordan Walker

2480.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a combined arms exercise featuring the M777 Howitzer weapon system during Assault Support Tactics One (AST-1) exercises at Fire Base Burt, Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range in California. Filmed on October 7, 2014.

Film Credits: LCpl Jordan Walker

2481.description:
A Marine Corps offensive air support exercise using AH-1Z Viper helicopters (also called Zulu Cobra), M224 60mm Lightweight Mortars, and the M2 .50 Caliber machine gun was held at Mount Barrow, Chocolate Mountain Aerial Gunnery Range in California on September 30, 2014. Day and night footage included.

Film Credits: LCpl Jordan Walker

2482.description:
Operation Hammerdown, a search and clearing operation for a suspected Taliban training camp turns into a lethal firefight with Taliban fighters. Filmed in Kunar Province, Afghanistan. Unit - 1st Platoon, B Company, 2/35 Infantry Regiment

Film Credits: SSG Elwyn Lovelace

2483.description:
Spectacular footage of F/A-18 Hornets and Super Hornets as they takeoff and land aboard the aircraft carrier USS Enterprise (CVN 65). Video includes the aircraft flying in tandem formation at low altitude above the water, conducting banking and rolling maneuvers at high-speed, and making high-speed passes over the aircraft carrier. Filmed from the cockpit and pilot point-of-view.

Film Credits: Lt. Ian Schmidt, Released by Lt. J.G. Michael Hatfield, Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Jared King
Cloud Surf Productions - https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCOqVMabToxLvzXQ850TCU9w
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2484.description:
Marines and Sailors aboard the USS America (LHA 6) man-the-rails as the ship pulls into port at San Francisco for Fleet Week 2014. During Fleet Week, Marine units will demonstrate assets available for the Bay Area in response to a sudden crisis. The intent is to showcase amphibious nature, readiness and the ability to respond to disasters and highlight the role the Navy-Marine Corps team can play in assisting disaster victims. Filmed October 6, 2014.

Film Credits: Cpl Christopher J. Moore

2485.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers attached to the 172nd Infantry Brigade battle Taliban insurgents in an intense firefight at Combat Outpost Margah in Paktika Province, Afghanistan. Filmed November 8, 2011. Units: C Company 2-28 Task Force Black Lion & Task Force Black Hawks

Film Credits:  Spc. David Barnes

2486.description:
Helicopter takes-off from the USS Stockdale (DDG 106), filming the Stockdale first and the USS Princeton (CG 59) afterwards, then lands on the Princeton.

Film Credits:  Cpl Gregory Boyd

2487.description:
F-22 Raptors takeoff from an undisclosed location in Southwest Asia. Filmed April 3, 2104.

Film Credits: TSgt Colleen Urban

2488.description:
B-52 flight out of Barksdale Air Force Base, pilots maneuver the aircraft for landing - cockpit view.

Film Credits:  TSgt Rebecca King

2489.description:
The U.S. Army Golden Knights Parachute Team perform a team jump at the 2014 Miramar Air Show - POV camera. Filmed October 4, 2014.

Film Credits: Cpl Maxwell Pennington

2490.description:
In August of 2011 U.S. Marines conducted Operation Black Sand, the destruction of the Ladar Bazaar in Helmand Province Afghanistan, which was being used by insurgents as an improvised explosive device (IED) factory.

Film Credits: Cpl Zachary Ouellette, Sgt Bryan Nygaard
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2491.description:
Flight deck operations aboard the aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN 77) as it launches aircraft to conduct or support airstrikes in Iraq and Syria. Filmed October 3, 2014. 

Film Credits: Released by the U.S. Navy October 4, 2014

2492.description:
An F/A-18 Hornet does a supersonic fly-by of the aircraft carrier USS John C. Stennis (CVN 74) as part of a VIP demonstration. Filmed from the USS Mobile Bay (CG 53), which was approximately 500 yards away from the Stennis. 

Film Credits: Armando Gonzales

2493.description:
EA-6B Prowler ground crew pre-flight checks and pilots prepare for takeoff at Andersen Air Force Base, Guam. 

Film Credits: Cpl Anthony Rayis

2494.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a training exercise to secure an airfield and setup a Forward Arming and Refueling Point (FARP) for AH-1W Cobra, UH-1Y Venom, CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters and MV-22B Osprey tiltrotors. 

Film Credits: LCpl Paula Kelly

2495.description:
U-2 pilots practice touch and go landings at Beale Air Force Base.

Film Credits: SrA Andrew Buchanan

2496.description:
For the Soldiers at Observation Post Mustang in Afghanistan, life is anything but easy. As one Soldier puts it, "I'd compare it to a really crappy camping trip, you don't go for a weekend, you go for a year." OP Mustang sits perched at the top of the rugged Kunar Province Mountains near the Afghan/Pakistan border. And the Soldiers of Troop C, 1st Squadron, 32nd Cavalry Regiment, Task Force Bandit, stand watch every minute of every day.

Film Credits: SFC Mark Burrell

2497.description:
The U.S. Navy aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN 77) continues air operations in the Arabian Sea in support of airstrikes in Iraq and Syria. Filmed October 2, 2014.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video/Released October 2, 2014

2498.description:
Two clips show in-flight refueling of U.S. aircraft during ISIS airstrikes. Clip one: A KC-135 Stratotanker refuels a B-1 Lancer bomber on a strike mission to Syria. Clip two: A KC-10 Extender refuels an F-22 Raptor at night on a strike mission to Syria. Both clips filmed on September 27, 2014.

Film Credits: TSgt Russell Scalf, MSgt Michael Garza

2499.description:
Pilots from the U.S. and Indonesian army conduct air to ground attacks during Operation Garuda Shield 2014 in Indonesia. Filmed September 26, 2014.

Film Credits: SGT Kerry Collier

2500.description:
The 155th Infantry Regiment conducts live fire training with the AT4 Shoulder-Fired Weapon at Camp Shelby Joint Forces Training Center in Mississippi. Filmed July 31, 2014.  

Film Credits: SGT Michael Needham

2501.description:
Marines at Camp Lejeune, NC fire the Non-Lethal/Tube Launched Munition System. The NL/TLMS is a 40mm 30-round flash-bang launching system that mounts on various vehicles or is deployed on a ground tripod. 

Film Credits: LCpl Kaitlyn Klein

2502.description:
"The Movie" Memphis Belle, a restored WWII B-17 Flying Fortress, flies a public tour flight over Columbia, SC. The Memphis Belle was one of the first B-17s to complete 25 combat missions during WWII, and the plane was the subject of the 1990 film named "Memphis Belle". Filmed September 28, 2014.  

Film Credits: SrA Molly Elder

2503.description:
U.S. Marines conduct an annual training exercise entitled Desert Fire at the Cannon Air Defense Complex in Yuma, Arizona. Marines respond to a deranged gunman/active shooter on base in an effort to further their skills and practice the force-in-readiness tactics needed to deal with any situation. All players used simulated weapons to ensure safety throughout the exercise. Filmed on September 26, 2014.  

Film Credits: LCpl Summer Dowding

2504.description:
A pair of MV-22B Ospreys land, fuel and depart Tinian Island. The aircraft were transporting the Commander Officer of 1st Marine Aircraft Wing, Deputy Commander of the U.S. 7th Fleet, and the Commanding Officer of Marine Aircraft Group 12 to visit Marines during Exercise Valiant Shield. Filmed October 1, 2014.

Film Credits: Cpl Anthony Rayis

2505.description:
U.S. Marines patrol Sangin, Afghanistan and engage Taliban fighters with small arms and a Venom "Super Huey" helicopter. 

Film Credits: Cpl Daniel Blatter

2506.description:
U.S. Army Special Operations Forces and Polish Special Forces (SOF) conduct a shoot-house training exercise. Filmed on September 19, 2014.

Film Credits: Nancy Fischer

2507.description:
Soldiers from the 173rd Airborne, Able Company and the Lithuanian Iron Wolf Mechanized Infantry Brigade sharpen their skills with the M249 SAW and the M240 Bravo on a live-fire range - cross training on small arms in Lithuania. Filmed on September 19, 2014.

Film Credits: SSG Matthew Keeler

2508.description:
Clips released by the Pentagon: Navy Rear Admiral John Kirby talks about collateral damage - operational video of two F/A-18 Super Hornets refueling in-flight enroute to ISIS targets - bomb camera footage of airstrikes on ISIS targets in Syria. Clips filmed September 23-25, 2014. 

Film Credits: SGT Adam Ross, MSgt Michael Garza, Sgt Fredrick J. Coleman

2509.description:
U.S. Army 3-21 Infantry engage Taliban in Panjwa'i district, Kandahar, Afghanistan. Plus, Army 205th ATAL clear Pan Kalay of EOD elements. Combat footage.

Film Credits: SFC Walter Talens

2510.description:
U.S. Marines Recon team jumps from a C-130 Hercules aircraft on a training mission above Camp Lejeune NC. 

Film Credits: Sgt Paul Peterson

2511.description:
Australian Army Soldiers with 5th Battalion, Royal Australian Regiment demonstrate proficiency in quick disassembly and reassembly of the AUG 5.56mm assault rifle, also known as the Bullpup.

Film Credits: Sgt Robert Bush

2512.description: The aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) is on station somewhere in the Persian Gulf/Arabian Sea/Red Sea area of operation conducting around-the-clock flight operations. Filmed September 22, 2014.

2513.description:
U.S. Marines live-fire test the GAU-16 .50 Caliber Machine Gun and the GAU-17 Defensive Weapon System (DWS) aboard an MV-22B Osprey at Marine Corps Air Station Yuma, Arizona on September 19, 2014.  

Film Credits: LCpl Jordan Walker

2514.description:
U.S. Marines conduct a series of close-quarters rifle drills and moving shooting exercises as part of pre-deployment training at Twentynine Palms, CA.

Film Credits: Sgt Paul Peterson

2515.description:
The guided-missile cruiser USS Philippine Sea (CG-58) launches Tomahawk Land-Attack Missiles (TLAM). Philippine Sea is deployed as part of the USS George H.W. Bush (CVN 77) Carrier Strike Group somewhere in the Persian Gulf/Red Sea area of operation. Filmed September 23, 2014.

Film Credits: Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Abe McNatt

2516.description:
The guided-missile destroyer USS Arleigh Burke (DDG 51) launches Tomahawk Land-Attack Missiles (TLAM). Filmed September 23, 2014.

Film Credits: Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Carlos M. Vazquez II

2517.description:
Marine Aircraft Group 24 (MAG-24) launch all available helicopters in a max launch training exercise out of Marine Corps Air Station, Kaneohe Bay in Hawaii. Mag 24 consists of CH-53D Sea Stallion, AH-1W Super Cobra, and UH-1Y Venom "Super Huey" helicopters.

Film Credits: Cpl Taryn McKenzie

2518.description:
U.S. F/A-18 pilots with Marine Aircraft Group 31 (MAG-31) conduct field carrier landing practice (FCLP) at Marine Corps Air Station Beaufort in SC. 

Film Credits: Cpl Donald Holbert

2519.description:
U.S. Marines and Sailors with Charlie Company, 1st Battalion, 2d Marine Regiment, conduct multiple security patrols in the area of Haji Tahir Estates, Helmand province, Afghanistan, from 9 to 13 September, 2014. 

Film Credits: Cpl John Martinez

2520.description:
U.S. combat engineers and explosive ordnance disposal technicians use C4 explosives to blow the wings off an unserviceable C-130 Hercules aircraft at Forward Operating Base Shank in Afghanistan. The controlled demolition was done in order to remove the aircraft from the airfield. 

Film Credits: SGT Bob Yarbrough

2521.description:
The U.S. aircraft carrier USS George H.W.Bush (CVN-77) sends warplanes to strike ISIS terrorists in Iraq. Filmed on September 19, 2014. 

Film Credits: Damon Moritz

2522.description: A Mark 32 shipboard torpedo launcher rotates and fires a MK 46 exercise torpedo into the Pacific Ocean during operation Valiant Shield 2014. Filmed September 19, 2014.

2523.description:
A KC-135 Stratotanker refuels F-15 Eagle fighter jets over the South Pacific as part of operation Valiant Shield 2014. Filmed September 19, 2014.

Film Credits: LCpl Abbey Perria

2524.description: A U.S. Soldier is targeted by insurgents in Iraq.

2525.description:
U.S.Army Troops from the 4th Infantry engage Taliban forces in the Waterpur Valley, Qatar Kala, Kunar in Afghanistan. 

Film Credits: SSG Justin Puetz

2526.description:
Two Clips - First clip showing Marine Corps Scout Snipers training with various sniper rifles at the Bradshaw Training Area in Australia. Second clip showing U.S. Army Snipers at Outpost Mace, AF.

Film Credit: Sgt John Lamb, SSG Elwyn Lovelace

2527.description:
Flight operations aboard the aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77), as F/A-18 Hornets and EA-6B Prowlers are recovered and launched during surveillance, and reconnaissance missions. The GHW Bush is the tenth and final Nimitz-class supercarrier of the United States Navy, and is currently stationed in the Persian Gulf. Filmed September 16, 2014.

Film Credits: Damon Moritz

2528.description:
USAF C-130 Hercules transport planes from the 142nd Airlift Squadron depart Ramstein Air Base, Germany headed for Lielvarde Air Base, Latvia to transport U.S. Army Troops back to Ramstein Air Base. Includes pilot POV scenes on takeoff and landing, plus communications. Filmed September 7, 2014.

Film Credits: TSgt David Clark

2529.description:
Members of Task Force Flying Dragons qualify as aerial gunners from a CH-47 Chinook using the 240B Machine Gun on September 8, 2014. The Flying Dragons are part of 1st General Support Aviation Battalion, 52nd Aviation Regiment, 16th Combat Aviation Brigade, stationed at Kandahar Airfield, Afghanistan.

Film Credits: SSG Lyndsey Prax, SFC Brock Jones

2530.description:
U.S. Marines qualify in the new Combat Pistol Program. Plus Marines participate in the marksmanship phase of a close-quarters tactics course aboard Camp Pendleton, California, September 9, 2014.

Film Credits: Sgt Joseph Scanlan, Cpl Anna Albrecht

2531.description:
Three clips (1) M1A2 Abrams tanks maneuver and fire at night. (2) U.S. Army Strykers call in A-10 Thunderbolts for close air support/live fire exercise. (3) Soldiers at Forward Operating Base Lightning react to indirect fire and return fire with the M-777 howitzer in Afghanistan.

Film Credits: SGT Aaron Ricca, SPC Jonathan Farris, SPC Erik Warren

2532.description:
U.S Marines conduct speed disassembly and reassembly drills on the M240 Bravo machine gun to improve proficiency with the weapon.

Film Credits: Cpl Taryn McKenzie

2533.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers are attacked and return fire at Combat Outpost Able Main in Konar Province, Afghanistan.

Film Credits: SGT Russell Gilchrest

2534.description:
F/A-18 Hornets land and catapult off the flight deck of the aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN 77) 9/10/2014. George H.W. Bush continues to launch airstrikes on ISIS/ISIL as of this posting, and President Obama is poised to engage the terrorist group in Syria. 

Film Credits: Damon Moritz

2535.description: A mission out of NATO Airbase Geilenkirchen in Germany highlighting the capabilities of the aircraft.

2536.description: Soldiers from the United Kingdom have always been on the forefront of contact and combat in Afghanistan. Thanks to our British allies... "Speaking for all Americans, I want to say how very much at home we feel in your house... Here the rights of free people and the processes of representation have been debated and refined." - President Ronald Reagan - June 8, 1982

2537.description:
An A-10 Thunderbolt II maintenance crew loads a "Warthog" with bombs, missiles, and bullets in preparation for a sortie. Plus aircraft takeoff, and guntape (gun camera) footage of combat missions over Afghanistan.  

Film & Image Credits: SrA Samantha Konieczny, SSgt Daniel Negrete, SrA Anthony Hetlage, SMSgt Cecilio Ricardo
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2538.description:
Guntape (gun camera) footage of various aircraft during combat operations over Iraq and Afghanistan. Footage includes clips of an F-16 Falcon strike with a 500lb GPS guided bomb in Iraq, A-10 Thunderbolt II "Warthog" bombing and strafing targets in Afghanistan, and AH-64 Apache Helicopters destroying targets with machine guns and missiles in Afghanistan.

Film Credits: SrA Anthony Hetlage
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2539.description:
U.S. Marines Rapid Amphibious Assault Training. Assault Amphibious Vehicles (AAV) are launched enroute to a beachhead at Camp Pendleton, then are recovered to the well deck of USS Rushmore (LSD-47).  

Film Credits: Cpl Mark Garcia
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2540.description:
A remote piloted drone used by the U.S. Military for reconnaissance, surveillance, target acquisition and battle damage assessment. It is launched from a trailer-mounted catapult and recovered by arresting gear similar to jets on an aircraft carrier. Filmed in Afghanistan. 

Film Credits: SGT Patrick Wolfe

2541.description:
A KC-130J Harvest Hawk Gunship test fires Hellfire missiles near Marine Corps Air Station Yuma, Arizona. The Harvest Hawk is equipped with Hellfire rockets on the wings and Griffin missile launchers in the cargo bay.  

Film Credits: Cpl Jesse Witten

2542.description:
U.S. Army Specialist Reyes performs her first slingload hookup, with GoPro (helmet cam) footage to give you a firsthand look at what it's like to have a helicopter hover a few feet overhead.  

Film Credits: SSgt Kyle Richardson

2543.description:
Paratroopers from 1st Squadron, 91st Cavalry Regiment, 173rd Airborne Brigade prepare in a hanger and then jump into Latvia from a U.S. Air Force C-130 on August 20, 2014.  

Film Credits: PO1 Brett Cote

2544.description:
U.S. Navy divers explore an underwater wreck during a joint dive with Colombian divers from the Departamento de Buceo y Salvamento. The dive was filmed on September 1, 2014 off the coast of Cartagena as part of Southern Partnership Station 2014. Southern Partnership Station 2014 is a U.S. Navy deployment focused on expert exchanges with partner nation militaries and security forces in Central and South America and the Caribbean. Unit - Mobile Diving and Salvage Unit Two (MDSU 2) Company 2-1.  

Film Credits: PO1 Brett Cote

2545.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers with Grimm Troop, 3d Squadron, 3d Cavalry Regiment conduct a foot patrol in Wardak Province, Afghanistan and make contact with enemy fighters, engaging them in a brief firefight. The soldiers were conducting a KLE (key leader engagement). Filmed August 26, 2014. Unit - Grimm Troop, 3rd Squadron, 3rd Cavalry Regiment based out of Fort Hood, Texas.

Film Credits: SGT Nicholas De La Pena

2546.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers from 3rd platoon Apache Company conduct a patrol through Shawali Khan, Afghanistan and take small arms fire from enemy insurgents. U.S. Soldiers engaged the enemy causing them to break and flee after a six minute firefight. Filmed March 2012. Unit - 3rd platoon Apache Company 1st Battalion 23rd Infantry Regiment based out of Joint Base McChord-Lewis, WA.

Film Credits: SGT Mark Jachlewski

2547.description:
Soldiers with the 4th Infantry Division qualify for the German Armed Forces Badge of Marksmanship Proficiency (Schützenschnur) at Kandahar Airfield in Afghanistan. The Schützenschnur is a decoration for weapons proficiency for enlisted soldiers, and is one of the few foreign awards U.S. military personnel are authorized to wear in uniform. To earn the badge, soldiers had to successfully shoot the German P8 pistol and G36 service rifle at targets from a standing, kneeling, and prone position, with a limited amount of ammunition. Filmed on June 19, 2014.

Film Credits: SSG Lyndsey Prax

2548.description:
The Phalanx Close-In Weapons System (CIWS) was designed to be a last line of defense for anti-ship missiles. It consists of a radar-guided 20 mm Gatling gun mounted on a swivel base and can fire 4,500 rounds/minute (75 rounds/second). The effective firing range is 3.6 km (2.2 mi). The CIWS can also be used to defend against fast-attack boats and surface threats. Filmed aboard the U.S. Coast Guard Cutter Bertholf (WMSL-750).

Film Credits: PO1 Henry Dunphy

2549.description:
A U.S. Air Force C-17 Globemaster airdrops humanitarian supplies over Amirli, Iraq at night on August 31, 2014.

Film Credits: MSgt Michael Garza

2550.description:
First Clip - U.S. Marines with Marine Rotational Force Darwin conduct a helicopter insertion followed by support by fire mission during Exercise Koolendong 2014. 
Second Clip - Australian Army soldiers with the 101 Battery conduct a small arms and defensive position live-fire range during Exercise Koolendong 2014. 

Exercise Koolendong 2014, held in August at Bradshaw Field Training Area - Northern Territory in Australia, is a joint military training exercise for US and Australian personnel to conduct a battalion-sized live-fire operation. http://www.abc.net.au/news/2013-08-27/operation-koolendong-preview-us-marines-bradshaw-field-training/4915944  

Film Credits:  LCpl Jacob Hug, Sgt John Lamb
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2551.description:
MV-22 Ospreys with 11th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU) refuel from a KC-130J Super Hercules as part of a long-range assault during WESTPAC deployment, off the coast of Hawaii on July 30, 2014. Plus 24th MEU aerial refueling and landing on the USS Iwo Jima (LHD-7). 

Film Credits: LCpl Evan White, LCpl Tucker Wolf

2552.description: U.S. Navy F/A-18F Super Hornets return to the flight deck aboard the aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN 77) following a mission over Iraq. Then more Super Hornets are launched to strike additional ISIL targets.  Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video/Released August 29, 2014

2553.description:
Marines with the 11th Marine Expeditionary Unit conduct close quarters training as part of WESTPAC deployment to Marine Corps Base, Hawaii. 

Film Credits: LCpl Evan White

2554.description:
Flight line operations are highlighted in this video filmed at Eielson Air Force Base in Alaska. Watch scenes featuring pilot prep, ground crews performing preflight duties, aircraft taxi and takeoff... including F-16 Falcons, A-10 Thunderbolts, and a C-5 Galaxy. 

Film Credits: TSgt Matt Hecht

2555.description:
Mass launch of C-17 Globemaster III, C-5 Galaxy, and KC-10 Extender aircraft from the 60th Air Mobility Wing at Travis Air Force Base in California, to test the combat capability of large formation operation. 

Film Credits: SSgt John Ayre

2556.description:
Members of the U.S. Army's 5-25 Field Artillery train an Afghan fire support team on the D-30 122mm howitzer. The D-30 is a Soviet made howitzer that first entered service in the 1960s, and is still used by many armies around the world. Filmed at Forward Operating Base Tagab, Kapisa Province, Afghanistan - 2013.

Film Credits: SSG Brittany Conley

2557.description:
Maintenance on an F-16 fighter jet requires removing the bombs, missiles, and engine to replace a hydraulic line. Filmed at Bagram Airfield, Afghanistan - 2014.

Film Credits: SrA Anthony Hetlage

2558.description:
F-16 fighter jets hot refuel (hot pit) at Tulsa Air National Guard Base, Oklahoma on August 13, 2014. Hot fueling means fueling with the engines running.

Film Credit: TSgt Jeffery Foster

2559.description:
173rd Airborne Brigade paratroopers cross-train on Polish anti-tank RPG weapons at Drawsko Pomorskie, Poland.

Film Credits: SGT Lloyd Harger

2560.description:
Aircraft Rescue Firefighters training to be the first on the scene for aircraft emergencies at Marine Corps Air Station Iwakuni, Japan on August 25, 2014.

Film Credits: Cpl Anthony Rayis

2561.description:
A U.S. Air Force C-17 Globemaster III transport plane performs touch-and-go landings at Travis Air Force Base, California.  

Image and Film Credits: NASA Photo/Jim Ross, A1C Chacarra Walker, TSgt Jason Robertson, SSgt John Ayre  
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2562.description:
The aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) deployed in the Persian Gulf, launches and recovers aircraft during flight deck operations in support of air strikes on ISIS targets in Iraq. Filmed August 23, 2014.

Film Credits: Sgt Paul Peterson

2563.description:
A combat training mission over the Pacific with F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 18th Aggressor Squadron USAF, and aircraft from the Japan Air Self Defense Force, and the Royal Australian Air Force - cockpit video from F-16.  

Image and Film Credits: TSgt Christopher Boitz,  LT Joe Painter, Staff Sgt. Angelita M. Lawrence, SSgt Michelle Revoir

2564.description:
Marines engage targets in a live-fire exercise designed to hone their ability to rapidly respond to combat situations from a vehicle.

Film Credits: Sgt Paul Peterson

2565.description:
B-52 bombers takeoff and land with drag-chute (also called drogue-chute) at Minot Air Force Base in North Dakota. 

Film Credits: SrA Brandi Hansen

2566.description:
U.S. Army 2nd Cavalry Regiment conducts demolition training with C4 explosive by blowing a railroad tie in half, and then chopping down 7 tree trunks in unison. Filmed at Grafenwoehr Training Area, Germany on August 21, 2014.

Film Credits: SGT Kyle Burns

2567.description:
U.S. Marines throw live hand grenades (frags) during a live-fire exercise at Arta Range in Djibouti. The 13th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU) is based out of Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton, California.

Film Credits: SSgt Erik Cardenas

2568.description:
Gun Camera footage from an AC-130H Spectre Gunship flying a combat mission over Afghanistan - striking insurgents in a wooded area. The Gunship, providing close air support for "friendlies", strikes with such force that it actually chops down a tree under which insurgents are taking cover. 

The AC-130H was retired from service in 2013 - to be replaced by the AC-130J Ghostrider.

Film Credits: SrA James Bell, SrA Brandi Hansen 
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2569.description:
AH-1W SuperCobra attack helicopters conduct a live-fire demonstration using machine guns, rockets, and anti-missile flares at Camp Pendleton, California. The Bell AH-1W is the primary helicopter gunship used by the U.S. Marine Corps.

Image & Film Credits: Sgt Isaac Lamberth, GySgt Matt Epright, Cpl Tyler Gregory, LCpl Katelyn Hunter, Cpl. Marcus J. Kuiper
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2570.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers from the 7th Infantry Division undergo training with CS gas, also known as tear gas. They enter the gas chamber to gain confidence that their masks will protect them. Then they take off their masks while in the chamber for a firsthand experience of what CS gas is like.   

Film Credits: SGT Chad Guthrie

2571.description:
Marine Light Attack Helicopter Squadron 369 (HMLA-369), also known as the "Gunfighters", conduct a live fire urban close air support exercise at Marine Corps Air Station Yuma on August 20, 2104.   

Film Credits: Cpl Reba James

2572.description:
U.S. Marines with Heavy Helicopter Squadron 464 use a CH-53E Super Stallion to airlift a Humvee, in a Helicopter Support Team (HST) training exercise at Camp LeJeune, NC. 

Film Credits: Cpl William Kresse

2573.description:
Flight deck operations aboard the USS Kearsarge showing AV-8B Harrier aircraft prep, takeoff and landing. The USS Kearsarge (LHD-3) is an amphibious assault ship - Landing Helicopter Dock - which carries U.S. Marines, AV-8B Harrier and MV-22 Osprey aircraft, various helicopters, and LCAC hovercraft.

Film Credits: MCS3 Scott Pittman

2574.description:
During Red Flag Operations at Nellis AFB, a multitude of different kinds of combat aircraft taxi, takeoff, and land - day and night. Scenes include, F-15 Eagle, F-16 Falcon, F-18 Hornet, F-22 Raptor, British Typhoon, B-52 Bomber, B-2 Bomber, and E-3 AWACS. Red Flag is an advanced aerial combat training exercise held each year at Nellis Air Force Base in Nevada.

Film Credit: SrA Aaron Hauser, William Lewis, and SrA Rachel Maxwell

2575.description:
U.S. Marines with Scout Sniper Platoon, 5th Marine Regiment practice marksmanship with the M40A5 bolt action sniper rifle, the M110 (SASS) Semi Automatic sniper rifle, and the M107 (SASR) .50 cal sniper rifle at the Bradshaw Field Training Area, Northern Territory, Australia, August 18, 2014. 

Film Credits: Sgt John Lamb

2576.description:
Multiple clips of the FGM-148 Javelin in action - a shoulder fired missile used against tanks. But it can also be used as an anti-personnel weapon. It has an effective range of 2500 meters.

Film Credits: SPC Britni Alexander, WO Michael Kropiewnicki, SFC Walter Talens, Stuart Chapman, Master Sgt. Christina Bhatti, Cpl Paul Torres 
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2577.description:
Pilots from the 421st Fighter Squadron, 388th Fighter Wing, Hill Air Force Base, UT, performs in air operations in a F-16 Fighting Falcon to maintain aerial currency on December 20th, 2012.

Film Credits: TSgt Kurtis Villavicencio, SSgt Roidan Carlson

2578.description:
Explosive Ordnance Disposal Marines are trained to handle hazardous materials and disarm explosives such as IED's and weapons of mass destruction. Their missions take them to every part of the world. They perform with the precision of a surgeon, operating on wires and detonators that could spell disaster at any moment.

Film Credits: Cpl Anthony Rayis

2579.description:
U.S. Marines with the 5th Marine Regiment conduct a live-fire company helo assault during Exercise Koolendong 2014 at Bradshaw Field Training Area, Northern Territory in Australia on August 18, 2014.

Film Credits: LCpl Joshua Chacon

2580.description:
An F-22 Raptor pilot inspects his aircraft, footage of takeoff and landing at Nellis AFB, and refueling air-to-air in the skies over Nevada. 

Film Credits: SrA Aaron Hauser, SrA Rachel Maxwell, SSgt Jose Rodriguez, A1C Rachel Webster, MSgt Amy Cartas  
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2581.description:
U.S. Marines with Marine Rotational Force-Darwin conduct a live-fire combat exercise at Bradshaw Field Training Area in Australia during Exercise Koolendong 2014. The exercise combined headquarters elements, directing ground, aviation, and logistics capabilities to hone the Marines skills in combat conditions. Filmed August 19, 2014.

Film Credits: Cpl Scott Reel

2582.description:
The Ultra Heavy-Lift Amphibious Connector (UHAC), a prototype amphibious transport vehicle, enters the well deck of the USS Rushmore. The U.S. Navy tested the UHAC during RIMPAC 2014 to evaluate it as a potential future technology solution for deployment. Includes GoPro footage.

Film Credits: Kyle Olson, GySgt Jeremy Vought
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2583.description:
Flight Deck Operations aboard the aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN 77) in the The Persian Gulf as aircraft are launched for airstrikes on ISIS terrorists in Iraq. Filmed August 17, 2014.


Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video/Released August 19, 2014

2584.description:
An AC-130 dispenses anti-missile flares, sometimes called "Angel Flares" because of the characteristic pattern they display. The flares are designed to confuse heat-seeking missiles. Filmed August 18, 2014.

Film Credits: TSgt Kevin Dennison and SrA Nicholas Koetz

2585.description:
Near Tactical Base Dwyerin in Afghanistan, "Suicide Charley" company with the 7th Marines conducts a night mortar fire mission with illumination rounds to keep an eye on the enemy. Filmed July 21, 2014.

Film Credits: SGT Christopher Tobey

2586.description:
U.S. F-16 Fighting Falcons from Spangdahlem Air Base in Germany taxi and takeoff enroute to a joint training exercise in Souda Bay, Greece. Filmed August 8, 2014.

Film Credits: A1C Sarah Denewellis

2587.description:
Marines with 1st Tank Battalion let it rip with their M1A1 Abrams Main Battle Tanks in an awesome display of ground-shaking firepower. The live-fire exercise was held at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center, Twentynine Palms in California.

Film Credits: Cpl Joseph Peterson

2588.description:
The U.S. Navy conducted the latest test launch & landing of the unmanned X-47B aboard the aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt (CVN 71) on August 17, 2014. The Navy tested the aircraft's ability to operate safely and seamlessly with manned aircraft.

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video/Released August 17, 2014

2589.description:
Multiple video clips of C-130s taking off.

Film Credits: William Lewis, SrA Garrett Wake, SrA Joshua Roberts, SrA Kristine MacDonald, A1C Rebecca Long, SrA Rachel Maxwell
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2590.description:
A live-fire exercise with Marines of Marine Rotational Force Darwin. The "movement to contact" training was part of Exercise Koolendong at Bradshaw Field Training Area, Northern Territory in Australia. Filmed August 15, 2014.

Film Credits: LCpl Jacob Hug

2591.description:
Multiple clips of guntape, or gun camera video from U.S. Army Apache helicopters in combat over Iraq and Afghanistan.
The AH-64 Apache is a twin engine attack helicopter with a two-man crew. The pilot sits above and behind the co-pilot, and each crew member is capable of flying the helicopter or operating the weapons systems. It is armed with a 30mm M230 Chain Gun mounted under the aircraft and just forward of the main landing gear. The Apache can also launch Hellfire, Hydra, and Stinger missiles. 

Film & Image Credits: SSG Roberto Di Giovine, Dustin Senger, TSgt Matt Hecht, Spc. Erin Dierschow, CWO2 George Chino, SSG Mark Shrewsbury
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2592.description:
U.S. Marines with 2nd Low Altitude Air Defense Battalion conduct a Stinger Missile live-fire exercise at Onslow Beach, Camp Lejeune - March 2014.  

Film Credits: LCpl Zachary Montgomery

2593.description: A-6 Intruders and C-2A Greyhounds takeoff & land aboard the USS Enterprise (CVN-65). Enterprise was the first nuclear powered aircraft carrier of the U.S. Navy. She was decommissioned in December 2012. The "Enterprise" name will live on though, with the USS Enterprise (CVN-80), a future Gerald R. Ford-class aircraft carrier. Filmed on March 12, 2012.

2594.description:
Officially known as the M1128, the U.S. Army's Mobile Gun System fires off a few rounds in this video to show the deadly power it can direct. The MGS is an eight-wheeled armored vehicle mounted with a 105mm tank gun... the same gun mounted on the original Abrams tank. The U.S. Army uses the MGS to provide direct fire support for infantry troops.

Film Credits: PFC Daniel Lograsso, SPC Andrew Geisler 
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2595.description:
A "Super Huey" UH-1Y Venom helicopter and crew takeoff on a live-fire training mission over Hawaii. The door gunners fire a M134 Minigun and a Browning .50 Caliber Machine Gun.

Film Credits: Sgt Robert Bush

2596.description:
Flight deck operations on the aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN 77) while launching F/A-18 Hornets and Super Hornets for airstrikes in Iraq on August 12, 2014.

Film Credits: Damon Moritz

2597.description:
Marines from Black Sea Rotational Force train in a live-fire platoon attack operation at the Novo Selo Training Ground in Bulgaria. The Marines trained alongside soldiers from Bulgaria, Romania, Azerbaijan, and the United Kingdom. Filmed July 2014.

Film Credits: SSgt Tanner Iskra

2598.description:
The 180th Airlift Squadron does a cargo airdrop from a C-130 Hercules with a camera mounted on the cargo. 

Film Credits: SrA Sheldon Thompson

2599.description:
Marines of the 7th Marine Regiment participate in a three-day battalion assault course at Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms. 

Film Credits: Sgt Joseph Scanlan

2600.description:
Airmen from Kunsan Air Base in South Korea board a C-17 Globemaster headed for the Red Flag Exercise in Alaska. Also 8th Fighter Wing F-16 Fighting Falcons from Kunsan takeoff for Red Flag Alaska. Red Flag-Alaska is an air combat training exercise held at Elmendorf Air Force Base, AK. 

Film Credits: SSgt Jose Rodriguez

2601.description:
F/A-18 Hornets and Super Hornets, plus an E-2C Hawkeye "Mini-AWACS" launch from the aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) in support of Operation Inherent Resolve. Filmed on August 11, 2014 - Location: Arabian Gulf. 

Film Credits: U.S. Navy Video/Released On August 12, 2014

2602.description:
U.S. Navy Sailors aboard the aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN 77) build GBU-54 bombs. Filmed on August 9, 2014.

Film Credits:  Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Preston Paglinawan

2603.description:
Cockpit video from an F/A18F Super Hornet - Fighting Black Lions of Strike Fighter Squadron (VFA) 213 - aboard the Aircraft Carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) in support of airstrikes on ISIS targets in Iraq. Filmed August 10, 2014.

Film Credits: Lt. Micheal Reilly

2604.description:
Footage of a Hawaii National Guard CH-47 Chinook routine training flight over Oahu Island, Hawaii.

Film Credits: TSgt Andrew Jackson

2605.description:
U.S. Marines from 3rd Law Enforcement Battalion conduct taser training with members of the Philippine Armed Forces and National Police. Participants were tasered by the Marines to experience the effects of the electroshock weapon.

Film Credits: Sgt Robert Bush

2606.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcons - 100th Expeditionary Fighter Squadron - preflight preparations and takeoff from Bagram Airfield in Afghanistan. The 100th EFS is deployed from Montgomery, Alabama and part of the 187th Fighter Wing. Filmed August 11, 2014. 

Film Credits: SSgt Miguel Lara

2607.description:
The 4th Infantry Brigade Combat Team (Airborne) jump over Big Lake in Alaska using the T-11 parachute for the first time in a water jump.  

Film Credits: SGT Balinda O'Neal, A1C Carly Kavish  
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2608.description:
The Aircraft Carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) recovers F/A-18 Strike Fighters after they pound the terror group ISIS with airstrikes in Iraq. Filmed July 8, 2014.

Film Credit: Mass Communication Specialist Seaman David Lee

2609.description:
The U.S. Army's M109A6 Paladin packs a powerful punch as seen in this video - several of the armored tracked vehicles send their 155mm shells downrange and shake the ground. The Paladin has an effective firing range of 11 miles with a sustained 3 rounds per minute, and a crew of 4: the commander, driver, gunner, and ammunition loader.   

Image and Film Credits: MAJ Brooks Little, SGT Quentin Johnson, SSgt Jeremy Bowcock, SPC Brian Chaney, SGT Kristi Potts, SSG John Higgins, SSG Christopher Jelle, SGT Fred Brown, SGT Ellis McDaniels, SPC John Brandenburg

Range 48 is the largest live-fire range on Fort Drum, allowing service members to train on everything from small arms to artillery, to allowing military pilots to practice firing weapons systems.

The CIWS is a radar guided 20 mm M61 Vulcan Gatling gun autocannon used primarily for defence against anti-ship missiles. It is installed on all U.S. Navy surface combatant ships, and is capable of locking onto incoming missiles and firing 4,500 rounds per minute.

2637.description:
The massive Ultra Heavy-Lift Amphibious Connector (UHAC) "you-hack" - it looks a lot like a tank but it actually floats like a boat. The new transport vehicle is being considered by the U.S. Marine Corps as a replacement for it's 20 year old fleet of LCAC hovercrafts. The UHAC travels across water much like an old river paddleboat did in years past.

Although the UHAC prototype appears slow and cumbersome, the full production model now on the drawing board will have some distinct advantages over LCAC hovercrafts currently deployed by the Marine Corps. The full sized UHAC (the prototype in this video is only 4/10 scale) has a deckspace of 2500 square feet, significantly larger when compared to the LCAC's 1800. Plus, the UHAC can carry three M-1 Abrams tanks, or up to 190 tons. In contrast, the LCAC can carry one M-1 or 65 tons.

With the added advantage of the UHAC's ability to transport cargo inland after landing on the beach, you can see why the Marines are giving this massive vehicle a lot of thought. All things considered, it will be very interesting to watch a full sized UHAC display it's capabilities.

Film & Image Credits: Kyle Olson, GySgt Jeremy Vought, Cpl Matthew Bragg, MSgt Ryan Kruse, LCpl Aaron Patterson 
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

Film Credits: SrA Benjamin Landon

2710.description:
Watch as U.S. F/A-18D Strike Fighters go through pre-flight checks, takeoff, aerial refueling, and landing - some good cockpit video and POV footage from a mission over Australia's Northern Territory. Aerial footage courtesy of Major Erik Sprague, VMFA(AW)-242, USMC out of RAAF Base Tindal.

Film Credits:  Cpl Anthony Rayis

2711.description:
F-15 cockpit video. Check out the reflection... is that the Devil?

Film Credits: SSgt Erin Mills
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2712.description:
Marine Warfighting Lab in Quantico, Virginia conducts live fire experimentation with robots to find out what is the most effective technique for Marines to engage moving targets.

Film Credits:  Cpl Allison Beiswanger

2713.description:
Marines from Camp Pendleton California travel to the firing range and conduct live-fire training with weapons systems of the LAV-25 light armored vehicle.

Film Credits:  Cpl James Gulliver

2714.description:
U.S. Marine Corp Harriers prepare for takeoff at Tyndall Air Force Base, Florida. Plus Harriers refuel in flight over scenic Southern California.

Film Credits:  Cpl Maxwell Pennington & Cpl Jesse Witten

2715.description:
The Missile Defense Agency's Flight Test 06b Ground-Based Interceptor launches from Vandenberg Air Force Base, California on June 22, 2014.

Film Credits: Debra Christman

2716.description:
Hot pit refueling of F-35B Lightning II jets at Marine Corps Air Station Miramar. Hot refueling is when the engines are still operating. Plus aerial footage of F-35s filmed from the back of a C-130.

Film Credits: Cpl Jesse Witten & Cpl Maxwell Pennington

2717.description:
The Aircraft Carrier USS Nimitz (CVN 68) launches an E-2C Hawkeye radar surveillance plane, and F/A-18 Hornet strike fighters.

Film Credits: PO3 Joshua Haiar

2718.description:
Flight operations at Bodø Main Air Station in Norway during Arctic Challenge Exercise 2013. Footage of U.S. F-15s from RAF Lakenheath, Norwegian F-16s, and Swedish JAS-39 Gripens.

Film Credits: A1C Amanda Sampson

2719.description:
Footage of an Unmanned Aerial Vehicle (Micro Drone) being considered by the U.S. Military for surveillance and recon operations.
  
Film Credits: Raymond Sarracino

2720.description:
The British Royal Air Force Red Arrows taxi, takeoff, and land at RAF Fairford on June 5, 2014.

Film Credits: SSgt Joseph Vigil

2721.description:
CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters from the USS Bataan conduct aerial refueling with C-130 Hercules aircraft over the Mediterranean Sea on June 15, 2014.

Film Credits: SSgt Tanner Iskra

2722.description:
The nuclear powered aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) conducts flight deck operations in the Persian Gulf. Filmed on June 17, 2014.

USS George H.W. Bush (CVN-77) is the tenth and final Nimitz-class supercarrier of the United States Navy. It is 1,092 feet in length (longer than 3 football fields), displaces 102,000 tons, and is powered by 2 Westinghouse A4W nuclear reactors. The Bush has a top speed in excess of 30 knots (56 km/h or 35 mph), and carries 90 fixed wing aircraft and helicopters. 

Film Credits: PO3 Ryan Seelbach

2723.description:
U.S. Marines with the 2nd Marine Division conduct a fire mission with M777 Howitzers at Ft. Bragg, NC in October 2013.    

Film Credits:  LCpl Justin Davis

2724.description:
F-16 fighter jets from Spangdahlem Air Base in Germany refuel and show off for the camera somewhere over Europe as part of Baltic Operations 2014 (BALTOPS). BALTOPS consists of surface, subsurface and aviation assets from 14 nations that are training together to enhance interoperability and capabilities to benefit regional stability.
  
Film Credits:  SrA Laura Yahemiak

2725.description:
U.S. M1A2 Abrams and Romanian TR-85M1 tanks take part in military exercises at Grafenwoehr, Germany June 2014.

Film Credits: SGT Ellis McDaniels

2726.description:
B-52 bombers are refueled in the skies somewhere over Europe as part of Baltic Operations (BALTOPS) 2014. BALTOPS consists of surface, subsurface and aviation assets from 14 nations that are training together to enhance interoperability and capabilities to benefit regional stability.

Film Credit: SrA Laura Yahemiak

2727.description:
Footage of remotely piloted aircraft MQ-1 Predator and MQ-9 Reaper out of Holloman Air Force Base in New Mexico. What is the difference between the Predator and Reaper drones? 

The Reaper is larger than the Predator and has a more powerful 950 hp turboprop engine, whereas the Predator has a 115 hp piston engine. The Predator can carry Hellfire and Stinger missiles. The Reaper can carry Hellfire and Stinger missiles, but can also be armed with Paveway laser guided bombs and JDAM bombs. The MQ-9 Reaper can carry 15 times more ordnance payload and cruise at almost three times the speed of the MQ-1 Predator. To tell the difference between the two drones at a glance... the Reaper has tail fins on top, the Predator has tail fins on bottom.

2728.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers with Delta 2-5 Cav - calibrate the sights of M1A2 Abrams tanks, and then test fire them at the Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany.
  
Film Credits:  SGT Fred Brown

2729.description:
A U.S. Air Force KC-135 Stratotanker refuels Swedish JAS 39 Gripens during Baltic Operations 2014.

Film Credits:  SrA Laura Yahemiak

2730.description:
F-22's From Joint Base Pearl Harbor-Hickam, takeoff and land at RMAF Butterworth, Malaysia during Cope Taufan 2014.  Cope Taufan is a joint military exercise between U.S. and Malaysian forces to increase combined readiness and capability.

Film Credits:  A1C Eric Mann

2731.description:
A KC-135 from the 100th Air Refueling Squadron at RAF Mildenhall, UK refuels a B2 Spirit stealth bomber in-flight on June 11, 2014.

Film Credits:  SrA Laura Yahemiak

2732.description:
F-15 Eagles arrive at RMAF Butterworth in Malaysia for Cope Taufan 2014. The fighter jets are part of the 104th Fighter Wing from Barnes Air National Guard Base - Massachusetts. Cope Taufan is a joint military exercise between U.S. and Malaysian forces to increase combined readiness and capability.

Film Credits:  A1C Eric Mann

2733.description:
Marines with the 5th Marine Regiment conduct fast rope training from a CH-46 Sea Knight helicopter. Fast Rope Insertion Extraction System - (FRIES) - POV view.  

Film Credits:  Sgt Jacob Harrer

2734.description:
U.S. Marines F/A 18 Hornets and a Navy EA-6B Prowler get in-air refueling over Afghanistan by a KC-135 Stratotanker on May 8, 2014.     

Film Credits:  SSgt Erin Mills

2735.description:
Aircraft and cargo from Aviano Air Base in Italy takeoff for Nellis Air Force Base in Nevada, where Red Flag operations will begin in June 2014. Red Flag gives pilots and air crew an opportunity to experience realistic combat training and scenarios. 

Film Credits:  A1C Abbey Whittaker

2736.description:
Royal Malaysian Air Force and U.S. Air Force jets takeoff and land during Cope Taufan 2014. Cope Taufan is designed to improve U.S. and Malaysian combined readiness and interoperability. Cope Taufan marks the first deployment of the F-22 Raptor to a Southeast Asian exercise.   

Film Credits:  TSgt Andrew Jackson

2737.description:
Cockpit view of a U.S. Marines F/A-18 Super Hornet during takeoff, in flight, and landing. The F/A-18 is a two seat, twin-engine all-weather multirole combat jet, designed as both a fighter and attack aircraft. It is used on all U.S. aircraft carriers.   

Film Credits:  Cpl Anthony Rayis

2738.description:
The USS Iowa (BB-61) was the first battleship of the U.S. Navy, and in 1943 carried President Franklin D. Roosevelt across the Atlantic to a meeting with British Prime Minister Winston Churchill and Soviet leader Josef Stalin. She was decommissioned for the last time in October 1990, and is now berthed at the Port of Los Angeles.

Film Credits:  SPC Derek Sherwood, SPC Benjamin Soler, and SSG Ronald Widerberg

2739.description:
A small helicopter with major fire power, the OH-58D Kiowa Warrior is a single engine reconnaissance helicopter that sports an airframe capable of firing a mix of Hellfire missiles, Hydra 70 rockets, Stinger missiles or 50-calibre machine guns (depending on the mission). FYI - 120 Kiowas were deployed in the Iraq War and 29 helicopters were lost. The U.S. Army Kiowa fleet achieved a total of 750,000 combat hours until the end of the war in Iraq (2011)... to be continued.    

Film Credits:  SFC Eric Pahon

2740.description:
U.S. Army, 1st Armored Division "Old Ironsides" conducts a live fire exercise with M777 howitzers and M109 Paladins.

Film Credits:  SGT Bryan Spradlin

2741.description:
A pair of British RAF Tornados takeoff from Kandahar Air Field for a mission in Afghanistan... Plus, a U.S. Air Force KC-135 refuels an RAF Tornado GR4 in the skies over Afghanistan.

Film Credits:  SSgt Michelle Revoir

2742.description:
Cargo airdrop by C-17 and C-130 aircraft as part of the Joint Forcible Entry Exercise (JFEX) at Fort Greely, Alaska on June 7, 2014.

Film Credits: SGT Eric-James Estrada

2743.description:
The USS Benfold (DDG-65), an Arleigh Burke-class destroyer, departs Pearl Harbor, HI. The Benfold was commissioned in 1996, is 505 feet in length, displaces 9000 tons, and has a top speed of 30 knots (56 km/h). Her armament includes 90 x RIM-156 SM-2, BGM-109 Tomahawk or RUM-139 VL-Asroc missiles, 1 x Mark 45 deck gun, 2 x 25mm chain guns, 4 x 50 caliber (12.7mm) guns, 2 × 20mm Phalanx CIWS, and 2 × Mk 32 triple torpedo tubes. 

The Benfold is also equipped with AN/SLQ-25 Nixie Torpedo Countermeasures, MK 36 MOD 12 Decoy Launching System, and AN/SLQ-39 CHAFF Buoys. There is also a flight deck aft of the ship which will accommodate all US Military helicopters except the CH-53 Sea Stallion.

Film Credits:  SN John Ciccarelli

2744.description:
MV-22 Osprey aircraft takeoff and land aboard the USS Bataan (LHD-5) in the Mediterranean Sea on June 7, 2014. 

Film Credits:  SSgt Tanner Iskra

2745.description: U.S. Navy hovercrafts use Pearl Harbor for training maneuvers.

2746.description:
Live Fire test shots of the High Mobility Artillery Rocket System (HIMARS) in Jordan on May 4, 2014. HIMARS is a mobile rocket launcher capable of firing 6 GPS-guided missiles with a range exceeding 70km.

Film Credits: SGT Dawn Bartlett

2747.description:
