A C-17 Globemaster III from Dover AFB lands at RAF Fairford in Gloucestershire, England to prepare for local training exercises. May 2, 2014 

Film Credit:  SSgt Joseph Vigil

2748.description:
A C-5 Galaxy lands at RAF Fairford in Gloucestershire, England to prepare for local training exercises. May 2, 2014 

Film Credit:  SSgt Joseph Vigil

2749.description:
Three B-52 bombers land at RAF Fairford in Gloucestershire, England to prepare for local training exercises. May 6, 2014 

Film Credit:  SSgt Joseph Vigil

2750.description:
Personnel from the 455th Expeditionary Aerial Port and 83rd Expeditionary Rescue Squadron at Bagram Airfield, Afghanistan load two HH-60G Pave Hawk helicopters into a C-17 Globemaster headed for Moody Air Force Base, Georgia.

Film Credit:  SSgt Miguel Lara

2751.description:
Close Air Support live-fire training from a UH-1Y Huey helicopter. Door Gunners of the UH-1Y Venom gunship fire a GAU-21 .50 caliber machine gun and an M134 minigun at targets in the California desert.

Film Credits: Sgt Chad Pulliam

2752.description:
A compilation of U.S. Marines aircraft including the MV-22 Osprey, UH-1Y Huey, AH-1W SuperCobra, AV-8B Harrier, CH-53E Super Stallion, and F-35B Joint Strike Fighter. For the benefit of those who are unfamiliar, VTOL means Vertical Takeoff & Landing (like helicopters) and STOVL means Short Takeoff & Vertical Landing (like Harriers). 

Marines aircraft launched and recovered aboard U.S. Navy ships.  

Film Credits: WO Michael Kropiewnicki, MSgt Chad Kiehl, LCpl Alexander Pool, and LCpl Evan White

2753.description:
The U.S. Army's 2nd Cavalry Regiment - 4th Squadron "Saber Recon" conducts a mortar fire mission in Kandahar Province, Afghanistan to disrupt Taliban operations near the Pakistani border. Filmed November 14, 2013.

Film Credits: SGT Carl Greenwell

2754.description:
A fully loaded U.S. Navy LCAC hovercraft exits the amphibious assault ship USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6) and heads for the beach.

Film Credits: LCpl Alexander Pool

2755.description:
U.S. Navy ships USS Bataan (LHD-5) and USS Elrod (FFG-55) picked up 282 migrants in the Mediterranean Sea after receiving a report from an Italian military patrol plane that it had spotted six small boats. One of the boats was sinking. The distressed people were provided food, water, and medical attention. Five of the migrants were medically evacuated to Malta and 277 were transferred to a patrol vessel from the Armed Forces of Malta. - Sat June 7, 2014

Film Credits: Damon Moritz

2756.description:
F-15 and F-16 fighter jets participate in combat training and weapons evaluations in the skies over Salt Lake, Utah - cockpit video.

Film Credits: SSgt Robert Harnden

2757.description:
U.S. Marines assigned to Force Reconnaissance Platoon, 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit conduct parachute operations in Army UH-60 Black Hawk Helicopters.

Film Credits: Sgt Chris Stone

2758.description:
U.S. Coast Guard helicopter medical evacuation of crew member from a Trident Nuclear Submarine.

Film Credit:  PO2 Katrina Parker

2759.description:
Footage of the crash scene of a U.S. Marines AV-8B Harrier aircraft. The fighter jet crashed in a residential neighborhood in Imperial, California on the afternoon of June 4, 2014. The pilot ejected safely and was unhurt... it's a miracle that no one on the ground was injured, considering how much damage was done.

Film Credit:  Cpl Owen Kimbrel

2760.description:
Members of the U.S. Coast Guard train international students in evasion and pursuit drills near Dickenson Bay, Antigua and Barbuda - during Operation Tradewinds June 5, 2014. 

Film Credit: PO2 Robert Simpson

2761.description:
Spectacular aerial footage of a USAF Lockheed C-5 Galaxy flying over picturesque scenery, and firing flares.

For a similar video of the Boeing C-17 Globemaster go here - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fX_uBvn35Ew

2762.description:
An aerial view of Pearl Harbor Naval Base, with Navy Ships docked. Footage includes shots of the aircraft carrier USS Ronald Reagan (CVN-76) - amphibious assault ship USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6) - Arizona Memorial & Ford Island in background.

Film Credit: Petty Officer 2nd Class Corey Traux

2763.description:
A British Westland "Battlefield Lynx" helicopter executes landing qualifications aboard the amphibious assault ship USS Kearsarge (LHD 3) of the U.S. Navy.

Film Credit: Sgt Chris Stone

2764.description:
U.S. Marines with the 8th Marine Regiment and Romanian Soldiers of the 17th Mountain Troop Battalion conduct live fire exercises together. During the operation, the two forces trade weapons and show each other how to fire them. Filmed in the Carpathian Mountains, Romania on May 14, 2014.

Film Credit: LCpl Scott Whiting

2765.description:
F-15 Eagle fighter jets taxi and takeoff at Nellis Air Force Base in Nevada. Plus, POV cockpit footage from an F-15 combat training mission over Guam.

Film Credits: SrA Aaron Hauser, William Lewis, A1C Rebecca Long, SrA Rachel Maxwell, and SSgt Michelle Revoir

2766.description:
A-10 Thunderbolt Warthogs from the 422nd Test and Evaluation Squadron fire their Gatling cannons and rockets on the Nevada Range.

More about the Gau-8 Avenger gatling cannon: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pHv50lXfDHQ

Film Credit: William Lewis

2767.description:
U.S. pilots and crew chiefs rush to prepare F/A-18 Hornets and F-16 Fighting Falcons for takeoff in a scramble competition with members of the Royal Jordanian Air Force on May 13, 2014. 


U.S. Marines assigned to Marine Air Group 50, Marine Corps Air Station Miramar, CA and USAF pilots and crew from 13th Fighter Squadron at Misawa Air Base in Japan compete with members of the Royal Jordanian Air Force for fastest takeoff.

Film Credit: A1C Danny Rangel

2768.description:
USS Chancellorsville (CG 62) departs Pearl Harbor, HI. The Chancellorsville is a U.S. Navy Ticonderoga-class guided-missile cruiser commissioned in 1989. It is 567 feet in length, displaces 9,800 tons with a top speed of 32.5 knots (60 km/h). The Chancellorsville has an armament of:
  
2 × 61 cell Mk 41 vertical launch systems containing

    122 × mix of:
        RIM-66M-5 Standard SM-2MR Block IIIB
        RIM-156A SM-2ER Block IV
        RIM-161 SM-3
        RIM-162A ESSM
        RIM-174A Standard ERAM
        BGM-109 Tomahawk
        RUM-139A VL-ASROC

8 × RGM-84 Harpoon missiles
2 × Mk 45 Mod 2 5-in/54-cal lightweight gun
2 × 25 mm Mk 38 gun
2--4 × .50 cal (12.7 mm) gun
2 × Phalanx CIWS Block 1B
2 × Mk 32 12.75-in (324 mm) triple torpedo tubes for lightweight torpedoes 

2 × Sikorsky SH-60B or MH-60R Seahawk LAMPS III helicopters

Film Credit: Mass Communication Specialist 1st Class Jason Swink

2769.description:
CH-47F Chinook crews load and unload troops in Afghanistan. The CH-47F is upgraded from the older D model. The CH-47F can fly at speeds of over 175 mph with a payload of more than 21,000 lbs. The primary roles of the Chinook are troop movement, artillery placement, and battlefield resupply. 

Film Credits: SFC Eric Pahon

2770.description:
Apache Helicopters are designed to be lethal killing machines. This video shows just how deadly they are, with combat/gun tape footage, plus takeoff and landing scenes.

The Boeing AH-64 Apache is a twin engine attack helicopter with a two man crew. The pilot sits behind and above the copilot/gunner. Both crew members are capable of flying the aircraft and engaging weapons systems. 

The Apache armament includes a M230 Chain Gun, AGM-114 Hellfire missiles, and Hydra 70 rockets. 

In addition to the United States, the Apache is used by Egypt, Greece, India, Indonesia, Israel, Japan, South Korea, Kuwait, Netherlands, Saudi Arabia, Singapore, Taiwan (Republic of China), United Arab Emirates, and United Kingdom.

Film Credits: SFC Eric Pahon, SSG Mark Shrewsbury, PO1 Michael Sandberg, and SSG Justin Puetz
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2771.description:
Pre-deployment training on the M10 & .50 caliber sniper rifles.

Film Credit:  MSG Thomas Hovie

2772.description: A brief documentary highlighting the history of Edwards Air Force Base, and the cutting-edge aircraft that have been tested and developed there.

2773.description: The USS O'Kane (DDG-77) departs Pearl Harbor, HI. The O'Kane is a U.S. Navy Arleigh Burke-class destroyer commissioned in 1999. It is 505 feet in length, displaces 9000 tons, and has a top speed of 30 knots (56 km/h). Armament includes SAM missiles, Tomahawk cruise missiles, Asroc anti-submarine missiles, Mark 45 deck gun, 25mm chain guns, .50 caliber machine guns, Phalanx CIWIS, and Mk32 torpedoes.

2774.description:
Members of the U.S. Army 20th Special Forces Squadron participate in a helocasting training mission out of a CH-47 Chinook. Helocasting is an airborne technique used to insert special operations forces from helicopters over a body of water. Filmed April, 30 2014 

Film Credit: SSgt Michelle Revoir

2775.description:
Soldiers practice various shooting techniques with their individual weapons and qualify on the .50 Caliber machine gun range. U.S. Army Soldiers from the 1-82 CAV, 41st IBCT are training for their upcoming deployment to Afghanistan. Filmed May 31, 2014. 

Film Credit: MSG Thomas Hovie

2776.description:
HIMARS missile launch at the Melrose Training Range in New Mexico. HIMARS is the M142 High Mobility Artillery Rocket System, used successfully in Afghanistan to attack Taliban positions. One battery can fire 6 GPS guided missiles. It can launch the extended range guided rocket GMLRS with a range of more than 70km - or the block 1 missile delivers 950 anti-personnel anti-material (AP/AM) baseball-sized M74 submunitions to ranges exceeding 165km. HIMARS has also been tested with a variant of the AMRAAM anti-aircraft missile.

Film Credit: A1C Carly Kavish and SrA Sarah Trachte

2777.description:
In Arctic Pegasus 2014, paratroopers and equipment are air dropped over Deadhorse, Alaska which is above the Arctic Circle.

Film Credit: A1C Carly Kavish and SrA Sarah Trachte

2778.description:
Multi National Forces including United States and French Infantry conduct offensive operations during military exercises in Germany on May 29, 2014. Other nations participating in these exercises... Albania, Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, Croatia, Georgia, Hungary, Lithuania, Romania, Serbia, and Slovenia.

Film Credit: SGT Fred Brown

2779.description:
The Legged Squad Support System, or LS3 is a robotic "pack mule" being developed for the Marine Corps to lighten the load that marines must carry during combat foot patrols. Typically a marine carries 100 lbs or more of equipment that the LS3 can carry instead.

Film Credit: Cpl Christofer Baines and Cpl Clayton Filipowicz

2780.description:
Launching amphibious assault vehicles aboard the USS Pearl Harbor (LSD-52). It's a tight squeeze maneuvering those big machines shipboard.

Film Credit: Cpl Megan Scullin

2781.description:
An F-15 Eagle takes on fuel in-flight during Icelandic Air Policing. Iceland does not have an air force, so in 2006, after Russian aircraft entered Icelandic airspace on several occasions they requested that their NATO allies assume the responsibility of protecting Iceland's air space. NATO agreed to the request in 2007. But the Icelandic Government also requested that NATO not maintain a permanent force at Keflavik. So instead, an average of three deployments are made per year, with each lasting from two to three weeks. The countries that have sent aircraft so far... France, USA, Denmark, Norway, Germany, Canada, Portugal, and Italy. Future deployments are also scheduled from... Finland, Sweden, and the Czech Republic.

Film Credit: A1C Amanda Sampson

2782.description:
A C-17 Globemaster airdrop over Afghanistan resupplies an Army outpost.

Film Credit: SSgt Jeffrey Curtin

2783.description:
Marines qualify with pistols in the new Combat Pistol Program at Camp Pendleton, CA. - November 2013.

Film Credit: Cpl Joseph Scanlan

2784.description:
U.S. Marines, 1st Tank Battalion conduct a live fire exercise at the Twentynine Palms range that lasts well into the night.

Film Credit: Cpl Joseph Peterson

2785.description:
82nd Airborne Division soldiers jump out of C-17 aircraft over the Luzon drop zone Fort Bragg, NC. Plus POV footage of a 173rd Airborne Brigade Combat Team "Sky Soldier" jumping over Yavoriv, Ukraine.

Film Credit: SrA Brandi Hansen and SrA Erin Mills

2786.description:
A KC-10 Extender mission over the middle east refuels four different kinds of aircraft... E-3 Sentry (AWACS), A-10 Thunderbolt II, French Mirage F1, and F/A-18 Super Hornet.

Film Credit: TSgt Matthew Pardini

2787.description:
Soldiers undergo a pre-deployment training with the AT-4 anti-tank weapon.

Film Credit: MSG Thomas Hovie

2788.description:
Multi-National Forces stage military exercises in Germany on May 26, 2014.

Film Credit: SGT Fred Brown

2789.description: USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6) arrives at Pearl Harbor, HI with the crew manning the rails (rendering honors) at parade rest. Parade Rest - the hands at the small of the back keeping the fingers of both hands extended and joined, with the head and eyes in the position of attention.

2790.description:
An A-10 Warthog refueling over Afghanistan shoots a flare into the darkness in a spectacular display of aerial fireworks.

Film Credit: MSgt Pedro Jimenez

2791.description:
Los Angeles-class submarine USS Pasadena (SSN 752) leaves Pearl Harbor, HI. The Pasadena is a nuclear-powered fast attack submarine, one of 41 in service with the U.S. Navy as of 2014. It has a crew of 12 officers and 98 enlisted, is 362 feet in length, and has an armament of Mk48 torpedoes, Tomahawk cruise missiles, and Harpoon anti-ship missiles.

Film Credit: Mass Communication Specialist 1st Class Jason Swink

2792.description:
In Operation Desert Scimitar 2014 - Marines with the 1st Tank Battalion blast enemy positions with M1A1 Main Battle Tanks. Footage filmed on May 24, 2014 at Twentynine Palms, California.

Film Credit: Cpl Christopher J. Moore

2793.description:
Footage of troop convoys through Iraq and Afghanistan... dirt roads, bomb craters, camels, and more.

Film Credits: SGT Tony McCaslin, Sgt Timothy Solano, SSG Robert Souza, and SrA Jaye Legate

2794.description:
Yellow shirt flight deck crew handle aircraft by using arm signals, called marshalling, to direct a CH-53 Sea Stallion helicopter and a V-22 Osprey landing aboard USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6).

Film Credit: Cpl Kenneth Jasik

2795.description:
A close-up look at the Northrop Grumman RQ-4 Global Hawk, an unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) used for surveillance. Using sophisticated radar and optics, the Global Hawk can fly above 68,000 feet and provide high resolution imagery to ground personnel for situational awareness, targeting, and bomb damage assessment. It can operate for more than 40 hours, day or night in any weather.

Footage of Global Hawk landing at Misawa Air Base in Japan May 24, 2014.

Film Credit: SrA Ashley Clingerman

2796.description:
A column of American M1 Abrams Tanks and Bradley Fighting Vehicles moves from Hohenfels to the Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany for military exercises (and the local population is unfazed). Movement took place on May 10, 2014.

Film Credit: SGT Fred Brown and CPT John Farmer

2797.description:
MICLIC explosions - The M58 Mine Clearing Line Charge (MICLIC) is a rocket propelled explosive line fired from an Assault Breacher Vehicle (ABV), nicknamed "The Shredder". The ABV is an M1 Abrams tank modified to carry and launch the 1750 pound C4 explosive line. The whole package is designed to explode IEDs and mines from a safe distance.

Film Credit: Sgt Bryan Nygaard, Sgt Joshua T. Greenfield, and Cpl John McCall

2798.description:
Paladins maneuver to set up a firing point. Officially known as the M109A6, the Paladin is a tracked self propelled 155mm howitzer with a 6 man crew capable of firing 6 rounds per minute. The Paladin cannot fire on the move, it must be stationary, but it can fire within 30 seconds after coming to a halt. The maximum speed of the Paladin is 35 mph, and the effective firing range is 18 kilometers or about 11 miles.

Film from taken from Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany, and Fort Carson, Colorado.

Film Credit: SGT Fred Brown and SSG Christopher Jelle

2799.description:
C-130 and C-17 aircraft drop cargo and crew over the Tonopah test range in Nevada. Includes footage of C-17s taking-off and landing on a dirt runway.

Film Credit: A1C Rachel Webster

2800.description:
F-16 and F-18 aircraft get fuel in-flight over Afghanistan, plus a short interview with an F-18 pilot while refueling on a KC-10 Extender.

Film Credit: SSgt Jeffrey Curtin

2801.description:
The U.S. Navy - Cyclone Class Patrol Boat may be small at approximately 175 feet, but with an armament which includes two Mk38 chain guns, two Mk19 automatic grenade launchers, twin .50 caliber machine guns, as well as six Stinger missiles... she packs a punch. 

With a crew of 30 sailors, the USS Firebolt (PC-10) is tasked with coastal patrol and interdiction surveillance in the Persian Gulf.

On 24 April 2004, Firebolt's rigid-hulled inflatable boat attempted a boarding operation on a dhow (sailboat) that was approaching the Khawr Al Amaya Oil Terminal in Iraq. As the boarding team pulled alongside the dhow, it exploded in an apparent suicide bombing. Two Sailors and one Coast Guardsman were killed when the inflatable flipped over, dumping her crew into the water.  

Film Credit: PO2 Danielle Brandt

2802.description:
An M1 Abrams Breacher vehicle shoots a Mine Clearing Line Charge (MICLIC), 1750 LBs of C4 explosives designed to clear IEDs. If the MICLIC doesn't explode, a Marine must do the "Medal Of Honor" run.

2nd Combat Engineering Battalion Assault Breacher Vehicle Team conducts a training exercise on a demolition range at Camp Leatherneck, Afghanistan. CPL Dylan McKee makes a daring 'medal of honor' run to set a charge to 1750 pounds of C4.

Film Credit: SGT Chiquita Peña

2803.description:
Marines ride across the water in amtracks. Officially known as Assault Amphibious Vehicles, the AAV-P7/A1 is an amphibious troop transport capable of carrying 25 combat equipped Marines from ship to shore. It is equipped with a .50 caliber machine gun and an Mk19 40mm automatic grenade launcher.

Designed to assault any shoreline from the well deck of a Navy assault ship, the AAV is a highly mobile, tracked armored amphibious vehicle that transports Marines and cargo to and through hostile territory.

Film Credit: Cpl Mark Garcia

2804.description:
Planes launch and land aboard the super carrier USS Harry S. Truman (CVN-75), the 8th Nimitz class aircraft carrier of the U.S. Navy. The Truman is 1092 feet in length, displaces 116,400 tons, and carries approximately 90 aircraft. Propulsion of the Truman is provided by two Westinghouse A4W nuclear reactors, four steam turbines, and four shafts - to give the ship a top speed in excess of 30 knots or 35 mph.

Flight operations filmed on 11/13/2013 somewhere in the U.S. 5th Fleet area of responsibility... Persian Gulf, Red Sea, Arabian Sea, and parts of the Indian Ocean.

2805.description:
Austrian Infantry conduct air assault training at Hohenfels Training Area, Germany on May 19, 2014 as part of Exercise Combined Resolve II. Combined Resolve II is a U.S. Army Europe-directed multinational exercise at the Grafenwoehr and Hohenfels Training Areas, including more than 4,000 participants from 15 allied countries.

Film Credit: SPC Dustin Stech

2806.description:
Service members receive hand gun training designed to train combat camera personnel to operate in a combat environment, and shoot the enemy in the eye.

Film Credit: PO2 Jonathan Chandler

2807.description:
U.S. Army Soldiers from the 101st Airborne Division conduct an air assault with field artillery dropped from Black Hawk helicopters from the 159th Combat Aviation Brigade. Sling load operations at Fort Campbell, KY with the M119 howitzer, a lightweight British 105mm howitzer used by the United States Army. 

Film Credit: SGT Bradley Parrish

2808.description:
Mid-air refueling of a C-17 Globemaster, a huge military transport plane capable of carrying an M1 Abrams tank, or approximately 85 tons of cargo (170,000 lbs).

Film Credit: TSgt Rachel Barton

2809.description: The USS Kitty Hawk aircraft carrier leaves Pearl Harbor, HI in 2008. The Kitty Hawk (CV-63) was decommissioned in 2009 not long after this video was filmed. It was the last conventional aircraft carrier (non-nuclear) in service with the United States Navy. Commissioned in 1961, the Kitty Hawk was in service for nearly 49 years.

2810.description:
Navy deck guns firing -- the MK-45/5-inch gun and the MK-75/76mm gun send some rounds down range.

Film Credit: PO2 Adrian White and PO2 David Cothran

2811.description:
U.S. Army soldiers with the 1st Armored Division firing the Carl Gustav recoilless rifle, an 84mm shoulder-fired reusable anti-tank weapon produced in Sweden. The Carl Gustav - M3 Multi-role Anti-armor Anti-tank Weapon System (MAAWS) can be used to attack larger stationary targets at up to 1000m. The British Special Air Service, United States Special Forces, and United States Army Rangers use the M3 in bunker-busting and anti-vehicle roles. 

In 2012 the U.S. Army deployed 58 M3s and 1,500 rounds of ammunition to units in Afghanistan to destroy enemy targets out to 1,000 meters, because Taliban RPG and machine gun teams could attack 900 meters away, while existing U.S. weapons like the M141 Bunker Defeat Munition, M72 LAW, M136 AT-4 and MK153 SMAW had effective ranges of only 500 meters.

Film Credit: SGT Nigel Robinson

2812.description:
F-15 Eagles get gas in the air then pose for pictures. 

United States Air Force

Film Credit: MSgt Pedro Jimenez

2813.description:
Cockpit camera captures pilots of a KC-135 Stratotanker performing "touch & go" to maintain proficiency.

Film Credit: SSgt Roidan Carlson

2814.description:
Step aboard the bridge of the USS John S. McCain (DDG-56) while cruising underway in high winds and rough seas and have a glimpse of what it's like on a routine watch. 

The McCain is an Arleigh Burke-class destroyer of the U.S. Navy approximately 500 feet in length. She is part of the Seventh Fleet, and her homeport is the Yokosuka Naval Base in Yokosuka, Japan.

Film Credit: PO2 Adrian White

2815.description: U.S. Marines continued to fight the Southern California wildfires on 5/16/2014 using helicopters and giant buckets to drop water on the advancing flames. A hot refueling point was set up at Camp Pendleton to keep the helicopters in the air and on constant rotation. "Hot Refueling" means rapid refueling with engines operating.

2816.description:
A brand new U.S. Navy Coastal Command Patrol Boat (CCB) is launched at Naval Support Center, Bahrain. The state-of-the-art CCB is assigned to Task Group (CTG) 56.7 which conducts maritime security operations in the Persian Gulf.

Film Credit: PO1 Shannon Renfroe

2817.description:
U.S. Navy Divers assigned to Task Group (CTG) 56.1 conduct a scuba familiarization dive with Royal Jordanian Navy Divers in the Gulf of Aqaba. CTG-56.1 conducts mine countermeasures, explosive ordnance disposal, salvage-diving and force protection operations.

Film Credit: PO2 Taylor Smith

2818.description:
U.S. Marines, 8th Marine Regiment, Romanian and Armenian soldiers conduct live fire training during Exercise Platinum Eagle at the Platoon Attack range in Babadag, Romania on May 8, 2014.

Film Credit: LCpl Samantha Barajas

2819.description:
The A-10 Thunderbolt "Warthog" aircraft is built around the GAU-8 Avenger gun, a 30mm Gatling-type cannon capable of firing 70 rounds per second. Take a look.... the "Gun" fires projectiles made of a lightweight aluminum body, cast around a smaller caliber depleted uranium penetrating core, and is lethal against tanks and all other armored vehicles.

More A-10 video - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CaBgxgjqZCE 

Film Credit: TSgt Rachel Barton

2820.description:
Canadian and American Paratroopers carry out Airborne operations on the Bledowska Desert in Chechlo, Poland on 5/6/2014.

Film Credit: SSG Anthony Johnson

2821.description:
The USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD-6) departs Pearl Harbor, HI. 

A Wasp-class amphibious assault ship, the Bonhomme Richard carries Marines, helicopters, Ospreys, Harriers, LCAC hovercraft, and displaces 40,500 tons - a large warship. Recently the Bonhomme Richard took part in search, rescue, and salvage operations with the South Korean Ferry disaster.

Film Credit: PO2 Brett Morton

2822.description:
A U.S. Marine Corps MV-22 Osprey with Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron 262 stationed at Okinawa, delivers VIPs in Crow Valley, Philippines during Balikatan on May 15, 2014.

Film Credit: SSgt Jason Fudge

2823.description:
Wildfires in Southern California have destroyed more than 10,000 acres, several homes, with 1 death reported. U.S. Marines joined the fight on May 15th, dropping water on several fires to help local firefighters battle the blaze.

Film Credit: GySgt Donald Bohanner,  PFC Maxwell Pennington, Sgt Isaac Lamberth, and LCpl Anna Albrecht

2824.description:
C-130 Hercules refuels a Pave Hawk helicopter in-flight as part of Angel Thunder exercises 5/9/2014.

Film Credit: AB Katelynn Moeller

2825.description:
U.S. Marines set off C4 charges and Philippine and U.S. Marines conduct live-fire squad attacks May 9 at Crow Valley, Philippines as part of Operation Balikatan 2014.

Film Credit: Cpl Lena Wakayama

2826.description:
Spectacular aerial footage of a USAF Boeing C-17 Globemaster III flying over scenic California inland and coastline - music audio. 

For a similar video of a Lockheed C-5 Galaxy go here - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rvFvSj0-1vQ

Film Credit: Douglas Lay

2827.description:
The USS Freedom (LCS-1) arriving and departing Pearl Harbor, HI. LCS stands for - Littoral Combat Ship - a new class of U.S. Navy ship. A littoral combat ship is a relatively small ship designed for operations close to shore.

Film Credit: PO2 Brett Morton and PO1 Jason Swink

2828.description:
Pre-positioned Bradley Fighting Vehicles conduct live-fire exercises at Grafenwoehr Training Area in Germany on 5/5/2014. 

The gunnery exercise is the first time U.S. Army Forces have used a set of armored vehicles and equipment prepositioned in Grafenwoehr, including the most up-to-date versions of the M2/M3 Bradley Infantry Fighting Vehicles, for live-fire training in Europe.

Film Credit: Gertrud Zach and Markus Rauchenberger

2829.description:
U.S. and German aircraft takeoff from Holloman AFB, N.M. in support of Bold Quest 14.2. Shown are T-38C,  VMX-22 Osprey, German Air Force Tornado, AV8B Harrier, U.S. Air Force F-16s, and F/A-18 Super Hornets.

Bold Quest will focus on coalition force integration to assess communications and network gaps with joint and multinational partners. 

Film Credit: SSgt Warren Spearman

2830.description:
U.S. Marines send rounds downrange during a live-fire exercise with .50 caliber machine guns, armored personnel carriers, and Abrams tanks.

Film Credit: SSgt Pete Thibodeau

2831.description:
U.S. Marines load LCAC Hovercrafts with equipment and personnel to depart Australia after completing military exercises.

Film Credit: SSgt Pete Thibodeau

2832.description:
A B-1 bomber taking off and multiple clips of B-1s refueling in-flight.

Film Credit: SSgt Roidan Carlson and SSgt Jose Rodriguez

2833.description:
Crew Chief readies a German Air Force Tornado prior to a test flight at Holloman AFB in New Mexico on May 12, 2014. This Interdiction/Strike variant of the Tornado has been retrofitted with a state-of-the-art Interface Computer Unit that allows the fighter aircraft to communicate with modern day joint terminal air controllers on the ground. Nearly 800 military and civilian personnel from eight countries have traveled to Holloman to test the real-world integration of their close air support equipment and personnel.

Film Credit: SSgt Warren Spearman

2834.description:
U.S. Marines Fast Rope training - Fast-roping, also known as Fast Rope Insertion Extraction System (FRIES), is a technique for descending a thick rope. It is useful for deploying troops from a helicopter. Fast-roping allows soldiers to respond to crises as a quick reaction force, conduct missions requiring stealth and board vessels while at sea. First developed by the British with UK rope manufacturer Marlow Ropes, its first combat use was during the Falklands War.

Film Credit: TSgt Micah Theurich

2835.description:
Combat Engineers from the U.S. Army 412th Theater Engineer Command build an Improved Ribbon Bridge to cross the Arkansas River during a training exercise in 2012.

The Improved Ribbon Bridge (IRB) provides wet gap crossing capabilities either as floating bridge or multi-bay raft for combat vehicles and trucks. IRB bays are transportable on trucks, railway cars and transport aircrafts or as underslung load of a helicopter. Total usable roadway width of 4.50 m for single-lane traffic for MLC 80T/96W vehicles.

Film Credit: SPC Mark O'Rear

2836.description: The USS Enterprise (CVN-65) at the heart of a strike group formation in the Atlantic, before she was retired on December 1, 2012.

2837.description:
A U.S. Marine Corps Harrier aircraft refueled in-flight over Afghanistan by a USAF KC-10 Extender. Amazing scenery.

Film Credit: SSgt Jeffrey Curtin

2838.description:
British Royal Air Force Tornado GR4 aircraft land at Lajes Field in the Azores. 

Film Credit: TSgt Anthony Plyler

2839.description: Canadian Navy sub HMCS Victoria sinks U.S. Navy ship USNS Concord as part of a live-fire exercise in the Pacific on 7/17/2012. The Victoria fired one MK-48 torpedo.

2840.description:
The Royal Canadian Navy Destroyer HMCS Algonquin (DDG-283) arrives at Pearl Harbor, HI.

Film Credit:  Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Daniel Barker

2841.description:
The Royal Australian Navy Frigate HMAS Warramunga (FFH-152) leaves Pearl Harbor, HI.

Film Credit: SN John Ciccarelli

2842.description:
Watch B-52 pilots and crew during flight operations - cockpit video.

Film Credit: TSgt Rebecca King

2843.description:
F-22 Raptor fighter jets take off from Nellis AFB and refuel in-flight.

Film Credit:  SrA Rachel Maxwell, SSgt Jose Rodriguez, SrA Aaron Hauser, and A1C Rachel Webster

2844.description:
B-2 Stealth Bomber taxi to runway and takeoff at Nellis Air Force Base near Las Vegas, NV.

Film Credit: SrA Aaron Hauser

2845.description:
U.S. Air Force Combat Controllers train in helicopter exit and boarding techniques. Combat Controllers are often assigned individually or as a team to Army Special Forces, Army Ranger, and Navy SEAL teams to provide expert air support coordination and communications.

Navy Helicopter Squadron HSC-84 "Red Wolves" train with Air Force Special Operations Command Combat Controllers to board and egress an HH-60G helicopter.

Film Credit: Senior Airman Greg Cerny

2846.description:
A close-up look at A-10 "Warthogs" on the taxiway at Nellis AFB, Las Vegas. It looks like a jet plane traffic jam, but the ground crew keeps everything running smoothly.

Film Credit: William Lewis

2847.description:
A Pave Hawk Helicopter is fitted with GoPro cameras on the refueling probe and on the undercarriage to give you an extraordinary view as it flies over the Mojave Desert.

Film Credit: SrA Armando Aparicio

2848.description:
Special Forces Soldiers conduct a helocast exercise at the Combat Readiness Training Center in Gulfport, MS. Helocast is an airborne technique used by small units, special operations forces to insert into a military area of operation. The training ensures that the units are trained and ready for any combat situation. The faces of special forces members have been blurred to protect their identity.

Film Credit: SGT Tim Morgan and SFC Bill Valentine

2849.description:
Filmed POV From Helmet Cam - U.S. Marines open fire from Humvees mounted with .50 caliber machine guns during a live fire exercise at Camp Adazi, Latvia on 4/16/2014. 

Film Credit: SSgt Tanner Iskra

2850.description:
U.S. Marines fire from Humvees mounted with .50 caliber machine guns and MK-19 Grenade Launchers to cover another group of Marines moving through a valley to take enemy held positions.

Marines from 2nd Battalion, 5th Marine Regiment push through a company live fire attack exercise in the Republic of Korea on 4/4/2014.

Film Credit: Cpl Eric Waddell

2851.description:
Planes launch and land aboard the "supercarrier" USS Nimitz (CVN-68). The Nimitz is a United States Navy aircraft carrier and has approximately 90 aircraft. Supercarriers are the largest warships ever built, typically displacing more than 70,000 tons. The Nimitz is 1,092 feet in length (over 3 football fields long), and displaces more than 100,000 tons. The U.S. Navy has 10 supercarriers that displace more than 100,000 tons as of 2014 - all nuclear powered. 
[1] http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_aircraft_carriers_in_service
[2] http://www.globalfirepower.com/navy-aircraft-carriers.asp

Flight operations aboard the USS Nimitz aircraft carrier in the Red Sea - 2013.

Film Credit: PO3 Vanessa David

2852.description:
A patrol boat from Coast Guard Port Security Unit 311 in San Pedro, CA conducts tactical boat maneuver training with a GoPro camera on the machine gun.

Film Credit: PO2 Gina Ruoti

2853.description:
F-16 fighter jets from the 169th Fighter Wing takeoff from McEntire Joint National Guard Base, SC at night with full afterburners glowing behind them.

Film Credit: TSgt Carl Clegg

2854.description:
The fast frigate USS McClusky (FFG-41) leaves Pearl Harbor, HI.

Film Credit: PO1 Jason Swink

2855.description:
Scenes include aerial refueling of F-16 fighter jets and an AWACs plane over Guam.

A U.S. Air Force KC-135 Stratotanker from Kadena Air Base, Japan refuels U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcons and a U.S. Air Force E-3 Sentry during exercise COPE NORTH 12-1, Andersen Air Force Base, Guam.

Film Credit: SSgt Michelle Revoir

2856.description:
The guided missile frigate USS Ford (FFG-54) arrives at Pearl Harbor, HI.

Film Credit: PO2 Brett Morton

2857.description:
Inside a B-52 Stratofortress during flight operations - crew members performing duties, and some of the updated avionics in this 60 year old flying beast.

A B-52 from Barksdale AFB training on air refueling and bomb runs.

Film Credit: SrA Anthony Gamez

2858.description:
The nuclear-powered attack submarine USS New Hampshire (SSN-778) breaks through 3 feet of ice in the arctic. The nuclear-powered attack submarine USS New Mexico (SSN 779) surfaces in icy arctic waters.

Film Credit: PO2 Joshua Davies

2859.description:
The U.S. Coast Guard Cutter Rush (WHEC-723) leaves Pearl Harbor, HI.

Film Credit: SN John Ciccarelli

2860.description:
U.S. Marines conduct combat operations in Fallujah and launch a shoulder-fired rocket on the enemy during the War In Iraq - November 12-13, 2004.

Film Credit: 1LT Jan Bender

2861.description:
Aerial refueling of a B-2 bomber. The bat shaped wings of the aircraft decrease its radar cross-section and increase stealth characteristics.

Film Credit: SrA Nathan Tucker

2862.description:
U.S. Marines AH-1W Super Cobra helicopters land at a forward arming and refueling point (FARP) in South Korea to take on fuel. It's a hot refueling - refueling while the engines are still operating.

Film Credit: LCpl Scott Smolinski

2863.description:
Members of the 197th Special Operations Airborne maintain proficiency by performing static line jumps from UH-60 Black Hawk helicopters flown by the 171th Aviation Regiment - Utah Army National Guard.

Film Credit: SSgt Robert Harnden

2864.description:
See what it's like to fly wingtip to wingtip with F-16 Fighter Jets in close formation. These guys make it look easy, but the slightest mistake means disaster.

Film Credit: SSgt Roidan Carlson - SSgt Kurtis Villavicencio

2865.description:
A HIMARS rocket launcher (High Mobility Artillery Rocket System) - shooting first in real time, then in slow motion.

Film Credit: CWO2 James A. Burks

2866.description:
The Guided missile destroyer USS Stockdale (DDG 106) arrives at Pearl Harbor, HI in 2012.

Film Credit: Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Daniel Barker

2867.description:
A KC-135 Stratotanker from Utah Air National Guard conducts aerial refueling of a B-52 Stratofortress from Barksdale Air Force Base over Utah.

Film Credit: SSgt Robert Harnden

2868.description:
The Destroyer USS John S. McCain (DDG-56) conducts live-fire exercises to increase proficiency in anti-surface and anti-air warfare.

Film Credit: PO2 Adrian White

2869.description:
Marine Heavy Helicopter Squadron 362 (HMH-362), also known as the "Ugly Angels" conduct their last flight in Afghanistan. consisting of ten CH-53D Sea Stallion assault support helicopters and 220 Marines and Sailors, the Ugly Angels have served during conflicts from Vietnam, the Iraqi War, and Afghanistan - their final combat deployment.

Film Credit: Sgt James Mercure

2870.description:
The Japanese Destroyer Shirane (DDH-143) arrives at Pearl Harbor, HI.

Film Credit: PO2 Tiarra Fulgham

2871.description:
Combat footage from a helmet cam shows fighfight battles in Afghanistan - footage of Soldiers returning fire during Insurgent attacks in Panjwa'i District.

Film Credit: SFC Walter Talens

2872.description:
A U.S. KC-135 Stratotanker refuels a Czech JAS-39 Gripen in-flight while MIG-29s provide escort.

A Nebraska Air National Guard KC-135R refuels a Czech JAS-39 Gripen fighter over Slovakia and gets mock-intercepted by MiG-29's as part of the NATO State Partnership Program.

Film Credit: SSgt Tristan McIntire

2873.description:
A B-1 Bomber gets fuel in-flight from a KC-135 Stratotanker. 

A B-1 Bomber from the 28th Bomb Wing at Ellsworth AFB, South Dakota, approaches and makes contact with a KC-135R Stratotanker from the 126th Air Refueling Wing.

Film Credit: MSgt Ken Stephens

2874.description:
A V-22 Osprey lands in Voinovich Park on Lake Erie as part of Marine Week Cleveland - 6/10/2012.

Film Credit: Sgt Todd Hunter - LCpl John Tucker

2875.description:
The HMAS Perth (FFH-157) of the Royal Australian Navy arrives at Pearl Harbor, HI.

Film Credit: PO2 Tiarra Fulgham

2876.description:
The 303rd Fighter Squadron - made up of A-10 Thunderbolt II aircraft - deployed at Bagram Airfield, Afghanistan. The 303rd is based out of Whiteman Air Force Base, Missouri. Recorded on 4/21/2014. 

303rd A-10 Warthog Fighter Squadron Reserve Unit based out of Whiteman Air Force Base Missouri deployed at Bagram Airfield, Afghanistan.

Film Credit: SSgt Miguel Lara

2877.description:
The AT4 is an 84-mm single-shot anti-tank weapon used by the U.S. Marine Corps. It is designed to give infantry units a means to destroy or disable armoured vehicles. And although it is generally not sufficient to defeat a modern main battle tank, it still packs a powerful punch. After firing, the AT4 is discarded because the outer tube is built to take the stress of only one firing - it is not reusable.

Marines assigned to the 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU), train with the AT-4 light anti-armor weapon during a familiarization and live fire exercise at Fort Pickett, VA - Sept. 17, 2012.

Film Credit: WO Michael Kropiewnicki

2878.description:
A test shot of the U.S. Navy's electromagnetic railgun, a long-range weapon that fires projectiles using electromagnetic energy instead of chemical propellants.

Mounted on U.S. Navy vessels, the EM railgun will be capable of firing a projectile at more than Mach 5, and up to 110 nautical miles.  The hypersonic projectile will destroy targets with kinetic energy instead of conventional explosives.

Technicians successfully fired the EM railgun prototype, developed by BAE Systems, at the Naval Surface Warfare Center in Dahlgren, VA.

2879.description:
The M1128 Mobile Gun System (MGS) is an eight-wheeled armored fighting vehicle mounting a 105 mm tank gun. Because the vehicle was designed without air conditioning, crews are given individual cooling vests that circulate cooled water from outside the vehicle to the garment. The MGS can store 18 rounds of main gun ammunition in the turret. It has a rate of fire of six rounds per minute

Soldiers of Alpha Company, 1-17th Infantry Regiment conducting training on the mobile gun system. 

Film Credit: SSG Katie Gray

2880.description:
The Russian Navy Destroyer Admiral Panteleyev (BPK 548) arrives at Pearl Harbor, HI in 2012.

Film Credit: Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Daniel Barker

2881.description:
The 101st Airborne Division conducts an air assault with UH-60 Black Hawk helicopters dropping equipment and troops while AH-64 Apache helicopters fly cover. Filmed at Fort Campbell, Kentucky on 4/4/2014.

Film Credit: SGT Joshua Dwyer

2882.description:
A USAF KC-135 Stratotanker refuels a British Royal Air Force Tornado in the sky over Afghanistan.

A KC-135 from the 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron refuels a British Royal Air Force Tornado over Afghanistan in support of Operation Enduring Freedom on 7/17/2012.

Film Credit: SSgt Michelle Revoir

2883.description:
Cockpit video from an F/A-18F Hornet as it is launched from the flight deck, and returns to land on the aircraft carrier USS Carl Vinson (CVN-70).

Film Credit: PO2 James Evans

2884.description:
Flight operations aboard the USS Harry S. Truman (CVN-75) include multiple takeoffs and landings of F/A-18 Hornets and one takeoff of an E-2 Hawkeye.

Film Credit: Seaman Apprentice Ethan Schumacher

2885.description:
A Republic of Korea (South Korea) Chang Bogo-class Submarine leaves Pearl Harbor. The Na Daeyong (SS-069) is a diesel powered sub, approximately 200 feet long, displaces 1400 tons, armament - torpedoes and harpoon missiles.

Film Credit: Mass Communication Specialist 3rd Class Sean Furey

2886.description:
U.S. Marines with 3rd Battalion, 8th Marines conduct a platoon live-fire attack at Camp Adazi, Latvia on April 9, 2014.

Film Credit: SSgt Tanner Iskra

2887.description:
A KC-135 Stratotanker refuels four F-16 fighter jets mid-air over waters near the Hawaiian Islands. The F-16s fly in formation and pose for pictures.

Film Credit: SrA Brandi Hansen

2888.description:
The USS Nimitz (CVN 68) arrives at Pearl Harbor, HI. The Nimitz is a U.S. Navy aircraft carrier, and one of the largest warships in the world.

Film Credit: PO1 Daniel Barker

2889.description:
U.S. Marines from Kaneohe Marine Corps Base, Hawaii land on the beach in Amphibious Assault Vehicles during training exercises.

Film Credit: LT Miranda Williams

2890.description:
A KC-135 Stratotanker refuels Italian AMX and United States AE-6B Prowler aircraft in the skies over Afghanistan.

Film Credit: SSgt Michelle Revoir

2891.description:
CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters drop U.S. Marines in a simulated air assault somewhere in the Hawaiian Islands. Aerial view of Waikiki and Diamond Head in the first few seconds of the video. Plus, HSC-4 Helicopters from the Black Knights Anti-Submarine Squadron carry VIP observers.

Film Credit: SrA Brandi Hansen

2892.description:
U.S. Marines fire 120mm mortar systems alongside members of the Japan Ground Self-Defense Force during Exercise Iron Fist 2014 at Camp Pendleton, California, February 3-6, 2014.

Film Credit: Sgt Jamean Berry

2893.description:
Sailors assigned to Task Group 56.7.4 conduct live-fire weapons training aboard riverine command boats (RCBs) in the Arabian Gulf on 1/21/2014.

Film Credit: PO1 Michelle Turner

2894.description:
M1A1 Abrams Tanks - 2nd Marine Regiment, take part in live-fire training at Udairi Range in Kuwait City, July 26, 2012.

Film Credit:  1LT Joshua Larson

2895.description:
The flight deck of an aircraft carrier during flight operations is one of the most dangerous places on earth. And even though it might look like total chaos, it's really a finely tuned and highly organized action. Everybody has a job to do.

The aircraft carrier USS Enterprise (CVN 65) conducts flight operations while deployed in the Mediterranean Sea.

Film Credit: Mass Communications Specialist 3rd Class Jared King

2896.description:
A new U.S. Navy, Coastal Command Boat (CCB) patrols the waters near Bahrain in the Persian Gulf on 2/26/2014.

The CCB is the first and only vessel of its kind, with increased payload capacity and better capabilities for maritime blockade and interdiction operations, sea port defense, sea lane control, and other waterfront and coastal maritime missions. The CCB can reach speeds in excess of 35 knots or more than 40 mph.

Film Credit: PO1 Martine Cuaron

2897.description:
The flight deck of USS Iwo Jima, a Wasp-class amphibious assault warship, is very busy with aircraft taking-off and landing. 

Aircraft in the video are AV-8B Harriers, MV -- 22B Ospreys, UH-1N Hueys and AH-1W Cobras.

24th Marine Expeditionary Unit conduct flight operations aboard the USS Iwo Jima (LHD-7), Sept. 10, 2012.

Film Credit: Gunnery Sgt. Chad R. Kiehl

2898.description:
Live fire training with a MK-19 Grenade Launcher mounted on a Stryker armored fighting vehicle.

The Mk 19 Grenade Launcher is an American 40 mm belt-fed automatic grenade launcher that entered U.S. military service during the Cold War, first seeing action during the Vietnam War and remaining in service to the present day.

The Mk 19 effective range is about 1,500 meters, with a practical rate of fire of 60 rounds per minute (rapid) and 40 rounds per minute (sustained).

25th Infantry Division of Schofield Barracks, HI conducts a Mk. 19 live range at Yakima Training Center, WA on 10/15/2012.

Film Credit: SSG Sean Everette

2899.description:
A Griffin guided missile is launched from a U.S. Navy ship and destroys a moving target boat.

Griffin Missile Exercise from Coastal Patrol Ships in the U.S. 5th Fleet on 3/20/2014.

2900.description:
A Harrier Jump Jet is launched from the deck of the USS Bataan (LHD 5).

U.S. Marine Corps AV-8B Harrier jets with Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron (VMM) 263 (Reinforced), 22nd Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU), take off from the flight deck of the USS Bataan (LHD 5) off the East Coast November 7 - 9, 2013.

Film Credit: Sgt Austin Hazard

2901.description:
Watch highlights of a combined military combat exercise including tanks, infantry, artillery, and helicopter support.

OPERATION HAMMER STRIKE - included the employment of the Assault Breacher Vehicle, Close Combat Support, Close Air Support, HIMARS, and Abrams tanks.

Film Credit: SPC Derrick Ramey and SPC Eddrenia Scott

2902.description:
Apache helicopters fire rockets and machine guns on enemy held positions in Afghanistan.

On 7/7/2009 Apache helicopters destroyed enemy fighting positions above the village of Donga, Afghanistan. The positions were discovered a day earlier during an ambush of a patrol conducting a key leader engagement. With help from a forward observer, the helicopters identified the targets, ensuring no civilians were present and then destroyed the positions using their 30 mm cannon and rockets.

Film Credit: SSG Justin Puetz

2903.description:
Spectacular footage filmed by the pilot of a U2 spy plane. This partial point-of-view video puts you in the pilot's seat at 70,000 feet. From takeoff to landing, see what it's like to be in the cockpit of the plane they nicknamed - Dragon Lady.

Film Credit: SrA Andrew Buchanan 9Th Reconnaissance Wing Public Affairs
Derivative Works: Gung Ho Vids

2904.description:
MV-22B Ospreys, tiltrotor aircraft conduct touch & go operations aboard the USS Bataan (LHD 5). LHD stands for Landing Helicopter Dock. The USS Bataan is a Wasp-class amphibious assault ship that carries:

    4 × CH-53E Super Stallion helicopters
    6 × AV-8B Harrier attack aircraft
    3 × UH-1N Huey helicopters
    4 × AH-1W Super Cobra helicopters
    8 × MV-22 Osprey VTOL tiltrotor aircraft
    2 × MH-60S KnightHawk helicopters

Film Credit: Sgt Chris Stone

2905.description:
Live Fire Exercise in Kuwait, firing the M109A6 self propelled howitzer, known as the Paladin.

Training exercise with 1-125 Field Artillery of the Minnesota National Guard, and the 1-82 Field Artillery from Ft. Hood, TX, soldiers in Kuwait on 2/17/2012.

Film Credit: SPC Linsey Williams

2906.description:
U.S. Marines and Philippine Marines are inserted by helicopters to conduct a live-fire air assault on a simulated hot landing zone.

31st Marine Expeditionary Unit team with Philippine Marines of the 33rd Marine Company.

Film Credit: Sgt Paul Robbins

2907.description:
Door gunners on a HH-60 Pave Hawk helicopter use GAU-17/A miniguns capable of firing 4000 rounds per minute.

Staff Sergeant Ed Drew, an HH-60 Pave Hawk helicopter aerial gunner, assigned to the 129th Rescue Squadron performs live-fire training at Fort Hunter Liggett, Ca, August 7, 2013.

Film Credit: TSgt Ray Aquino

2908.description:
The Boeing Vertol CH-46 Sea Knight is a medium-lift tandem rotor transport helicopter. It is used by the United States Marine Corps to provide all-weather, day-or-night assault transport of combat troops, supplies and equipment. Nicknamed the "Phrog", the Sea Knight has been used in all U.S. Marine combat and peacetime environments since its introduction in 1964. CH-46E Sea Knights were used by the U.S. Marine Corps during the 2003 invasion of Iraq.

U.S. Marines of the 1st Marine Division from Camp Pendleton, California conduct an airfield seizure aboard seven CH-46 Sea Knight transport helicopters with the 3rd Marine Aircraft Wing, also from Camp Pendleton, at Twentynine Palms, California on Dec 11, 2013.

Film Credit: MSgt Daniel Kauppila

2909.description:
Members of the 82nd Airborne Division conduct a mission to Tarin Kowt, Urugan province in Afghanistan on March 1, 2014 as part of their Theater Response Force mission. The TRF is a battalion sized quick reaction force that can deploy anywhere in Afghanistan and conduct operations on a moments notice.

Film Credit: CPL Harold Flynn

2910.description:
1st Field Artillery Regiment conducting a fire mission at night on Forward Operating Base Shank in Afghanistan. All rounds fired in the video were for Illumination.

Film Credit: SGT Austin Berner

2911.description:
U.S. Marines go through a lot of ammo firing the .50 caliber machine gun at the range.
 
Marines with 1st Reconnaissance Battalion train with .50 cal machine guns during a live-fire range at Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton, California on March 6, 2014.

Film Credit: LCpl Jonathan Boynes

2912.description:
KC-135 Stratotanker refuels A-10 Thunderbolt "Warthogs".

Film Credit: SSgt Robert Harnden

2913.description:
Watch a Harrier Jump Jet hovering in mid-air while doing a 360 degree spin. Then it accelerates almost straight up, in this clip from the Cherry Point Air Show in 2012.

Cherry Point Air Show, May 5, 2012 at Marine Corps Air Station Cherry Point, N.C.

Film Credit: Cpl S.T. Stewart

2914.description:
AV-8B Harriers assigned to Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron (VMM) 266, 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU), conduct landing certification on the flight deck of the USS Kearsarge (LHD 3), Jan. 22, 2013.

Film Credit: LCpl Juanenrique Owings

2915.description:
F-16 Fighter Jets takeoff in early morning twilight showcasing the power of afterburners. 

F-16 Fighting Falcons from the 36th Fighter Squadron launch from Osan Air Base, Republic of Korea on November 19, 2013.

Film Credit: SSgt Anthony Kuhn

2916.description:
Take a look inside a B-52 Stratofortress cockpit during takeoff, flying, and landing operations. See what it's like to pilot this 60 year old, long range bomber.

B-52 crew members from the 96 Bomb Squadron at Barksdale AFB, LA conduct an aerial training mission.

Film Credit: SSgt David Clark

2917.description:
The F-35 Lightning II Joint Strike Fighter Jet in action. An F-35B conducted its first Vertical Landing operation at Marine Corps Air Station in Yuma, Arizona on March 21, 2013.  This marked a critical step for the F-35, showing the ability of the aircraft to land vertically outside of a test environment.

Film Credit: Cpl Casey Scarpulla

2918.description:
U.S. helicopters and tanks light up the night sky during a firefight with insurgents in Afghanistan.

U.S. Marine AH-1W Cobras and M1A1 Abrams engaging enemy insurgents surrounding VSP Shurakay while supporting Marines with Combat Logistics Regiment 2 (CLR-2) during Operation Dynamic Partner, Helmand Province, Afghanistan on Feb. 15, 2013

Film Credit: Sgt Anthony Ortiz

2919.description:
Ride along in a UH-60L Blackhawk helicopter with the Utah Army National Guard as they fly through canyons and some amazing scenery.

Members of the 2nd Battalion, 211th Aviation Regiment of the Utah Army National Guard fly UH-60L Blackhawk helicopters to Grand Junction, Colorado from South Valley Regional Airport near Salt Lake City.

Film Credit: SSgt Robert Harnden

2920.description:
A K-MAX unmanned helicopter demonstration - landing, takeoff, and lifting cargo.

A Cargo Resupply Unmanned Aircraft System (CRUAS) with Marine Unmanned Aerial Vehicle Squadron (VMU) 3, Marine Air Control Group 38, 3rd Marine Aircraft Wing (Forward) lands and takes off at Camp Bastion, Helmand province, Afghanistan, Dec. 1, 2012. The K-MAX is built by Kaman Aircraft.

Film Credit: Sgt Gregory Moore

2921.description:
At sea carrier flight deck operations - AH-1W Super Cobra and UH-1N Huey takeoff and land. Close up views.

A UH-1N Huey and an AH-1W Super Cobra assigned to Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron (VMM) 266 (Reinforced), 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU), conduct touch and go landings during flight operations aboard the USS Kearsarge (LHD 3), sailing off the coast of Onslow Beach, N.C., Jan. 30, 2013.

Film Credit: LCpl Juanenrique Owings

2922.description:
The Paladin is a 155mm howitzer on tracks - sort of like a howitzer and tank combined. It needs to stop when firing on a target. The Paladin can halt from the move and fire within 30 seconds. This short firing sequence improves survivability by allowing the battery to operate dispersed, and allowing the howitzer to quickly move between salvos.

4th Infantry Division, conducted a live fire exercise using self-propelled howitzer cannons at Fort Carson, CO.

1st Cavalry Division participating in a combined arms live-fire exercise at Destiny Range and Contingency Operating Site Marez in Ninewa Province, Iraq. The Soldiers fired M109A6 Paladin 155mm Howitzers.

Film Credits: SSG Christopher Jelle - SGT Kristi Potts

2923.description:
The HIMARS (High Mobility Artillery Rocket System) is fired for the first time inside South Korea - multiple views of the same shot.

U.S. Marines from III Marine Expeditionary Force fire the HIMARS at Rodriquez Range, Republic of Korea on March 27, 2014. This exercise is the first time the HIMARS has been deployed and fired within the ROK.

Film Credit: CWO2 James A. Burks

2924.description:
The MV-22 Osprey is the premier troop carrier for the U.S. Marines. It has a combat range of up to 400 miles, much farther than previously used helicopters.

Philippine and US Marines participate in MV-22 movements at Crow Valley, Capas, Tarlac Province, Philippines.

Film Credit: SSgt Michael Cowley

2925.description:
An artillery battery operated by U.S. Marines "fires for effect" in South Korea. Fire-For-Effect basically means the target has been acquired -- cut-loose and hit it with everything you have.

U.S. Marines with Golf Battery, 2nd Battalion, 11th Marines fire for effect on a gun line April 3 at Su Seong-Ri Range in Pohang, Republic of Korea during exercise Ssang Yong 2014.

Film Credit: SSgt Joseph Digirolamo

2926.description:
MV-22B Osprey aircraft takeoff during flight deck operations aboard the USS Kearsarge (LHD 3). LHD stands for - Landing Helicopter Dock.

Film Credit: LCpl Juanenrique Owings

2927.description:
The U.S. Navy LCAC (Landing Craft Air Cushioned) is an amphibious landing craft. The large hovercraft transports heavy equipment and troops to and from the beachhead.

LCAC operations on the well deck of the USS Kearsarge (LHD 3) sailing off the coast of Onslow Beach, N.C., January 24, 2013.

Film Credit: LCpl Juanenrique Owings

2928.description:
Maritime Raid Force Marines and Sailors conduct advanced marksmanship training using M4 Carbines and M240B Machine Guns in the U.S. 6th Fleet area of responsibility.

Film Credit: Sgt Chris Stone

2929.description:
A KC-135R Stratotanker refuels F-18 Hornets in the skies over Afghanistan, and records some spectacular footage.

Film Credit: SSgt Roidan Carlson

2930.description: F-16 fighter jets form an "Elephant Walk" at Kunsan Air Base in South Korea on December 18, 2012. Elephant Walk is a term coined by the U.S. Air Force to describe close formation taxiing of aircraft before takeoff. The term originated during WWII when large fleets of allied bombers would conduct attack missions with thousands of aircraft.

2931.description:
A Marine Corp Harrier Jump Jet hovers and lands vertically on a carrier deck at night.

26th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU), conduct nighttime flight deck operations aboard the USS Kearsarge (LHD 3), sailing off the coast of Onslow Beach, N.C., Jan. 28, 2013.

Film Credit: LCpl Juanenrique Owings

2932.description:
U.S. Marines live fire exercise with machine guns and guided missile rockets.

U.S. Marines with Black Sea Rotational Force 13 conduct field exercises at Camp Adazi, Latvia.

Film Credit: Cpl Michael Dye

2933.description:
F-16 Fighting Falcons take-on fuel in-flight with boom interphone communications. KC-135 aircraft from the 155th Air Refueling Wing refuel F-16's.

Film Credit: SSgt Rashelle Knickerbocker

2934.description:
KC-135 aircraft from the 155th Air Refueling Wing refuel F-22A Raptors from Holloman Air Force Base, NM.

Film Credit: SSgt Rashelle Knickerbocker

2935.description:
U.S. Joint Force Protection Team practices live-fire advanced shooting techniques on a range in Kabul, Afghanistan.

Film Credit: SSgt Jayson Price

2936.description:
F-16 "Swamp Fox" fighter squadron - South Carolina Air National Guard - Readiness Exercise at McEntire Joint National Guard Base.

Film Credit: SMSgt Edward Snyder

2937.description:
U.S. Marines live fire exercise - practice at the range with rifles and handguns.  26th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU), conduct a live-fire range at Vaziani Airbase in the Republic of Georgia.

Film Credit: LCpl Juanenrique Owings

2938.description:
U.S. Marines conduct helicopter hook and go airlift training with a 8500 lb weight.

Film Credit: LCpl Paula Kelly

2939.description:
A CH-46E helicopter tail gunner fires a machine gun during a live fire exercise at night. U.S. Marines - M240D machine gun - night-vision footage.

Film Credit: Michael Watkins

2940.description:
Republic Of Korea and U.S. Marines stage a mass amphibious forced entry - landing at Dokseok-ri Beach in Pohang, South Korea on March 31, 2014.

Film Credit: Cpl Matthew Manning - SSgt Joseph Digirolamo

2941.description:
A squadron of F/A-18C Hornets refuels mid-air in the skies over Afghanistan. 

A KC-135R/T Stratotanker from the 340th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron air refuel F/A-18C Hornets on September 4, 2013. 

Film Credit: MSgt Pedro Jimenez

2942.description:
Qatar Emiri Land Forces conduct parachute training and war games with U.S. Marines and Sailors assigned to the 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit in Al Galail, Qatar - wide view of the battlefield.

Film Credit: LCpl Juanenrique Owings

2943.description:
U.S. Marines conduct amphibious assault training on South Korea beach March 29. 2014.

Marines with the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit and Combat Assault Battalion rehearse for Amphibious landings exercises as part SSang Young 2014. The Marines train and work along side our partners allies in the Republic of Korea during the exercise.

Film Credit:  Cpl Eric Waddell

2944.description:
Night Vision of operations on a helicopter carrier. It takes a tremendous amount of skill and teamwork for these aircraft to land and takeoff safely.

Expeditionary Unit (MEU), conduct nighttime touch and go landings during flight operations aboard the USS Kearsarge (LHD 3), sailing off the coast of Onslow Beach, N.C., Jan. 28, 2013.

Film Credit: Sgt Chris Stone

2945.description:
Door gunners hunt & seek to shoot the enemy on the ground.

 Crewmembers of a UH-1Y Huey Venom helicopter fire the GAU-21 .50 caliber machine gun and an M134 minigun during a training mission out Marine Corps Air Station Yuma.

Film Credit: Sgt Chad Pulliam

2946.description:
US Army and Canadian Armed Forces learn how to use the shotgun in close quarters combat training.

Film Credit: PO2 Jonathan Chandler

2947.description:
U.S. Army UH-72 Lakota helicopters fly through some scenic Colorado and Utah canyons, with radio communications.

Members of the 2nd Battalion, 211th Aviation Regiment of the Utah Army National Guard pilots fly two new UH-72 Lakota helicopters through scenic mountains of Colorado and Utah.

Film Credit: MSgt Pedro Jimenez

2948.description:
Refueling the Stealth B-2 Bomber while flying expands range of operation. A KC-135 KC-135 Stratotanker gives fuel to a B-2 mid-flight.

Film Credit: A1C Jarrod Vickers

2949.description:
Missile Defense Agency test flight - guided missile intercept. Shooting down a missile with another missile.

The Missile Defense Agency (MDA), U.S. Pacific Command, and U.S. Navy Sailors aboard the USS Lake Erie (CG 70) successfully conducted a flight test of the Aegis Ballistic Missile Defense (BMD) system, resulting in the intercept of a complex separating short-range ballistic missile target over the Pacific Ocean by the Aegis BMD 4.0 Weapon System and a Standard Missile-3 (SM-3) Block IB guided missile.

Film Credit: Chris Szkrybalo

2950.description:
U.S.Army mortar fire at night - illumination rounds. Filmed by night-vision camera.

The 116th Cavalry Brigade Combat Team's 2nd Cavalry Regiment from Caldwell, Idaho light up the night sky. Fire teams fired 120 mm illumination and infrared illumination rounds as part of their combat training.

Film Credit: SPC Christian Duplessie

2951.description:
Members of the 82nd Airborne Division make ready an artillery piece which has just been air-dropped into their landing zone. Then they fire it.

Soldiers from 82 ABN DIV, 2BCT, A BTRY 2-319th AFAR, conducting live fire drills after a simulated sling load drop during a JOAX at Fort Bragg, NC.

Film Credit: SSG DeShannon Austin

2952.description:
Aerial refueling of a C-17 Globemaster transport plane. 

191st Air Refueling Squadron executes an air refueling mission from a KC-135 Stratotanker on Feb 05, 2014.

Film Credit:

2953.description:
Look down the barrel of a .50 caliber machine gun Humvee during live-fire in Grafenwoehr, Germany.

Film Credit: SPC Arthur Haring

2954.description: An F-35B Lightning II completed the first short takeoff and vertical landing at night on April 2, 2013. The test flight was conducted at NAS Patuxent River, Md.

2955.description:
Mid-air refueling of Air Force HH-60G Pave Hawk helicopters.

An HC-130J COMBAT KING II air refuels two HH-60G Pave Hawks during Exercise Angel Thunder 2013.

Film Credit: MSgt Pedro Jimenez

2956.description:
View what it's like to ride in a UH-60 Blackhawk helicopter.

Service members from various units working alongside Second Battalion, Third Marine Regiment (2/3) are given a ride in the UH-60 Blackhawk helicopters at the Marine Corps Mountain Warfare Training Center (MWTC) in Bridgeport, California on 13 April 2013.

Film Credit: Cpl Taryn McKenzie

2957.description:
U.S. Marines conduct mechanized assault training using the shoulder fired (M136 ATA4-6) rocket launcher.

U.S. Marines with Combined Arms Team 2, 2nd Battalion, 3rd Marines conduct weapons training including the M136 ATA4-6 in support of Exercise Ssang Yong 14 at Suesongri Range, Pohang, South Korea, March 26, 2014.

Film Credits: PFC Lyman Green and Cpl Matthew Manning

2958.description:
First catapult launch of the X-47B Unmanned Combat Air System (UCAS) from the deck of the aircraft carrier USS George H.W. Bush (CVN 77) on 5-14-2013.

The Northrop Grumman X-47B is a demonstration unmanned combat air vehicle designed for carrier-based operations for the U.S. Navy.

Currently the X-47B is undergoing flight testing, having successfully performed a series of land and carrier-based demonstrations. Northrop Grumman intends to develop the prototype X-47B into a battlefield-ready aircraft, the Unmanned Carrier-Launched Surveillance and Strike (UCLASS) system, which will enter service by 2019.

Film Credit: Gregory Wilhelmi - Specialist 3rd Class Sade Lucas

2959.description:
A loaded Navy hovercraft (LCAC) returns from the beach to the carrier ship and embarks. LCAC stands for Landing Craft Air Cushioned.

Landing craft, air cushion vessels transport vehicles and equipment assigned to 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU) to the USS Kearsarge (LHD 3), off the coast of Onslow Beach, N.C., March 13, 2013.

Film Credit: Sgt Chris Stone

2960.description:
The Ch-53E Super Stallion Helicopter and MV-22 Osprey, the work-horses of Marine Corp aviation, are shown landing - close up.

Marine aircraft from Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron-163 (Reinforced) footage from Fort Hunter Liggett, Calif., March 19, 2014.

Film Credit: Sgt Melissa Wenger

2961.description:
Staff Sgt. Kara Santos, U.S. Marines Band flute player, performs The Piccolo Solo from John Philip Sousa's March, "The Stars and Stripes Forever" during a Friday Evening Parade at Marine Barracks Washington, D.C., May 31, 2013.

Film Credit: Sgt Dengrier Baez

2962.description:
HIMARS is the M142 High Mobility Artillery Rocket System. It can launch six rockets at a target of up to 26 miles away.

On February 14, 2010, the International Security Assistance Force (ISAF) for Afghanistan said that it was thought that two rockets fired from a HIMARS unit fell 300 metres short of their intended target and killed 12 civilians during Operation Moshtarak. So, ISAF suspended the use of the HIMARS until a full review of the incident was completed. Later it was confirmed that the rockets were on target, that the target was in use by the Taliban, and use of the system was reinstated. 

Reports indicate that the civilian deaths were due to the Taliban's use of an occupied dwelling, and the presence of civilians at that location was not known to the ISAF forces. An October 21, 2010 report in the New York Times credited HIMARS with aiding the NATO offensive in Kandahar by targeting Taliban commanders' hideouts, forcing many to flee to Pakistan, at least temporarily.

Film Credit: Sgt Michael Ito

2963.description:
Members of the 82nd Airborne Division night jump over Fort Bragg, NC - simulated hostile territory. Filmed by night-vision camera.

Credit: SSgt Roidan Carlson

2964.description:
Night jet operations at Nellis AFB near Las Vegas get extremely loud. Taxi & Takeoffs at Nellis AFB. Filmed during Red Flag  operations 2014.

Film Credit: SrA Aaron Hauser, William Lewis, and SrA Rachel Maxwell

2965.description:
MV-22 Ospreys conduct a mass troop airlift at Twentynine Palms, California.

Aircraft from 3rd Marine Aircraft Wing move a battalion of Marines from MCB Camp Pendleton to MCAGCC 29 Palms in participation with exercise Dawn Blitz 2013.

Film Credit: Sgt Isaac Lamberth

2966.description:
Refueling a U.S. Air Force CV-22 Osprey aircraft from air.

Film Credit:  SrA Laura Yahemiak

2967.description:
U.S. Marines comes under fire from insurgents in Helmand Province.

Film Credit: Travis Sauls

2968.description:
Mid-air refueling of the C-5 Galaxy military transport plane, one of the largest aircraft in the world.

Utah Air National Guard members from the 191st Air Refueling Squadron execute an air refueling mission on a C-5 Galaxy from a KC-135 Stratotanker to maintain their job proficiency on May 21, 2012.

Film Credit: MSgt Pedro Jimenez

2969.description: A new advanced flight simulator for the C-17 Globemaster provides realistic training to pilots at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base.

2970.description:
Live- fire with .50 cal machine gun, the barrel gets almost too hot to touch.

U.S. Navy Sailors fire a .50 caliber machine gun during a Crew Fired Weapons Drill aboard the forward-deployed amphibious assault ship USS Bonhomme Richard (LHD6).

Film Credit: LT Desiree Frame

2971.description:
U.S. Marines live-fire exercise with various weapons - mortars, howitzers, armored personnel carriers, shoulder fired rockets, and machines guns.

Featured live-fire of M777A2 Howitzers, the 120mm Expeditionary Fire Support System, Light Armored Vehicles, M240G Medium machine guns, and Browning M2 .50 caliber machine guns, the SMAW shoulder fired assault weapon, plus a vertical assault by MV-22 Osprey tiltrotor aircraft from the USS Bonhomme Richard more than 300 miles away.

Film Credit: Sgt Jonathan Wright

2972.description:
U.S. Marines are loaded onto helicopters and Ospreys as a part of air assault training operations.

Marines with 2nd Battalion, 1st Marine Regiment load into MV-22 Ospreys and CH-53 Super Stallion helicopters as part of large-scale air assault to Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center Twentynine Palms, California.

Film Credit: Cpl Scott Reel

2973.description:
U.S. Marines land on the beach transported by amphibious assault landing craft.

U.S. Marines of Company K, Battalion Landing Team 3/2, 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU), ride ashore from the USS Carter Hall (LSD 50) aboard amphibious assault vehicles during sustainment training in the 6th Fleet area of operations, Aug. 1, 2013.

Film Credit: Cpl Michael Lockett

2974.description:
U.S. Marines and Sailors aboard the USS Kearsarge conduct night live-fire exercises  - night-vision camera.

Credit: WO Michael Kropiewnicki

2975.description:
F-35 Lightning II and Nellis Air Force Base montage - multimedia video highlights the fighter jet based there.

Credit:  SrA Cody Griffith, SrA Aaron Hauser, William Lewis, SrA Rachel Maxwell and SSgt Jose Rodriguez

2976.description:
A camera mounted in the cockpit of a U.S. Marines AV-8B Harrier "Jump Jet" during flight operations gives you a pilot's view.

Capt. David Neely, an AV-8B Harrier Pilot, conducts flight operations off the USS Kearsarge (LHD3) in the Mediterranean Sea on March 28, 2013.

Film Credit: WO Michael Kropiewnicki

2977.description:
U.S. Marines and Australian Army soldiers conduct a live-fire assault in Australia.

Credit: Sgt Jonathan Wright

2978.description:
The V-22 Osprey tiltrotor aircraft can land and takeoff like a helicopter, but it can also fly like an airplane.

Flight deck operations aboard the USS San Antonio, and flight operations from the USS Bataan (LHD 5) to the USS George H.W. Bush (CVN 77).
  
Film Credits: LCpl Juanenrique Owings - Cpl Joshua Rudy

2979.description:
U.S. Marines are transported by large hovercraft - air cushion landing craft - as they conduct amphibious operations.

Credit: LCpl Juanenrique Owings

2980.description:
An V-22B Osprey lands aboard the USS Kearsarge during nighttime flight operations at sea.

Credit: Sgt Chris Stone

2981.description: A documentary highlighting the 82nd Airborne from WWII to Vietnam - the first airborne division of the U.S.Army

2982.description: Multiple shots of an F-22 Raptor fighter jet taking off.

2983.description:
An F-22 Raptor fighter jet and crew chief. F-22 departs the hanger to takeoff.

Credit: SrA Austin Willhoit

2984.description:
A U.S. Navy hovercraft amphibious transport LCAC (Landing Craft Air Cushioned) lands on the beach and then returns to the ocean. 

Credit: WO Michael Kropiewnicki

2985.description: Notable athletes who put their pro careers on hold and joined the military during wartime. This documentary features interviews with Bob Feller, Art Donovan, and Rocky Bleier.

2986.description:
Live Fire Exercises - Sailors from the USS Shoup (DDG 86) and Helicopter Strike Maritime Squadron (HSM) 75 participate in a ship and aerial gunnery exercise.

Film Credit: PO1 Daniel Gay

2987.description:
The Aircraft Carrier USS Nimitz (CVN 68) sails in formation with a task force made up of USS Princeton (CG 59), USS Stockdale (DDG 106), USS Mason (DDG 87), USS Shoup (DDG 86), USS William P. Lawrence (DDG 110).

Film Credit: PO2 Ashley Berumen

2988.description:
U.S. Soldiers set up an observation post to keep tabs on the Taliban.

Infantry soldiers from Forward Operating Base Airborne in Afghanistan scan for enemy activity.

Film Credit: Cpl Joshua DeFour

2989.description: A documentary that explores cutting-edge technology for the battlefield and soldier of the future.

2990.description:
A B-1 Bomber jet engine test shakes the building and produces an ear-splitting scream. T-9 jet engine.

Film Credit: A1C Timothy Kirchner

2991.description:
The F-35 is the world's most advanced multi-role fighter jet. It can take off in a short hop, plus it can hover and land like a helicopter. The short takeoff and vertical landing capabilities (STOVL) of the F-35 makes it ideally suited for carrier operations as in this video. It also has stealth technology which makes it virtually invisible to radar.

Film Credit: GySgt Cruz Sotelo

2992.description:
Artillerymen from 4th Battalion, 1st Field Artillery Regiment, U.S. Army conduct a live fire exercise with the M777 Howitzer.

Film Credit: SGT Adam Gregory

2993.description:
Have a glimpse of what it's like to live and work onboard the most advanced United States nuclear submarine. The USS Minnesota (SSN-783) was commissioned on September 7, 2013 and is the newest sub in the fleet at the time of this upload. The USS North Dakota (SSN-784) is scheduled to be commissioned in May 2014.

Film Credit: PO2 Amara Timberlake

2994.description: The Congressional Medal Of Honor is the highest military honor. Here are four stories about the courageous men who hold this honor, and what they did in battle so that others might live.

2995.description:
U.S. Marines with the 1st Battalion, 11th Marine Regiment fire the M777 Howitzer, capable of hitting a target from 25 miles away.

Film Credit: LCpl Christopher J. Moore

2996.description: An inside look into the latest technology the U.S. Army is developing, including more deadly and advanced weapons systems for the battlefield of the future.

2997.description:
Little girl greets her daddy as pilots return home after a six month deployment at Kandahar Airfield, Afghanistan.

Film Credit: A1C Sarah Denewellis

2998.description:
The first F-35A Lightning II Joint Strike Fighter arrives at Hill Air Force Base, Utah. The multirole, fifth-generation fighter arrived from the 422nd Test and Evaluation Squadron, Nellis AFB, Nev., and is scheduled to undergo post-production modifications at the Ogden Air Logistics Complex.

Film Credit: TSgt Genevieve Armstrong

2999.description:
Time lapse video of flight deck operations aboard the USS Kearsarge (LHD-3) - a Wasp-class amphibious assault ship of the United States Navy. 

Marine Medium Tiltrotor Squadron (VMM) 266 (Reinforced). 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU), and U.S. Navy MH-60s -- one day in a life.

Film Credit:  Sgt Chris Stone

3000.description:
Hot jet exhausts can cook a man or blast him overboard. Sometimes the air is so hot it's nearly impossible to breath. A jet intake can pull a man off his feet and suck him into an engine. It's a dangerous job, but Sailors aboard the aircraft carrier USS Nimitz (CVN68) perform flight operations, proficient as always.

Credit: PO3 Joshua Haiar and PO3 Samuel Souvannason

3001.description:
U.S. Marines parachute into a dark night sky over Djibouti, Africa.

Force Reconnaissance Platoon, Maritime Raid Force, 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU), and Reconnaissance Platoon, Battalion Landing Team (BLT) 3/2, 26th MEU, conduct parachute operations  Sept. 20, 2013.

Film Credit: Sgt Kyle N. Runnels

3002.description:
A guided missile is launched from the USS Lake Erie and successfully intercepts a medium-range ballistic missile target off the coast of Kauai, Hawaii during a US Navy test.

Film Credit: Jessica Kosanovich

3003.description:
U.S. Marines conduct qualification in the Mine Resistant Ambush Protected vehicle Egress Trainer (MET). Marines must qualify in the MET prior to entering a deployed environment.

Credit: Cpl Donald Holbert

3004.description:
A simulated IED attack obliterates a Humvee.

Credit: Mark Gordon

3005.description:
The AC-130H Spectre gunship is a heavily armed ground-attack aircraft used in Afghanistan. The squadron motto, "You can run but you will only die tired."

The 16th Expeditionary Special Operations Squadron, deployed to Afghanistan, bids farewell to the oldest and most prolific AC-130 model in the fleet. The AC-130H Spectre gunship is on its final combat deployment which marks a historic moment in its over forty year career. The airman of the 16th ESOS are sad to see the Spectre retire, but are equally excited about the new opportunities that lie on the horizon. 

Credit: SrA Brandi Hansen

3006.description:
On May 25, 2011 nearly 400 Taliban ambushed a U.S. Coalition force of 50 near Do Ab, Afghanistan. In the ensuing 13 hour fire-fight USAF Forward Air Controllers called in close air support to save coalition forces from being overrun and slaughtered. Throughout the day, air strikes by US Air Force F-16s, F-15s, and AC-130 gunships, US Navy Super Hornets, and US Army AH-64 Apaches and OH-58 Kiowas pounded the Taliban forces, resulting in an estimated 270 enemy killed.

Credit: SrA Andrew Buchanan

3007.description: The crew chief of a V-22 Osprey must be able to handle multiple jobs including machine gunner, forward observer, and load master. Film by Cpl Joshua DeFour.

3008.description:
Helicopter door gunners rain fire from above.

U.S. Marines with Marine Light Attack Helicopter Squadron 169 "The Vipers" conduct aerial patrols and live fire training in a UH-1Y Huey and a AH-1W Super Cobra at Pohakuloa Training Area, Hawaii on July 20, 2012. Filmed by Lance Cpl. Robert Bush.

U.S. Marine Corps Staff Sgt. Richard G. Deibler, UH-1Y Venom door gunner and Lance Cpl. Joshua S. Martinez, UH-1Y Venom crew chief with Marine Light Helicopter Squadron (HMLA) 469, Marine Aircraft Group 38, 3rd Marine Aircraft Wing (Forward), conducts operations over Helmand province, Afghanistan, Oct. 17, 2012. Filmed by Sgt Keonaona Paulo.

U.S. Marines with the air interdiction force (AIF) assigned to Marine Light Attack Helicopter Squadron (HMLA) 469, Marine Aircraft Group 39, 3rd Marine Aircraft Wing (Forward), conduct Operation Aero Hunter with other Regional Command (Southwest) elements in Helmand province, Afghanistan, Oct. 24, 2012. Filmed by Sgt Gregory Moore.

3009.description:
The hovercraft is a Landing Craft Air Cushioned - LCAC - used by the U.S. Navy for amphibious operations. They transport weapons, equipment, and people from ship to shore and across the beach.

Weight - 182 long tons (185 t) full load
Length - 87 feet 11 inches (26.4 meters)
Width - 47 feet (14.3 meters)
Crew - 5
Main armament - two 12.7 mm machine guns. Gun mounts will support: M2HB .50 cal machine gun; Mk 19 Mod 3 40 mm grenade launcher; M60 machine gun
Engine - gas turbine
Payload capacity - 60 tons (up to 75 tons in an overload condition)(54/68 metric tons)
Operational range - 200 NM at 40 kt (370 km at 75 km/h) with payload - 300 NM at 35 kt (550 km at 65 km/h)with payload
Speed - 40+ knots (46+ mph; 74 km/h) with full load, 70+ knots maximum speed

3010.description:
Navy air cushioned hovercraft bring Marines and equipment onshore during amphibious exercises.

Marines and Sailors of the 26th Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU) come ashore from the ships of the Kearsarge Amphibious Ready Group at Onslow Beach, Camp Lejeune, N.C., Feb. 16, 2013. Filmed by SSgt Edward R. Guevara Jr.

3011.description: A 70 ton M-1 Abrams tank is loaded aboard a huge C-17 transport plane. Giant plane takes off and lands safely. Tank is off-loaded. Filmed by SGT Toby Wall.

3012.description:
Army Airborne Paratroopers jump on the Malamute Drop Zone in Alaska.

Paratroopers with the Airborne 25th Infantry Division, filmed by SGT Eric-James Estrada.

3013.description:
The first F35 Lightning II fighter jet arrives at Luke AFB in Arizona. - 3/10/2014

Luke Air Force Base is the premier fighter training base in the United States for the U.S. Air Force. There, F35 pilots will train in preparation for combat. The infrastructure at Luke Air Force Base is unmatched. The weather is perfect and the military support in the Phoenix community is second to none. Filmed by TSgt Fernando X. Burgos-Ortiz on 3-10-2014.

3014.description:
A riverine command boat patrols the Arabian Sea, and packs a punch.

Sailors assigned to Commander, Task Group 56.7.4 conduct a live-fire weapons exercise aboard a riverine command boat (RCB) in the Arabian Gulf. RCBs provide a multi-mission platform for the U.S. 5th Fleet area of responsibility by focusing on maritime security operations, maritime infrastructure protection, and theater security cooperation efforts, in addition to offensive combat operations. U.S. Navy video by Mass Communication Specialist 1st Class Michelle L. Turner.

3015.description:
Mid air refueling operations. Pilots and crew exchange small talk. Just another day on the job.

KC 135 Aircrew from 151st ARW refuels F16s out the 388th Fighter Wing, Hill AFB, Utah. This mission was a routine training mission for both units. Filmed by MSgt Jason Wilkerson.

3016.description:
A U.S. Navy LCAC hovercraft lands troops and equipment on the beach.

U.S. Marines and soldiers from the Japan Ground Self-Defense Force conduct an amphibious landing during Exercise Iron Fist 2014 at Camp Pendleton, California. Filmed by Lance Cpl. Anna Albrecht.

3017.description:
The V-22B Osprey can hover like a helicopter and fly like a plane.

Service members from, the Kingdom of Thailand, the Republic of Korea, and the United States conduct Fast Rope Insertion Extraction operations at Hat Yao Royal Thai Naval Base, Kingdom of Thailand. Filmed by Lance Cpl. Jacob A. Hug.

3018.description: Flight operations at Nellis Air Force Base, Nevada. Ear-splitting jet engine noise and afterburner fire are a daily occurrence for ground crew personnel. Filmed by SrA Cody Griffith.

3019.description:
Live fire exercises on a river patrol boat with .50 caliber machine guns

U.S. Sailors with Coastal Riverine Group 2, Training Evaluation Unit (TEU), instructed Sailors with Coastal Riverine Squadron 2 (CRS-2) during the Open Water Engagement exercise on the Neuse River, N.C., March 4, 2014. TEU helped prepare CRS-2 for their upcoming deployments. (U.S. Marine Motion Imagery by Lance Cpl. James R. Skelton) Includes interview with Commander Raul Gandara, OIC CRG-2 TEU.
